name: House on waterfront, last minute reduction!
summary: Nice house with a lot of space and fantastic view on the water. Close to the center of Amsterdam. Place for 4/5 adults, eventually 2 small children. You can put together the 2 single beds in sleepingroom 2 for a double bed, room 3 has 2 beds for children.
space: Sunny, light (family)house close to the city in a quiet, green relaxing neighbourhood wih a spectacular view on the waterside. It is great to spend an afternoon in the hammock in the backyard after you have walked or cycled around in the busy city or after you have been to a concert in the Ziggo Dome or Heineken Music Hall.   It is located in the southeast of Amsterdam, 15-20 minutes by metro to the center of Amsterdam. It is close to the Heineken Music Hall, Ziggo Dome and the Arena (3,2 km), where you find Ajax! but also nice restaurants (very good sushi), a big cinema and modern shopping stores. The house is spacious, 135 m2 and all on one floor with a garden in front and in the back of the house. It is possible to stay here with 4-6 persons.  The house has a nice kitchen. There is a bath and a shower and two toilets. Of course there is internet. Parking is free. There is a washing machine and a dryer. Just send me an e-mail and I will explain more to you!

summary: Stylish room close to the Bijlmer Arena (Ziggo Dome, Heineken Music Hall),  RAI and a metro ride away from Amsterdam's city centre. Great for a young crowd as you'll be sharing the house with awesome roomies who are all students!
space: Everything in the house (except the other private rooms ofcourse) including, kitchen, bathroom, living room, balcony and garden.  You can have as much and as little privacy and contact as you wish! Everybody is very open and hospitable.  Mostly family homes, and close to a student campus makes it a versatile place to hang around. Especially known for the many different cultures! Make sure to try the Surinam Roti!!  Great transportation. You can take the bus, metro or train almost anywhere directly! Make sure to realize that this is a student dormitory, where things can get messy once in a while. No worries, your room is spotless and we like to call the rest of the house 'homey'.

I have irregular shift, therefore I'm often away. But when I'm at home, feel free to ask any questions. Very green neighbourhood, ideally for walking, jogging or cycling. Arena area with Ajax football stadium for sightseeing, shopping mall and biggest
neighborhood_overview: Very green neighbourhood, ideally for walking, jogging or cycling. Arena area with Ajax football stadium for sightseeing, shopping mall and biggest concert halls in the Netherlands. - DIRECT environment may have the tendency to be  boring because unfortunately, there are no pubs/cafes or somewhere nice to have a drink and enjoy. You can do this at the Arena area (10 minutes with bus). If you prefer or are in need of this outings, then my place is not the right spot. - There is a shopping mall from 3 minutes walking distance. The supermarket is open till 22:00h; There are 4 shops nearby open till 23:00h to get a warm meal. - Feel free to stay out in the night. Last metro (subway) is at 0:30 from Amsterdam Central Station. Hereafter, you can take night bus 757 and get off at bus stop Koornhorst (Kraaiennest). The trip takes 35 minutes.
transit: 2 minutes walking to the metro station. Metro 53 goes directly to Amsterdam City centre and Centraal Station. The journey takes approximately 15 minutes. There are 4 buses you can take also to the centre and also if you want to have a nice view of Amsterdam.
access: There is a fridge. Bathroom is shared. You are allowed to use the kitchen for cooking, only if you have a permit/diploma for cleaning.
interaction: I'm a physician in Geriatric Medicine. I have irregular shift, therefore I'm often away. But when I'm at home, feel free to ask any questions.
house_rules: - Smoking in the house is prohibited - No drugs - Neat and tidy - No walking with shoes in house - Men, prior to peeing, take a seat on the WC - In the late evening and early morning be silent because of other guest sleeping - You are allowed to use the kitchen for cooking, only if you have a permit/diploma for cleaning.
host_about:
Hi guys,
I'm Kofi Kwarteng, originally born in Ghana-West Africa. I'm intern (physician) in  Emergency and Geriatric care. Due to my profession, I work different shifts and the only regularity in my life is that there is no regularity. I'm a content single guy living by myself. Therefore is no partner or kids in the house.

I like meeting new people all over the world. It helps me remember that no matter the colour of the skin, race, religion, that we are all in essence the same.

My hobbies are reading, running and trying to make time to clear my mind by meditation. 

It's lovely to welcome you in my home and looking forward meeting you.

Best regards,

Kofi

You can do this at the Arena area (10 minutes with bus). If you prefer or are in need of this outings, then my place is not the right spot. - There is a shopping mall from 3 minutes walking distance. The supermarket is open till 22:00h; There are 4 shops nearby open till 23:00h to get a warm meal. - Feel free to stay out in the night. Last metro (subway) is at 0:30 from Amsterdam Central Station. Hereafter, you can take night bus 757 and get off at bus stop Koornhorst (Kraaiennest). The trip takes 35 minutes.
transit: 2 minutes walking to the metro station. Metro 53 goes directly to Amsterdam City centre and Centraal Station. The journey takes approximately 15 minutes. There are 4 buses you can take also to the centre and also if you want to have a nice view of Amsterdam.
access: There is a fridge. Bathroom is shared. You are allowed to use the kitchen for cooking, only if you have a permit/diploma for cleaning.
interaction: I'm a physician in Geriatric Medicine. I have irregular shift, therefore I'm often away. But when I'm at home, feel free to ask any questions.
house_rules: - Smoking in the house is prohibited - No drugs - Neat and tidy - Not allowed to walk with shoes in the house - Men, prior to peeing, take a seat on the WC - In the late evening and early morning be silent because of other guest sleeping - You are allowed to use the kitchen for cooking, only if you have a permit/diploma for cleaning.
host_about:
Hi guys,
I'm Kofi Kwarteng, originally born in Ghana-West Africa. I'm intern (physician) in  Emergency and Geriatric care. Due to my profession, I work different shifts and the only regularity in my life is that there is no regularity. I'm a content single guy living by myself. Therefore is no partner or kids in the house.

I like meeting new people all over the world. It helps me remember that no matter the colour of the skin, race, religion, that we are all in essence the same.

My hobbies are reading, running and trying to make time to clear my mind by meditation. 

It's lovely to welcome you in my home and looking forward meeting you.

Best regards,

Kofi

name: Bright room, green park, arty flat!
summary: A home away from home - that's how we want you to feel at our place! Private room and 110 m2 flat perfect for families and travelers. Amsterdam city center 15 min away, free parking, tranquility of nature under balcony - this is the place to be!
space: Welcome to our humble abode - 110 square meter spacious, light and modern looking apartment with a personal touch. It is situated on the third floor overlooking the vast green park and there is an elevator in the building You get to use one private room with one double bed for 2 persons (160 cm wide  x 200 cm long) and a small balcony with a hanging egg chair. The room belongs to you so you can relax and enjoy the park view to your heart's content! The rest of the apartment you can enjoy with your hosts - we share everything including a fully equipped kitchen (induction stove, big fridge, oven, microwave, dishwasher), bathroom (shower cabin, bath tub) and a separate toilet. Big living room can accommodate 2 to 3 people on extra beds - 160 cm wide x 190 cm long aerobed and an additional stretcher if necessary. And we all share the TV - you can pick your favourite movies and series, we have a huge collection :). Additionally, there is another balcony with a lake and trees view where you

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is situated in Amsterdam Zuidoost (South East) in the residential area De Bijlmer - a quickly developing area where a vibrant multicultural community is shaping itself.The atmosphere on streets is palpably different than the atmosphere in the city centre of Amsterdam. Walking around, you encounter different faces, hear different accents and smell different flavors. The shops sell products foreign to the Dutch, and at the market you can find vegetables, fruits and fish from all over the world.  You can enjoy the big-entertainment world of the Amsterdam ArenA, the Heineken Music Hall and the Ziggo Dome, plus numerous gleaming office buildings. It’s 15 minutes away by metro from your typical canals-and-clogs image of Amsterdam, but with around 100,000 residents from more than 150 ethnic backgrounds, it is a side of Amsterdam that shouldn't be overlooked. A bit of history The area is surrounded by countryside and picturesque waterways. Many of the Bijlmer’s inhabitants have C
notes: The extra bed(s) is situated in the living room. It is possible to leave your luggage after check-out and pick it up later that day. Kitchen items you can use include plates, pots, frying pans, cooking oil, salt, pepper and all the spices that we also use! We will provide you with towels, linens and toiletries (hair dryer, soap, organic shampoo).
transit: Metro is a 5 minute walk away and brings you in 15 minutes to the center of Amsterdam. Two main highways leading to Amsterdam (the A1 and the A2) are also 5 minutes away and give good access for those coming by car. Having easy access to the highway also gives the opportunity to do city trips and see other interesting parts of Holland (Leiden, Utrecht, several beaches, Rotterdam).
access: Living room, open kitchen, balconies, bathroom, toilet and the bed room - in other words, we share all facilities and amenities, except for bedrooms.
interaction: We are available and open to help you out with any inquiries and questions you might have during your stay. We can keep in touch by phone or email at all times when you are out. When you are in the flat we can have meals together, discuss everything from Dutch cheese to high politics. Of course, if you prefer privacy, it's also fine - everything is up to you!
house_rules: Smoking (all kinds) is allowed on the balconies No drugs/weed are allowed in the apartment. Preferred check-out time is 11 pm. Try to keep the apartment tidy. We can put your dishes in a dishwasher and wash you laundry with ours (or separately), but if you are not sure how to turn a machine on, please do ask before you try-we are here for you! You are welcome to use all the cookware you need.
street: Gouden Leeuw, Amsterdam Zuid-Oost, Noord-Holland 1103 KX, Netherlands

name: Big, sunny spacious house
summary: Our house (a bungalow of 140 m2) has all the comforts you need and is located in a green, peaceful neighborhood in Amsterdam Southeast, an 8 minute walk from the metro, which brings you to the center of Amsterdam in 15 minutes.
space: Our light and spacious living room with conservatory looks out over the big sunny, private garden (70 m2). Our big dining room table (seats 6 people) is a lovely spot to have a sunny breakfast and/or dinner. The living room also contains 3 comfortable couches, a large bookcase (with Dutch and English literature as well as children’s’ books) and a nice TV (Netflix!).  Our house is a bungalow and accessible to wheelchairs. In the large kitchen you may find everything you need, such as a dishwasher, a Quooker, a microwave oven and a 6 burner stove with double oven. The master bedroom has a king size bed and a walk-in closet. Room Two can be used by 2, maybe even 3 people. We have a big airbed, suitable for one and a camp bed for a baby or toddler (both including bedding). This room can easily fit 3 adults if you bring your own extra airbeds. Our bungalow is child friendly with lots of toys (since we are grandparents :)) and we have two high chairs you can use. The bathroom is very modern

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Southeast is a unique area with a very diverse, multicultural population. Our bungalow is situated in the green area called the Bijlmerweide. Within 5 minutes of walking, you’ll find yourself in a nature reserve called Diemerbos. During the week there are markets throughout Southeast, with many exotic products and a lively atmosphere. From July 16th to August the 5th the famous Kwaku summer festival will be held every weekend in the Nelson Mandela Park nearby. This festival is famous for its music, football, great food and drinks and unique atmosphere.
notes: Our bungalow is located near nature reserves such as the Diemer Bos and the Gaasperplas. Perfect places for walking, hiking and cycling. We have two bicycles you can use (one gentleman’s and one lady’s). Beautiful old places like Weesp, Muiden, Abcoude and Ouderkerk aan de Amstel are near. And don’t forget the villages and places around the IJsselmeer, like: Volendam, Edam and Enkhuizen!
transit: Our house is located within a few minutes of metro station Ganzenhoef. The metro will take you to Amsterdam Central station in less than 20 minutes. At the edge of our neighborhood you will find the bus stops for buses that bring you to IJburg (new district with interesting architecture), for example, and the Dappermarkt in East (lively market). From our house you can access the Amsterdam Ring Road and motorway in 5 minutes. There is free parking in our neighborhood and you can also use our garage.
access: Our whole house is at your disposal, except for one room, where we keep our private items. But we’re sure that the room won’t be missed. You will have the house to yourselves when you stay here, but we will be there at your arrival to welcome you and show you “the ropes”. We can also pick you up from the airport or train station when you don’t come by car (small fee). We will keep in touch by phone and/or email and since we are staying in Holland, we can come “to the rescue” within the hour, if you need us.

host_about:
Hi guys,
I'm Kofi Kwarteng, originally born in Ghana-West Africa. I'm intern (physician) in  Emergency and Geriatric care. Due to my profession, I work different shifts and the only regularity in my life is that there is no regularity. I'm a content single guy living by myself. Therefore is no partner or kids in the house.

I like meeting new people all over the world. It helps me remember that no matter the colour of the skin, race, religion, that we are all in essence the same.

My hobbies are reading, running and trying to make time to clear my mind by meditation. 

It's lovely to welcome you in my home and looking forward meeting you.

Best regards,

Kofi

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is in walking distance (10min) of Heineken Music Hall, Ziggodôme, Arena, cinema, terrasses and a lively shoppingcenter (10min). Daily shopping can be done in the nearby supermarket (5 min). Recommended is the Tropical market on saturday (3min). From the apartment you can make endless walks through the many parks and recreation areas with woods, lakes and swimbeaches, old fashioned dutch landscape with streams, meadows, cows and pittoresk villages.
notes: We kindly ask you to respect the following house rules: - Please keep the noise down, especially when entering the complex. After all, you share the building with other people living there. All in all: we kindly ask you to respect your neighbours;   - We guarantee a clean house when checking in. When checking out, please leave the apartment closely to the same state as it was provided to you, in order to avoid double cleaning charges;  - No loud noises after 22:00;  - Smoking and/or using drugs in the apartment and/or complex is prohibited.  Smoking is allowed on the balcony only. - No additional guests allowed without approval;  - Make sure to turn off the lights and heating  when it is not needed - respect the environment;  - No house parties;
transit: The metro (5 min walk) takes you to the city-center in 12 min. If needed, the nightbus brings you back to your frontdoor in 30 min. Perfect connection to Schiphol Airport by train. If you prefer we can transfer you from and to the airport by car (25 euro per trip). The apartment is easily accessible from the highway. There is plenty free parkingspace.
access: The whole apartment is yours!  We are happy to adjust to your wishes, after consultation. For example: earlier check-in, later check-out, extra person, small animal, babybed, toys etc. Babies 0-2 are free of charge.
interaction: We are happy to give you info about Amsterdam and anything else you want to know about your stay. We try to be available by telephone all the time, for questions or if you need help.
host_about: Born and raised in Amsterdam, there is no other place I would rather be. But, me and my family also like to travel, often in private apartments, witch gave us many wonderful experiences in other cities. We are happy to join the airbnb community with our beautiful apartment and give others the opportunity to enjoy our beloved city from our home. We hope to meet you soon!Majo

name: Unique Eco Tiny House on Wheels with breakfast
summary: Greenzzz is a completely furbished,unique self built ecological tiny house on wheels. It's situated in one of the most picturesque and quiet places in Amsterdam with endless views of the fields. You have your own entrance and there is parking space. A make-your-own-breakfast-basket is included!
space: GreenWheels has been built with love and care and has kept the nature in mind. All the electrical equipment runs on self generated solar energy. There is a water free compost toilet and the water system has been designed so that you use 50% less water than usual without even noticing it. Furthermore GreenWheels has as much as possible been built with local and recycled wood. For example, the oak floor comes from an old ship in Amsterdam and the framework of the bed, the table and all the shelves have been hand made with local Maple wood. The mattress and bedding is made from organic cotton and wood fibres. The chairs are from a vintage fleemarket. The stairs and drawers were made from 'scrap' wood.  Sleeping You sleep in a beautifully handmade and comfortable double bed. Cooking The fully equipped kitchen contains a mini fridge, two burner stove, sink and basic kitchen utensils. Everything for a delicious breakfast is the house including organic tea and coffee.   Refreshing yourself Th

neighborhood_overview: GreenWheels is situated in the front garden of a farm house overlooking the beautiful fields of Amsterdam. You find yourself in very peaceful rural surroundings where the noises of grazing sheep and an occasional tractor are your only noise diversions.  At this same spot there is a resting point for hikers and bikers. U do not share any facilities with them.  This is the ultimate location for a romantic get away.  You will not find a better place to rest. There are various walking and cycling routes that take you through beautiful sceneries. Bird watchers will love it here due it's divers bird culture. Canoes and electrical driven 'whisper boats' are for rent in the near vicinity and the bustling Amsterdam is just a short bike ride away.  Please see travel guide I made for further information on what to do.
transit: GreenWheels is just a stones throw away from Amsterdam central station. It's approximately 15 minutes by car, 30 minutes by bike and is also reachable by public transport.
interaction: I will be there to meet check you in and help you on your way. During your stay I can always be reached by phone.
house_rules: - Smoking is only permitted outside the house.  The location is situated in a peaceful area where people come to relax. Please take this into consideration. There are sheep in the garden please do not feed them.
host_about:

My life long passion has been the hospitality industry.  I am a chef and entrepreneur by profession. My latest adventure was building my tiny house.. an absolute wonderful project to do. 

I love good food, meeting new people, hiking, dancing, taking care of people.. I adore my friends and family. I believe that true kindness to oneself and others is the key to a happy world. 

Looking forward to meeting you soon!

host_about:
I am a friendly, easygoing young lady and love to help. I was born in Amsterdam. My father was a spanish immigrant and my mom is a daughter of a chinesh immigrant and a dutch mom, so i am a multiculti lady with respect for other cultures and religions.

I like to communicate with different people and to get to know you and your interests. 

I am used to share a house, so i will always respect your properties and privacy. 

I love cats, music, nature, the beach and the sea, good and healthy food, spending time with family and friends or my sweet boyfriend. 

Really like the principal of Airbnb. I studied tourism and have the dream to open my own B&B one day. With airbnb i can practice a little.

If you need any tips on how to spend your time in Amsterdam, i would like to share some stories.

Please ask if you like to know anything else.

host_about: We live on the ROMA since 1997 and constructed our home in the cargo compartment. We like to construct and renovate ourselves but decided to ask a professional (ship) carpenter to help us renovate the deck-house. We are very pleased with the result and like to share it with you! I love cooking (we mainly eat ecological and vegan food) and enjoy living at the edge of the city. My daughter Yelle and Ghani  run into the fields regularly. During the school season we enjoy going to the theater and see lots of contemporary dance. During holidays we like to travel (Senegal, Cuba, Indonesia, Bali, Marocco) and/or we stay home and enjoy the cosy athmosphere in Schellingwoude. I work at the dance department of the Amsterdam School of the Arts, Ghani owns a carrousel and works as a performer and Yelle is in her final year of her secondary education (A levels).

summary: Situated in the north of Amsterdam. Best for families; 2min to the A10 highway (exit116) and close to nature/city. The property has a front and back garden and is situated in a charming and quiet street. Great to come home to after a day in the city.
space: The house is located in a quite street, with several semidetached houses. Its a three floor modern house (160 square meters) with lost of windows and sunlight inside.  The open kitchen is located at the ground floor attached by a small living room. From here you have acces to the beautiful garden.  First floor is a spacious living room with a big corner seat for relaxing after a busy day. Sunny balcony. Second floor has a big double bed bedroom, a bedroom with two single beds and a bathroom with shower and bath. Kitchen with all facilities, digital tv, wifi. Sun all day in the garden with lots of privacy.

neighborhood_overview: Living in the thriving northern part of Amsterdam brings you the perfect blend of tranquility and the vibe of the city. The house located in a rural area ( 5 minute bike ride to meadows) with the advantage that after a 20 min bikeride in the other direction (or 10 minutes by bus) you will be in the centre of Amsterdam. The ancient villages Durgerdam, Holysloot, Ransdorp, Marken and Volendam can easily be reached by bike or car.  If you take the bike to the centre of Amsterdam you can choose to take the ferry from the NDSM area. On the grounds of this old shipyard restaurants and culture have nicely mixed.  Directly opposite from Central Station, in ‘our' north, is the former Shell officetower. This has been transformed into a breeding ground for creative businesses and artists and nightlife. Also here is the brand new small hall of the worldfamous venue Paradiso: they have created their own northern department called “de Tolhuistuin". Next to this is also the big white building; the EY

name: Your own waggon at the cow paradise
summary: A large carriage is redesigned as a hotel room and located on a farm just outside Amsterdam. On this farm 150 cows are milked. A unique way to become familiar with the life on the countryside. The modern stable is very nice to visit.
space: The pipowaggon, as we call the caravan, is located on a modern farm where cows are milked. You have a marvellous view over the countryside and you will experience silence and darkness. So close to Amsterdam you are in an overwhelming nature. The cowstable is a real adventure to visit. Cows everywhere. They walk around freely and in the same stable you can see the just born calves. Ben, the farmers is very willing to show you around. Outside the waggon is a terrace with a marvellous view on the countryside. In the night you can count the stars.

Cycling around in this area, with its beautiful 17th century villages is a life time experience.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. More and more hotspots are popping up! Visit urban beaches like Café de Ceuvel and Pllek! Both perfect spots to relax and enjoy the warm weather on the waterfront. Other nice places overlooking the IJ-lake are film museum EYE (enjoy the sunset on their beautiful terrace!), seafood restaurant Stork and THT restaurant. One of our favourite areas in Amsterdam North is the NDSM Wharf. Known as one of the best festival locations of Amsterdam. North is also the place to be for vintage and thrift shopping. You can’t miss the monthly flea market in the IJ-hallen, a true second hand heaven.
notes: Guests we look for: - Respectful of neighbours (keep level of noise down) - Non-smokers (or smokers that smoke outside) - Above 30 when in a group - Any age if staying as a couple At time of departure: make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done, the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean. name: Family-friendly freestanding dykehouse Amsterdam
summary: Our 135 m2 freestanding (mainly wooden) dykehouse in the 'rural North' of Amsterdam has a 70 m2 garden. It has free views on a green field and the IJ-lake in the front and and free views on a creek and woods at the back.  Despite the green surroundings it is only 7 km from Amsterdam Centre. You can get anywhere from our complimentary bikes.  There is also free parking in front of the house: unique for Amsterdam! The house is located on one of the 'old dykes' which is frequented by tourists.
space: Our dykehouse was built around 1890 and is mainly from wood. From the the outside it is pittoresque, but from the inside we recently renovated it in a modern way. You can cook in a well equiped kitchen complete with inductionplate, steam-oven and Nespresso coffeemachine. After that you could watch a movie on the 46 inch built-in LED-screen in the TV-room, just chill out in the gardenroom, stream your own music via Bluetooth with our soundsystem or enjoy the freestanding bath in the master bedroom.  A freestanding house like this is pretty rare in Amsterdam. But free views on both sides are even more rare. In the front there is a large picknickfield, a soccerfield an the IJ-lake. In the back you can enjoy our large garden with a view on a brook and lots of nature. Our dyke is a green oasis within the city of Amsterdam. And that only 6,5 km from Amsterdam Central Station and 7,5 km from the central Dam-square!  -The displayed juniorbed in the kid's room can be replaced for 2 adult beds.
description: Our 135 m2 freestanding (mainly wooden) dykehouse in the 'rural North' of Amsterdam has a 70 m2 garden. It has free views on a green field and the IJ-lake in the front and and free views on a creek and woods at the back.  Despite the green surroundings it is only 7 km from Amsterdam Centre. You can get anywhere from our complimentary bikes.  There is also free parking in front of the house: unique for Amsterdam! The house is located on one of the 'old dykes' which is frequented by tourists. Our dykehouse was built around 1890 and is mainly from wood. From the the outside it is pittoresque, but from the inside we recently renovated it in a modern way. You can cook in a well equiped kitchen complete with inductionplate, steam-oven and Nespresso coffeemachine. After that you could watch a movie on the 46 inch built-in LED-screen in the TV-room, just chill out in the gardenroom, stream your own music via Bluetooth with our soundsystem or enjoy the freestanding bath in the master bedroom.
neighborhood_overview: We are living on a touristic but tranquil route with lots of wooden houses, green fields and water. Don't be surprised to see rabbits around the house or antique sailingships passing by. Our dyke is in the middle of a a strip called 'the Old Dykes'. The beautifull Durgerdammerdijk  will lead you out of the city to monumental villages like Marken, via popular cyclingroutes. On the other side you will find the Nieuwendammerdijk. It is elected by our local newspaper 'the most beautifull street of Amsterdam'.  This dyke will lead you to the northern shore of the IJ-lake. This area, with filmmuseum Eye as its landmark, is now called  'one of the hippest neighbourhoods in the world' by international media. Especially on the old NDSM-shipyard you will find lots of festivals, restaurants, art-exhibitions and a huge flee-market. A perfect reflection of the area can be seen in a videoclip made by an enthousiastic inhabitant on Vimeo with the query 'NOORD North Amsterdam' (AirBnB does not allow d
notes: Our dyke used to be a fishermen's village but is now part of Amsterdam. The village-feel is still here though. Inhabitants organise many communal activities. The name 'Schellingwoude' is said to be based on the Dutch word for coins (schellingen) and wood (woude). The myth was that there were coins burried in the woods here: will you be able to find this treasure? In winter, if the ice is thick enough to skate on, the inhabitants of Amsterdam use our neighbourhood as their startingpoint for endless iceskating tours.  The original fishermen who lived here founded the dykehouses on cowskins.
transit: In most parts of Amsterdam it's hard to find parking space and you will pay a fortune to park your car. But we have unique free parking in front of the house.  There is also a busstop right in front of the houses where you can hop on a minibus which takes you to the 'Waterland'-villages Durgerdam, Ransdorp and Holysloot.  On a ten minute-walk there are busstops where you can get busses to Central Station (centre) or Amstel Station (east part).  Bridges and tunnels will get you on the other side of the IJ-lake, but the nicest way is the 24/7  free ferry.
access: Our guests have acces to the full house and garden, with exception of a little office.
interaction: We will be gone on holiday ourselves during your stay, so you will have full privacy.
house_rules: No smoking No pets No parties
host_about: Rudy is a TV-reporter and Carol a business controller. We have a 8-year old daughter.
street: Schellingwouderdijk, Amsterdam, North Holland 1023 ND, Netherlands

name: Family dike house with great view
summary: Located in a quiet neighbourhood, the house is about 20 min cycling from the central station of Amsterdam. Free parking in front of the house.
space: Our house is located at the very charming and characteristic Schellingwouderdijk, in the northern part of Amsterdam, a calm neighbourhood that brings you a perfect blend of rural landscape together with the vibe of the city.  The house is a typical Dutch ‘Dijk House’ with three levels. On the dike level are the main entrance and the living kitchen.  Below dike level is living room and on the first floor are the bedrooms.  There is a private garden with a terrace on the water behind the house. Directly across the street lays a stretched out lawn/playground where you'll find our own picnic table with great views on Amsterdam IJ, horses and ships sailing by. It's a lovely place to be when you come home after a day in the city.  The house has 2 bedrooms and a 2 person sleeping couch in the living room. Two bathrooms are at your disposal, one next to the living room and one on the first floor next to the bedrooms.  The kitchen is equipped with an oven, water cooker, microwave, fridge and di

neighborhood_overview: In a 5-minute bike ride you get to meadows or to the ancient villages Durgerdam, Holysloot, and Ransdorp, while Broek in Waterland, Marken and Volendam are close by car. A beautiful start to explore Amsterdam North is the EYE movie centre, which is located near the ferry and gives you a wonderful view at the IJ river and Amsterdam. And at the banks at the North side of the IJ (ten minutes ride) you will find previously disused warehouses which host creative start-ups, festivals, restaurants and, once a month, mega flea market.
notes: The house is near the IJsselmeer lake where you can swim and sail in summer. The area is perfect for bike trips, running and walking. All necessary shops are nearby, about 7 minutes walk is the local indoor farmer market, Landmarkt.
transit: It’s only a 20-30 min bike ride to the centre of Amsterdam (including a ferry ride to the central station).  From Schiphol Airport it takes 30 to 45 minutes with public transport (train, bus).  Bus 32 takes you from the central station in 10-15 minutes to our house (+5-10 minutes walk).  The A10 motorway (no noise) is nearby, exit S115 and then 3 minutes to go.
access: The entire (three floor) house of about 100m2 is at the guest's disposal (except the extension in which private stuff will be stored). The access to the house is by the main entrance on the street.  You can park your car for free in front of the house and bicycles (2 adult, 2 children and 1 'bakfiets') are available.
interaction: We won't be there during your stay. In some cases we might be there at you arrival and departure. Sometimes someone else will be present. You can always reach us by phone in case of emergencies, questions etc.
house_rules: We live in a neighborhood with a countryside feeling. The house is very suitable for families with children or friends that are looking for a calm and relaxing place near the citycenter.  No loud noise, no smoking and no pets.

name: Cosy B&B in 'rural Amsterdam'
summary: Our cosy and comfortable cottage - only 15 minutes from Amsterdam citycenter - has a unique view of the typical Dutch countryside. Visit the city, or use the bikes for a great bike ride to Monnickendam.  Free parking. Breakfast? No problem (€10 pp).
space: "Bed in Waterland" is situated in the yard of an old farmhouse.  The B&B, has many comforts and the view is endless.  In the winter you can enjoy fantastic skating and in summer you can walk, bike, go boating and swim.  All this on the outskirts of Amsterdam, near picturesque Broek in Waterland and only 8 km from Volendam. Anything goes here: from sightseeing to quietly enjoying nature. There's a double bed upstairs. The downstairs room has a sofa that unfolds into a full bed. That makes the B&B ideal for families.  The downstairs-room is also provided with a kitchenette with a small fridge and two burners, on which you can bake your eggs and bacon in the morning and if you want, prepare something for yourself during the day.

neighborhood_overview: B&B 'Bed in Waterland' is: - located on a typical Dutch dyke, along the Volgermeerpolder: a nature reserve, great for bird-watching, long walks and cycling;  - near the pretty village of Broek in Waterland;  - ten minutes by bus to Amsterdam City-center;  - 8 km cycling to Volendam;  - near a boat rental where you can rent what they call 'whisper boats' (electric boat), or canoes for boating through protected wetland and bird-rich nature;  - attractive for birdwatchers as the Volgermeerpolder attracts more and more different birds every year. - Pieter is an enthusiastic road racing cyclist. He can show you all kinds of nice routes.
notes: If need be, our neighbor has a Land Rover Defender you can rent. Let us know, if you are interested.
transit: We have two bikes you may borrow, to get around. They are also very convenient for getting you to the bus which will take you to Amsterdam, Volendam, etc. We also have plenty of parking space and free parking. And if need be, our neighbor has a Land Rover Defender you can rent. Let us know, if you are interested.
access: We have two extra bikes you may borrow. And you will find your own terrace in front of your barn. You also have your own entrance and parking lot. We have a trampoline and a small football field.  What you will receive as standard: - A warm welcome  - Use of 2 bicycles  - WiFi   - Cable TV   - Complimentary drinks and snacks in fridge  - Complimentary coffee and tea  - Basic kitchen with small fridge and microwave oven  - Fresh luxury hotel towels, linen and bed sheets  - Amsterdam map, Waterland map - Free parking if you arrive by car
interaction: We will welcome you when you arrive to explain a few things and see if you need anything. From that point on, you will have the B&B entirely to yourself. We will provide you with breakfast in the morning upon request.
house_rules: - No smoking inside. - Dogs are aloud with an extra surcharge. Please let us know beforehand.

neighborhood_overview: Discover Amsterdam-Noord (Amsterdam North). Noord is not only spacious and green, but also inspiring and vibrant. Here you will find an exciting mix of experimental festivals, picturesque country villages and stylish restaurants on the water.  Explore Noord on a bike! Just around the corner of our house you will find Nieuwendammerdijk and Schellingwouderdijk. They were built as dikes and among the first streets of Noord to be inhabited. For some locals, living on these streets is like living in paradise. Detached old houses with space to have kids. Outside the crowded city, but still minutes away. Garden cities like Nieuwendam, Schellingwoude, Durgerdam (an authentic village with wooden fisherman cottages), Ransdorp and Zunderdorp are nearby and all well worth a visit.
notes: Free access to bikes!
transit: From the airport, you can take the train to the central station and from there you can take the bus ( line 32 or 33) . After a short walk of 5 minutes you will arrive to the house. Of course is a taxi also possible (20 minutes drive).
access: Our guests will have access to our house, sunny garden and our bikes.
house_rules: Generally we expect our guests to treat our place as if its your own. Please take care of the neighbours, and greet everyone you come across. Please no pets, no smoking and no additional guests in the house. Thank you and enjoy your stay!
host_about: Hi, we are a family of four (our children are 6 and 2 years old) and we live happily in a quiet and lovely neighbourhood in Amsterdam. We love culture, books, traveling and the outdoors. As a couple we love city trips and discovering new places together. We have travelled to Africa, Australia, China, USA en Brasil but we also love Europe very much. We are well educated and nice people and we will love to tell you more about our beloved Amsterdam and surroundings. Our house is nice and light and has a child friendly garden and can fit a family of 4 or a couple.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam-Ransdorp is a rural village just under the smoke of Amsterdam. Back in the days the house was originally from the Mayor of the village. Rembrand used to paint from the church a couple of times and the village is now a protected monument of Amsterdam. One of our ministers told in a tv documentary that, in his point of view, this is one of the most beautiful spots to live in Amsterdam. This is really the comfortable old style Dutch living with modern convenience!
transit: 5 minutes from our house there is a 18 hole golf course. It's easy to reach the city.  By bike you will have a beautiful bike ride of 15 minutes to the centre of Amsterdam. By car it is a 5 minute drive to the park and ride where you can leave your car protected for only € 8,- for 24 hours. You will get maximum 6 tickets (two ways) for the tram and it will take you to the centre in only 10 minutes. 5 minutes by car or 10 by bike you will find a very nice high quality supermarket. It has fresh products from the area. 10 minutes by car you will find a huge shopping mall. 5 minutes from the farm you can rent a whisper boat and have a beautiful tour through waterland.Have a lunch in Broek in waterland or go all the way with the boat to Monnickendam. There is a city beach nearby and all major tourist spots are reachable in less than a 30 minutes. Also a lot of options to go out sailing. The charming villages and tranquil surroundings of neighbouring Waterland region make it a perfect destination for exploring by bike. We will lay out two lists for you. One with our favorite places to visit in the center of lovely Amsterdam and one with our favorite spots in Amsterdam-North, the 7th most hip neighborhoods of the world, according to (URL HIDDEN)  "Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. At the beginning and at the end of the village are small beaches where you can swim. From the village you are in the city within half an our by bike or car. Also public transport available.
transit: You will reach downtown Amsterdam in 15-30 minutes by car/bike. There is also public transport available. You can also rent a bike at MacBike at Central station and cycle to and from the house in around 30 minutes.

neighborhood_overview: Holysloot is the loveliest small village just outside Amsterdam: 15 minutes from Central Station. It is the best of both worlds: close to the city, but in the peace and quiet of the countryside.  For canoeing, walking, cycling it is a lovely area.  A canoe is available at the house (including life vest) and you can rent a boat at the other side of the village.  There are two bikes and a children's bike available including a child seat at the one of the bikes. In the local restaurant you can enjoy a good lunch and dinner from Wednesdays through Sundays.
notes: Details about closest supermarket, local restaurants and boat or bike rent is available at the house. It is approximately 7 - 12 minutes by car.  Upon request we can rent bikes delivered at the house for the whole family against a rent fee. There are toys, small bikes and cars, cutlery for children available. It is a very child-friendly house!
transit: A car is preferred (there is parking space for 2 big cars) as the bus goes once every hour and only during the week. If you need to rent a car let us know, we can help you with details.
access: You have access to the entire house except for two areas in the basement. Also the barn is kept locked.  We leave a lot of toys and stuff for the children. There is canoe with paddles available.  The kitchen has a large oven, as well as a microwave, grill, Jura coffee machine, juicer, blender, fridge and of course a dishwasher.  We offer WIFI and a new Samsung LED TV with Netflix and Internet.
interaction: Details and info is available about the surrounding and things to do. Brenda (she lives 3 houses away) is there to answer all your questions!
house_rules: After 10 PM no music outside and smoking is only allowed outside. Pets not allowed.  Please the house as it is yours and keep it clean! We expect you to leave the house clean: turn on the dishwasher (when you have dirty dishes), leave the house sweep-clean and tightly up things you have used.
host_about:

Enjoy the spacious garden with trampoline and great view over the water. The house is situated at a beautiful dyke in a calm area close to Amsterdam: Durgerdam. space: This amazing family dyke house offers at dyke level a spacious living room and modern kitchen with a stunning view to the lake at front side of the house and the endless meadows at the back side. At first floor you find two bedrooms: one romantic bedroom with double size bed and one bedroom with two single beds. Lovely extra livingroom at garden level with direct access to the large garden with trampoline: perfect to relax or play. Last but not least the large balcony at backside of the house bordering the kitchen area.

neighborhood_overview: The house is situated in a calm little village called Durgerdam next to Amsterdam: The Durgerdammerdijk is a lovely, authentic, very popular dyke with at the front side of the house a view over the small harbour and a small beach at the IJmeer, really nice to have a dip after a day in the city.
notes: In the garden there are chickens, the neighbours take care of them. Also there are three cats in the house, you need to take care of them.
transit: You can get to the house from Central Station by bus, it takes around 30 minutes. In the city centre you can rent bikes at several places or you can use the public transportation like trams and metro's to travel with.  By car: It is free parking at the parking place at the end of the village, 250 meters from the house. If you want to use the car to get into the city you can drive to closeby P+R park your car and take tram to Central Station (10 minutes), or Bus to East side of Amsterdam.
access: You have full and private access to the house during your stay.
interaction: For the rental of my house I asked Jolanda and Rob from Home2host to take care of everything, from the booking, the welcome at the house, the cleaning of my house after your stay. They will also handle all communication with you.
house_rules: Please respect the house and the neighbourhood. No smoking inside, no loud music, parties or drugs. Let us know your estimated time of arrival ánd departure as soon as possible.  We charge €20 for late check ins after 9.00 PM.
host_about: Hello I am Zander together with my family I live at a nice dyke in Durgerdam, a picturesque village at the lake close to Amsterdam. I am excited about renting our house to people who want to explore the great city of Amsterdam and love to stay in calm area.

name: Spacious room with private bathroom
summary: In the upcoming Amsterdam North we offer a spacious room with private bathroom on the first floor. Our  70's house is next to a bus stop to the centre and offers free parking. Enjoy our garden at the waterfront! Guests with reviews only.
space: Amsterdam = unique Amsterdam North is trending hugely. Pop up restaurants and bars, superfood markets, art etc. You can reach the Amsterdam city centre easy by bus, the bus stop is just around the corner. But you can also enjoy the countryside of Broek in Waterland, Monnickendam, Volendam and Edam (cheese market).  Our house is a 70's block-architecture, recently refurbished by us in an industrial way.  Your room is located on the 1st floor of our home. The room has a private bathroom with a shower. The toilet is located at mid-level. We offer 1 double bed or 2 single beds. We provide towels and bedlinen. We are clean and your linnen is washed with anti allergy detergent. We have a fully equiped kitchen you can use and cosy tv room with Netflix at your disposal. Our garden is for Amsterdam standards big, 400m2. Situated at a wide ditch/ canal south west side. Free parking on site/ at our street and a bus stop around the corner is also a big plus.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North gives you easy access to the city centre of Amsterdam and the rural pastures as well.  We have public transport in front of our house and we offer mountainbikes to go explore. If you like to visit the country side; Broek in Waterland, Monnickendam, Volendam, Edam are nearby and easy accesable by bus, car and bike (the latter if you are up for a workout). Amsterdam-North is booming, it hosts one of Amsterdams most modern building designs: the Eye film museum. It is also nice to cross the canal here with the ferry from and to Central Station. There is a great view over the water as well. North offers many hipster places to hang out, enjoy drinks and good food: Plek, Loetje aan 't IJ, Bistro Noord, Noorderlicht, Hotel de Goudfazant, Il Pecorino and so on. For vintage shopping we recommand the IJhallen it is the largest flea market in The Netherlands, held once a month on Saturday and Sunday. There is small supermarket across the street, but very close in the Waterlandplein
notes: 1 single bed extendable to double bed (two matrasses) 1 sofa bed 140cm wide so very cosy!
transit: The bus stop is litteraly around the corner. Less than 30 min to central station. Very close to A10 ring road. Easy access to tourist sites around Amsterdam. Free parking! You can rent our Piaggio MP3 (car drivers license) motor bike. Free parking in the centre! Only 12 minutes to Dam Square. You can rent our mountain bikes (2) to enjoy Amsterdam by bike.
access: You can use your room and private bath room. You are welcome to use our spacious garden for outside drinks. We can provide cutlery for your food and drinks. You can use our kitchen for cooking small dishes. We have a dish washer for your dishes. We have a large punch bag to facilitate your stress level.
interaction: We will welcome you on arrival and are at your disposal for local tips and to do's. Since we both have fulltime jobs we are not always around. This is not a hotel so don't expect 24/7 service :-).
house_rules: You respect our home and leave it as you have found it on arrival. You understand the principle of being a guest in someones house :-) You understand that we do this out of hobby. We are not a hotel with 24/7 service, since we have fulltime jobs. The room you rent is where you stay. The living room is ours. The 70's TV room can be used. Netflix available :-). Other rooms are out of bounds for you as you may understand. You can use our kitchen for small dishes. Leave it as clean as you have found it. We have a funky espresso machine. Only use after full understanding how it works. € 1,00 per coffee/espresso/cappu due to high qulity fresh roasted beans. Tea is on the house. We have an electronic front door lock. You will get an electronic key that you can use with your smartphone.
host_about:
Dealing with travel health for the last 2 decades I have a more than strong interest in travelling, but are bored of hotels. I live in a 70's design house in Amsterdam-Noord with Corine. Your room is spacious and on the first floor, with private bathroom. Privacy guaranteed! Looking forward to seeing you there.

Save travels!

Arnoud & Corine

name: Charming dikehouse A'dam North (2 kayaks/1 boat)
summary: Our cosy typical Dutch dike house has 3 levels. Below dike level there is the comfortable kitchen with kitchentable facing the spacious garden.  The kitchen includes: oven, dishwasser, nespresso machine, Smeg Fridge. In the kitchen is also a washing machine and a dryer. The living room on the middle floor, has a couch, sofa and piano. On both sides big windows with a great view. On the upper floor there are two bedrooms and a bathroom with shower. Big garden with two kayaks & boat.
space: De Schellingwouderdijk is one of the most characteristic streets of Amsterdam.  It’s a typical smalltown neighbourhood, with a quiet and green surrounding, it’s like a hidden gem.  You have the impression of living in a old dutch village within the city ring, with all great famous museums, boutique stores and great restaurants & cafes easy to reach. This northern part of Amsterdam brings you the perfect blend of quitness and the vibe of the city.   Our very typical Dutch style dikehouse, small and cosy, has 3 levels. The house is suitable for 4 persons (2 adults and 2 childs suits best), great for families with 1 or 2 kids.   Below dike-level there is the comfortable kitchen with an expanding round table facing the spacious and private garden (140m2).  The house includes a fully equiped kitchen with dishwasher, oven, Nespresso machine, juicer, water cooker etc. In the back kitchen there’s the washingmachine and the tumble dryer. neighborhood_overview: Discover Amsterdam-Noord (Amsterdam North). Noord is not only spacious and green, but also inspiring and vibrant:   At he banks at the North side of the IJ (ten minutes ride) you will find one of the most hipster neighbourhoods in the world. Previously disused warehouses host creative start-ups, festivals, restaurants and, once a month, mega flea market.   On the other hand Amsterdam Noord has picturesque country villages. The historical polder landscape is on cycling distance. You can visit towns like Volendam, Edam, Monnickendam and the historical village of Broek in Waterland.  By car you can easily visit “Edam” or “Monnickendam” on the banks of the “IJsselmeer” or visit the “Zaanse Schans” with its historical windmills. And at the several beautiful lakes it’s possible to swim or sail.   And Amsterdam Noord has stylish restaurants on the water (visited regurarly by Amsterdammers). For example we have Landmarkt (with terrace), Restaurant Stork (with an amazing terrace), Hotel de Goud
notes: Child friendly house  Lot of toys and playgrounds for the kids, in the garden and in front of the door. Paradise for kids.
transit: Public transportation to the centre is found nearby, 7 min. walk and by bus it takes 10 minutes to get to Central Station. We have free parking in front of the house and good acces to the main highway. Schiphol Airport is just 20 minutes away by car and it takes 30 to 45 minutes with public transport (train, bus).
access: You can use the whole house with all facilities, including 2 bikes and 2 little bikes for children. But most of all enjoy the spacious garden with BBQ, a trampoline, 1 rowing boat and 2 kayaks.
interaction: During you're stay, there will be nobody in the house, but you can always contact us. Also all of our neighbours (who are like family) will help you as much as they can.
house_rules: No pets  No smoking inside
host_about:
Hi, we are Ernst, Jessica and Madelief. Madelief is our 5 year old daughter.
Jessica is owner of an artgallery and restaurant. Ernst is a Sr. Event Producer.
We love our beautiful dike house. When we come home after work (we work in the city center), arriving on the dike, we have the feeling of being on a holiday (still every day, after 9 years). We would like to share this feeling with you! Enjoy your stay and have a great time in Amsterdam.

Zelf heb ik ook een heel aantal mooie reizen gemaakt, o.a. naar Zuid Amerika, Azië en Noord en Zuid Europa. Mijn favoriete bestemmingen zijn Cambodja en Japan, omdat het zeer gastvrij op mij overkwam. Uiteraard staan er ook nog een hele hoop landen op mijn wish list, maar voorlopig houd ik het bij Amsterdam op mijn mooie schip en hoop ik anderen gastvrij te mogen ontvangen op B&B de Griend.

name: Lovely Country side house Amsterdam
summary: Het appartement  is landelijk gelegen en maar 15 minuten van het Centrum van Amsterdam. Geniet van rust en ruimte in een geheel ingericht appartement met tuin en alle voorzieningen voor een prettig verblijf.
space: Het appartement is vrijstaand. Grote woonkamer met vide met tweepersoonsbed. Extra slaapkamer met stapelbed en bed van 1.40 bij 2.00 meter. Keuken met magnetron en koelkast in de woonkamer. Openslaande deuren naar de tuin met terras. Douche en toilet. U kunt voor het huis parkeren met uw auto. Vlakbij is er een supermarkt en een winkelcentrum. In 5 minuten bent u met de auto bij de park and ride waar u kunt parkeren en in 10 minuten bent u midden in het centrum van Amsterdam. U kunt op loopafstand vissen. Vele wandelpaden. U kunt in Durgerdam in het Ijsselmeer zwemmen. U bent vlakbij typische nederlandse dorpjes, Marken, Volendam,Durgerdam. Het unieke aan de plek is dat u vlakbij het centrum van amsterdam bent maar kunt genieten van het landelijk karakter van nederland met zijn koeien en schapen en de rust.

neighborhood_overview: Ransdorp is one of the most authentic places in the very close vicinity of Amsterdam centre (10 minutes). The house is located in Ransdorp, a typical Dutch village with characteristic wooden houses set around a monumental tower; where circa 1645 Rembrandt made many drawings. The town is called the 'Garden of Amsterdam'. Our well located country suite makes it easy for you to visit the busy city centre of Amsterdam with its many museums, the Anne Frank House, shops, bars, restaurants and canals.  You can also enjoy the tranquility of Waterland: taking our bicycles (free) or boat (rent) that will take you through country site roads, lakes, outstretched meadows, polder landscape, and picturesque villages with wooden houses and farms. You can just relax in our garden and enjoy the amazingly panoramic view. The village of Ransdorp is 20 minutes drive from tourist places Marken, Volendam, Edam and Zaanse Schans.
notes: Breakfast and bicycles are included in the room price. We have a children's playground in the garden with a trampoline, slide and swings. The area is wonderful to bike and hike. There are special bike tracks to bike/hike safely. There are some good restaurants in the vicinity. There is a P&R point at 5 minutes drive, where you can park your car and take a tram to the centre (10 minutes).
transit: There is a bus stop at 100m from our house and there is a tram stop at 5 mins. by car or 12 mins by bike. You can also take the bike into town to get around. A car would be handy. There is a P&R (Park & Ride) point at 5 minutes drive, where you can park your car very cheaply and take a tram to the centre (10 minutes).
access: The Suite:  A lofty 65m2 peaceful room with a sleeping and a living area. The sleeping area has a comfortable double bed, a shower and a wash basin. The living area has a sofa, TV/DVD set, a sofa bed (for 2 extra people/children), a dining table, a refrigerator (minibar) and a water boiler to make tea/coffee. The beds are made with fresh sheets and blankets. There are daily fresh towels and toiletries available in the room. The room is on the first floor; your private toilet is on the ground floor. The room offers a great view over the surrounding farmland. You can relax in our garden and enjoy the amazingly panoramic view. We have free bikes for you to use.
interaction: Interaction: as much as the guests want themselves. I shall welcome the guests personally to explain things and hand them the key. We can see each other at breakfast if the guest wish to and if needed I can give guests information about the area/city/activities. Guests are asked to inform me about there arrival time before their arrival and whether they are adults or adults and children.
house_rules: Guests are asked to inform me about there arrival time before their arrival and whether they are adults or adults and children. Feel at home and enjoy the place with respect to the house, environment and neighbors. We do not allow pets. The room is a non smoking room. There is plenty of room to smoke outside.
host_about:
My husband and I have travelled extensively all over the world and have tried to learn through our good experiences as well as from our bad ones. We love traveling, nature, beaches, mountains, cities, good food, great wines, dancing, movies, reading, sports, and last but not least playing with our 2 sons.
We are sure you will enjoy staying in our country house in the close vicinity of Amsterdam Centre as much as we enjoy living here. We like to mix intimacy with good service and the freedom to enjoy, what is for us, a wonderful place to be yourself.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. More and more hotspots are popping up! Visit urban beaches like Café de Ceuvel and Pllek! Both perfect spots to relax and enjoy the warm weather on the waterfront. Other nice places overlooking the IJ-lake are film museum EYE (enjoy the sunset on their beautiful terrace!), seafood restaurant Stork and THT restaurant. One of our favourite areas in Amsterdam North is the NDSM Wharf. Known as one of the best festival locations of Amsterdam. North is also the place to be for vintage and thrift shopping. You can’t miss the monthly flea market in the IJ-hallen, a true second hand heaven.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is green and quiet. There are nice parks  where you can run or just strole. But within 15 minutes you are in the bustling center of Amsterdam with all the turistic highlights.  A 5 minute walk from the appartment there are many grocery shops, 2 supermarkets, a pharmacy, a bakery and some take-aways and a Coffeeshop where they sell weed and hash.That's legal in Holland. Within a 10 minute walk there is a shopping center with many clothing stores and some nice lunch places. The appartment is situated a 10 minutes walk from the only real Amsterdam golf course, if you are into golfing. There are some beautiful traditional Dutch fishermen's or farmers villages within 20-30 min cycling like Durgerdam, Zunderdorp or a little further Monickendam.
notes: I do my best to make your stay a pleasant and comfortable one.  But unfortunatley im not a mind reader ;) So if there is something that you have questions or complaints about, please dont hasitate to talk to me about it, so I can do somethig about it.
transit: There are two busstops a 2 minute walk from the apartment. The busses will take you to the historic center of Amsterdam in 15 minutes. During the day they go every 10 minutes, in the evening every 15 minutes and when you go clubbing there is a nightbus every hour. The night bus also is a 2 minute walk from the apartment.
access: Besides of course the bathroom and toilet, you will have access to the kitchen with oven and dish washer. interaction: From monday to thursday I will usually be there in te evening. Friday, saturday and sunday it's variable. Im a social person, so if you need tips and advise about how to get around Amsterdam, just ask. I will do my best to make the most out of your Amsterdam experience.
house_rules: Im easy going and flexible. Just treat me and my apartment with some basic respect. But for the record: - Minimum age 18. - No extra guests. - Do your smoking in the garden.
host_about:
Hello!  Here a little info about me,

Im a 30 something girl with Colombian roots. I live in this neighboorhoud since 2012. The gentrification just started here, so its a dynamic area to live. But what I like the most is the village feeling while your a 15 minutes commute away form the bustling center of Amsterdam.

I love to travell and meet new people myself. My travelling style is ouside the box. My favorite destinations are Colombia and New York City. 
I can't go without my friends, music and dancing, good food/ wine and the calmness of nature. I like to read litterature and articles about social/politcial issues. 

With an open mind, mutual respect and friendlyness I like to connect with people. I like people to feel at home when they stay at my place.

So hope to welcome you soon as a guest in my apartment!

Carolina

summary: A large carriage is redesigned as a hotel room and located on a farm just outside Amsterdam. On this farm 150 cows are milked. A unique way to become familiar with the life on the countryside. The modern stable is very nice to visit.
space: The pipowaggon, as we call the caravan, is located on a modern farm where cows are milked. You have a marvellous view over the countryside and you will experience silence and darkness. So close to Amsterdam you are in an overwhelming nature. The cowstable is a real adventure to visit. Cows everywhere. They walk around freely and in the same stable you can see the just born calves. Ben, the farmers is very willing to show you around. Outside the waggon is a terrace with a marvellous view on the countryside. In the night you can count the stars.

Cycling around in this area, with its beautiful 17th century villages is a life time experience.

summary: This authentic restored dike house from 1903 is situated on the Schellingwouderdijk in Amsterdam. The beautiful surroundings are the perfect combination for people who love both the City Centre and rural life. The unique, characteristically decorated 3 floor (118 m3) Family House offers views on the Amsterdam IJ waterside and a meadow with wooden children's playground and tables from where one can enjoy the panoramic view of horses and the ships sailing by.
space: Schellingwoude is a former Fishing-village in the Northern part of Amsterdam. Various (sustainable/organic) grocery stores, supermarkets and bakeries are at walking distance. Free parking in front. neighborhood_overview: Schellingwoude is a former Fishing-village in the Northern part of Amsterdam. The Monumental Dike is situated between meadows, park and the IJ, with the City Centre just at the other side of the water. Various (sustainable/organic) grocery stores, supermarkets and bakeries are at walking distance. A perfect area for cycling, Marken and Volendam are a 30 minute bike-ride along the dike, Edam and Monnikendam are at the distance of an hour by bike through the beautiful meadows with horses, cows and sheep. One can have a break or High Tea in one of the authentic Cafes or a glass of biological milk, or biological ice-cream in a farm on the way. Excellent (sustainable) restaurants in both the rural countryside and in the artistic part of Northern Amsterdam - De Ceuvel, Pllek, Il Pecorino, Wilhelmina Dok (with views on the large cruiseships), Loetje, De Goudfazant, etc. Or one can have a cool beer or white wine on a terrace at Het Sluisje, Het Schoolhuis, Beer Brewery Oedipus, Landmarkt or in

I was born in a nonexistent city (Frunze) of a nonexistent country (Soviet Union). However, the place does exist on a map and is nowadays called Kyrgyzstan. It has the highest mountains I have ever seen and also the most beautiful lake one can ever imagine.
While studying Physics and Mathematics at Moscow State University I was leading a group on meditative jogging.
After finishing my thesis on corneal topographer at VU I felt in love with Amsterdam and decided to stay here forever.
I enjoy cooking, my speciality is spicy korean salad with organic carrots.

summary: Best of both worlds! Quiet street on authentic Dutch dyke very close to Amsterdam city centre. - On North shore of the Amsterdam IJ - Amazing views  - 15 min bike ride from Dam square - Perfect for children - Free parking in front
space: Situated on the waterfront of the Amsterdam IJ lays  the peaceful almost fairy-like Schellingwouderdijk, one of the most remarkable streets of entire Amsterdam. On this typical dutch dyke stands our charming 3/4 bedroom house (130m2). Surrounded by lots of greenery, with a private garden and a large rooftop terrace the perfect place for a relaxing holiday just a couple of steps away from the Amsterdam city centre.  The House Our three level house is built on/in a typical dutch dyke, with our garden laying ten feet below the main entrance. It's recently renovated and  surprisingly spacious. There are three different bedrooms and a extra queen size bed on the first floor passage. The cozy kitchen (email hidden) and is equipped with an oven, gascooker, large Smeg refrigeartor,  dishwasher, watercooker and an espressomachine. neighborhood_overview: Schellingwoude is one of two (Nieuwendam is the other) former fishing-villages which nowadays are fully incorporated in upcoming creative and trendy Amsterdam North. The atmosphere however is still that of a rural community, where everybody's laidback and enjoying the better things of life.
notes: Take into account that our petcat Loki is staying in our house when you are visiting. This means that we will ask you to feed him. This will only take one minute a day.
transit: There's a bus stopping nearby which takes you to the city centre in 7 minutes.  By car it's only 5 minute ride to the city centre, but beware of the expensive parkingfees. All main exit routes are very easy to reach (3 min), so in the blink of an eye you're on your way to discover the rest of Holland
access: The entire house is at the guests disposal, including a private garden, rooftop terrace and our picnic and playground directly in front of our house.
interaction: I will be there at your arrival and departure. In the meantime the house is completely yours. Off course you can always reach me by phone in case of emergencies, questions etc.
host_about:
Before coming to Amsterdam, I've lived, worked and studied in Utrecht, Groningen, Salamanca, Guatemala City and Madrid. 

Nowadays I'm busy raising my two children (2,5 years and 4 years), enjoying the vibrant Amsterdam city life and meanwhile for a living helping to bring the Olympics 2028 to Amsterdam.

name: 房间空旷舒适，阿姆斯特丹北坐公交到中心站十五分钟左右，步行到Dam广场
summary: 位置在阿姆斯特丹北离阿姆火車站只需要十多分钟的车程,徒步到附近的购物中心也只需要十多分钟,购物逛街非常方便!我们的公寓有空旷的阳台,舒適的晒太陽,寬敞的客廳!
space: 房子在公寓的一楼,房子有两个卧室其中一个出租,一個客廳,一個開放式廚房,一個浴室一個廁所,還有一個大陽台!
description: 位置在阿姆斯特丹北离阿姆火車站只需要十多分钟的车程,徒步到附近的购物中心也只需要十多分钟,购物逛街非常方便!我们的公寓有空旷的阳台,舒適的晒太陽,寬敞的客廳! 房子在公寓的一楼,房子有两个卧室其中一个出租,一個客廳,一個開放式廚房,一個浴室一個廁所,還有一個大陽台! 出租的臥室裡兩張單人床,衣柜,椅子可以隨意使用,但不希望被破壞,厨房,卫生间,客厅共用,不提供早餐,中餐和晚餐,可提供厨房,鍋,碗,筷子,調味料等免費使用,可以自己去超市購買食材做飯 ! 使用完後,請清洗乾淨放回原處。注意:冰箱裡的食材是房主自己一家吃的,不能隨意取用,不是免費的,如果需要請諮詢房主。 希望是中國人入住或者會講中文的旅客,房主英文不好,英文交流可能會產生很多誤會,可以每天交流,房主一家三口住一起! 环境优美,鸟语花香,距离boven't winkelcentrum 走路十来分钟,购物逛街都很便捷! 非常便利,出门3分钟就有公交站,十几分钟就可以到阿姆斯特丹中心站,那裡有轉各個地方的公交與地鐵甚至各個國家的火車!友情提示:荷蘭的公交,地鐵,火車都是有時間表的,提早下載一份,方便出行不耽誤時間!,从史基浦机场到我家路线:坐火车3-4站,到达阿姆斯特丹中心站,走到33路公交站点上车,9站,15分钟左右在Amerbos站下车,分钟内可到我家。 晚上十点之后不能太大声喧哗,这是一个安静的生活区域!房主一家三口也住一起!我们会为每位旅客准备好干净的毛巾,(牙刷请自带)我们不收取清洁费,離開時保持房間整潔乾淨,如果你把房间弄的很脏乱,请付额外的清洁费用€10-50不等!入住時間是下午的14:00,沒有房客住在裡面可以提早入住,退房時間為中午的12:00,沒有其它旅客須要入住的情況下時間可以延遲到17:00,如果妳的行程時間還有多餘需要暫時存放行李,我們可以提供免費場地存放!

name: Family house in Amsterdam
summary: We offer a countryside cottage at one of the most beautiful locations of Amsterdam.Outside but still at cycling distance of the center's heart. Walking, cycling, canoeing, shopping, restaurants, art galleries, theatre, it's all possible and close by.
description: We offer a countryside cottage at one of the most beautiful locations of Amsterdam.Outside but still at cycling distance of the center's heart. Walking, cycling, canoeing, shopping, restaurants, art galleries, theatre, it's all possible and close by. The neighbourhood is nice and quiet but if you like to do something, there's enough. There are cycling, walking and canoeing route's. Nearby you can have coffee or lunch and there are some restaurants. Supermarket is at cycling distance. The city and it's theatre's, galleries, restaurants and so on is at cycling distance and there's a bus going. If you cycle you ca cross the water with a very small ferry, which is nice. There are buses, but they take a while. Bus 37 stops near our house.

host_about: Hallo, ik ben een werkende moeder van 3. Samen met mijn man wonen we op het platteland bij Amsterdam. We houden van lekker eten, reizen, de zee & de zon!

name: B&B in 't Hooi
summary: In 't Hooi is a property( 45m2) situated in a completely renovated and comfortable haystack. This accommodation is situated in an old and historical village, only 6 km from the centre of Amsterdam
space: The haystack is a very comfortable small appartment (45m2) with private covered terras, located independently. Its surrounded by grass-land and a often lot of sheep. Downstairs you will find the well equiped kitchen and sittingroom and upstairs the bedroom with large comfortable bed, and the bathroom with shower and toilet.
description: In 't Hooi is a property( 45m2) situated in a completely renovated and comfortable haystack. This accommodation is situated in an old and historical village, only 6 km from the centre of Amsterdam The haystack is a very comfortable small appartment (45m2) with private covered terras, located independently. Its surrounded by grass-land and a often lot of sheep. Downstairs you will find the well equiped kitchen and sittingroom and upstairs the bedroom with large comfortable bed, and the bathroom with shower and toilet. There is a lot of space around the haystack and a private terras with chairs, a large table and with bbq and outside heater. We are very pleased, if required, to give our quests all the information they need, concerning the city but also the area around Amsterdam. We have a lot of information available in the appartment. The extra value of this area is that it is only 6 km from the centre of Amsterdam. Its a very quiet place (farmland) to rest after a long day in the busy
neighborhood_overview: The extra value of this area is that it is only 6 km from the centre of Amsterdam. Its a very quiet place (farmland) to rest after a long day in the busy city of Amsterdam. Apart from the city, this ar ea is very attractive for cycling and walking. There are special bikeroads everywhere. We rent bikes. Also its very nice to hire a small boat (electric) just nearby to explore the area and the beautiful small villages from the water.
notes: De accommodatie is een appartement met een volledig ingerichte keuken, maar wij kunnen op aanvraag ook een ontbijt serveren. Het appartement is comfortabel ingericht en heeft vloerverwarming op de begande grond en in de slaapkamer centrale verwarming.
transit: Public transport is available but not very frequently. 3 km from our place is a cheap parkingplace and a fast streetcar to the centre which takes only 5 minutes. All the information about these possibilities are also available in the appartment.
access: There is a lot of space around the haystack and a private terras with chairs, a large table and with bbq and outside heater.
interaction: We are very pleased, if required, to give our quests all the information they need, concerning the city but also the area around Amsterdam. We have a lot of information available in the appartment.
house_rules: Smoking is forbidden in the appartment. Pets are on request.
host_about: Ik ben geboren en getogen in Amsterdam, heb op verschillende plekken in Amsterdam gewoond. Ik woon nu op de mooiste plek in de gemeente Amsterdam, nl. op het platteland van Amsterdam, en toch slechts op een kwartier van het centrum. Ik ben gastvrij, vind het erg leuk gasten te ontvangen en te informeren en organiseer, naast de B&B, ook evenementen voor bedrijven.

name: Lovely family home with garden - free parking
summary: Our home is located in Amsterdam-Noord, about 20 minutes from Central Station. It is perfect for discovering both the sights of Amsterdam, as well as places like Volendam, Edam and the Zaanse Schans. We have lots of toys for your kids to play with, and a small, but nice garden, with a barbecue you can use. The house is very comfortable, with a fully equiped kitchen, large sofa to lounge on and a bathroom that has both a bath tub and a shower.
space: The house has a roomy living room with attached kitchen, with an adjacent garden. The first floor has a master bedroom with double bed, two smaller bedrooms (for children), and a bathroom with bathtub, shower, toilet and sink. The washing machine and dryer are located on the attic. You can park you car for free in the front yard, or on the street behind ours (H. Stolleplantsoen).

name: Spacious waterfront house w garden
summary: Spacious 4 floor semidetached house near the center of Amsterdam, yet in a beautiful, charming and quite environment. Overlooking the water Private garden with terraces and BBQ.
space: The house is situated on a dike on the edge of the green hinterland of Amsterdam. The villages Durgerdam, Ransdorp and Holysloot are nearby. The center of Amsterdam can be reached in about 15 minutes.  The house has four floors. On the basement floor,  that connects to the garden, you'll find a large living-/play-/TV-room with a separate toilet.  You enter the house on the dike level floor, that has a very spacious living-/diningroom with a fully equipped open kitchen. On this floor there is a bedroom with a queensize bed, ensuite bathroom (sink and shower), a separate toilet and a laudry room with washing machine and dryer. On the first floor is the large master bedroom with kingsize bed, ensuite bathroom (double sink and shower) and a separate toilet. On the second floor there are two bedrooms available, one with a single bed (extra matress under the bed) and one with a queensize bed and a small balcony overlooking the water. On this floor there is a separate toilet, and a bathroom w
description: Spacious 4 floor semidetached house near the center of Amsterdam, yet in a beautiful, charming and quite environment. Overlooking the water Private garden with terraces and BBQ.
neighborhood_overview: The house is situated on the edge of the green hinterland of Amsterdam, in the village Schellingwoude, part of the popular district Amsterdam-North. The house is built on a dike, overlooking the water IJ on the front, and the greenland on the back. The villages Durgerdam, Ransdorp and Holysloot are nearby.
notes: If needed, a baby bed can be arranged for.  Bed linen and towels can be made available against payment (EUR 1,50 per person per day). End cleaning is mandatory (EUR 65), on request extra cleaning during your stay is possible (EUR 50 for 3 hours).  Public transport to the center is on walking distance, on request you can make use of our bikes. There is a nice country-style supermarket and restaurant on walking distance.
transit: The center of Amsterdam can be reached by car, public transport or bike in about 15 minutes. You can park your car for free on the (quiet) road just in front of the house.
access: Two rooms in the house (our office on the first floor and one bedroom on the second floor) will be locked to store our private belongings. Still with four bedrooms left there will be more than enough room for you and your family!
interaction: Check-in and check-out will be taken care of by a friendly host who will also be available for questions during your stay. If needed, we can be reached by phone and/or email.
house_rules: Smoking in the house is prohibited. We expect our guests to treat our property with respect. No loud music or parties allowed. No pets allowed.

name: Romantic Houseboat
summary: Welcome aboard! You will stay in the original skippers' cabin from our into a house converted historic ship from 1925. You have your own entrance and a roof terrace at your disposal.
space: Our ship is in the vibrant port of Schellingwoude and is surrounded by other inhabited ships as well as craft ships. Parking is free and 50 m away there's a supermarket where you can eat as well.The center of Amsterdam is easily accessible by bike or by tram (15 minutes walking distance from our ship). The surroundings of Schellingwoude is very beautiful, a paradise for walkers and cyclists! The price is € 80 per night and the minimum stay is two nights. We provide a simple breakfast for the first day.  If you book a whole week you will pay € 500 (instead of € 560)  NB. the average standing height in the room is 1.80m! And you have to cross 5 ships before you are on our ship!
