neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood:  My house is located in the north of the city, near a park, close to the NDSM terrain. As a former shipyard this is a unique part of town where you can find nice restaurants and hangouts, shopping, art and great (music) events. You'll also find the Eye filmmuseum at this side of town.  By bus you'll be in 10 minutes in the city centre at Central Station. From here you'll get quickly to the Dam Square, Jordaan, Vondelpark, red light district and museum area.  Seen the urban city and wanna experience the country side of Amsterdam? Visit picturesque Volendam, Holysloot or for example Durgerdam, and refresh body & mind at the IJsselmeer.  Shopping centre Buikslotermeerplein is a 200 mtr walk from the apartment, there are many shops and supermarkets in the neighbourhood, open untill 21h.  There are some good places i can recommend for cheap and healthy breakfast or dinner (Thaifood, typical Dutch, Arabic, sushi, organic food, KFC, Chinese, etc).
transit: Public Transport:  Next to my frontdoor you'll find the busstop; every 10 minutes bus 33 takes you in 10 minutes to the Central Station.  You can also get bus 32 or 34. Nightbus number 361 too stops in front of the house.  Another way is to explore the city by bike, it's  a nice ride to one of the 5 ferry's. The ferry's are all free and cross the river IJ all day & night to get you into town or back 24/7. About 5 minutes from the apartment there's a bike rental for approximately €13,- a day.  You can get to all parts of the city easily.  If you travel by plane, it's easy to come by train to the Central Station, then take bus 33 (stop at Halte Bakkerswaal).
access: The apartment: I offer a 70 mtr.2 clean, spacious, modern apartment. It's a cozy designed place with a comfortable living.  In the fully equipped kitchen you'll find everything to make yourself a nice meal if you're not eating out.  Seperate bedroom (double boxspring bed, size 160-200) with bathroom, this has a big size shower. Nice fresh towels and bed sheets.  Seperate toilet. Free WiFi. Spacious balcony.
interaction: I always love to meet and welcome my guests personally at their arrival. This way we can get to know each other a little; I can show you around at the apartment and answer any questions you might have. I can be reached by phone or email 24/7 and can get there in a minute if there's anything you need assistance with.
house_rules: No Smoking, only on the balcony. No drugs. No exeptions at this.  To get you started I'll welcome you with some real good coffee, tea, and a bottle of wine.  If you lose the key, it will cost €25,-  Please respect the nightrest of our neighbours. If there's a problem, let me know! We can solve it.
host_about:
LANGUAGE:  English, Nederlands

WORK: Interior design projectmanager 

ABOUT ME: Hi, I'm your host, Mirjam. As a guest I started to use airbnb about two years ago in 2013. It was such a good experience for me that I decided to start renting my own apartment at airbnb beacuse i'm travelling on a regular basis for my job.   
I offer a modern cosy apartment near the centre of Amsterdam. A relative new and upcoming part of town at the IJ river, near a park, station, fast 10 minute connection to the city with many bus- and tram options. I live in a nice, modern building. In daily life I work as a manager on interior design projects. I like to work with creative people and the artists of craftsmanship. As I lived many years in the city now, I like to share the nice spots (not only touristic!) in Amsterdam. We have a rich history, beautiful canals (have a boattrip!) with the characteristic houses from the 17th century. But also many modern and special shops like in the 9 Streets, the area which the city of Amsterdam is built on. Many restaurants and cafès... Musea, Van Gogh, Rembrandt, the Anne Frank House. The new Eye filmmuseum. So much to see & things to experience!

space: Our large and luxurious mobile home on the outskirts of the city is located at the “De Badhoeve” campsite in Durgerdam. The property is an ideal base from which families and small groups of up to four persons can explore Amsterdam and its surroundings as well as engage in recreational activities at the well- equipped campsite. Location The “De Badhoeve” campsite is located less than 10 kilometres from Amsterdam city centre, close to the picturesque village of Durgerdam. Situated between the Ijssel Lake and the Kinsel Lake, the campsite offers a wide range of reacreational activities, including cycling, swimming and fishing. For those seeking the occasional change of pace, Amsterdam can be reached by car in approximately 15 minutes and by public transport in 45 minutes. name: Wooden Garden House
summary: 15 minutes from Amsterdam, in the back yard of our traditional farm house, we can offer you a wooden garden house. It's a spacious but simple accommodation with a magnificent view on the lake and meadows. Shared garden with the owners.
space: After a 15 minute drive from Amsterdam's city centre, at the end of a dead end road you'll find a picturesque village of about 60 houses amidst the meadows: Holysloot. The village can be reached with public transport (bus) but only on working days and not in the evenings. Coming with your own car is probably most convenient. Unless you love cycling: it's about 20 minutes to the closest store and 45 minutes to the center of Amsterdam. In the back yard of our traditional farm house we can offer you a wooden garden house. It's a spacious but simple accommodation with a magnificent view on navigable water and meadows.  The garden house measures 75 m2, sleeps three (3) with the possibility to add a bed for a baby/child, has central heating and a wood stove, a bathroom and a kitchen. You share the large garden with the owners – a couple with two girls (9 and 13 ys) – but you'll always be able to find a quiet spot if wanted.  Be welcome!

description: Ruime sfeervolle woning met eigen oprit, ideaal met kleine kinderen in zeer kindvriendelijke wijk. Een tuin  met vlonder aan het water. Op fietsafstand van zowel de weilanden als het Centrum. Fietsen te leen (met kinderzitjes). Veel speelgoed aanwezig, de keuken is modern uitgevoerd en van alle gemakken voorzien. neighborhood_overview: The house is situated close to the authentic Dugerdammerdijk next to the church.  The house is in the green, before and behind the house are meadows. Durgerdam is a picturesque village on the IJ lake with wooden houses, some of them date from the 17th century overlooking the water. At the beginning and at the end of the village are small beaches where you can swim. From the village you are by bike or car within 30 minutes into the city.
notes: We house five cat!  The house is clean and the cats are outside living in the garden and sleeping in the garden cottage during our holidays. Our Neighbour take care of them, the cats are used to be outside at night. For people with allergic reaction to cats the house is not suited!
transit: Free parking next to the house! You can get to the house from Central Station by bus, it takes around 40 minutes. In the city centre or in Amsterdam North (closeby) you can rent bikes at several places or you can use the public transportation like trams and metro's to travel with.  By car: It is free parking at the parking place at the end of the village, 250 meters from the house. If you want to use the car to get into the city you can drive to closeby P+R park your car and take tram to Central Station (10 minutes), or Bus to East side of Amsterdam.
access: You have full and private access to the house during your stay.

One of these two bedrooms will be rent to you - the small room for one person and the big room for two persons. Rental includes use of the bedroom and shared bathroom. The bathroom with floor heating is new,
neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is very green, quiet, safe and specious. You will see the wild rabbits running around, while just about 18 minutes to the absolute centre (centre station) by bus.  It's just a few minutes walk to the Dutch countryside, where you have a great view of cows, fields and villages...
notes: You can arrive at my apartment by bus 24 hours a day. From the Central Station, the day bus comes every 5 minutes in rush hours and 10 minutes in other time. The night bus is between 00:30 and 06:00, twice per hour. You can purchase day or multiple day card entitles you to unlimited travel around Amsterdam - day and night - on bus, tram and metro.
transit: Address: Jisperveldstraat 547 Amsterdam north. From Amsterdam airport Schiphol you take the train  (15 minutes) to Amsterdam central station. From central station you take bus33 direction Nieuwendam, get off the bus at the stop "Beemsterstraat" after about 18 minutes. Walk back 50 meters along the road where the bus comes from, on the other side of the road there are 4 white high buildings (exactly the same with 11 floors). On the 3rd floor of the last building, at the end of the gallery is my apartment. You can just take the odd elevator or the stairs to my apartment, and ring the bell next to the door. If you come by car, there are enough FREE parking places around the building.
access: The entire apartment is accessible for the guests:  the private bedrooms - the living room - the kitchen - the bathroom - the balcony
interaction: One important reason to rent my apartment is because I like travel and meet people from the whole world, so a relaxed and nice conversation is very appreciated. However, I'm quite often not at home due to my work. In that case, you will be the only person(s) at my home, then the whole apartment is private, just for you.
house_rules: Respectful and quiet. You may come and go as demand. Smoke is only allowed on balcony, it's forbidden inside. Please treat the apartment as if it were your own, and keep in mind that you have neighbours.  The apartment is a regular home, not a hotel nor an afterparty place - so no parties, no loud music, etc. The owner reserves the right to remove you from the apartment if you do not follow these guidelines.
host_about:
I'm a single man, live in Amsterdam north, and have been working at financial world. My biggest hobby is traveling. I've been to many places in the world. Travel brings me lots of energy and spirit, helps me finding myself and discovering the world, and just makes me feel happy. 
Since I have enough space at my own apartment, I'd like to provide a good opportunity to people who want to explore Amsterdam. Meanwhile, I could collect some money to realize my dream, to be able to travel more.

interaction: During your visit, the hostess is present and her female partner sometimes. There is always the possibility to ask the hostess for information or a demand The hostess is often away for work or social activities.

Please don't invite other people from outside in the apartment.  Be careful in dealing with fragile items. Always close the house well. Be polite to neighbours
host_about:
I like it when more people can enjoy the wonderful home that I own. While in Amsterdam you will experience the peace and tranquility that you normally only find outside the city. I really love nature because of the peace it gives me . The older I get, the more I enjoy silence . This also has to do with my love for consciousness development. I also train people in mindfulness alongside my practice as a therapist . What I also really enjoy is that my gardenhouse is a short distance from my house . The rooting with hands in the earth, grow and bloom of flowers and plants I love it. I like to eat healthy but with a focus on animal welfare and the preservation of our planet so that my nieces and nephews can still have a future. I want my guests to feel at home in my house and I will endeavor to contribute to that.My house is cozy and comfortable rather than modern , stylish and sleek . I am open to feedback because  next guests can benefit from it.  My life motto is . "Quietly to not break the line " (Dutch expression) So I hope that my guests can unwind in my apartment and develop a sense of enjoyment here, of the relaxed city of Amsterdam and the relaxed atmosphere in the house .
You are welcome! See you at my house , Mirjam

summary: Best of both worlds: a quiet green place to sleep, within walking distance to cool waterside hangouts and a free ferry to the city's Central Station.
space: Wake up with the birds singing and the sun rising behind your curtains, In a spacious room with modern facilities.
description: Best of both worlds: a quiet green place to sleep, within walking distance to cool waterside hangouts and a free ferry to the city's Central Station. Wake up with the birds singing and the sun rising behind your curtains, In a spacious room with modern facilities. The room is yours, the toilet and separate bathroom is shared. On request you can store your stuff in the fridge or wash your clothes. I sleep in the room next door. I work during weekdays and occasionally in the weekend. In between I'm available for all your questions and feedback. The rusty former shipwharf 'NDSM' offers loads of cool things: Bungee jumping at Feralda, a city beach with bonfire at bar 'Pllek', live music at hippie hangout 'Noorderlicht', Phenomenal steaks at 'Loetje', Europe's largest flea market at the 'IJ-Hallen'. Further out the sustainable bar/restaurant 'De Ceuvel' is totally built up out of scrapwood and former boats. The North side of Amsterdam is accessable by (free) ferry from the back of Central S
neighborhood_overview: The rusty former shipwharf 'NDSM' offers loads of cool things: Bungee jumping at Feralda, a city beach with bonfire at bar 'Pllek', live music at hippie hangout 'Noorderlicht', Phenomenal steaks at 'Loetje', Europe's largest flea market at the 'IJ-Hallen'. Further out the sustainable bar/restaurant 'De Ceuvel' is totally built up out of scrapwood and former boats.
notes: The North side of Amsterdam is accessable by (free) ferry from the back of Central Station. The west/left-most ferry called 'NDSM' takes about 15 minutes to the other side. A city bus stops very near too. Car parking is save and free.

Born just outside Amsterdam, but I've always worked and lived in and around the city. I have a bachelor degree in Tourism.

I love visiting museums, playing guitar, cycling, bringing people together for picnics/jamsessions in the Vondelpark. 
After great Airbnb experiences in Budapest, Saint Petersburg and Holten I decided to do something in return to this traveling community. 

I'm looking forward to welcome you at my place. 

Regards, Tays

neighborhood_overview: Ons huis ligt in Tuindorp Oostzaan, een oer-Hollandse wijk gebouwd in de jaren dertig voor de scheepswerf arbeiders. Het ligt vlakbij de NDSM werf, een oud haventerrein met industrieel uiterlijk die volop in gebruik is als culturele broedplaats. Liefhebbers voor cultuur, horeca, festivals en vlooienmarkten kunnen hier hun hart ophalen. Zo is er maandelijkse de grootste vlooienmarkt van Europa (IJhallen), zijn er diverse horeca gelegenheden zoals Pllek, Noorderlicht, IJkantine, Loetje, de Pannenkoekenboot en meer. De andere kant op, op 10 minuten fietsafstand bevind zich het natuurgebied 't Twiske waar de natuur liefhebber zijn hart kan ophalen. Ook is er veel te beleven voor kinderen met een biologisch dynamische boerderij, avonturenspeelplaats, zwemgelegenheid in natuurwater, kanoën en meer. Op loopafstand is sinds kort Noordoogst, een bruisende groene plek rondom de duurzame voedselketen met lokale ondernemers en horeca. Op 5 minuten loopafstand bevindt zich een kleine buurtsuper, ba
notes: We hebben zelf een kat die dagelijks wat eten en drinken van de gasten moet krijgen. Deze kat is gewend aan kinderen. Ze kan zelf in- en uitlopen en haar behoeftes doen dus behalve eten geven heb je hier geen omkijken naar. We vinden het ontzettend leuk om tips te geven over Amsterdam en de omgeving. Dus geef van tevoren vooral aan welke interesses u heeft, dan kunnen we u op maat enkele tips geven.
transit: Ons huis ligt binnen bereik van Schiphol. Met de trein naar Amsterdam Centraal en dan bus 35 (halte Meteorenweg) of bus 391 of 394 (halte Keerkringpark). De bushalte is op 1 minuut loop afstand.  Gratis pont vanaf de NDSM werf voor fietsers en voetgangers naar Amsterdam Centraal en Westerdoksdijk (ongeveer 12 minuten fietsen vanaf het huis).
access: De volledige tuin (exclusief schuur die afgesloten is), de begane grond met woonkamer, keuken en toilet en de eerste verdieping bestaande uit de twee slaapkamers en een badkamer.
interaction: Ontvangst gebeurd door onszelf of door de buren. Het is mogelijk 2 fietsen te gebruiken inclusief kinderzitjes. Gebruik wasmachine en droger mogelijk. Gebruik van bedlinnen en handdoeken. Extra campingbed voor kind t/m 4 jaar op aanvraag is gratis. Incheck- en uitcheck tijden in overleg. Tussentijds schoonmaken van huis kan tijdens verblijf optioneel aangevraagd worden. Extra kosten hiervoor zijn 35,- per keer.
house_rules: Huisdieren en roken niet toegestaan. Geen feesten. Alleen families bestaande uit 2 volwassenen + 1 kind + 1 baby/peuter of een koppel
host_about: Samen met mijn man en zoon woon ik in Amsterdam. Ik werk parttime als programmeur bij poppodium Duycker en ben daarnaast zelfstandig ondernemer op het gebied van theater, rollerskaten en educatieve projecten.

space: Our house is very convenient for a family with two or three kids or for families/ friend groups consisting of max. four adults visiting Amsterdam. The house contains three bedrooms, one with queen size bed, one with double bed and one bunk bed for two children. Bordering the back of the house you find a spacious 55m2 garden on the northeast side. In the garden you find a spacious table with six chairs and childrens toys. There is also running water and electricity in the garden. Bordering the front of the house you find a cosy front garden of about 15m2 on the southwest side with a lot of sun. The house is equipped with all modern conveniences like bath, shower, washing machine, dryer, fridge, microwave, wireless internet etc.  making your stay in Amsterdam as convenient as possible.

neighborhood_overview: The house is situated in the North part of Amsterdam, just above the IJ river. It gives you a more countryside feeling but the bustling city is only a short  bike- or busride away. This part of the city is very upcoming.  The area around is close to the natural park ‘Twiske’ where you can swim, walk, bike, picnic and relax. Officially this neighbourhood is called 'Kadoelen’. Opposite of our house is a nice Amsterdam ship wharf. They have electric silent boats that are for rent. You can sail in 10 minuten to center ! The trendy NDSM wharf is only 7 minutes by bike and has many restaurants and café's. A monthly flea market and lots of events are happening at this wharf area. From there you can also take the free ferry to the city center. It's a 12 minute boat ride to the central station.
notes: If you stay at our house you can use our bikes for free. We'll ask a deposit for that, you get this back from Airbnb after your stay.
transit: About the (public) transport options: From the central station you can go by ferry to the NDSM wharf, then 20 minutes by foot or 7 minutes by bike. Behind central station you can take bus 34 (to Buikslotermeerplein) and ask the bus driver to drop you at the Tjalkstraat. From there it's a 10 minute walk to our house.
access: You can stay with 4 adults and 2 kids. We have two double bedrooms and 2 childrens rooms. Besides these beds we have 2 extra mattresses available for children.
interaction: We won't be around during your stay but you can contact us when you've got any questions. We will make sure you will find all instructions about our house in a folder and some nice tips to explore Amsterdam.
house_rules: No smoking inside please. We don't allow pets. We expect our guests to use our house with care and respect, like you would use your own house.

name: The green Hornet + 2 free bikes
summary: Book a Camper, Caravan, Circus Wagon or Boat located @ the NDSM Shipyard. Close to nature and just minutes away from the city cen Its a cool interesting place for hippie, laid-back, budget backpackers so don't expect a 5 star Hotel ;)
space: The green Hornet is fully equipped with a heater, 2  bed's  and a place to sit and relax.  Also you will get 2 bikes for free with your Caravan experience!
description: Book a Camper, Caravan, Circus Wagon or Boat located @ the NDSM Shipyard. Close to nature and just minutes away from the city cen Its a cool interesting place for hippie, laid-back, budget backpackers so don't expect a 5 star Hotel ;)
neighborhood_overview: The green Hornet is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas. NDSM (a former shipyard) located on the banks of the River IJ has blossomed into an enormous cultural hot spot in recent years.There are festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events. The Caravan is 20 minutes away from the vibrant city centre, and just 10 minutes away from Twiske.  Twiske is a beautiful nature park with canals, bridges, a windmill and lakes where you can swim.
transit: From central station you can take Citybus 34 (direction Buikslotermeerplein) get off at busstop Tjalkstraat. (20 min). From there its a 5 minute walk to the barn. You can also take the free ferry from behind central station. Take the one to NDSM (10 minutes) from there its a 15 minutes walk. From the Camper to the City-centre:  Hop on the (free) ferry at the NDSM-werf and set sail for the charming City Centre. The trip takes 10 minutes and you can bring your bike (also free). There is also a (night) bus 5 minutes from the barn that goes to central station (15 minutes) There is a night ferry that runs 24/7, so its never a problem to get back from the city center.
access: The Caravan is situated on a courtyard with also a Camper, Circus Wagon and a Boat. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travelers.  There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner. There's a fully equipped kitchen, toilet's and shower's. Towels are included. You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, a dog, 2 cats and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs! There's also a big fireplace in the barn to keep you nice and warm during the winter!
host_about:
Hi, my name is Florus and i'm a fireman in Amsterdam. 
I like to travel and see the world. 
Love to host interesting, new people from different countries.

Hope to see you soon!

Surroundings:  We highly recommend you to visit the NDSM Wharf, where you can have a drink at bar/restaurant PLLEK or Noorderlicht. Do visit the Westerpark. Maybe it is off the beaten track but we like it more compared to the busy  Vondelpark. On saterday morning you can visit Noordermarkt (Farmersmarket). And so on. I will provide you a custom lists of must sees if you like. No problem!
transit: Public Transport: In a 2 minute walk you will find a busstop, line 38 (will take you to the city center in 12 minutes) In less than 10 minute walk you can take the ferry Parking is free and at front of our home From Schiphol airport you can take the train and the bus. Within 40 minutes you will reach our place.
access: What is included during the rental period? We have spacious sleeping area on the top floor for two adults. Want to rent it with more adults? We can offer you an air mattress in our spare bedroom. There is one room for kids on request (we can host up to 2 kids).  Facilities:  There is a washing machine, dishwasher, television, wifi connection, ipod dockingstation, Italian coffee machine and so on.  What is not accesible? Our computers we don't share. The rest can be shared.
interaction: Contact:  During your stay we are on a holiday. We will be connected by phone or email (once daily). You can ask us anything.
house_rules: House rules: We trust you to take care of our home if it where yours.  The way we left you the home is the way we wanna welcome it back. No smoking inside & lock safely. Handle and enjoy with care!
host_about:

We work in the healthcare and I'm a non profit professional (with a passion for youngsters and coaching). We believe in a good balance between a family life, professional ambitions and enjoy what Amsterdam has to offer. Our family and friends come first.

neighborhood_overview: For the lovers of flea markets, shopping, café’s, bars and restaurants, or culture: Our house is situated in the neighbourhood “de Bongerd”, a new housing development  in the vicinity of the NDSM wharf and the traditional Dutch “Tuindorp Oostzaan”. Many festivals are organised at the NDSM wharf including the biggest flea market (IJ Hallen) in Europe. The NDSM wharf, an old harbour area, is a cultural hotspot, with a nostalgic yet robust appearance, with many social establishments: PIIek, Noorderlicht, IJ kantine, de Pannenkoekenboot and  more. The free ferry service departing from the NDSM wharf will take you in 12 minutes to “Centraal Station” or in 15 minutes to “Westerpark or Haarlemmerstraat”. From “Centraal Station” buses and trams depart in the direction of “Museumplein”. From the “Centraal Station” the shopping district of Amsterdam is at walking distance. In case you have more of a love for nature, our house is located on a route towards “ ‘t Twiske” and “Waterland”, only at 10
notes: For fans we have created some architectural routes, but also some nice routes to museums (‘t Schip) and pleasant shopping areas (Haarlemmerdijk).
transit: Our house is easy to reach from Schiphol Airport. Use the train to “Amsterdam Centraal” and from there take bus 35 direction “Molenwijk”, or use the free ferry service to the NDSM wharf. Total travel time ca 1 hour.
access: The private bathroom, including toilet, bath, shower and washbasin,  is situated on the same floor as the private room and doesn’t need to be shared.

Children friendly, a child’s bed can be placed in the room. In the evening there is a possibility the look after children. Free parking in front of the house. Bicycles can be parked in our garden. We do own a cat. ATTENTION Price includes 2 person per night 3rd person costs an additional € 30,- (euro) p.p.p.n. Children up to and including* 5 years old stay free of charge. host_about:
We are a spontaneous creative family: Nienke (45, born in “Friesland”), Gert (49, born in Amsterdam), Noor (8), Maud (5) and our cat Bob.
We both work to provide in our cost of living. Nienke is an architect with a big engineering bureau. Gert is an ICT systems manager at the “Rietveldacademie” and volunteer fireman. We enjoy having guests in our new home and familiarizing them with “Amsterdam Noord” and the NDSM wharf. During our holidays we like to go to B&B’s ourselves due to the personal touch. We also like to go camping with the family. We can’t live without Bob, our cat. Gert has a love for flying (the real thing and the simulation thereof) and rollerskating. Nienke likes flea markets, cooking and visiting museums. Noor and Maud are real girly-girls, they like the colour pink and ballet. We live an intensive life, but with a healthy structure. We look forward to having you nicest room in our home!

neighborhood_overview: The North of Amsterdam has been really developing the last couple of years. Many of the old ship yards have become a breedingplace where artists and entrepreneurs have created a lively work and living environment with many bars and restaurants. It has become known as the Berlin of Amsterdam.
notes: We can accomodate 5 adults max and 3 children max, theoretically at the same time, but we would recommend not more than 5 people staying here at the same time. For the children we have 160 cm bunkbeds. For adults we have full size beds. When 5 adults are staying keep in mind that the second bedroom is really full with 3 full size beds. During week days there are 1 to 2 people working in a garden house office at the far end of the garden. You won't see them from the area that you will be using, including the terrace and the sun deck, but they will be using the same entrance to the garden.
transit: Parking is free here! You can walk in 5 minutes to a busstop, and the central train station of Amsterdam is a 12 min bike ride away (using the ferry). We recommend renting bicycles to get around in Amsterdam!

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. More and more hotspots are popping up! Visit urban beaches like Café de Ceuvel and Pllek! Both perfect spots to relax and enjoy the warm weather on the waterfront. Other nice places overlooking the IJ-lake are film museum EYE (enjoy the sunset on their beautiful terrace!), seafood restaurant Stork and THT restaurant. One of our favourite areas in Amsterdam North is the NDSM Wharf. Known as one of the best festival locations of Amsterdam. North is also the place to be for vintage and thrift shopping. You can’t miss the monthly flea market in the IJ-hallen, a true second hand heaven.
access: You will access to the entire apartment. Make yourself at home!
interaction: I will meet you at the apartment, handle the keys and show you around. After that feel free to contact me on Airbnb if you need any assistance or tips! I am more then happy to help you!
house_rules: Treat the apartment as if it were your own and keep in mind that you have neighbours. The apartment is a regular home not an after hours club, so no parties, no drugs, no loud music/TV, etc. Police will fine when complaints are made after 23:00 (11pm) or before 07:00 (7am). At time of departure: make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done, the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean. Smoking of any kind is not allowed, this may also result in a triggering of the fire alarm. All keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee. Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment. If host is not informed of defects, host cannot be held liable for resulting damage to personal items.

neighborhood_overview: The house is centrally located in a very trendy upcoming neighborhood north of the river IJ. This is where the new hotspots are in a hip, industrial and creative part of Amsterdam. From my house every spot can be reached bij foot or bike. Think of the NDSM-wharf, the new film institute and museum EYE, recently opened (highest building in A'dam) A'dam tower, the new music venue Paradiso Tolhuistuin, several trendy restaurants, a city beach at Pllek, and many many festivals on the NDSM-wharf. It is the area where the hipsters go these days, because it is very central, close to the city center, but yet green and spacious - near the waterfront and also close to rural Amsterdam, like Twiske and Waterland (recommended to visit by bike!) and little old Dutch towns like Marken and Broek in Waterland.
notes: In case you are interested in sailing in the Netherlands, please ask for more information.
transit: Free parking in front of the house! At a 3-5 minutes walk you will find 3 different busstops, that will take you every few minutes to Central Station within 10 minutes. Also during the night, as well back from the city center of course.  Consult (URL HIDDEN) for bus numbers and schedules. Cycling to the city center on the south bank of the IJ-river is real fun and highly recommended. Take the bus to Central Station, rent a bike overthere, cycle through Amsterdam and back to my house. The house is located 5-12 minutes cycling from each ferry (there are 3 ferries available, 1 also during night times, no costs).

access: You will have access to the room indicated in the pictures, located just after the shared main entrance, separated from our private space/ living area. Free Wifi Flatscreen TV Complimentary bike use (1 available at deposit) Babies and kids friendly!
interaction: We are more than happy to welcome you and to help you get the most out of your stay! Whether you need help with public transport, tips on which places of interest to go or reservations at a popular restaurant, we are here at your disposal! However, we are a busy family with small children, so don't expect us to go about in the city, even though we'd love to ;-) May be you are busy or prefer privacy. You don't need to interact with us if you don't wish to. The set up of the room is so that you can enter and leave the house without passing trough our private area. Only the main entrance is shared. We respect your privacy and we ask the same in return.
house_rules: No smoking (not in garden either) No pets No more than 2 adults (+ baby or child at no charge) Lock doors before going out as instructed Respect our privacy like we'll respect yours We request that you hold a valid ID, to be shown upon arrival Thanks for your understanding.

Onze vrijstaande jaren 30 woning bevindt zich in een charmante, kindvriendelijke buurt in Amsterdam noord. In slechts 12 minuten met het openbaar vervoer of 20 minuten fietsen ben je in het centrum van de stad! In de directe omgeving vind je het Twiske, een natuurgebied met strandjes, speeltuinen en de mogelijkheid om een bootje te huren. Een leuke afwisseling met een bezoek aan de stad. Amsterdam Noord is door de NY Times uitgeroepen als DE plek waar je moet zijn, wanneer je in Amsterdam bent. De noordoever biedt dan ook vele leuke restaurantjes en cafe's als Noorderlicht en PLLEK op het NDSM terrein of restaurant de Goudfazant en visrestaurant Stork.

In de directe omgeving vind je het Twiske, een natuurgebied met strandjes, speeltuinen en de mogelijkheid om een bootje te huren. Een leuke afwisseling met een bezoek aan de stad. Amsterdam Noord is door de NY Times uitgeroepen als DE plek waar je moet zijn, wanneer je in Amsterdam bent. De noordoever biedt dan ook vele leuke restaurantjes en cafe's als Noorderlicht en PLLEK op het NDSM terrein of restaurant de Goudfazant en visrestaurant Stork. Op het NDSM terrein worden geregeld leuke evenementen georganiseerd zoals concerten en festivals. Verder wordt er in de de IJ-hallen de grootste vlooienmarkt van Nederland gehouden. Heb je zin in een avondje naar de film, breng dan een bezoek aan het EYE-filmmuseum. Voor een avondje livemuziek is de Tolhuistuin een aanrader!
transit: Openbaar vervoer is op 5 minuten loopafstand te vinden. Voor de deur kan gratis geparkeerd worden. Verder zijn er meerdere fietsen aanwezig, waaronder een bakfiets en een fiets met kinderzitjes. Dit is uiteraard de leukste manier om de stad en omgeving te verkennen. Een (gratis) ritje met de fiets op de pont naar de stad zullen uw kinderen niet snel vergeten!

name: Beautiful green city cottage
summary: In a sunny, calm street in Amsterdam North we own a beautiful house with a green front & back garden. No city noises & exhaust fumes but singing birds & the smell of flowers. The city center is within 10 mins reach by bike & free ferry. Free parking!
space: The location of Tuindorp Oostzaan in Amsterdam North, close to the city centre, reachable by a lovely free ferry ride and even closer to the beautiful countryside, together with the ambiance in and around our house, make this spot quite unique. Here you get to unwind and relax after a busy day exploring the city buzz or nearby countryside. This will be your home away from home. We happily invite guests to enjoy all the good things in our house and garden. We expect you to respect our house, garden and cat like you would your own.  There is a lovely garden table, chairs and, fire pot to maximize the sunny hours in our garden. Or you might enjoy a relaxing soak in the lovely bathtub upstairs...

neighborhood_overview: Our neighbourhood (and especially our sunny street) have an exceptional village feel to them. This village connects the city centre to the North and adds to the typical North-Holland ambiance with nearby canals and the historical NDSM warf within walking distance. There you will also find the IJ Hallen, Europe's largest flee market.  Nature reserves Twiske and Ilperveld, as well as Waterland and world-famous Zaanse Schans, are just around the corner. On the other hand, you can reach the center of Amsterdam in under 20 minutes, either by bus or on your rental bicycle (riding the free ferry over the IJ just adds to the joy of living in North and we highly recommend this so that you will experience life as a true local! ) From the Central Station, you take the free ferry to NDSM. Then take bus 38, 37 of 35 to Molenwijk. If you have a bicycle, you follow the signs to Twiske. From Central Station you can also take bus 35 to Molenwijk. If you are travelling by car, you take exit S118 towards
notes: Staying in our home requires you to be a cat lover. While we are away you will be kept company by our lovely red cat, Fela. He comes and goes as he pleases through the cat flap so he is completely independent and hardly any nuisance. Staying in our beautiful home will therefore need you to be a cat lover.  You can keep him from going upstairs by simply closing living room door. We kindly ask you to feed Fela during your stay in our home which is reflected in the night rate.
transit: From the Central Station, you take the free ferry to NDSM. Then take bus 38, 37 of 35 to Molenwijk, Tuindorp Oostzaan.  If you have a bicycle, you follow the signs to Tuindorp Oostzaan.. From Central Station you can also take bus 35 to Molenwijk, from there it is a 4 minute walk to our street. If you are travelling by car, you take exit S118 towards Tuindorp Oostzaan.
access: You enter via the front door in the hallway of the ground floor. This gives you access to the spacious and light living room of 35 m2 , open kitchen and back garden of 40m2. The stairs in the hallway gives access to the first floor with the very spacious, stunning bedroom of 30m2. The bedroom has a high ceiling with beautiful beams. The spacious and light bathroom is directly next to the bedroom with shower and bathtub and toilet. The bathroom is your very own little zen spa. Perfect to relax. In the hall upstairs there is also a little storage room where the washing machine is.
interaction: As you will be renting the entire private house, we will not be around during your stay but we want to make sure that our guests are comfortable and enjoy their stay, not just in our house and garden, but in our city as well. We will be reachable during your stay and will leave you with some nice recommendations of things to see and do in the area.
house_rules: No smoking Not suitable for pets No parties or events
host_about: I am a Yoga teacher and writer from Amsterdam. I love the outdoors, good food, animals, travel and cozy places. In the city I lke to explore coziness, art, music and people. I balance this with hiking preferably along the seaside.

name: Urban Villa, bright and spacious!
space: Bright and spacious design urban villa in Amsterdam  Free Parking! (saves you about 40 Euro on daybase) Great, sunny family home in the northern part of Amsterdam. Quiet surrounding but yet 20 minutes from downtown Amsterdam! 130m2 design in Amsterdam The whole district was designed a couple of years ago by dutch architects.  This area is called the new “garden area” of Amsterdam because all the houses have gardens and the whole area has a countryside feeling in the city. Very nearby you will find the former NDSM wharf where lot’s of ships were build untill 1979. Today it’s a upcoming area on the waterfront with trendy restaurants, a bakery, a skating hall, factory buildings, a gallery and a city beach.  MTV Europe, Greenpeace, IDTV, Red Bull a.s.o. have chosen this area for their headquarters. We are a family of 4 persons, 2 adults and 2 kids. As we wanted the benefits of both a quiet surrounding for the kids as well as the advantages of the city we found our perfect spot in this part

neighborhood_overview: The Caravan is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas. NDSM (a former shipyard) located on the banks of the River IJ has blossomed into an enormous cultural hot spot in recent years.There are festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events.  The Caravan is 20 minutes away from the vibrant city centre, and just 10 minutes away from Twiske. Twiske is a beautiful nature park with canals, bridges, a windmill and lakes where you can swim.
transit: Getting to the Caravan: Take Citybus 34 (direction Buikslotermeerplein) get off at busstop Tjalkstraat. (20 min). This is a link with the route from the busstop to the caravan: (URL HIDDEN) From the Caravan to the City-centre: Hop on the (free) ferry at the NDSM-werf and set sail for the charming City Centre. The trip takes 14 minutes and you can bring your bike (also free).
access: The Caravan is situated on a courtyard with also a Camper and a Boat. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travelers. There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner. There's a kitchen and shower / toilet .  You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, a dog and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs, you'll also get bred and spreads.   There's a big fireplace in the barn to keep you nice and warm during the winter! Its a cool interesting place for hippie, laid-back, budget backpackers so don’t expect a five star hotel ;)
house_rules: Hi guys, thanks for booking! We can't wait to welcome you here.  Before you arrive we want to help you out with some practical information. Check in: from 1 pm Keep us posted about your arrival time, we are waiting for you :) Check out: before 11 am Rental Please do not smoke inside your rental. Do not forget to turn off your heater if you are leaving your rental Barn The Barn is your common area with a place to relax, 2 bathrooms, 3 showers (towels are included) and 2 fully equipped kitchens. Please keep it clean and do your dishes so other guests can use it too. Bikes The bikes are for free use. Please handle them with care, and ALWAYS lock them. If you want we offer a bike insurance. space: Family house with 2 bedrooms, located in the upcoming Amsterdam North area.  The house has 1 bedroom with double bed and attached balcony, 1 bedroom with single bed and extra bed on the floor. neighborhood_overview: The house is located in a quiet area, with lots of family’s and children, it’s next to the ringroad, free parking, but only 30 minutes away from central station, red light, Dam-square with the palace by bus. Supermarket is around the corner and is a 4 minute walk. It’s open every day from 8 till 20.00 except Sundays. Thrillist has put Amsterdam Noord on number 3 in their list of the TEN MOST HIPSTER NEIGHBOURHOODS ON EARTH.
notes: Busstop 2 minutes walk. (if u walk fast or run it’s 1 minute :-) This bus takes you to Central station in 30 minutes. Busstop molenwijk is 8 minutes walk This bus takes 16 minutes to the NDSM wharf.. From there u can take a ferry to central station. Or hang out in one of the relaxed industrial beach restaurants like Plekk, Noorderlicht or have the best steak in town at Loetje aan het IJ.  It’s a creative hotspot.  On this former shipyard on the northern bank of the IJ grows a self-made city 'with hundreds of artists, creative businesses, sustainable business, unconventional homes, innovative culture and media, amazing cafes, hotels and restaurants and ground breaking events, on land and on water. NDSM is the new focal point for creative urban energy. At the NDSM wharf is also the biggest flea market of Europe. It’s worth a visit if u are here.
transit: With car it’s only 25 minutes to Volendam which is a village of fishermen, music and cheese. The Cheese Factory is one of the newest attractions in the centre of Volendam. Despite the name, it’s much more than a factory – it is an interactive experience that will introduce you to the wonders of Dutch cheese. Or another good spot is Zaanse Schans. Only 15 minutes by car.
access: There is 1 spare room downstairs on first floor which will be locked for our personal stuff, but other then that you can use the whole house.
interaction: If you have any questions during your stay you can phone the number we will leave in your welcome note.
house_rules: We love our house and hope u do too. Please make sure the house is the same as how you found it when u arrived. Clean and everything in place.

name: Modern Apartment w Cat (weekly & monthly discount)
summary: MINIMUM STAY OF 15 (PREFERABLY 21) DAYS STARTING IN THE WEEK OF JULY 11TH! My apartment is simple, yet designed with a keen eye on detail. It's the perfect place to escape the crowd as it is only a 10 minutes walk from a beautiful park nearby, while also on a 5 minute cycling distance (bicycle provided) to NDSM, which is the main nightlife area. And from there another 10 minute free ferry ride (every 15 minutes) to city center. Check out my monthly discount!
space: Its a spacious apartment that would suit all the needs of either a couple or a couple of friends out and about to discover the gems of Amsterdam The sun rises and sets at the back of the building, so you will be woken up by it in the morning as well as have all day natural light in the living room. The entire apartment was renovated a few years ago, so all the sanitary facilities are top notch. With the balcony looking out over the park, you can literally see the seasons changing from green to brown and yellow. It's truly w remarkable process. The apartment is situated on the sixth floor but with an outstanding elevator you won't have to climb a single step.
description: MINIMUM STAY OF 15 (PREFERABLY 21) DAYS STARTING IN THE WEEK OF JULY 11TH! My apartment is simple, yet designed with a keen eye on detail. It's the perfect place to escape the crowd as it is only a 10 minutes walk from a beautiful park nearby, while also on a 5 minute cycling distance (bicycle provided) to NDSM, which is the main nightlife area. And from there another 10 minute free ferry ride (every 15 minutes) to city center. Check out my monthly discount!
neighborhood_overview: It's a peaceful and quit neighborhood with the shopping mall on a 3 minutes walk for all your needs (supermarket, liquor store, cheese shop, cafeteria for typical Dutch fries and snacks, pharmacist, hair dresser etc.). My personal favorite is the newly opened cafe at the Zonneplein called Lokaal Spaanders. Wanna have dinner? Why don't you try the restaurant nearby called Eten Aan De Dijk. There is enough to be explored! Go check it out!
notes: I have a sweet little cat who needs to be fed every day. He will be thankful for it, trust me, you will know it. Just make sure he doesn't go outside trough the front door, the balcony in the other hand is his domain to play (and chase pigeons whenever he can).
transit: At the shopping mall there's a bus stop where every 15 to 20 minutes busses leave to central station (20 minutes), Sloterdijk station (15 minutes, ideal for travelers arriving and departing for Schiphol airport, which is only another 10 minutes by train), and Amstel station (about 35, 40 minutes). You can also choose to cycle of course. To get to central station, it's only a 7, 8 minutes cycling to NDSM from where the free ferry leaves every 30 minutes to central station in about 12 minutes. There are also other ferries to other locations. Don't miss out on the experience of seeing Amsterdam from the decks of a ferry along the river IJ. The cruises, ships, but also beautiful architecture (with Eye museum being the biggest eye catcher) along the way are definitely worth the while.
access: You won't be sharing the apartment with anyone else, which means you have access to all the facilities that range from a clean and sanitary toilet and shower to a lovely kitchen. There is free internet connection, however, I don't have a television for multiple reasons. But it shouldn't be a problem to find the channels you're looking for online these days.
interaction: The interaction goes trough me of course, however at some occasions I might not be around so I will put you in contact with a family member or friend just in case there are unresolved issues, complications, or even questions (it wouldn't be the first time someone locked themselves outside)
house_rules: I would appreciate if you considered the neighbours as I have a good understanding with them and would like to keep it that way. Besides that I would also prefer if you took your cigarets outside, onto the balcony and not allow the cat to go into the bedroom or out the front door.
host_about:
Hi there, interested who I am? Well, let me tell you a little about myself then. I am a certified yoga instructor who works as a nurse, while trying to get a job as a history teacher. Trust me, it's not as complicated as it sounds.

I've been around the world, visiting different countries, ranging from India to Canada, from Korea to New Zealand, from Jordan to Sweden. It's always exciting to visit new place and can be quite a challenge from time to time to find your way around. 

I therefor understand that when you arrive in a new city, you want things to go smoothly. If you choose to stay in my apartment, I will make sure nothing is left to doubt and all will be provided so that you (and your partner) will only worry about which museum to visit, what restaurant to dine at.

I look forward welcoming you.

neighborhood_overview: The area is very 'up and coming' with some spectacular views across the water from Central Station.  The NDSM wharf is an alternative/creative hotspot in Amsterdam where fun events, concerts and festivals take place regularly. Some attractions include the Eye Film Museum, Skatepark Amsterdam and the MTV studios. There are also some fabulous restaurants Pllek, Noorderlicht, De IJkantine, and a Pancake Boat - where, you guessed it, you can eat any kind of pancake on a boat.  If you love nature you can take some incredible walks any time of year in either of the two nature reserves ‘Het Twiske’ and ‘Ilperveld.’
notes: We are very pet friendly with two overly loving Golden Retrievers and two in/outdoor cats.
transit: The bus stop is a 2 minute walk with buses leaving frequently for the city centre.  A 10 minute (by car or bicycle) ride will get you to the NDSM wharf where you can take a free ferry to Amsterdam Central Station.
access: You'll have access to full bathroom including a rain shower and jacuzzi bathtub right next to your room.  You're welcome for coffee or tea in the kitchen or on the couch.
interaction: I will be here to welcome you and am available by phone or text any time you need help when you’re out and about.
house_rules: Trust and Respect. No smoking. No parties.

name: The Sailing Dutchman + 2 free bikes
summary: Book a Camper, Caravan, Circus Wagon or Boat located @ the NDSM Shipyard. Close to nature and just minutes away from the city center. Two free bikes are included.
space: The Boat is fully equipped with a heater, toilet, big bed  and a place to sit and relax, outside and inside.  Also you will get 2 bikes for free with your Boat experience!
description: Book a Camper, Caravan, Circus Wagon or Boat located @ the NDSM Shipyard. Close to nature and just minutes away from the city center. Two free bikes are included. The Boat is fully equipped with a heater, toilet, big bed  and a place to sit and relax, outside and inside.  Also you will get 2 bikes for free with your Boat experience! The boat is situated on a courtyard with also a Caravan and a Camper. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travelers.  There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner. There's a fully equipped kitchen, toilet and 2 showers. Towels are included. You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, a dog, 2 cats and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs! There's also a big fireplace in the barn to keep you nice and warm during the winter! Its a cool interesting place for hippie, laid-back, budget backpackers so don't expect a five star hotel ;) Th
neighborhood_overview: The Boat is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas. NDSM (a former shipyard) located on the banks of the River IJ has blossomed into an enormous cultural hot spot in recent years.There are festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events. The boat is 20 minutes away from the vibrant city centre, and just 10 minutes away from Twiske.  Twiske is a beautiful nature park with canals, bridges, a windmill and lakes where you can swim.
transit: From central station you can take Citybus 34 (direction Buikslotermeerplein) get off at busstop Tjalkstraat. (20 min). From there its a 5 minute walk to the boat. You can also take the free ferry from behind central station. Take the one to NDSM (10 minutes) from there its a 15 minutes walk. From the Boat to the City-centre:  Hop on the (free) ferry at the NDSM-werf and set sail for the charming City Centre. The trip takes 10 minutes and you can bring your bike (also free). There is also a (night) bus 5 minutes from the boat that goes to central station (15 minutes) There is a night ferry that runs 24/7, so its never a problem to get back from the city center.
access: The boat is situated on a courtyard with also a Caravan and a Camper. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travelers.  There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner. There's a fully equipped kitchen, toilet and 2 showers. Towels are included. You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, a dog, 2 cats and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs! There's also a big fireplace in the barn to keep you nice and warm during the winter! Its a cool interesting place for hippie, laid-back, budget backpackers so don't expect a five star hotel ;)
house_rules: Hi guys, thanks for booking! We can't wait to welcome you here.  Before you arrive we want to help you out with some practical information. Check in: from 1 pm Keep us posted about your arrival time, we are waiting for you :) Check out: before 11 am Rental Please do not smoke inside your rental. Do not forget to turn off your heater if you are leaving your rental Barn The Barn is your common area with a place to relax, 2 bathrooms, 3 showers (towels are included) and 2 fully equipped kitchens. Please keep it clean and do your dishes so other guests can use it too. Bikes The bikes are for free use. Please handle them with care, and ALWAYS lock them. If you want we offer a bike insurance. For 5 euro a bike your bikes are insured against theft. If you don't want the insurance and the bikes get stolen we expect you to refund the bikes and locks (150 euro a bike and 50 for the lock). Please do not use the bikes on check out day, we need them for the new guests. Keys You'll get keys; of the
host_about:
Hi my name is Maik. 

I'm a school teacher and work with autistic children. I 'm super laid-back and I love to travel and meet new people from other countries.

In my spare time I love to sail through the canals of Amsterdam, pure freedom :) 
Are you also adventurous and do you like a challenge? Do you love nature and the outdoors?

Yes?!  Hope to welcome you soon! 

Enjoy life!

summary: Onze eengezinswoning met drie slaapkamers staat in een rustige buurt, op 15 minuten van het Centrum en dichtbij natuur en uitvalswegen. Speciaal geschikt voor gezinnen met kinderen, speelmogelijkheden in de buurt en voorzieningen in huis.
space: Ons huis is een tussenwoning met drie verdiepingen, een kleine tuin achter op het Noord-oosten en een dakterras op het Zuid-westen. Er zijn drie slaapkamers, met in totaal twee tweepersoonsbedden en een stapelbed. Er is een badkamer met bad en douche in één, een toilet en wastafel. Beneden is een extra toilet. De woning is uitermate geschikt voor een gezin met kinderen, of mensen die het fijn vinden om in een rustige woonbuurt te logeren terwijl ze Amsterdam en omgeving verkennen. Er is een eigen parkeerplek voor het huis en ook in de rest van de wijk is parkeren gratis.

neighborhood_overview: Kadoelen is een rustige woonwijk aan de rand van Amsterdam. Het is groen, met veel water. Het is gelegen nabij de ringweg Amsterdam, op 15 minuten van het Centrum, en op 5 minuten van natuur- en recreatiegebied Twiske.  Op 10 minuten loopafstand is een winkelcentrum met supermarkt, drogist, slager en bakker. Ook het dorp Landsmeer is op 15 minuten loopafstand, met diverse winkels en eetgelegenheden.
transit: Op 3 minuten loopafstand is de bushalte met regelmatig (2-4 keer per uur) een busverbinding naar Amsterdam Centraal Station (15 min) en naar station Amsterdam Sloterdijk (15 min). Ook is er verbinding met Zaandam (15 min).
access: In principe hebben gasten de beschikking over het hele huis, alleen een bergkast zal afgesloten zijn met wat persoonlijke spullen. Afhankelijk van de wensen van de gasten zal het huis voorbereid worden.
interaction: De intentie is om op de dag van aankomst aanwezig te zijn om de gasten persoonlijk te ontvangen. Op de dag van vertrek ook. Wij zullen een telefoonnummer achterlaten voor in geval van nood. Ook zullen buren op de hoogte zijn van de aanwezigheid van gasten zodat zij kunnen helpen indien nodig.
house_rules: Het belangrijkste is dat we hopen dat gasten zich op hun gemak zullen voelen in ons huis. Wij wonen er met plezier en hopen dat gasten dit ook zo ervaren. Verder verwachten wij dat gasten respectvol zullen omgaan met onze spullen. Wij willen niet dat er in huis gerookt wordt, dat kan in de tuin of op het dakterras. Ook willen we dat gasten rekening houden met de buren.
host_about: I work at FairWork, a Dutch organisation fighting against modern slavery in the Netherlands. I live in Amsterdam with my two daughters of 13 and 6 years old. We love to travel and meet other people and at the same time we love to receive travelers in our home. The interesting thing about Airbnb is that it provides the possibility to get to know new places from a locals' point of view. You experience something of the life of the owners of the room or appartment that you rent, and that is much more interesting than staying at a hotel.
street: Thomas Prinslaan, Amsterdam, Noord-Holland 1035 SJ, Netherlands

summary: Nice apartment for a city trip. Good to reach by public transport. It also offers free parking.
space: The apartment is a good place to relax after a day city sightseeing . The rooms are big and bright. neighborhood_overview: Countryish Amsterdam Noord. Close (7 minutes cycling) to the NDSM Dock (NDSM werf). The place to be nowadays; A culture breeding place where you find nice lunch and dinner places and music in the weekends, with amazing views over the water 't IJ. This is also where the ferry arrives from Amsterdam Central Station (city center). By this ferry you're in 13 minutes at Central station. en livemuziek in het weekend.  The house is part of the Neighbourhood Tuindorp Oostzaan, which is close to the recreation nature area called 't Twiske. I love it to cycle around here, do some shoppings at the farmshop and have a chill between the (typical dutch) polders. Nearby the house there is a little square with some shops and on cycling distance there is small shopping centre incl a big supermarket.
notes: I have a beautiful sweet cat, called Jacky. She like's attention but is totally independent. We can decide together if i will give here food once in the two days or either you will do this.
transit: I have two bikes for you, you can use. I would recommend you to rent extra bikes if you are with more people; cause it is so much fun to cycle around Amsterdam and it makes you being so much more flexbibe. While public transport in Amsterdam is good organised as well btw. FREE CAR PARKING in front on the house. On the corner you can take the bus (number 35) towards Amsterdam Central Station (city center) and there are also nightbusses going. It takes about 20 minutes by bus to get there. in 7 minutes cycling you are at the ferry at the NDSM werf and that brings you for free in 13 minutes at Amstedam Central Station. You will love this route, cause the views from the ferry are amazing :)

At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travellers.  There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner (common area). There's a fully equipped kitchen, toilet and 2 showers. Towels are included. You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, a dog, 2 cats and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs! There's also a big fireplace in the barn to keep you nice and warm during the winter! The Caravan is situated in the northern par
neighborhood_overview: The Caravan is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas. NDSM (a former shipyard) located on the banks of the River IJ has blossomed into an enormous cultural hot spot in recent years.There are festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events. The Caravan is 20 minutes away from the vibrant city centre, and just 10 minutes away from Twiske.  Twiske is a beautiful nature park with canals, bridges, a windmill and lakes where you can swim.
transit: Ferry: It's a 10 minute bike ride to NDSM, from there you can take the (free) ferry to the centre.   There's a night ferry that runs 24/7, so it's never a problem to get back from the city. Bus:  5 minutes walking from the place there's a bus stop. The bus takes 15 minutes to get to central station. Also the bus runs all night.
access: The Caravan is situated on a courtyard with also a Camper, Circus Wagon and Boat. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travellers.  There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner (common area). There's a fully equipped kitchen, toilet and 2 showers. Towels are included. You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, a dog, 2 cats and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs! There's also a big fireplace in the barn to keep you nice and warm during the winter!

Do not forget to turn off your heater if you are leaving your rental Barn The Barn is your common area with a place to relax, 2 bathrooms, 3 showers (towels are included) and 2 fully equipped kitchens. Please keep it clean and do your dishes so other guests can use it too. Bikes The bikes are for free use. Please handle them with care, and ALWAYS lock them. If you want we offer a bike insurance. For 5 euro a bike your bikes are insured against theft. If you don't want the insurance and the bikes get stolen we expect you to refund the bikes and locks (150 euro a bike and 50 for the lock). neighborhood_overview: Located in a quiet street, but minutes away from where it is happening. Thrillist has put Amsterdam Noord on number 3 in their list of the TEN MOST HIPSTER NEIGHBOURHOODS ON EARTH. The former industrial warehouse of Amsterdam Noord have been overtaken by the city's urban explorers, who now use them as art galleries, skate parks, pop restaurants and for music festivals. The seeds of gentricication have already been shown here: Red Bull and MTV have opened up offices on the waterfront and smaller start ups are also starting to reshape the landscape. Tuindorp Oostzaan was originally a working-class neighborhood. It's is one of the so called 'garden villages' that was developed around 1919 between the First and Second World War as a counterbalance to the impoverished neighborhoods in the city. Another reason for the neighborhood of Tuindorp Oostzaan to arise was the need of housing of the growing group of workers from the new industry and shipyards on the north banks of the IJ. Nowadays th
transit: The bus to Amsterdam Central Station stops at two minutes walking distance from the house and takes you directly to the city centre in 20 minutes. You can also take the ferry from NDSM Wharf. Free parking in front of the house.
access: You will have acces to the entire house, including the back garden.
interaction: Please don'nt hestitate to call me if you have any questions during your stay. I will be happy to help you find your way in the house and in the lovely city of Amsterdam.
house_rules: I expect you to leave the house clean. My cleaning lady can clean after you have left. Costs will be 70 euro's. I don't allow smoking and no pets please.

I hope you love my house as much as I do!

There you have the monthly held IJ-Hallen flea market, one of europ
neighborhood_overview: We are situated in a quiet neighbourhood close to the NDSM werf. There you have the monthly held IJ-Hallen flea market, one of europes biggest indoor flea markets. In summer there is a lot of bigger events, like concerts and festivals held. If you rent a bike it'll take you 15 to 20 minutes to the centre of Amsterdam.  If you decide that biking isn't for you then there is the option to take the bus from central station. This will be an half an hour ride. A supermarket is around 5 minutes from our house through a nearby park.
notes: We do have a super sweet dog and shy cat in the house.
transit: There is free parking in front of our house. It is also very easy to take the bus to get to our place or rent a bike.

We also offer Reiki or a foot massage for additional prices after you come home from a long walk.
house_rules: We don't allow smoking in the house. It is also very important to always close and lock the doors when you leave. Please clean after yourself when you use the kitchen or shower/toilet since we share the house. Use the swiper in the shower for the tiles and doors. Please don't take a shower in the middle of the night as it wakes up the other people in the house.
host_about:
I am an outgoing person who like so laugh a lot. I try not to take everything too serious. I am also honest and straight forward.
Travelling is part of my life and I've been also living overseas for a couple of years. My favourite country was Australia because of the people that I've met and the beautiful landscape. I like spending time outdoors, going camping, hiking or just sitting in the park with friends and having a nice bbq, yummy!
My Motto is: life is short, eat dessert first!

space: Tuindorp Oostzaan is a neighborhood in Amsterdam filled with the real "Amsterdammers", who moved in the early 30's from De Jordaan to here. It feels like living in a small village, but close to the city. If you go 10 minutes North, you'll be surrounded by the nature of "T Twiske", and if you go 15 minutes South, you'll be in the city center. The neighborhood is beautiful and quiet, a small secret of Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview: A former shipyard located on the banks of the River IJ in Amsterdam Noord, the NDSM Wharf has blossomed into an enormous cultural hotspot in recent years with a vibrant artist community and an ever-expanding variety of bars and restaurants. With grounds exceeding the size of ten football pitches, the area hosts multi-disciplinary festivals, performances, exhibitions, dance parties and a wide range of other events in unique, post-industrial surroundings.
notes: One important thing to know, we have two cats. They are very sweet and outside or sleeping all day. It would be fantastic if you are willing to put some food in the bowls every morning. And of course, if you like cats, you can play with them as much as you want.  If you don't want to do this, our neighbor is happy to do this, so don't feel obliged.
transit: There's a free ferry close to the house (5min) which will bring you to the city center in 12 minutes. You could also take a bus (37).
access: You have access to our complete house, including living room, kitchen en two gardens downstairs, and a bedroom, separate room en bathroom upstairs. You are also allowed to use our bikes, we only need a deposit for this (100 euro each), in case something happens.
house_rules: We expect our visitors to treat our house with respect. It's perfect to have the most comfortable stay during your visit, but not very suitable for big parties. Because of the village-characteristics of this neighborhood, it's important to be a bit quiet at night.
host_about: My name is Johan, I'm 27 years old and I'm working as a Project Manager at the University of Leiden. I'm always very happy with using AirBnB while travelling to other countries, so it would be my pleasure to give visitors of Amsterdam a great experience during their visit.

name: Charming little red-brick house
summary: Ons kleine huis heeft alles wat je nodig hebt om te ontspannen na een dagje Amsterdam. Vanaf het CS ben je met de pont in 20 minuten bij ons huis, rustig gelegen in landelijk Noord met gratis parkeren voor de deur.
space: Ons kleine huis voorziet in al onze woonwensen. We hebben een open keuken die overgaat in de woonkamer. Als het mooi weer is, is onze woning twee keer zo groot doordat we een fijne tuin hebben. In de tuin hebben we bramen en druiven en prachtige hortensia's. Je kunt er lekker zitten, eten, een vuurtje stoken in de vuurkorf, in het gras liggen of spelen in de zandbak. Boven hebben we een kleine badkamer met douche, toilet, wastafel en kinderbadje. Er is een ouderslaapkamer en een kinderkamer met ledikant. Op de zolder is nog een kinderkamer met eenpersoons matras. Er kunnen nog twee extra personen slapen in ons huis, aangezien we in de woonkamer een slaapbank hebben. In de kinderkamers kunnen desgewenst luchtbedden/matrassen neergelegd worden voor grotere kinderen.

neighborhood_overview: We wonen in landelijk Amsterdam Noord. Met een pont vanaf het Centraal Station ben je in 20 minuten bij ons huis. Het is hier lekker rustig, vlakbij natuurgebied het Twiske, maar je bent ook snel in het Centrum om musea te bezoeken, te winkelen of lekker uit eten te gaan. Vanaf ons huis zit je met de auto in vijf minuten op de snelweg, en kun je zo andere delen van Nederland bezoeken. Ons huis ligt vlakbij het NDSM-terrein, een culturele broedplaats met steeds meer mogelijkheden. Zo zijn er diverse leuke eettentjes, een indoor skate-baan en elk eerste weekend van de maand een grote tweedehands markt, de Ijhallen.
transit: Parkeren kan gratis voor de deur. Er stoppen meerdere bussen nabij ons huis, in de richting van Amsterdam Centraal. Vlakbij ons huis ligt de pont, die naar het Centraal Station vaart.
access: Wij zullen zelf niet in het huis aanwezig zijn wanneer er gasten zijn, gasten kunnen dus van alle algemene voorzieningen gebruik maken
interaction: Wij houden contact via de telefoon en/of email. Er zal altijd een aanspreekpunt zijn in de buurt, bijvoorbeeld de buren.
house_rules: Wij gaan ervan uit dat je met onze spullen omgaat, zoals je dat met je eigen spullen doet. Wees welkom en geniet van Amsterdam!

summary: BRAND NEW! On the topfloor of Elien & Franky's house, they designed a private Loft! The loft is a cosy space of 35 m2, with an open ensuite bathroom, separate toilet, kitchenette and a king size bed. The room is light & spacious.
space: Amsterdam North is an upcoming neighbourhood with it's artistic NDSM wharf (5min). Close to nature (5min) and close to the city (20min). This area is called the Bongerd (orchard of apple trees) and is part of the bigger area ‘Tuindorp-Oostzaan.’ This neighbourhood has been built in the last 7 years. Our home was completed in September 2014 and has been built with the newest construction materials. The windows are triple glazed so with a bit of sun in the winter the house gets to almost 21 degrees by itself. We painted and decorated everything ourselves and are very happy in our new home.

neighborhood_overview: Our house is located in Amsterdam North in the so called ‘Tuindorp-Oostzaan neighbourhood (garden village). In case you get lost, you should ask for the NDSM-wharf, which is closeby and very well known. Bongerd means orchard, so all our streetnames are names of different sorts of apples, like our street ‘Kaneelappelstraat’ (apple cinnamon street). On weekdays in the months October and November there are construction works in the neighbourhood. This starts at 8:00 in the morning, so no need to set your alarm during the week ;-) This used to be a harbour. You can still see an old crane at the end of the street, which had been used for building 80% of the houses that are in this area as of the 1950s. Our neighbourhood is trying to preserve & restore the old crane. Amsterdam North is becoming more hip every day. You can find really good restaurants in the most spectacular places. You can have a party in an old factory or have an exclusive dinner in an old ferry, garage or sea-container! Th
transit: We would recommend to rent a bicycle to explore Amsterdam, best way ever! The best way to our house by public transportation: 1. From Amsterdam Central Station: -Take bus 35 (direction Molenwijk) at the waterside from the trainstation. Get out at busstop 'Nageljongenstraat'. From here it's a 4 minute walk to our house OR -Take the free ferry (at the waterside of the trainstation) to the NDSM wharf. It's a 12-minute sceneric boat trip. When you arrive at the NDSM, it's a 20 minute minute walk to our house. You can also go for option 1 and do the boat trip with your bicycle. Saves you a long walk ;-) 2. From Schiphol Airport: Take the train to Amsterdam Central Station, then see the options above Public transport is expensive. A ticket on the bus will cost you about EUR 2,50 (valid for an hour on tram/bus/metro). (URL HIDDEN) (maps, timetables, costs, transport by night) If you come by car you can park your car in front of our house for free.
access: We share the same entrance and hallway. The top floor is totally yours. The loft it the best part of the house. We designed it ourselves and friends of us, artists and professionals, built it. We kindly ask our guests to take off their shoes and use slippers in the house, this because of hygiene reasons.
interaction: We are happy to answer all your questions and give suggestions.
house_rules: We take very good care of our house and the Loft. Please treat it the same way you would like others to treat your home.  Some house rules: - No smoking - No excessive alcohol abuse - No drugs - No party - No other people allowed - No shoes in the house, only slippers/socks -If we are away, please feed the cat ;-) Balou will be grateful Thank you!
host_about:
Hello there!

My husband - Frans - and I have been living in Amsterdam for more than 8 years now. For us it's the most wonderful city to live in!

I'm 29 and Belgian, Frans is 35 and a Dutchman. Together we've done quite some traveling. We met in Mallorca, lived together in Ghent, Belgium for 3 years, lived in Istanbul, Turkey for 1/2 year, extensively travelled through Italy & Spain and in 2013 we came back from a 1 year trip around South-America. Though having seen all these beautiful places, Amsterdam has stolen our hearts and we can't imagine living anywhere else but here. Cycling through the city, across the bridges and next to the canals always puts a very large smile on our faces! 

We invite you to come and explore all the magic this city has to offer!

Elien & Frans

name: Picturesque, quiet, free parking
summary: In a dead-end street in Amsterdam North, we own a beautiful house with lovely garden on a small canal. No city noises and exhaust fumes, but singing birds and the smell of flowers. And the city center is only 20 minutes away (via the free ferry).
space: The location in Amsterdam North, close to the city and even closer to the beautiful countryside, together with the ambiance in and around our house, make this spot quite unique. The layout of the house, with extra stairs from the garage, ensures sufficient privacy for our guests. The room is on the first floor, the shower and toilet are on the ground floor.  You enter via the garage and your own stairs to the first floor. The space above the garage features a spacious library room, which gives access to your bedroom. On cold or rainy days, the library is also where you will have your breakfast. We want to make sure that our guests are comfortable and enjoy their stay, not just in our house and garden, but in our city as well. We are usually home when we have guests. We like meeting people but we respect your need to be left to yourselves.  Our neighbourhood (and especially our dead-end street) have an exceptional village feel to them. The canal that connects to the countryside to the N
