neighborhood_overview: Our neighbourhood (and especially our dead-end street) have an exceptional village feel to them. The canal that connects to the countryside to the North add to the typical North-Holland ambiance. Nature reserves Twiske and Ilperveld, as well as Waterland and world-famous Zaanse Schans, are just around the corner. On the other hand, you can reach the center of Amsterdam in under 20 minutes, either by bus or on your rental bicycle (riding the free ferry over the IJ just adds to the joy of living in North).
notes: We have a fridge and  microwave for the guests in their room.  If needed, an extra bed can be used (at 15 euros). We have a sauna, which is available at a small fee. Also, we have a (very) small boat with an outboard motor, which will take you to the Waterland in the North of Amsterdam at the cost of some petrol. For those of you who like reading: the library that leads to your bedroom is filled with literature and philosophy books in 4 languages. We have 2 cats that roam the house as well as the garden. While we have guests, we will try to keep them out of the guest quarters.
transit: From the Central Station, you take the free ferry to NDSM. Then take bus 38, 37 of 35 to Molenwijk. If you have a bicycle, you follow the signs to Twiske. From Central Station you can also take bus 35 to Molenwijk.  If you are travelling by car, you take exit S118 towards Oostzanerwerf.
access: You enter via the garage and your own stairs to the first floor. The space above the garage features a spacious library room, which gives access to your bedroom. On cold or rainy days, the library is also where you will have your breakfast.
interaction: We want to make sure that our guests are comfortable and enjoy their stay, not just in our house and garden, but in our city as well. We are usually home when we have guests. We like meeting people but we respect your need to be left to yourselves.
house_rules: We happily invite guests to enjoy all the good things in our house and garden. We will do our utmost to make your stay a happy one. We expect you to respect our house, garden and cats. We kindly ask you to refrain from smoking in the house and to not bring any pets to the house. Musical instruments are more than welcome.
host_about:
I love making music, gardening, riding my bicycle and turning my house into a beautiful and cozy space. Together with my husband Jang, I love to receive guests and sharing all that makes our spot such a wonderful place to live in. I love the colours in and around our house.

I teach music to very young children (I used to be a kindergarten teacher) and was able to turn my music hobby into my profession. I love classical pieces, but also folk and world music. We love visiting small music festivals, especially in summer.

When I stop moving around and take the time to sit down and read, I usually pick up a psychological novel. We try to minimize watching TV, but if we do watch it, we choose travel and housefinding programmes. Going to a movie with a friend is another one of my regular treats.

We eat food from various foreign cultures, such as Turkish, Indonesian, Mexican, Libanese, Thai, etc. Of course we also love to travel, together or on our own. Portugal, Czech Republic, France, Norway, Turkey, America, Aruba, Lebanon, Syria, South-Africa. These are some of the countries we have visited. Ik like camping as well as staying in a bed and breakfast. A hotel is fine for a couple of nights, but not my favourite stay on a holiday trip. I like to travel by train or bicycle.

My life's motto would be: sharing my good fortune and happiness with others.

Wij zijn Joke en Gerard, beiden 50+. 
Wij wonen nu sinds 2005 op deze woonboot en het is fantastisch.
Het heerlijke gevoel van vrijheid en luxe van wonen op het water is echt iedere dag een kado. En dit gevoel willen wij graag doorgeven en laten ervaren aan onze gasten. 
Joke werkt op de luchthaven Schiphol bij de KLM en Gerard heeft een baan in de sales.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. More and more hotspots are popping up! Visit urban beaches like Café de Ceuvel and Pllek! Both perfect spots to relax and enjoy the warm weather on the waterfront. Other nice places overlooking the IJ-lake are film museum EYE (enjoy the sunset on their beautiful terrace!), seafood restaurant Stork and THT restaurant. One of our favourite areas in Amsterdam North is the NDSM Wharf. Known as one of the best festival locations of Amsterdam. North is also the place to be for vintage and thrift shopping. You can’t miss the monthly flea market in the IJ-hallen, a true second hand heaven.
access: You will access to the entire apartment. Make yourself at home!
interaction: I will meet you at the apartment, handle the keys and show you around. After that feel free to contact me on Airbnb if you need any assistance or tips! I am more then happy to help you!
house_rules: Treat the apartment as if it were your own and keep in mind that you have neighbours. The apartment is a regular home not an after hours club, so no parties, no drugs, no loud music/TV, etc. Police will fine when complaints are made after 23:00 (11pm) or before 07:00 (7am). At time of departure: make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done, the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean. Smoking of any kind is not allowed, this may also result in a triggering of the fire alarm. All keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee. Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment. If host is not informed of defects, host cannot be held liable for resulting damage to personal items.
host_about: Love design, staying active and meet new people!

The former industrial warehouse of Amsterdam Noord have been overtaken by the city's urban explorers, who now use them as art galleries, skate parks, pop restaurants and for music festivals. Tuindorp Oostzaan was originally a working-class neighborhood. It's is one of the so called 'garden villages' that was developed around 1919 between the First and Second World War as a counterbalance to the impoverished neighborhoods in the city. name: Great house, 10 min to Centre
summary: It's an amazing place, where we live. In the city and yet so much space around & a park at our doorstep. Use the house while we're on vacation. Put on the fireplace or go out to explore Amsterdam. The house is big, a bit messy, but cosy.
space: The living room is amazingly big. The kids can do gymnastics in the house but they can also use the trampoline or the swing in the garden. The master bedroom has a big double bed, and the kids each have their own bedroom. On the attic there is one bed plus a mattress on the floor. The bathroom has two sinks, a bath and a separate shower. All the comfort you will need! The kitchen has an oven, microwave, and all kinds of materials. We have a small sit-on canoe you can borrow, there is a gas BBQ in the backyard, and perhaps, if we don't need it, you can borrow the long bicycle which you can see in one of the pictures.  The arrangement of the furniture changes once in a while. Most of the furniture is on wheels, so we like to move them around once in a while.

neighborhood_overview: We live in a very quite, nice neighborhood. The (small) park is a half a minute away, a small shoppingcenter is five minutes by bike, and has free parking inside the parking hall inside it. A very large recreation area is 20 minutes by bike, and 15 minutes by car. It's called Het Twiske. You can be behind central station by bike in 15 minutes and by public transportation in about the same time.
transit: There's public transportation to Central Station in walking distance.
access: Everywhere, as long as you respect our private things.
interaction: We will rent our house when we are not around.
house_rules: We expect people to be respectful to our things, and to do as they promise. For example, if you say you come with five people, we expect you to come with five, not with ten. We expect people to respect our neighbor's peace and quite, within normal limits. And of course, we would like you to enjoy our house very much!
host_about:
Hello, 
We are a family of five, and we live in a very nice house in the north of Amsterdam. We have a huge living room with fire place, and a front and back yard with a trampoline in it. It's a wonderful neighborhood that we live in, and still we can be in the centre in about 10 cycling minutes. Our kids are 9, 10 and 12 years old, and we have two dogs. When we are renting out our house we are probably on our bikes, cycling around. We've done that for a year.

i am a widow since 20 years. My husband was a general practitioner and had his praxis in this beautiful house. I helped him throughout the years. After his death I decided to stay on living in this house with my daughter. After a while the house was offered for buying and was renovated and got the status of monument of state. Amsterdam School with rural elements. Because it is a wonderful villa and very expensive I decided top start a B&B. This was in the year of 1998.
Since than I had a beautiful carreer on this point see my website (URL HIDDEN) chapter Kwint in the media.
I decided to rent out the studio - the former praxis of my late husband - especially for Airbnb, normally it goes also with the guestrooms in the house, as it still does.
I am a collector of modern arts and antiques. My house is full of it and guests appreciate the atmosphere and the collections.
The breakfast in the morning is bountiful.

I am Karin (50), I have been living in Amsterdam for 32 years now. I work as a free-lance actress and voice over, my husband Eddy(59) works at the Amsterdam Theatre School of Arts, we have two children who both study and dont live at home anymore.
Our part of the city, Noord, is very upcoming and has nice cafe' s and restaurants near the IJ river, like Pllek, IJkantine, Stork, and of course the brand new EYE filmmuseum.
About our house: We have been living here for 28 years and did a lot of decorating ourselves.We find that this house is avery peaceful and comfortable house to live in, in a quiet area but within 20 minutes of the livelyness of the centre. We have lots of information for you about the cultural life of Amsterdam,Museums, Art centres, restaurants, markets, ect.
We hope you have a great time here and treat the house respectfully.

name: Amsterdam North, hip and happening
summary: Our friendly guestroom has it's own private bathroom and toilet. The NDSM docks (third hippest place according to  the New York times) are at walking distance. Down town Amsterdam is easily reached by public transport, day and night.
space: Deze plaats in Amsterdam-Noord is uniek, omdat het hippe NDMS terrein vlakbij is, maar ook omdat het centrum dag en nacht makkelijk bereikbaar is. Daarnaast fietst men zo het schilderachtige waterland in.
description: Our friendly guestroom has it's own private bathroom and toilet. The NDSM docks (third hippest place according to  the New York times) are at walking distance. Down town Amsterdam is easily reached by public transport, day and night.      This is a wonderfull neighbourhood. The NDAM docks are nearby. Downtown is easily reached, but also the charming scenery of North Holland is easily accessible on bicycle, on foot or even by bus. Parking is still free. There is a daybus and a nightbus  nearby to the city center and also a ferry from the NDSM docks.

interaction: Ik geef de gasten  informatie over de stad.
host_about:
Ik woon in Amsterdam Noord en heb al langere tijd een B&B. Amsterdam Noord zit in de lift, er komen steeds meer gasten maar ook steeds meer concurrenten, daarom zet ik mijn B&B op nóg een site. 
De vijf dingen waar ik niet zonder kan zijn: boeken, gezellige etentjes met vrienden, dansen, de poezen en de natuur. Ik houd van reizen, maar ver hoeft dat niet te zijn, een weekend naar Kijkduin vind ik ook leuk. Verder ga ik graag naar 'koele' (poëtische) landen zoals Schotland of Rusland. De tropen zijn te warm en te arm voor mij. Ik verhuur een kamer op de begane grond maar eigenlijk is dat de hele beneden verdieping, verder ben ik een vriendelijke gastvrouw. Ik probeer de gastenkamer zo mooi mogelijk te maken, dus die verandert nogal eens,  het ontbijt is zonder vlees en zoveel mogelijk biologisch.

neighborhood_overview: The nicest part about my house is the fact that is so quiet after a busy day in the city center. You will enjoy arriving here and feel like you are away from it all. Sit by the waterside and enjoy my garden as you drink a refreshing glass of wine or a hot cup of tea while talking about all the things you've done all day. My house is not near the city center but you can take a bus that will bring you right to the heart of the city in less then 20 minutes.
notes: What people like about my house is the fact that it feels like home. There is an easy going atmosphere and you feel welcome as soon as you arrive.  There are 2 cats and a small dog in the house! People that love pets will be delighted but if you are not a pet friend you might want to choose another listing :-) My pets are very sweet and won't bother you at all.  The fact that the house is not on walking distance to the city center is for some people a point to dislike the location although it's really easy and a short bus ride to get into the heart of the city. If you are intending to spend a lot of time in the room, please note that the room is not very big and if you are with more then 2 persons that could be a bit tight. Also if you are a group of big people ;-) you might find the room too small for you.
transit: My house is on the North side of Amsterdam, just 5 minutes from the trendy NDSM warf where you will find amazing spots to eat and chill-out and less then 20 minutes with the bus to the city center.  The bus is only 5 minutes walk from my house.  There is a small shopping center 10 minutes walk through the park and a supermarket even more close by where you can get some snacks or drinks.  Parking is free in my neighborhood. You can park your car just around the corner.
access: Guests are welcome to sit in the living room during breakfast and to use the garden anytime they like. Smoking is allowed in the garden.
interaction: At check-in I will give you as much information as I can to help you around and let you prepare for a good time in Amsterdam. Mostly I am around to help you with anything during your stay. At breakfast is a good time to drop your questions and tell about your experiences. If you prefer to have breakfast quietly in your room that is also possible :-)
house_rules: Please make sure you read the full description of my listing and feel free to ask me anything you need to know.  Most important is that you enjoy your stay and that you make sure I know what your expectations are and what I can do to make you feel comfortable.
host_about: Friendly and curious about people in general

space: Located in a quiet street, but minutes away from where it is happening. Thrillist has put Amsterdam Noord on number 3 in their list of the TEN MOST HIPSTER NEIGHBOURHOODS ON EARTH. The former industrial warehouse of Amsterdam Noord have been overtaken by the city's urban explorers, who now use them as art galleries, skate parks, pop restaurants and for music festivals. The seeds of gentricication have already been shown here: Red Bull and MTV have opened up offices on the waterfront and smaller start ups are also starting to reshape the landscape. The bus to Central Station stops in front of our house and takes you to the city centre in 20 minutes. You can also take the ferry from NDSM wharf.

neighborhood_overview: Tuindorp Oostzaan was originally a working-class neighborhood. It's is one of the so called 'garden villages' that was developed around 1919 between the First and Second World War as a counterbalance to the impoverished neighborhoods in the city. Another reason for the neighborhood of Tuindorp Oostzaan to arise was the need of housing of the growing group of workers from the new industry and shipyards on the north banks of the IJ. Nowadays the district has more than 10,000 inhabitants. Relatively speaking, there are many elderly people and families with children compared to all of Amsterdam-Noord. Single family homes are in the majority. The old, low-lying part of Tuindorp Oostzaan is mostly built in the twenties. The upper part is built in different periods of time and contains more modern houses, lofts, apartments and villas. Present-day Tuindorp Oostzaan will offer you an exciting mix of experimental festivals, picturesque country villages and stylish restaurants. Closeby you will f

neighborhood_overview: Our houseboat is located in Amsterdam North in the so called ‘Tuindorp-Oostzaan neighbourhood (garden village). In case you get lost, you should ask for the NDSM-wharf, which is closeby and very well known.   This used to be a harbour. You can still see an old crane at the end of the street, which had been used for building 80% of the houses that are in this area as of the 1950s. Our neighbourhood is trying to preserve & restore the old crane.  Amsterdam North is becoming more hip every day. On some hotspot lists, we are number 7 worldwide!!! You can find really good restaurants in the most spectacular places. You can have a party in an old factory or have an exclusive dinner in an old ferry, garage or sea-container! The area NDSM wharf (Dutch docking and shipping company) is a well-known area. Thousands of workmen used to work here building enormous ships. The old factories, piers and cranes are beautiful sights, which have been transformed into restaurants, hotels or venues for parti
notes: At this moment the street is under construction, which will be finished by the end of November. Op dit moment wordt onze straat heringericht. Dit kan wat ongemakken veroorzaken.

The ferry's go frequently and fri-sat even until after midnight.  walking to the ferry and the ferry ride itself will bring you to the central Station within 25 minutes. And its very relaxing to make this short trip to the center. The bus stop  (ATATURK)  is around the corner. frequently and affordable.Bus no 35 brings you to Central station. Night bus 363 brings you back from the Central station. Openbaar vervoer is om de hoek, frequent en betaalbaar. De veren naar Centraal station zijn gratis. Er rijden nachtbussen ( bus 363) vanaf CS naar Molenwijk, uitstappen bij Ataturk.  's zomers is er een nachtveer van Centraal station naar NDSM.  Op de fiets naar Centraal station is ongeveer 15 min. description: Book a Camper, Caravan, Circus Wagon or Boat located @ the NDSM Shipyard. Close to nature and just minutes away from the city center. Two free bikes are included. This unique old-timer Camper is nicely decorated and is fully equipped with a heater, little toilet, big bed and a place to sit and relax. You can open the back window and enjoy the water view :) The Camper is situated on a courtyard with also other Campers, Caravans and 2 Boats. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travelers. There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner. There's a kitchen, toilet and 2 showers.  You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, 2 cats and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs! neighborhood_overview: The Camper is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas.  NDSM (a former shipyard) located on the banks of the River IJ has blossomed into an enormous cultural hot spot in recent years.There are festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events.  The boat is 20 minutes away from the vibrant city centre, and just 10 minutes away from Twiske. Twiske is a beautiful nature park with canals, bridges, a windmill and lakes where you can swim.
transit: Ferry: It's a 10 minute bike ride to NDSM, from there you can take the (free) ferry to the centre.   There's a night ferry that runs 24/7, so it's never a problem to get back from the city. Bus:  5 minutes walking from the place there's a bus stop. The bus takes 15 minutes to get to central station. Also the bus runs all night.
access: The Camper is situated on a courtyard with also other Campers, Caravans and 2 Boats. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travelers. There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner. There's a kitchen, toilet and 2 showers.  You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, 2 cats and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs!  Also you will get 2 bikes for free with your Camper stay! There's a big fireplace to keep you nice and warm during the winter! Its a cool interesting place for hippie, laid-back, budget backpackers so don’t expect a five star hotel ;)
house_rules: Hi guys, thanks for booking! We can't wait to welcome you here.  Before you arrive we want to help you out with some practical information. Check in: from 1 pm Keep us posted about your arrival time, we are waiting for you :) Check out: before 11 am Rental Please do not smoke inside your rental. Do not forget to turn off your heater if you are leaving your rental Barn The Barn is your common area with a place to relax, 2 bathrooms, 3 showers (towels are included) and 2 fully equipped kitchens. Please keep it clean and do your dishes so other guests can use it too. Bikes The bikes are for free use. Please handle them with care, and ALWAYS lock them. If you want we offer a bike insurance. For 5 euro a bike your bikes are insured against theft. If you don't want the insurance and the bikes get stolen we expect you to refund the bikes and locks (150 euro a bike and 50 for the lock). Please do not use the bikes on check out day, we need them for the new guests. Keys You'll get keys; of the
host_about:
Hi my name is Maik.

summary: Book a Camper, Caravan, Circus Wagon and Boat located @ the NDSM Shipyard. Close to nature and just minutes away from the city center. We can host 26 people.

All places are nicely decorated and are equipped with a heater and place to sit and relax.  Depending on the accommodation they have 1 or 2 beds. The accommodations are situated on a courtyard at the water. There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, play games, play pool and have some diner. There are 2 fully equipped kitchens, 2 toilets and 3 showers. Towels are included. You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, 2 cats and 4 chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs! There are also 2 big fireplaces in the barn to keep you nice and warm during the winter! Campsterdam is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas.
neighborhood_overview: Campsterdam is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas. NDSM (a former shipyard) located on the banks of the River IJ has blossomed into an enormous cultural hot spot in recent years.There are festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events. Campsterdam is 20 minutes away from the vibrant city centre, and just 10 minutes away from Twiske.  Twiske is a beautiful nature park with canals, bridges, a windmill and lakes where you can swim.
transit: Ferry: It's a 10 minute bike ride to NDSM, from there you can take the (free) ferry to the centre.  There's a night ferry that runs 24/7, so it's never a problem to get back from the city. Bus:  5 minutes walking from the place there's a bus stop. The bus takes 15 minutes to get to central station. Also the bus runs all night.

notes: The space is part of the main house. On the upstairs we have the other room rented too so please keep in mind that you can hear the footsteps. When you are going to book our place, please indicate about yourself (name, nationality, age) and your travelmate. Please give us indication about your ETA (Estimation of Arrival) at our place so we can arrange our schedule to receive you. Upon your arrival, we will make a copy of your ID that is needed for the administration.
transit: The house is located about 7 km to the city center. Check the address of Landsmeerderdijk, Amsterdam. There are three access of bus to go to the city centre, in which 2 busses are the GVB bus. Public transportation is available for 24 hours. It will take you about 25-35 minutes from the house to the city center with public transportation. Another option: if you're coming with car, you can also drive your car to the nearest ferry terminal NDSM. Park your car at the nearest residential area, walk about 15 minutes to the ferry, then take the 12-15 minutes free ride to the backside of the Amsterdam Centraal Station. But keep in mind that the ferry has a specific schedule and only operates before 24:00. NDSM is also interesting to explore. So when you missed the ferry, you can use the time to walk around the area; and take the next one. After your bookings, we'll send you a pdf document concerning the public transportation. So please send us your email address.

notes: As I like to respect the privacy and peace of my neighbours, I ask my guests only to make use of the back entrance of the house.  There are two cats present; Jack and Minous. And sometimes my daughter of 10 years old, who stayes with me every wednesday and every other weekend. She is like me, out going, spontaneous, friendly and optimistic. And enjoyes meeting and talking to guests.
transit: To arrive to the house, you can take Bus 35 from Amsterdam Central Station that runs every 10 minutes. Take exit at 'Pomonastraat'.  The best thing to do is to rent a bike at the central station, and take the free ferry behind Amsterdam Central Station to KNSM (+/-15 minutes, which alwys is a nice ride over the IJ). From there it's 5 to 10 minutes bike ride to the house.
access: Your private room, the bathroom, toilet, and garden. Please no usage of kitchen, and limited usage of living room. Washing machine and dryer are present. However, based on prior experience I would like to ask you to limit usage and for a small contribution of eur. 5,- per laundry, should you wish to use it anyway.
interaction: From 2010 up to 2012 I also offered B&B on Airbnb, which I really enjoyed a lot. As I am a traveller myself, I like meeting travellers, and offer them a warm, friendly, neat, tidy and comfortable please to stay. I like to offer you a place where you feel safe, respected, relaxed and at home. I am outgoing, and have an optimistic and positive personality and always like to try to read and meet with peoples needs and wishes. So when you feel like chatting, we chat. When you prefer privacy, I will offer you your space. When you look for adventure, I will do my best to help you find it in Amsterdam, as there is always plenty of opportunities for doing so in Amsterdam.  I speak English, German, French, and a bit of Spanish.
house_rules: My goal is to contribute to making your stay in amsterdam beautiful, superb and unforgettable. From the many guests that I already served in the past, there wasn't a single person whom I couldn't get a long with. They, as well as myself always had a great time. Key is respect, friendliness and spontaneousness. I like to respect, and serve you, as well as I would have liked that myself. Usually things to do and not to do in the house complies with your own standards. After 11 PM I would kindly like you to keep the volume limited. And should you wish to bring a friend(s), please contact me first to discuss. Although every once and a while I smoke myself, I would kindly like to ask you, not to smoke in the room.

neighborhood_overview: The Camper is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas.  NDSM (a former shipyard) located on the banks of the River IJ has blossomed into an enormous cultural hot spot in recent years.There are festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events.  The boat is 20 minutes away from the vibrant city centre, and just 10 minutes away from Twiske. Twiske is a beautiful nature park with canals, bridges, a windmill and lakes where you can swim.
transit: Getting to the Camper: Take Citybus 34 (direction Buikslotermeerplein) get off at busstop Tjalkstraat. (20 min). From the Camper to the City-centre: Hop on the (free) ferry at the NDSM-werf and set sail for the charming City Centre. The trip takes 15 minutes and you can bring your bike (also free).
access: The Camper is situated on a courtyard with also a Caravan and a Boat. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travelers. There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner. There's a kitchen, toilet and 2 showers.  You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, a dog and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs!  Also you will get 2 bikes for free with your Camper stay! There's a big fireplace to keep you nice and warm during the winter! Its a cool interesting place for hippie, laid-back, budget backpackers so don’t expect a five star hotel ;)

neighborhood_overview: The district of Amsterdam -North is considered to be one of the "Up and coming areas" in Amsterdam. Formerly a place where industry and ship-building were the word, it is now transforming into a birth-place for many young creatives. Especially around the water-shores of "Het IJ" many interesting sites can be found: -EYE: the new cinema museum. Spectacular architectural design with a beautiful view over the water. It offers an amazing collection of movies and their history. A definite must-see. -NDSM; a former shipyard turned into a cultural venue / art-city. Here, about two hundred artists, designers and architects have their space. It is also home to MTV's European HQ, media producers, as well as other creative industries. Many festivals and other cultural activities. Check out "Noorderlicht-cafe" and "Pllek" for a relaxed drink&bite with beautiful panoramic view over the water. Generally a very interesting place to check out. Also: -Tolhuistuin : like NDSM, but this time on a former
notes: IMPORTANT: Please Please DON'T EVER DISPOSE OF SANITARY TOWELS or other cotton-based hygienic wipes in our toilets. This will cause the sewage-pump to fail, with very serious consequences indeed. Warning signs are visible in the bathroom. Please also notify your children about this very important issue. You can put these items in the hygienic-bin beside the toilet. Please realise that if the pump fails: -you CANNOT shower -you CANNOT go to the toilet -you CANNOT use the dishwasher/laundromat -you CANNOT flush or use any water whatsoever effectively ruining your stay for at least two days. We cannot emphasize enough how important this is.
transit: From Schiphol-airport you take the train to Amsterdam Central station. From there you can choose from: -Taxi (be sure to make a price of max E 25,00). Cab drivers in Amsterdam can be dodgy, so be careful. -Bus : Take line 35 to "Molenwijk"and exit at "Ataturk"-station. 5 mins walk from there to our place. -Ferry: exit north side of central station and take the free ferry to "NDSM". Arriving there it's 15 min walking and either we pick you up if possible, or you order a taxi from there. Car-drivers use their NAVI, this usually works fine. Public transportation from our place to Central Station is very accessible, frequent and affordable, by bus or ferry. You might want to buy a public transportation chip-card, but you can also pay cash. The ferries to central station are free of charge, but if you park your car at the terminal be sure to pay a parking fee. In summer, there is a night-ferry service to NDSM. This area is called the Bongerd (orchard of
neighborhood_overview: Our home was completed in September 2014 and has been built with the newest construction materials. The windows are triple glazed so with a bit of sun in the winter the house gets to almost 21 degrees by itself. We painted and decorated everything ourselves and are very happy in our new home. This area is called the Bongerd (orchard of apple trees) and is part of the bigger area ‘Tuindorp-Oostzaan’ (garden village). Bongerd means orchard, so all our streetnames are names of different sorts of apples, like our street ‘Kaneelappelstraat’ (apple cinnamon street).This neighbourhood has been built in the last 7 years.  We live very close to the NDSM-wharf, which is in the Top-10 of the hippest area's in Europe. This used to be a harbour. You can still see an old crane at the end of the street, which had been used for building 80% of the houses that are in this area as of the 1950s. Our neighbourhood is trying to preserve & restore the old crane. You can find really good restaurants in the m
notes: There is a cat in the house, Balou. Please be nice to him, he might be nice as well ;-)
transit: We would recommend to rent a bicycle to explore Amsterdam, best way ever! There is a MacBike at the Central station, 10 Euro for 24hrs. The best way to our house by public transportation: 1. From Amsterdam Central Station: -Take bus 35 (direction Molenwijk) at the waterside from the trainstation. Get out at busstop 'Nageljongenstraat'. From here it's a 4 minute walk to our house OR -Take the free ferry (at the waterside of the trainstation) to the NDSM wharf. It's a 12-minute sceneric boat trip. When you arrive at the NDSM, it's a 20 minute minute walk to our house. You can also go for option 1 and do the boat trip with your bicycle. Saves you a long walk ;-) 2. From Schiphol Airport: Take the train to Amsterdam Central Station, then see the options above Public transport is expensive. A ticket on the bus will cost you about EUR 2,90 (valid for an hour on tram/bus/metro), 7,50 for 24hr. (URL HIDDEN) (maps, timetables, costs, transport by night) If you come by car you can park your car
interaction: You will have the entire house to yourself and you can of course always reach us by phone or text message with any questions you may have. We are there to make your stay as comfortable as possible.
house_rules: We take very good care of our house. Please treat it the same way you would like others to treat your home.  Some house rules: - No smoking - No excessive alcohol abuse - No drugs - No party - No other people allowed -Please feed the cat ;-) Balou will be thankful - No shoes in the house, only slippers/socks because of hygienic reasons Thank you!
host_about:
Hello there!

My husband - Frans - and I have been living in Amsterdam for more than 8 years now. For us it's the most wonderful city to live in!

I'm 29 and Belgian, Frans is 35 and a Dutchman. Together we've done quite some traveling. We met in Mallorca, lived together in Ghent, Belgium for 3 years, lived in Istanbul, Turkey for 1/2 year, extensively travelled through Italy & Spain and in 2013 we came back from a 1 year trip around South-America. Though having seen all these beautiful places, Amsterdam has stolen our hearts and we can't imagine living anywhere else but here. Cycling through the city, across the bridges and next to the canals always puts a very large smile on our faces! 

We invite you to come and explore all the magic this city has to offer!

Elien & Frans

neighborhood_overview: We are located inside the Amsterdam ring, at 20 minutes by bus from the city center and even closer to the big recreational area "Het Twiske". Yes, there are cows at a walking distance from home, and several beaches close-by. You can enjoy all the delights of the capital during the day and still relax in a cute, almost hobbit-like environement at night. However, the fancy NDSM area is not far from home, with its cafés, venues, exhibitions and busy festival programme.
notes: Adventurers, activists, wanderers, vegans, Burners, hippies, polyamorous people and all lovely weirdos, welcome! Complimentary tea and coffee are available all day.
transit: There is a free parking option right in front of our house, where space is almost always available.  There is also a bus at less than 5 minutes walking that regularly goes to/from Amsterdam CS train station in a 20 minutes ride.  If you rent bikes, you can park them in front of the house.
access: * Besides the bathroom and toilets, our guests are welcome to use the kitchen for breakfast and meals, provided that they leave it as clean as it was found. interaction: Our schedules are very flexible. Depending on how busy we are when you come, we may enjoy a cup of coffee with you and be available for tips and friendly discussion.  We do have some maps for guests and know some alternative venues, social centers, and events in town. Do not hesitate to ask.
house_rules: * Do not do anything in this house which you would not do at a friend or parent. This is a shared space. * Please communicate with us about your check-in and check-out time preferences. We will always try to be flexible.  * You can come in and out of the house at any time, as long as you keep the noise level down at night.  * As vegetarians, we would appreciate if you did not cook meat or fish at home.  * We recycle plastic and paper and we have a compost pile. Please try to do the same and ask us if you have any question about that.  * You can smoke in the garden, where an ashtray is available.   * Many people come to the Netherlands to enjoy coffeeshops or smartshops, and to experiment with products that are not legally available elsewhere. We don't mind if you smoke weed in the garden as long as you know your limits and behave responsibly. No other substance should be used at home. I'm a 45 year old graphic designer/art director/photographer, working at an Amsterdam based ad agency (specialist in sustainability and non-profit clients) in the centre. I myself live in the north part of Amsterdam, with the ferry across the IJ river. 
I have a naughty son of 5 which lives with me most of the time.
I like to travel to experience great places (although I would like to do it much more often), but I also like everything that has to do with homes, like interiors, gardening etc. 

On my days off I like to take my bike or car to do things inside or outside town, with my son, friends or family, like hang out on the beach, places with good coffee ánd a playground, cycling, drink wine and eat nice food at nice places.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is very diverse and historical. A 100 meters from our house you can find the historical "Buiksloterkerk" (a church) which was build in 1609 and is now used to host all kinds of events. It's right next to a historical dike with beautiful Dutch houses. A sight to see! There are two shopping areas with shops nearby, so you could do groceries to cook at "home" for example!
notes: There is a free ferry 15 minutes away from our place that goes 24/7, 365 days a year from Amsterdam North to the other side which is the Central Station of Amsterdam in 1 minute. Or bike the other direction for 10 minutes and you are right in the middel of the Dutch "polders". Other awesome stuff on the North side of Amsterdam are the Eye Film museum/cinema, NDSM Warf, Pllek and many other things.
transit: Bus 34 (500m from our place) goes every day of the week and will take you to Amsterdam Central station in 10 minutes. Bus 37 (200m from our place) goes every day of the week until late but you would have to transfer to another bus.

neighborhood_overview: It is located in the suburb area. So you need to commute to reach the centre. As a local, it took us about ½ hour to be in the down-town area with a bike or the bus. There are some bus options you can take with different routes. I’ll provide you with the information. I think it’s genius if you want to see Amsterdam from the real perspective (not only the tourist area). You can also take a bike then took the 3 different ferry routes that will bring you directly to the Central Station pier. So if you take a bike, scooter, or on foot; the only access to reach downtown is by using the FREE ferry, which is the NDSM, Buikslotermeerplein, and Ijplein. The nearest shopping centre is about 700 m from the house. There is a cheese and nuts store (there you can buy cheaper price for your souvenir), bread store (you have to taste the excellent Dutch brown bread), liquor store, convenient store (Blokker), drugstore (Deo), and of course the supermarket (Albert Heijn). You can go there on foot (approx
notes: Please give us indication about your ETA (Estimation of Arrival) after you positively booked your stay at our place so we can arrange our schedule to receive you. Upon your arrival, we will make a copy of your ID that is needed for the administration.
transit: The house is located about 7 km to the city center. Check the address of Landsmeerderdijk, Amsterdam. There are three access of bus to go to the city centre, in which 2 busses are the GVB bus. Public transportation is available for 24 hours. It will take you about 25-35 minutes from the house to the city center with public transportation. Another option: if you're coming with car, you can also drive your car to the nearest ferry terminal NDSM. Park your car at the nearest residential area, walk about 15 minutes to the ferry, then take the 12-15 minutes free ride to the backside of the Amsterdam Centraal Station. But keep in mind that the ferry has a specific schedule and only operates before 24:00. NDSM is also interesting to explore. So when you missed the ferry, you can use the time to walk around the area; and take the next one. After your bookings, we'll send you a pdf document concerning the public transportation. So please send us your email address.

interaction: Our schedules are very flexible. Depending on how busy we are when you come, we may enjoy a cup of coffee with you and be available for tips and friendly discussion.  We do have some maps for guests and know some alternative venues, social centers, and events in town. Do not hesitate to ask.

neighborhood_overview: Het huis heeft een perfect ligging wanneer je Amsterdam met kinderen wil bezoeken. Gelegen in een rustige, pittoreske buurt, met heerlijke tuin en gratis parkeren voor de deur. In 10 minuten fietsen bereik je het pontje dat je (gratis in 10 minuten) naar het centrum van Amsterdam brengt. Daarnaast staat Amsterdam-Noord in de top-10 van meest interessante plekken om te wonen omdat er continu veel nieuwe leuke, hippe tentjes starten. Dus ook in de nabije omgeving is veel te beleven.  Tot slot ligt het op 3 minuten fietsen van het natuurgebied Het Twiske met veel recreatie mogelijkheden zoals fietsen, zwemmen (strandjes) en een speeltuin.
notes: Onze tuin staat vol met fruit bomen en planten. Heel graag water geven en opeten wat er rijp is.
transit: Parkeren kan voor de deur, gratis. Vlak om de hoek is een bushalte met een directe verbinding naar de stad en naar de pittoreske dorpjes ten noorden van Amsterdam. Vanuit Schiphol kan het huis met de taxi (ongeveer 30 euro) of met de trein en bus bereikt worden.

space: The studio is a former horse stable and stands on an terrain of an old farm. This part of Amsterdam used to belong to Oostzaan and consisted of mostly farmers. The land has also an authentic barn and old haystack surrounded by (fish) water. The total site dates from circa 1890.

And in 15 minutes on the Dam in Zaandam and Zaanse Schans... Recreation area 't Twiske is around the corner for cycling and hiking and water recreation. North itself has beautiful bike rides through authentic Waterland and dikes. In addition, we are close to the NDSM site where many activities and festivals take place during spring- and summertime.

neighborhood_overview: Our neigbourhood looks like a little village in big Amsterdam and our street is very quiet and everybody knows each other. At the same time within cycling distance there is the NDSM:  a area with a lot of new, young and creative initiatives, and a hotspot of new restaurant, bars and festivals and live music.
notes: Breakfast is available on demand. let us know and we will arrange a breakfast according to your wishes.
transit: When you arrive at central station you can take the bus or even nicer take the ferry NDSM ( on the backside of central station ) a lovely 15 min over the IJwater and we try to pick you up at the other end. We have free bikes available and please use them Amsterdam is great by bike.There is a bus stop 400 m from our house and the bus goes directly to Central Station in 10 minutes.
access: The access of the garden is through our house. You have access to your own blue house and you can sit in the garden of course, and even make a BBQ or a little fire in the evening.
interaction: Of course when you have any questions we will try to help you if we can. Peter speaks very well english and german and Katja speaks french and english.We love to cook, and in the summer we often sit in the front garden and invite neighbors and friends to drink a glass wine with us. This often ends in a bbq together.
house_rules: We built our blue house ourselves with a lot of love and effort, so take good care of her. Please try not to waste any energy and put the heating low when you leave the house. Please don't be to noisy in the evenings.
host_about:
Peter: I'm a outgoing guy, like everything related to good Food,  fine wines ( we have our own cellar ) and most of all eating with good friends, I love to travel and work abroad, I worked as a Chef Cook in Turkey, Portugal, Belgium and so on. I love music, like to go to the movies and enjoy sports like squash and yoga.
Katja: I am more the creative of the two, love to make arts and crafts and making interiors beautiful. Working in the garden and being in nature is also important to me. My passion is traveling and especially horse riding in every country I visit. My sports are cycling, swimming and yoga.

space: The sleeping couch ( 140x200) can be used for 1 adult or 2 kids. We rent bikes 8.- Free WiFi Nespresso coffee machine Watercooker  Mini fridge Hairdryer Microwave Campingbed & children chair available, also bike seat for kid.

neighborhood_overview: The location is in the north of Adam, nearby NDSM wharf, a unique industrial spot. Upcoming neighbourhood, up & running. At this place (15 min. biking) is also the free ferry to Central station. The busstop to the Central station is across the street.
notes: First floor not accessibel for disabled people.
transit: Bike can be rent for 8 euro a day.  The bus to the Central station is on the other side of the street. (20 min to CS). There is also free parking in this part of the city. How to reach the inner city ( Central Station ) * The busstop to the main CS station bus 392(  to center of the city) is 200 m. from our house, 22 min. by bus. In the night take bus N92. * If you can bike ( we rent bikes ) there is a nice route to the ferries; bike to NDSM Wharf, 15 min. take the free ferry to CS. Total 30 min. * Walk to the busstop Molenwijk, take bus 35 or 38 , stop at busstop Ataturk ( 7 min) walk to ferry, take the free ferry to CS or Westerdoksdijk. * The last alternatieve is walk 5 min. to Molenwijk . Take bus 38 for  14 min. to ferry Buiksloterweg,  then 3 min. short free ferry to CS. Nightbus CS-Molenwijk N363. So you need 20 till 30 min. to reach the center. Bus 392+N92 is a connexion line ( Amsterdam-Zaandam) beware can't be used with daypass GVB. The other busses are GVB.
access: Picknick table  in the back garden at the water!
interaction: Nice to interact if not , also nice
house_rules: Welcome dear quests, Let me introduce my family. We are a family of four. Daan (23) Ward (21), Ron en Ellen. Ron is a photographer with a big passion for underwaterphotography. Ellen is a teacher who loves sports.  Together we explore every weekend our city, there is so much to do, see and to experience! The boys work in the horeca and come home late, if you hear some noise in the middle of the night, they return home from work. Transport The best way to reach  Zuideinde 329 from Central Station take bus 392 (Connexion) Amsterdam-Zaandam. Zuideinde 329 is opposite the LIDL. ( the seventh bus stop from CS). After 24.00 take the nightbus N92. It's also possible to take bus 35 (GVB)  from CS to de Molenwijk and walk 10 min. When we are home, you can also take the ferry (NDSM) and we pick you up there. This option is not always possible for us, so first contact us about this! There is also a bus from NDSM ferry, bus 38 to Molenwijk Train or bus from CS to Sloterdijk is also a option, then
host_about: I'am a teacher at a primery school and Ron is a Photographer. His hobby is underwaterphotography. We both love the city we're living and check outoften bars, musea, restaurants, neighbourhood and all nice places who need to be explored.

name: Lovely house garden front and back!
summary: Vlakbij hotspot NDSM met kunst en cultuur, restaurants, clubs. Je zult genieten vanwege de ongedwongen sfeer, de tuinen. Mijn ruimte is vooral geschikt voor stellen en gezinnen (met kinderen). Er wonen drie katten maar desgewenst kunnen zij uit logeren. Attention: we have enough beds but in case of taxes and rules by local authorities we do not rent the house to more than 4 persons. (Only the persons that already have booked the house for more persons can still come of course).
space: Heel fijn huis in Amsterdamseschool stijl, arbeiderswoning uit de jaren 30 in het mooie monumentale Tuindorp-Oostzaan dichtbij NDSM in de hipste en groenste wijk Amsterdam Noord. Heerlijke tuin met veel vogels, bloemen en met biologische groenten en kruiden om te plukken en te eten. Hangmat en vuurplaats en bbq in tuin, veel zon en ook schaduwplekjes. In de keuken kook je op gas, verder is er een oven, een combimagnetron,  een juicer,  espressomachine,  broodbakmachine en een blender. De afwas doet de afwasmachine. Boven op de eerste verdieping is de eenvoudige maar prima badkamer met lekkere douche, toilet en wastafel. Op de overloop staan de wasmachine en droger alsmede een extra vriezertje. Op deze etage bevinden zich ook de kinderkamer met een babybed (70cm x 1.20m) en een juniorbed (1.50m x 70 cm) en de tiener kamer met een 2persoonsbed (1.40m x1.90m), 1 slaapbank (2persoons) en een hoogslaper (90cmx 2.00m). Op de tweede etage bevindt zich een tweepersoonsbed in een zeer romantisc

neighborhood_overview: Prachtige wijk. Veel groen en rust. Maar ook dichtbij genoeg voor gezelligheid en hippe cafés en restaurants aan de IJ-oever op het NDSM terrein of achter centraal station. Beautiful green monumental area.  Closeby shops and hotspot bars/ restaurants like Noorderlicht café, Pllek etc and the Adamtoren the North of Amsterdam which is the place to be nowadays! Free parking in front of the house!!
notes: Attention: We have three really sweet cats! We would like them to stay in the house but if you insist we can take them with us.
transit: Op 2 minuten lopen diverse stadsbussen. Die rijden binnen 25 minuten naar het stadscentrum/ centraal station. Op 10 minuten fietsen de veerboten naar centraal station via NDSM. 24/7. Dus ook midden in de nacht. On 2 minutes walking from the house citybus will bring you to central station in 25 minutes. 24/7!  Ten minutes biking from the house at NDSM area the ferry will take you in ten minutes to central station. We recommend you to rent bikes because it is the very best way to discover town.
access: Het hele huis en tuin... The whole house an both gardens
interaction: Of ik of een vriend van ons zal er altijd zijn om sleutels te geven, je welkom te heten en uitleg te geven. Tijdens je verblijf mag je ons altijd bellen met vragen of problemen. We zullen voor veel toeristische informatie zorgen zodat je snel wegwijs bent in de stad of omgeving.  We zullen altijd in de buurt zijn of heel soms vrienden inschakelen bij calamiteiten. Wij willen graag dat je je thuis voelt, niet alleen in ons huis maar ook in onze stad/ons land. Hopelijk vind je het goed dat onze drie lieve katten er ook zijn, wijzelf of de buren kunnen ze voeren of in overleg met jou kun jij het zelf doen. Maar als je wilt kunnen we de katten meenemen uit logeren. Schroom niet om ons te vragen voor ruimere aankomst- of vertrektijden.  Over alles valt te overleggen! Me or one of my best friends will be here to give you the keys and show you around the house. We will have lots of  maps and touristic  information for you to use and find your way. We will always be nearby and you can always c
house_rules: Wees svp behoorlijk stil na 22.00 uur. Laat het huis achter zoals je het vond alsjeblieft. In huis mag niet gerookt worden. Je mag wel een klein kampvuur maken in de achtertuin alsmede een bbq aansteken maar maak het vuur uit voor je gaat slapen svp. De hangmat alsjeblieft binnen leggen wanneer het regent. Laat het huis net zo schoon achter als je het gevonden hebt. Please be a bit quite in the evenings after 22.00.  No smoking inside. You can have a bbq or a little campfire in the backyard but please make sure it is extinguished before you go to sleep. When you use the hammock please bring it inside when it is raining.  Leave the house as clean as you found it please.
host_about:
Warmte, gezelligheid, vrienden, familie, eten, koken, natuur, fikkie stoken, tuinieren, lezen, rust, ruimte, kortom het leven is een feest dat gevierd dient te worden. 
Elmer is chefkok bij de Stadsschouwburg Amsterdam en Nynke rawfood patissier en dessinontwerpster maar  vooral moeder. 
In onze keuken zul je alles vinden voor de gezonde (rawfood) en/of ayurvedische keuken, alsmede een slowjuicer, sapcentrifuge, blender, dehydrator, 2 ovens en vele, vele (gedroogde) kruiden en oliën. Desgewenst kunnen wij maaltijden verstrekken voor de dag van aankomst, vraag gerust naar de mogelijkheden.
We hebben 4 kinderen: Pepijn van 16, Jupiter van 13, Menoega van ruim 5 en Stash van bijna 3. 
Ons fijne huis staat voor jullie open. Omdat wij dan ook lekker op reis kunnen met zijn zessen. Er wonen drie ultra lieve katten bij ons: Moos de zwarte, Vonk de rode en Vloed de grijze. Als jullie er zijn kunnen de katten uit logeren (geef dit alsjeblieft even aan voordat je komt)  maar mocht je echt allergisch zijn dan kan ik je ons huis waarschijnlijk niet aanraden.  Wij kijken er naar uit jullie te mogen ontvangen! 

Let op: In de periode 1 augustus -8 augustus 2016 verhuren wij alleen de volledige week. Dit in verband met onze eigen korte vakantie.

summary: Book a Camper, Caravan, Circus Wagon or Boat located @ the NDSM Wharf. Close to nature and just minutes away from the vibrant city center. Two free bikes are included.
space: This Romantic Circus Wagon is based next to the well-known NDSM shipyard. After a FREE 10 minute ferry-tour it only takes a 2-5 min walk to Amsterdam’s charming City-centre.  The Wagon is equipped with a heater, bed and place to sit and relax.  Also you will get 2 free bikes with your circus experience!

This Romantic Circus Wagon is based next to the well-known NDSM shipyard. After a FREE 10 minute ferry-tour it only takes a 2-5 min walk to Amsterdam’s charming City-centre.  The Wagon is equipped with a heater, bed and place to sit and relax.  Also you will get 2 free bikes with your circus experience! The Wagon is situated on a courtyard with also a Camper and a Boat. There's a big fireplace in the barn to keep you nice and warm during
neighborhood_overview: The Wagon is situated in the northern part of Amsterdam which is one of the most up-coming areas. NDSM (a former shipyard) located on the banks of the River IJ has blossomed into an enormous cultural hot spot in recent years. There are festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events.  The Wagon is 20 minutes away from the vibrant city centre, and just 10 minutes away from Twiske.  Twiske is a beautiful nature park with canals, bridges, a windmill and lakes where you can swim.
transit: Getting to the Wagon:  Take Citybus 34 (direction Buikslotermeerplein) get off at busstop Tjalkstraat. (20 min).  This is a link with the route from the busstop to the Wagon:  (website hidden) From the Wagon to the City-centre:  Hop on the (free) ferry at the NDSM-werf and set sail for the charming City Centre.  The total trip takes 14 minutes and you can bring your bike (also free). The ferry runs 24/7. There's also a (night) bus you can take (20 minutes).
access: The Wagon is situated on a courtyard with also a Camper and a Boat. At night there's a campfire where you can meet other interesting fellow travellers.  There's a big barn next to the courtyard where you can hang out, watch a movie, listen to music, have some diner. There's a kitchen and shower / toilet .  You'll also be sharing the place with two bunny's, a dog and three chickens. So for breakfast there are fresh eggs, you'll also get bred and spreads.  There's a big fireplace in the barn to keep you nice and warm during the winter! Its a cool interesting place for hippie, laid-back, budget backpackers so don’t expect a five star hotel ;)
house_rules: Hi guys, thanks for booking! We can't wait to welcome you here.  Before you arrive we want to help you out with some practical information. Check in: from 1 pm Keep us posted about your arrival time, we are waiting for you :) Check out: before 11 am Rental Please do not smoke inside your rental. Do not forget to turn off your heater if you are leaving your rental Barn The Barn is your common area with a place to relax, 2 bathrooms, 3 showers (towels are included) and 2 fully equipped kitchens. Please keep it clean and do your dishes so other guests can use it too. Bikes The bikes are for free use. Please handle them with care, and ALWAYS lock them. If you want we offer a bike insurance. For 5 euro a bike your bikes are insured against theft. If you don't want the insurance and the bikes get stolen we expect you to refund the bikes and locks (150 euro a bike and 50 for the lock). Please do not use the bikes on check out day, we need them for the new guests. Keys You'll get keys; of the

Hi my name is Maik. 

I'm a school teacher and work with autistic children. I 'm super laid-back and I love to travel and meet new people from other countries.

In my spare time I love to sail through the canals of Amsterdam, pure freedom :) 
Are you also adventurous and do you like a challenge? Do you love nature and the outdoors?

Yes?!  Hope to welcome you soon! 

Enjoy life!

neighborhood_overview: Every wednesday, friday and saturday there is a market, just a few steps away. Two supermarkets are just a few steps away. Visit the most beautiful cinema from Amsterdam: the eye-film museum, 5 minutes by bicycle, (check out the website of EYE). There are also enough nice places to have dinner or just a drink, for example on the 'NDSM-werf', 5 minutes by bicycle. We love the place called 'Pllek', they have a great terrace that looks like a beach and a great view over the IJ. You can also take a ferry from there to central station. A terrific Italian restaurant is 'Il pecorino', wood-oven baked pizzas and delicious italian food, just a few steps away. You can also visit the countryside easily by bicycle. Small pictoresque villages (nice houses, cows, a lot of green) are just 15/30 minutes away from our house. Surf (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) images for the places: Ransdorp, Durgerdam, Holysloot, Marken, Monnickendam, Volendam, etc. In our apartment you will find information how to reach
notes: The deposit is 300 euros. You don't have to pay this in advance.
transit: During the day (till 00.30) - You can take a bus every 5 minutes to our apartment. Take bus 34, bus 35, bus 391 or 394 and the second stop (called Mosplein) will take you to our apartment (only 10 minutes). The busses with the same numbers (direction Central Station) will bring you to Central station from our apartment. During the night (whole night) - You can take two night-busses every 20 minutes from Central Station (the stop is called St. Nicholaaskerk, kerk = church) to our apartment: bus 361 direction Banne Buiksloot (stop Johan van Hasseltweg) or bus 363 direction Molenwijk (stop Mosplein). If you prefer to walk, it is a 15 minutes walk from Central Station to our apartment (take the ferry Buiksloterweg). By bicycle it is only 5 minutes to the ferry (direction Buiksloterweg), which will take you to Central Station in a two minute travel over the 'IJ'. The ferry to buiksloterweg runs every 5 minutes, it is free of charge and runs 24/7. Parking is free of charge before our house!

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Noord is at the moment according to Skykenner the 7th trendiest neighborhood of the world. That is because of the festivals, the giant flee market, the new restaurants, the new film museum and all the artist who have their studios here. The most agreable thing of our neighborhood is the calmness and the green with all the flowers! There are two ferryboats who will bring you in 5 minutes to the Central Station if you get fed up with the quietness.  A very good idea is to rent a bike : that’s possible here on the dike. The dike where we live is a very picturesque road with all kinds of wooden and brick stone houses. The oldest are build in the 17th century. The dike borders on the Vliegenbos, an untamed and very quiet wood, where you also can find the tennis loans.  An in- and outdoor swimmingpool you can find at a distance of two kilometers, if you follow the dike to Buiksloot. Most people of the north of Amsterdam however go for a swim in the lakes of the national park Het Tw

We will always answer your questions directly. On those occasions we also stay in the private homes of people and we are always very satisfied. Now w're doing it ourselves!

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North is hip! Nice and quiet, yet multicultural and so close to the city center. Groceries, supermarket and cafe's just around the corner at two min. walking, hip cafe's for the 'modern minded' with great food and famous for their riverside also nearby. It's an "up-coming" neighbourhood, meaning that the barns and barracks around are filled with galleries, ateliers, and handcraft workshops. Just from a stone rock distance you find yourself at the North Boulevard, from whereon you can straw endlessly along the riverbank ... Especially at night the view on the city, with all its lights, is magic. The neighbourhood and surounding have a rich history, where you can still find the 'typical Amsterdam' people and habits of living. The famous Dutch architect Rem Koolhaas contributed to the design of this neighbourhood, and left his mark in the work of art on the square.
notes: There is the ability to park your car for free, just in front of the door or around the corner.
transit: Just 5 minutes walk to the ferry 'De Pont' that brings you - for free - in one saugh directly to the Central Station. Where, as only locals know and to mention between the lines, is sold the best Italain coffee-to-go.   The second ferry departs all non-stop night long. So don't worry, at nighttime it is very easy to reach back home by foot.
access: Besides your own two private bedrooms, you can take fully use of the kitchen and its equipment, the living room, the bathroom and toilet.  In consultation there is the possibility to make use of the bike.

summary: A nice little sailing boat very near the centre of amsterdam, There is room for three people to sleep and relax., But there is no luxury , but you can make a cup of coffee or tea, and it gives a good shelter after partying  The boat can even sail !
space: This is a very good relaxing place, for little money! The boat is situated in a little amsterdam-north harbour, 7 minutes by bike to the ferry opposite the central train station. Busses are a 2 minutes walk away.  I can even take you on a sailing trip, or give you some sailing lessons, the sailing area around amsterdam is very nice and we have a big lake nearby which has some nice green islands... This is a little 6 meter sailing boat, in which you can sleep and sit with 3 people. So you can't stand up straight or walk around in it. Bring your own sleeping bags /sheets and towels. There is also no running water but you can make a cup of tea/coffee with a little tank of water I'll provide. There's a stove for cooking. The toilet is not more then a bucket with a seat on it which you have to empty yourself in the canal. So are you ready for a camping trip in amsterdam?...

neighborhood_overview: It's a unique space (a full house with a garden in/near the city centre is kind of rare), located in a unique neighbourhood: Disteldorp was founded in 1917 to provide housing in an overcrowded city (also because of Belgian refugees). The situation in the city centre was unhealthy so they created these 'garden villages' in the North to give the poor a better place to live.  Now, Amsterdam North is rapidly turning into the hippest neighbourhood of Amsterdam, with lots of creative start ups settling here, many places to have food and drinks, shop for vintage, visit warehouse parties and the newest edition is Adam Tower (next to the spectacular EYE museum) with a brand new club, restaurant, viewpoint etc. In short: a bustling neighbourhood where there is still space to breathe and some non-conformative rough edges to enjoy. The Brooklyn of Amsterdam.
notes: I have plants and a garden that would love to be watered...
transit: 10 minute walk to the ferry which takes you straight (3 min trip) to the city centre. Alternatively you can take a short bus ride (7 min). Two bikes could be made available as well (4 min bike ride, 3 min boat ride).
access: The whole house and the garden are accessible for guests. You can smoke in the garden. I also have a Weber BBQ you can use, and two bikes that can be made available.

As you enter the living area, you will be greeted with a warm, homely feel, beautiful stained glass windows, wooden floors and authentic ceiling beams.  The spacious kitchen provides a large table for enjoying home cooked meals together, which can be prepared using the oven, grill, hob, fridge and freezer.  Patio doors lead out into the sunny garden, which backs onto a forest and makes a fantastic spot for absorbing the warm summer sunshine.  The bedroom at the most upper floor contains a double bed and a flatscreen TV.  An extra room houses a double sofa-bed. In the ettic you find 2 single beds. Be aware all the bedroom rooms have open ceilings so limited privacy! Two bathrooms add convenience, each fitted out with a toilet, washbasin and shower, with a relaxing bathtub also available. neighborhood_overview: Situated north of the IJ River, the apartment encourages you to explore authentic Dutch life unspoilt by the tourist crowds. Safe and peaceful, the surrounding area is home to two beautiful natural highlights adored by the local community, the Florapark and the Vliegenbos. The latter has existed for over 100 years as a charming city forest, highly recommended for a leisurely stroll or picnic. Several cafes and stores can be found within easy reach and the impressive EYE Film Theatre and Museum is accessible by bike in less than ten minutes. Discovering Amsterdam’s historic core, home to such famous highlights as Dam Square, the Red Light District and the Canal Belt, is simple. The nearby bus link allows access to Central Station in just twelve minutes, although a brief bike ride to the water’s edge provides an alternative method, with a series of ferries departing across the IJ free of charge on a regular basis.

transit: Easy to reach by car, public transport and bicycle. There is a free parking lot right in front of the house. For pedestrians and bicyclists, there is a ferry departing from Amsterdam Central Station that reaches the house in less than 5 minutes. The ferry is free and runs 24 hours a day. Schiphol airport is less than 20 minutes away by train which makes this a great location for travelers wanting to stay close to the city center. 5-minute with the ferry and a 10 minute walk: Central Station, Lovers boating company, Mac Bike Rental.  5- minute with the ferry and a 10-minute walk: Dam square, Anne Frank House, Beurs van Berlage, Bijenkorf Department store, Mademe Tussaud, The Red light district

host_about:
Hello, I'm Emma, nearly in my thirties and love to explore the world! 
I've been to South-America, Asia and many European cities, my wishlist is only expanding.. Although I love to travel and get to know many different cultures, I still have a passion for my hometown Amsterdam that I would really love to share with you! Not only during my travels but also when I'm in Amsterdam I'm always haunting on local hotspots such as museums, restaurants, exhibitions and musically orientated places and events suchs as concerts, festivals and clubs. Because I was born and raised in Amsterdam I can recommend you all kinds of places that will make your trip unforgetable!

name: Quiet Studioapartment, Free Parking
space: Welcome to Amsterdam!  This cozy studio apartment is situated in a quiet neighborhood, very close to one of Amsterdams most picturesque areas. Parking is FREE! You can reach the center of the city within 10 minutes by bus, which stops in front of the building. Or you can rent a bike nearby and cycle to the free 24h ferry.   The apartment is very comfortable and has everything for your convenience such as a modern kitchen with a dishwasher, cable-television, free Wifi, a stereo set compatible with your smart phone, washing-machine, refrigerator with freezing compartment and a lovely balcony on the south side. Within walking distance you will find a great number of shops, and some good restaurants.

name: Spacious apartment, stunning views
summary: Modern apartment in the most up-and-coming neighbourhood of Amsterdam, a stone's throw from Central Station. Spacious, light, cosy and with an unbelievable roof terrace where you can enjoy views of the sunset over Amsterdam.
space: Welcome to our stunning and light home on the 5th floor of a new apartment building, a stone's throw away from Amsterdam Central Station. The apartment has a spacious open-plan living area and kitchen, with huge windows overlooking the 'IJ': the water separating the North from the centre of Amsterdam. You can sit for hours just watching the boats sail past! From the living room, you can access the immense roof terrace (about 110m2) which enjoys the same amazing view of the Amsterdam skyline, and where we grow our own fruit, flowers and vegetables.  There is a large bathroom with separate shower and bath, two sinks and a toilet, and a separate toilet off the hall, where there is a desk and computer. The main bedroom has a double bed. Bedroom  2 (children's room) has a single bed and lots of toys. It looks out at the A'DAM tower, film museum and Central Station. Bedroom 3  is at the back and has a double sleeper plus extra box-spring mattress, and can acccomodate three people if necessar

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in a peaceful green neighbourhood on the banks of the Ij in Amsterdam Noord - dubbed the most up-and-coming part of the city. In front of the house, a park is being planned, but 50 metres down the street is a park running along the water: perfect for a picnic, people-watching or gazing at the water. The EYE film museum is practically on our doorstep and prominent in our view (it's the white space-ship looking building in the photos). Further towards the ferry is the 'Tolhuistuin', which is an art space, concert hall cafe and restaurant all rolled into one. By early 2016, the A'dam tower should be opening, boasting a revolving restaurant at the top. The NDSM wharf is close by, with its industrial charm, creative industry and plenty of good cafes and restaurants. Closer to home is a market 3 times a week, shops and cafes, and a number of playgrounds.
notes: This is a  calm residential building. The apartment is not suitable for groups of party-goers. Also we have a hamster.
transit: The ferry to Central station is a 4 minute walk away, and runs continuously 24 hours a day, taking only 3 minutes to get to the other side. There, you find yourself in the city centre with its canals, shopping, cafes, restaurants and markets. It is also the hub for all bus, train and metro connections to areas further afield or the rest of the country. Our home is also a great base for exploring the characteristic countryside to the north of amsterdam, with its green fields, waterscapes, windmills and historic towns: Zaanse Schans, Monnickendam, Marken, etc. You can take a bicycle or travel there by car - we are well-connected to the highway around Amsterdam.
access: Guests have exclusive access to the entire apartment, as well as the roof terrace around the apartment (110m2).
interaction: If you are staying at our place, this means that we are probably on holidays ourselves. In case you have issues or questions, you can reach me by cell-phone. Also, my parents live in the same building, and can usually resolve any issues you may have right away.
house_rules: - This is our home. You are welcome to use our stuff, but please treat it with care.  - We live in a quiet residential apartment block, and we care about our relations with the neighbours. Please respect them and  keep the noise down.  - No parties - No outside visitors allowed - No smoking inside. Do not leave cigarette butts on the roof terrace or in the plants (we have no ashtrays) - Please take off your shoes inside the house, especially high heels
host_about:
Hi, my name is Jessica. I live in Amsterdam with my two daughters. We love travelling! As I do a lot of it for work (I'm an advisor in a philanthropic institution), when I go away I like to relax and stay away from hotels. AirBnB is perfect for that, and for meeting interesting people in new places. 
Similarly, I like to open my place with visitors to Amsterdam, sharing the experience of living in this wonderful city which is so easy to explore from here - on foot, bicycle or through public transport.

neighborhood_overview: Pay a visit to Amsterdam with its highlights like the Rijksmuseum, Van Goghmuseum, the typical Amsterdam canals, Bloemenmarkt (Flower market) and the Jordaan. Amsterdam has also a lot of nice terraces and a rich nightlife. Besides, the campsite is located close to the rustic `Waterland` area with pastures and cities like Edam, Marken and Volendam.
notes: If you like to cook a meal please go to Fied 4 and use the open kitchen of the campsite. It is free to use.
transit: Vliegenbos is only a 15 minutes walk (or 5 minute bike-ride) away from the free ferryboat that brings you to the center of Amsterdam (5 minutes) You can also walk 100 meters to the bus stop near the campsite.

We are always willing to help you at our reception desk. Restaurant with terrace:  You are welcome at our terrace from 8.00 hrs on, and until 22.00 hrs you can order anything you like from our menu. Start your day good with a nice breakfast, go for a delicious lunch with a freshly prepared sandwich and dine with a fish or meat platter. Or if you prefer, just a pizza of course! Would you rather take your meal with you? No problem, we can pack it for take-away. Kitchen opening hours:8.00 - 22.00 hrs restaurant opening hours: 8.00 - 23.00 hrs Camping shop: Our bakkery offers: rolls, (chocolate) croissants, sweet treats like waffles and much more delicious stuff. interaction: I won't be at the camping. The reception desk of the camping takes over the check-in and the checkout. You can always contact me on the airbnb app for questions.

At departure day, check-out is before 11.00 hrs. To secure a pleasant stay for everyone there is no loud music allowed. Cars need to be parked at the place the campsite manager points out. We have separate sanitary installations for men and women, which is made clear explicitly. Don't throw garbage on the ground, but in the bins. We expect the campsite to be quiet between 23.00 hrs and 8.00 hrs to ensure our guests can rest well. Access to the campsite is restricted to registered and paying visitors of the campsite. It is only allowed to make a fire / barbecue in consultation with the manager. If necessary, the manager is allowed to deny access or to remove people from the campsite. Campsite Vliegenbos is not responsible for fire, theft or damage caused by third parties. For more information, please ask our manager.

host_about:
Hallo, I am Nienke and Michel is my husband. We love to travel the world but with our apartment we love the world to come to us too. At our voyages we go diving, or walk through the city or landscape. We have an old farm-house in Tsjechië where we go swim in the summer and barbecue in our garden or ice-play in winter and read in front of our fire-place. We have a little sail-boat in Horn, North Holland. We truly love dining, which was great on Madagascar, and which we like te make ourselves in Slavetin, Tsjechië, where we have time.
And of course we love Amsterdam where we combine our passions of culture and cookery

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Noord is booming. There is the new film museum EYE and loads of nice restaurants , bars and shops. We are happy to give you tips. (turkish) supermarket and bakery are around the corner, a Dutch Albert Heijn is a 5 min walk away. Parking is free of charge before our house!
notes: The house is co-owned by two house panthers which almost have no needs (dry food twice a day, a clean toilet and an occasional petting session) and are very affectionate in return. you can rent bikes in Amsterdam Noord at  At Velox, beside the Pont restaurant, Buiksloterweg 5A, 1031 CC Amsterdam (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN), (URL HIDDEN)
transit: During the day (till 00.30): From Amsterdam Cental Station: Bus 34, 35, 391, 394 stop: Mosplein 5 minutes bus ride 2 minutes walk from the apartment to the bus stop  During the night (whole night) - You can take two night-busses every 20 minutes from Central Station (the stop is called St. Nicholaaskerk, kerk = church) to our apartment: bus 361 direction Banne Buiksloot (stop Johan van Hasseltweg) or bus 363 direction Molenwijk (stop Mosplein). If you prefer to walk, it is a 15 minutes walk from Central Station to our apartment (take the ferry Buiksloterweg). By bicycle it is only 5 minutes to the ferry (direction Buiksloterweg), which will take you to Central Station in a two minute travel over the 'IJ'. The ferry to buiksloterweg runs every 5 minutes, it is free of charge and runs 24/7.

There is one big light flooded living room and an open kitchen on the first floor which is overlooking the gardens. As well there is a big balcony and an marvelous 18 qm2 roof terrace (third floor with fixed stairs).
interaction: We are both professionally active in the creative world of Amsterdam (graphic design, literature and photography) and we are happy to provide you with our personal insider tips on where to go, eat, look and hang in the centre of Amsterdam as well as in the up and coming neighborhood of Amsterdam-Noord.
