summary: The flat is located in a new area across from the central station, on the IJ, the main water in Amsterdam. It is a modern building, designed by architects, with floor heating and double glazing. The interior is a mixture between modern and antique.
space: My flat is very close to the central station and centre of Amsterdam, on the waterfront of the main water 'Het IJ'. From the balcony you have a view of the water with big boats sailing through. It is a new flat in a area with a few new luxury apartment blocks and you reach there by a short ferry-ride (2 minutes from the central station, the ferry is free and runs al day and night every few minutes). This is a trendy upcoming neighborhood with the new film institute (open air cinema and 4 indoor screens with an excellent choice of classic and new film), the new Pop-temple Tolhuis, with a waterfront beach-like terrace. There is a museum, trendy restaurants and other initiatives. It is the area where the hipsters go these days, because it is very central, yet green and spacious. neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is trendy and upcoming. There are many new buildings, since it is an area that has been developed the last 10 years. Right behind the neighborhood is older and some buildings are monumental with new restaurants due to the new developments. The neighborhood is across from the central station, opposite the center. Hence, it has a large waterfront with big boats, sailing ships and cruise ships as well as smaller boats.  It is very close to the center, but a bit quieter and more spacious, because it is newer. As an area across the water from the centere, there is music, cafes, restaurants, parks, festivals, etc., etc.
notes: SOmetimes I change furniture. I try not to change the character of the flat, but like to keep things clean and new. If you want the flat exactly to look as in the pictures, please let me know to avoid miscommunication. Also, plants come and go by the season, so do not pin me down on a plant dying or loosing leaves. This is nature.
transit: The ferry from the central station runs 24/7 and a bike rental is just when you get off the ferry. From the ferry it is a 5-10 minutes walk. There is a bike rental right when you get off the ferry and the surroundings in this part of town are very green and rural.

And, for the same reason, no smoking indoors please!

name: Oasis in heart of City-free parking
summary: If you are looking for an oasis in the heart of the city with a lovely garden in a quiet area of Amsterdam at walking distance from Central Station, then this is the place for you!  And guess what? You can park for free!
space: Wake up to the sound of birds and the occasional cruise ship's horn in the distance and enjoy the evening peace and quiet after a day or evening of exploring this amazing city.  This ground floor property offers a lounge, a fully equipped kitchen, a recently (2014) refurbished bathroom, a bedroom and a garden. The lounge has 2 chairs and a very comfortable sofa, a dinner table with 4 chairs and a TV. The bedroom (with view of the garden) has a double bed and a dressing table. There is also a baby cod available for young children. The bathroom contains a shower, sink and toilet. There is wifi and heating in every room. Parking is free! Parking fees in Amsterdam are generally very high, but near the apartment you can park for free.

neighborhood_overview: Things to do closeby 'This side of the water' was recently ranked no. 7 of the 20 most hipster neighbourhoods in the world. Here is your chance to find out why! At walking distance you will find some very nice restaurants along the waterside and soon a revolving restaurant on the rooftop of the former Shell tower. After crossing a small 19th century lock you will pass the Tolhuis Park. During the summer this is a great place for intimate live music performances. Walk a little further and along he river IJ the architecturally striking EYE Film Institute catches your eye with four cinemas, a restaurant and a bar and amazing sunset views. The NDSM shipyard is a former shipyard located on the banks of the River IJ. It has become a booming industrial and cultural creative hotspot in recent years. The shipyard hosts festivals, performances, exhibitions and a wide range of other events. It is also home to a huge range of artists, craftspeople and theatre producers. Explore and then relax at o
notes: In short: - FREE PARKING - smart, chic apartment with quiet, lush green garden - TV, free wifi, heating in the entire apartment - lounge, refurbished bathroom with shower, sink and toilet, fully equiped kitchen - baby cod available for young children - supermarket around the corner - 10 minutes from Central Station - all public transport available from CS: bus, tram, metro and train In the apartment you will find a welcoming folder listing things to do and off the beaten track tips for special and undiscovered places. If you have any other questions then please feel free to contact me. I look forward to welcoming you!
transit: By train: from Amsterdam Central Station take the free ferry which leaves from the back (Northern) exit) of the station and after an 8 minutes walk you'll arrive at the apartment. By plane: take a train to Amsterdam Central Station (20 min) and then follow the directions above. By car: set your GPS for Leeuwerikstraat. Upon arrival you can park your car (for free!) in front.
access: You have full access to the apartment and the garden.
interaction: You will have the apartment entirely to yourself. If you have any questions, then please feel free to ask them, I will be happy to help.
house_rules: Upon arrival you will be given the key to your home away from home and your 'Welcome to Amsterdam' package with extensive information on off the beaten track places and any practical information that you may need during your stay. The apartment is non-smoking but you are very welcome to enjoy the garden and light up there! I will take a copy of your passport and then it is time for you to fully enjoy your stay!
host_about:
Having travelled extensively and enjoyed other people's hospitality, I like the idea of extending that same level of hospitality to other people. I work for a career coaching company, where we help people discover their unique talents and then to define in what position they can thrive by using these talents. 

In my free time I take acting classes, I go outdoors (swimming, hiking) and I love to travel. I frequently have friends visiting from abroad and I enjoy taking them around to undiscovered places in Amsterdam and beyond.

I look forward to welcoming you and hope that you enjoy your stay in this amazing city to the fullest!

access: Guests have access to the kitchen, the guest room, the balcony, bathroom, and shower.

house_rules: Here are some notes that I send to all of my guests before they arrive: *Please make sure you ring at the right bell and not at one of my neighbors when you first arrive. *Do keep in mind and respect the fact that this is not a hotel in the citycenter but I welcome you into my home in a quiet and save neighborhood.  The building itself is made of stone and wood. Too much noise will spoil the fun for my neighbors, for me, for you and for other guests who are yet to come after you. *It's my livingroom I rent as a private room. Not an entire appartment. And yes, I too will be in the house but mostly upstairs in my bedroom. We share kitchen, toilet and bathroom. *TURN OFF LIGHTS (and close doors) when you're done in the toilet, kitchen or the shower.  Also when you go out, turn off the lights in the rented room. *You can get in the citycenter in 15-20 minutes by foot + ferry, or by public transport. The ferry is free of charge (24 hours a day) and the bus costs €2,90 per person for a ticke
host_about:
Artistical free spirit, been living in Amsterdam for more than 40yrs. 
Just finished one business in childrenclothing. Looking out for new ideas to do. In the meanwhile I wonna meet people from all over the world. 
A friend telling me about Airbnb inspired me to also become a host. 

Things I can't do without for instance are my daughter, music, a dailly laughter or smile, my health and socks....
I've traveled to a few places like England. France, Germany  several times, Los Angeles once and my favorite trip was to Jamaica. That was really adventurous cause I went on a 3 weeks journey but only booked a bungalow for 3 days and I had faith that I would meet people who would took me in and so happened. 
My favorite book is Segou, written by Marisa Condee. To me that was not just a story but a script to a movie. A story that pulled me in everytime I would start to read. Like I was right in the middle of what I was reading. 
My Favorite movie is a classic one, from the 1960's and it's called Imitations of live. A story about mental conditions and positions as result of colorlines and racism. 
HipHop, R&B (especiallyl golden oldies) Soul and Reggae are my favorite kinds of music. But actually I don't mind listening to lots of kinds of music.
When it comes to food, I must say I'm from the caribean (Suriname) so I like caribean food a lot. It's sort of a variety of african, native american, Indian, indonesian, chinese, dutch dishes and mixtures of it. 
But over here in Amsterdam you get to meet with a lot of food of other cultures, fot instance japanese, turkish and italian
 
I actually live in walkingdistance from Amsterdam Central Station/Center. There are a few bars(pubs), restaurants and supermarkets. 
3 days a week there's a market around the corner. Also let me mention, there are a few coffeeshops in the erea for those who like to smoke marihuana. So there's no need to go all the way to town for that. 
The EYE-Museum is also in the neighborhood. Around that area is enough action, daytime as well as at night.

I just registered myself as host so I'm about to get my first experience. I'm used to having friends and family over for weekends or sometimes even during weekdays. I always try to make sure my place is somewhere people like to come over and feel welcome to stay. Make them feel at home or at least, make them feel save while they're away from home. 

I live in a nice little quiet street where you can hear people talking when they pass in the evening or at night. 
It's on the first floor so there's not much stairs to cllimb. Only for the shower wich is on the second floor. I'm not used to playing loud music. That kind of developed because I have two families with young children on opposite sides of me. 

My lifes motto is "Live and let live". The universe has enough to provide for everyone.

Enjoy the tranquility, passing ships and the city skyline. In less than two minutes you can take the free ferry (24/7, every 5 minutes) in the center of Amsterdam! Walk straight to the Jordan with cozy cafes, restaurants, shops and special markets, the Nieuwmarkt or stroll along the famous Amsterdam canals. Or take the tram that takes you within five stops to all major museums like Van Gogh Museum, Stedelijk Museum, Rijksmuseum, Anne Frank house, the Hermitage etc.  But from the houseboat you can walk starting at the 19th century lock to the architecturally striking Eye Film Institute with four cinema's, bar and restaurant, the Tolhuispark with music programming during Summertime and soon a hotel with revolving restaurant transformed as former Shell Tower.  The houseboat is spacious (100m2) and light and has a modern ba
host_about:
Hi, I am Reinhart, welcome to my profile: I have been living in Amsterdam for many years now. I work in the (international) creative industry. I like to travel, do city trips but also like to visit remote destinations. Love to be on the water, visit museums, go to theaters, enjoy live music, festivals, nice bar's and to meet nice people.
I enjoy to open my house to anyone that likes to have a truly local Amsterdam experience (on the water). We might meet soon?

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Noord is een heerlijke uitvalsbasis na een dagje in het drukke Centrum. De woonboot ligt op de mooiste locatie van Amsterdam, direct naast het Vliegenbos in de oude historische haven van Nieuwendam. Het alom bekende Cafe ' het sluisje ' ligt direct tegenover de woonboot dus met een bootje naar toe te roeien of te lopen via Nieuwendammerdijk. Het centrum van Amsterdam is zowel met de bus als met de fiets in 10 a' 15 minuten te bereiken. Ook het NDSM terrein in Amsterdam Noord is een aanrader. De Zaanse Schans en Volendam met het openbaar vervoer of met de auto in ca. 30 minuten. Even geen zin in om de stad in te gaan. Wij kunnen u vele zeer goede restaurants in de nabijheid van uw verblijf aanbevelen.
notes: Wij kunnen bijna al uw wensen verzorgen, denk bijvoorbeeld aan, met een boot opgehaald worden op het centraal station welke u vervolgens naar uw verblijf brengt, of de boot brengt u vanaf uw verblijf naar het centrum van Amsterdam. Ook een rondvaart behoort tot de mogelijkheden. Een roeiboot tijdens uw verblijf. Zwemvesten zijn beschikbaar. Fietsverhuur, zelfs een bakfiets of kinderstoeltje is mogelijk.
transit: De bushalte vanwaar de meeste bussen naar het Centraal Station (centrum) gaan is op 5 minuten loopafstand. Met de fiets bent u in 10 minuten bij de veerpont die u naar het Centrum brengt. taxi word desgewenst voor u verzorgt.
access: de hele ruimte staat tot uw beschikking

house_rules: Huisdieren zijn toegestaan na overleg.  Er mag niet gerookt worden op de boot.

name: Large luxury Studio FREE parking
summary: Large, sunny apartment with luxury bathroom and sauna. Quiet location. Only 6 mins from the city center by bus (3 stops) or 7 minutes by bike to the FREE ferry behind the Central Station. FREE parking in front. Beautiful garden and sunny terrace.
space: In very popular Amsterdam North on one of Amsterdam's ancient 17th century sea dikes: Buiksloterdijk, is located our  totally renovated studio apartment of 45m2 . It is a oasis of peace and yet only 6 minutes by bus to the Central Station. Only three stops! Although you are in Amsterdam North, you are in fact much closer to the city center than a lot of other places in Amsterdam. You are just behind the Central Station across the river IJ. Free ferries run day and night every 5/10 minutes. They bring you across in 2 minutes. The Buiksloterdijk used to be the place where the Dutch East India Company captains retired. The 17th century houses where called 'the captains heaven'. The water of the IJ-river that runs behind the Central Station came up right to the house. Since 1870 it is a polder.  If you want to go to the city by bike, this is also very easy and quick. In fact we recommend renting bikes as this is the best way of transport in Amsterdam.  Right in front of our house is a bicy

neighborhood_overview: The Buiksloterdijk used to be the place where the Dutch East India Company captains retired. The 17th century houses where called 'the captains heaven'. The water of the IJ-river that runs behind the Central Station came up right to the house. Since 1870 it is a polder.  Amsterdam North is the starting point of numerous bicycle and walking routes through rural North Holland. These routes go right past our house.  Just a few kilometers away, along the North Holland Canal, you get to the Ilperveld, a bird sanctuary and nature park. It is possible to rent so called 'whisper boats' (electric engine) and tour this very special area. A very good idea if you feel like a pick-nick or a swim in summer. An 18 hole golf course is just around the corner. Amsterdam North is the where the artist live in Amsterdam. The brand new Eye film museum with the best terrace of Amsterdam is located here. MTV resides here, so is Universal. There are many specialty restaurants, such as the IJkantine, Café Moder
notes: The use of the sauna is optional.  For a 2 hour period we charge €15.
transit: The bus stop to the center of town Dam Square and Central Station, Canal District is at 350m. Busses 34 and 35 run every 5 minutes. The trip takes 6 minutes, just 3 stops.  You can also walk to the FREE ferry behind Centrak Station, 25 minutes. Or go thre by bike, 7 minutes.
access: The studio apartment consists of a living/sleeping area, a separate kitchenette with induction cooker, fridge, microwave and nespresso coffee machine.  There is a separate toilet and a luxury bath room with shower and sauna. The apartment has floor heating, large windows overlooking the garden and a double bed of 1,80m x 2,00m. There is a sofa and a dining table for 2. You are very private with your own entrance through the gate at the side of the house.
interaction: We have been living in this house for more than 20 years. We are happy to give you any tips or help you might need. But also we let you have your privacy. We travelled the world extensively, lived in Australia for 6 years and know why good accommodation and feeling at home is important.
house_rules: The apartment is non-smoking. Smoking is allowed on the terrace and in the garden. Pets are not allowed. No noise outside please after 10pm as a courtesy to our neighbours.
host_about: I am a film director, mainly produce documentaries, my wife Ellen is a school teacher.
street: Buiksloterdijk, Amsterdam, North Holland 1034 ZD, Netherlands

name: Landelijk in de stad (free parking)
space: Eengezinswoning met tuin met uitzicht op de oude dijk. De woning beschikt over een moderne woonkamer met ruim uitgeruste keuken (voorzien van oa afwasmachine, oven/magnetron, koel/vriescombinatie, wasmachine en wasdroger), toilet. Op de bovenverdieping bevindt zich de badkamer met wastafel en douche, 1 ruime slaapkamer met 2-persoonsbed (160x200) en nog een slaapkamer met een 2-persoons hoogslaper (140x200). Het huis ligt op een kleine 10 minuten fietsen van de pont naar het CS Amsterdam. Een rechtstreekse busverbinding naar het CS is een paar minuutjes lopen.  In de buurt zijn 2 winkelcentra. Naast de pont naar het CS is het nieuwe filmmuseum 'Eye', leuk om naar de film te gaan en ook het restaurant met groot terras is een aangename plek om te vertoeven.  Even een dagje geen zin om de stad in te gaan? Fiets lekker de stad uit naar het nabijgelegen natuurgebied 'Twiske', hier kun je oa lekker zwemmen. Ook richting Durgerdam, Marken en Volendam is een leuke fietstocht. Er wonen 2 katten

First level has the entree, a toilet and a well equipped kitchen with fridge, microwave/hot-air oven and a gas stove with six burners. Next to the kitchen is the dining area with eight seats. In the dining area the sliding French doors give access to the garden, situated next to a small canal. There is good garden furniture and a parasol. Bicycles are easy to rent at Central Station, only 5 minutes by bus away. The second level has de living room. The flatscreen tv measures 0.80 m and also a DVD player is there to use. neighborhood_overview: This area has the best of both worlds: it is quiet, there is room to play, yet it is extreme close to the city center and the upcoming buzz of Amsterdam Noord. Previously this area was a bit of a wasteland, now the disused warehouses host creative start-ups, festivals, restaurants and, once a month, mega flea market. We name: The Eye Film Museum (10 minutes by bicycle), trendy restaurants like Pllek, Noorderlicht, de IJkantine and Hotel de Goudfazant and little cosy and affordable places like De Soepboer, Thai restaurant Pasoek and Italian restaurant San Remo.  Up north only 5 kilometers far away you will find yourself in the typical Dutch countryside called Waterland with beautiful authentic villages like Monnickendam, Broek in Waterland, Marken and Volendam. Open air museum de Zaanse Schans is only 10 kilometers away. It shows the way of living in the Netherlands during the last centuries in authentic buildings and windmills. Several  Specific informations you will find in the folder
notes: Needless to say you'll be careful with the fireplace!
transit: On foot to the next busstop: less than 5 minutes. Bus to Amsterdam Central Station: 3 stops, 8 minutes. Walking distance to Eye Film Museum 20 minutes. Walking distance to (free) ferry crossing the river IJ to Central Station: 25 minutes. Cycling to the city Centre: 10 minutes.

interaction: When you need help or advice we are available.

name: Modern @ old shipyard "Het Dok"
summary: Find yourself within the very heart of Sail Amsterdam 2015 at this excellent riverside spot! Boat parade just in front of the door.  Bright and spacious apartment (73m) with three creatively decorated rooms and a balcony. Free parking availabilities and a 10 min walk to CS. The romantic free ferry around the corner takes you every 15 min right to the city center. Enjoy how the sun goes down-or up, or get amazed by the heavy sea-going ships at river 't IJ.
space: Very centrally located, and yet so peaceful and spatious! For its location, atmosphere, and comfort an ideal home stay in a apartment for a couple, for expats, or for your short term business-stay. One private bedroom in a 73 square meters apartment that you share with me only (check if the cat is not on loge). Additionally there is a huge shared bright light living room with view on the river, a spacious kitchen, with a small balcony on the Southeast. From the hallway, where you can hang up your coats, you have entrance to the two bedrooms, the bathroom and separate toilet.  Your private bedroom is, due to recent redecoration, not yet to be seen on the pictures (but trust me, it is very guest-friendly).  The bedroom has 11m with large windows with view on the square. A comfortable very soft 2person bed is awaiting you.

neighborhood_overview: Nice and quiet, yet multicultural and so close to the city center. Groceries, supermarket and cafe's around the corner, likewise some great bars with terrific food and riverside view. ..  This neighbourhood in Amsterdam North is rapidly transforming, dubbed by New York Times as the "up-coming" hood, resulting in trendy bars, art & music scene to be found around the corner, and the barns and barracks around are filled with galleries, ateliers, and handcraft workshops. Just from a stone rock distance you find yourself at the North Boulevard, from whereon you can straw endlessly along the riverbank ... Especially at night the view on the city, with all its lights, is magic. The neighbourhood and surounding have a rich history, where you can still find the 'typical Amsterdam' people and habits of living. The famous Dutch architect Rem Koolhaas contributed to the design of this neighbourhood, and left his mark in the work of art on the square.
notes: There is the ability to park your car unlimited for free, just around the corner. In front of the door you can park for 2,5 hours Please do note that for a month rental or longer, extra costs are charged for two persons.
transit: Only 5 minutes walk to the ferry 'De Pont' that brings you for free to the Central Station. Besides, the Italian lady from the tiny shop is said to have the best coffee-to-go and homemade sandwiches in the city. Also at nighttime it is very easy to reach back home by foot, the ferry goes all night long.

host_about:
im Jerome, 44 years young and am a dj / producer for 31 years and have played on many big festivals and clubs around the world, and have released over 80 releases under my own name on many labels worldwide between 1997 and working with music is a passion for me since the age of 13.
Also run a world famous record label named "Outland Records" where i release underground dance music since 1993 and had some big hits released on my label with tracks from very know artist, nothing commercial, mostly underground en puristic music.

Next to that run my store "Outland Designer toy Store" now for 11 years.
A unique shop in the Netherland Where i sell a rare form of art called,  Designer toys together with other art collectibles / Ltd. editions, Art Books and more rare products that you cant find anywhere. 

The shop is located on one of the oldest streets in Amsterdam on the Zeedijk, als an awesome street for other special curiousity shops and great restaurants area in the amsterdam centre and run it by myself 6 days a week, often 7 days and am not home much most part of the day.

Im a very clean & tidy and that reflects in the apartment. 

See you soon in Amsterdam for a welcome in my cosy apartment! I would like to meet kind, friendly and unselfish people from all over the world.

Kind regards,
Jerome

neighborhood_overview: Between city and grassland the house is located on the beautiful Nieuwendammerdijk with idyllic dike houses, next to the Vliegenbos, the oldest city forest of Amsterdam.  The neighbourhood is quiet and charming and very near to the centre. The district Amsterdam-North is originally a neighborhood with lots of (port) industry that develops in recent years into a hip breeding with many creative and quirky initiatives. At the NDSM-warf district is always plenty to do, festivals, concerts, raves, a huge flea market. You can make bike trips through Dutch polders (reclaimed land), around old fishing villages like Durgerdam and Marken.  Go see a movie at the beautiful EYE filminstitute, have lunch or dinner at one of the quirky relaxed places like Pllek, the Ceuvel, the Goudfazant, Cafe Modern and Noorderlicht.
notes: There is free WiFi.  Mostly organic basics for your breakfast like coffee, tea, crackers, muesli, honey, jams etc are in the apartment ready for you. If you have any special requirements please let me know. There is a chair to the table and crib for small children.
transit: Bus 32 and 33 takes you in 5 minutes to the Centre.  It is 10 mins cycle to the free ferry that brings you in 2 mins to the other side of the IJ river, the centre. Bikes you can easily hire, if you let me know i reserve them or you. The car you can leave in the street. Parking is free, day and night.
access: Via the main entrance you enter the hallway. Behind one of the doors the stairs lead you to the fully self-contained apartment.  If you need to do some laundry, nearby is a professional laundry service.  You can also use the laundry of the house which costs a small fee.
interaction: We live on the ground floor & basement. When we are present we welcome you and are always available for tips and information. We are are willing to provide you extra service where needed to make the most of your stay in Amsterdam.
house_rules: I expect my guests to be social civilized and respectful of environment and accommodation. Unfortunately, no pets allowed in the apartment. Smoking is possible outside at the balcony - no weed please. You are not allowed to invite people to sleep over. No parties.
host_about: My house, organic lifestyle, sustainability, (healthy) cooking, design, documentaries, photos, (vegetable) garden, self-development, traveling are things that keep me busy. As a graphic designer I make house styles, logos, brochures, websites. Together with my boyfriend Arie, three dogs and a cat I live in this house we have furnished upstairs to welcome guests. I love it when I can let people enjoy this special place. Feel welcome.

neighborhood_overview: The house is located on a charming shopping plaza in Amsterdam North. On this plaza are some activities and a wide range of miscellaneous stores.  Restaurants, Fast food, Turkish Donor kabab, fishmongers are examples of the local culinary businesses.  But also a Computer shop, bike shop (selling/no renting), audio / video shop, tobacconist, hairdressers and clothing- and shoe stores.
notes: You can use everything that is in the house with care. Only if you want to use the washing machine, you have to bring the powder and conditioner yourself. Please also note that the toilet is small because of the construction of the house. Please notice that NO SHOWER TOWELS are included. If you need shower towels, you can rent them when you check-in.  Reservation is needed, so please notice at booking if you need or not.
transit: If you come by car, you can park for free on the big parking lot or in front of the house.  If you come by public transport, there is a bus stop 50 meters away which takes you in 12 minutes to Amsterdam Central.  From the airport you can take the train to Amsterdam Central Station and then by bus to the house.  The busplatform is on the backside of the trainstation. just follow the signs inside the trainstation. Bus 32 is on platform J, and it will pass almost every 10-15 minutes. Take care of buying your tickets in advance, the public transport tickets are available for 1 hour and 1 day inside the bus. For more days you need to buy at the central station. But also you can always take a taxi, but is more expensive.
access: You will have full access to the entire house.  2 sets of keys are given at checkin.

house_rules: The house is a non smoking accommodation. Unfortunately, pets are not allowed. You agree that you will use the house and the furniture like you should use your own. We also ask you to respect the neighborhood and the neighbors. Meaning no hard noise in the evening. If there are any complains, the owner will contact you. Since the stores are open at normal weekdays, we ask you to park across the street. Loading/unloading is allowed in front of the house. The host at the location can give you more information about this. Any damage should be report to the host immediately. Atleast before leaving the house. Beautiful country nearby! There's great views of the wide canal, the forest opposite and, ofcourse, the garden. It is very quiet. The new filmmuseum EYE is near,  Waterland, with great authentic villages is just around the corner. It's a 5 minute walk to the 17th century dike and one of the oldest pubs in Amsterdam.  Nearby is bus 32, 15 minutes to the Central Station. There are two sturdy citybikes available for free. The country beyond: WATERLAND is very prety and has many byciclepaths. The weekend of the 10th of april you can come friday morning and stay untill sunday 5pm. Free bycicles available.

notes: Eco, environmentally and animal friendly house, vegetarians and yogini's are preferred. Dogs and cats are allowed, if you know they respect furniture.

There is also free parking space in my street, usually there is a spot free right in front.

host_about: Having travelled a lot, from New Orléans and Cuba to South Africa and back, my house reflects an ecclectic style that's all about feeling good. Being surrounded by green is important to me, which is why living in Noord is so great, the 10 min bike ride to the free ferry takes you along the park and the waterside, lovely!

name: Cosy houseboat in artistic centre!
summary: You have often wondered what it would be like to live aboard of a cosy authentic Dutch Houseboat? Please come and spend a night or two. All the comforts and let nature rock you to sleep, very rare and special just behind the NDSM wharf, the hotspot of Amsterdam!
space: Situated in the middle of the hotspot area of Amsterdam, the NDSM-warf, this 100 years old authentic houseboat helps you to be in the middle of what Amsterdam also has to offer: small beaches, authentic restaurants, artistic area with studio's and galleries, old shipyard, 2nd hand markets, festivals, filmuseums and best view over the city! Lots of things you didnt expected, away from the touristic crowd and still less then 25 minutes walk from the city centre.  The harbour is in the middle of an historcal maritime area, with typical Dutch architecture as warehouses, wooden bridges and old houseboats. Also surounded by the nature with lots of green and hidden small parks (famous and artistic people live here, to be free and still very close to the city centre).

Also surounded by the nature with lots of green and hidden small parks (famous and artistic people live here, to be free and stil
neighborhood_overview: Very nice neighbours and a cafe as very good restaurant to eat your breakfast in the morningsun next to the boat.
notes: The houseboat is perfect for people under 1.78m high, the ceiling won't bother you. If you are longer it will be difficult to stand up straight.  Please be aware that during the summer the boat stays at an other romantic area in the North of Amsterdam then in the winter months, as spring. In this period the boat is situated in the historical city centre of Amsterdam. Both area's are famous for their typical Dutch architecture, cosy and romantic surrounding and easy going ambiance.
transit: You are in 24 minutes at the houseboat from the Central Station with a free ferry (take at the back of the central station). You can also rent a bike at the central station or just across the waters at the Tolhuistuin. With the bike its only 10 minutes away. Everything is in walking/biking/ferrying distance.
access: A typical Dutch boat where only 5 of exist in the whole world! Inside you have a marvelous view over the canals and everything you need to have a cosy weekend or evening. Even provided with an computer-controlled wood stove, hot and cold running water, a warm shower and toilet.
interaction: If you have any question, dont hesitate to ask. I'll be around if you need anything, love to give you tips about recent art shows and special bars or markets. Dont forget to eat the famous apple-pie around the corner before you leave at cafe Papeneiland.
house_rules: As I treat the boat and the neighbours myself, with care and respect.  Please beware my boat is a non-smoking-area. But on the deck there is much space off course.
host_about:
Hey there,

I am a visual artist and next to my work I like to travel the world, preferably with my boyfriend and good friends.

I lented for 5-years my old house with lots of fun through airbnb and bought recently my own boat, so I have chosen to go with a new profile. 

You are very welcome on my lovely boat at very special historic and cultural areas of Amsterdam:

- in the winter we lay down in a cosy harbor in the middle of the historcal maritime area, with typical Dutch architecture as warehouses, wooden bridges and old houseboats. A true pearl in the city centre of Amsterdam!

- in the summer we lay down in a small romantic harbor in the North of Amsterdam, perfect to swim and walk at the green fields near the IJ-waters. 

Love,
street: Klaprozenweg 67, Waterside, Amsterdam, Noord-Holland 1032 KK, Netherlands

neighborhood_overview: I live in Vogeldorp which means birdvillage in English. It was build over a 100 years ago to accomodate the poor families of dockworkers. It was ment to be used for just 10 years. The little houses didn't have a bathroom, there was communial bathhouse, which is now museum Noord. The village now is a monumental village. If you (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) amsterdam vogeldorp you'll find some nice pictures.
notes: The house you'll rent, is the house I normally live in with my dog Darka, a Belgium shepard. So if you have any allergies I wouldn't recommend staying in my house. I clean it very thorhourly offcourse. I don't know how she does it, but she always seems to hide some hairs in places I don't know about. The dog never enters the bedroom and isn't allowed on the couch. Yes I'm very strict ;)
transit: Public transport is available day and night . My house is located just 10 minutes by bus from central station. Taking the bus you will pass a tunnel. You can also take the ferry from central station to cross the river called "het ij". (also 24h available and free) and a walk 15 minute to my house.
access: My guests will have acces to the hole house. I'll be staying elsewhere.
interaction: I'll welcome you with a cup of tea or coffee and a traditional stroopwafel, a real dutch cookie. After that you can enjoy your privacy. Most of the time I'll be staying elsewhere in Amsterdam, so if any problems occur I'll be around to solve them.
house_rules: I love my neighbours so please respect them by not sitting outside and chat all night or smoke grass all day. Please no smoking in the house either, there are plenty of coffeeshops in Amsterdam that are very nice.  Just treat my house like it is your own..... or maybe better as if it was your mam's :)

name: Family house with a garden (112m2)
summary: Modern, comfortable and spacious house in upcoming Amsterdam-Noord. In 10 bicycle minutes you are either in the centre of Amsterdam or the beautiful countryside of Noord-Holland. The house is especially suitable for families with (small) children.
space: Specs:  Family house (112 m2) with sunny garden and two bikes in Amsterdam Noord district. On the ground floor there is a spacious living room which is connected to the open kitchen with all facilities. The master bedroom, plus working space are also situated on this level. On the first floor we have two bedrooms, and a modern bathroom with a bathtub. Neighbourhood: Our house is in the Amsterdam North district; a no frills but upcoming borough across the river IJ with trendy restaurants and cafes. In just ten minutes by bike/bus you'll be at Central Station. Also in ten minutes by bike you are in Waterland, a unique landscape of grassland and water, with authentic Dutch villages like Zunderdorp, Marken and Volendam. Across the street there is a park, a playground, and an outdoor swimming pool.

neighborhood_overview: The house is situated in residential area in the more calm Northern part of Amsterdam. The cosy shopping area Purmerplein just around the corner. Within 15 minutes by bus you are in the middle of the city centre. But North itself has also many nice hotspots, like Nieuwendammerdijk, Eye filmmuseum, NDSM area. So for great restaurants ( de goudfazant, cafe modern, il Pecorino) and culture you are at the right spot in this part of the city. You can rent bikes neare camping 'Vliegenbos' and explore the city, but dont forget 'the backyard' of the city: the so called 'waterland'. the countryside of Amsterdam. To good to be true ;-)  Canoe and (wisper)boat rental is a recommendation if you like to be in full nature and see typical old authentic Dutch village form the water.
notes: Then there is our precious Jhoanna, she cleans our house and will do that before and after your stay as well. Because the guests often come and leave at the same day its important to know you respect the check-in (14:00) and check-out time (11:00). (except if we made other, personal, agreements over it.
transit: Getting to the house is easiest done by Bus (from Central Station take bus 32 to 'Buikslotermeerplein' and hop off at 'Wervershoofstraat') busstation is at the nothside (backside) of the station. If the bus leaves you already enjoy the skyline of the northside of  Amsterdam. Or you go by cab, which will cost you around 20 euros.
access: As a guest you will have access to the WiFi internet, digital TV, washer and all kitchen appliances you can find. In the kitchen you will find a dishwasher and a esspresso machine. You have access to all the rooms except for the barn in the garden.
house_rules: We don't want smoking inside the house. No party's and no noise during the night. No pets (allergic family members :-( ). Take care of the key, always lock the doors. Also when you go upstairs. Its a friendly quite neighbourhood, but please take care.
host_about: Werkzaam in het hbo, moeder van drie zonen (15, 14 en een kleintje van 2). Zeer gelukkig getrouwd. We wonen in een lieflijk dorpje in Amsterdam noord. Onze zonen werken hard op school. De oudste surft graag, de middelste voetbalt. De Benjamin houdt van de boerderij, kan alle dieren imiteren en is voor het hele gezin het mooiste wat ons overkwam. Mijn man is gewoon de leukste, hij is webdesigner en programmeur. En hij is super handig.

name: New cozy room for girls near center
summary: The house is located in the North, the new hip area of Amsterdam. The center is close by and there are great bicycle routes and artistic hubs to explore in the North.    The room is colorful and cozy with a bed, closet and table and a nice view over a square. You can use the facilities of the house, like the kitchen, washmachine and roof terrace.  Free parking spaces right in front of the houses are available for your car. In the close vicinity there´s a supermarket and nice restaurants.
space: The room is cozy, the bed is antique with a comfortable mattress 110 by 190 cm and nice warm and comfy blankets. There is central heating in the whole house.  It has a view over a nice square with trees and is a quiet street. The room has a beamer to watch movies (I can give you the instructions if you like).  There is a simple closet in the room to leave your clothes, a table and chair. I can give you a code for WiFi access. You´re welcome to use the living room and the roof terrace (which I just finish building).

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North is the new hip neighborhood in town. There are many artistic and nice places to discover, like the new film museum EYE or the Ceuvel, an artistic working hub of houseboats on the land with a nice cafe and swimming area, on a 5 minutes walk from my house.
notes: If you like I can rent out a bike and lock for 15 euros a week. Amsterdam is so much more fun on a bike and it's really easy going to the city center from my house in 5 minutes, which takes you 15 by bus..
transit: To go to the center, you can take a bus (every 5-10 minutes) to the central Station. From there you can reach anything in the center. It will only take you 10-15 minutes. I also have a bike, which I can rent out or you can walk to the ferry in 20 minutes (goes day and night for free).  On Wednesday, Friday and Saturday there is a great food market around the corner.   You can make some cool and very dutch bike or running trips from my house. I would love to advise you about those.
access: I have a simple house, no television, no microwave, no dishwasher. You may use the oven, stove, fridge and freezer in the kitchen. The shower is warm and the house comfortable.  We share the bathroom, kitchen en toilet. I just like you to feel at home.
interaction: Please feel free to ask me anything and I´ll try to help you out. . I prefer to host girls. Since I often live alone in the house. I do have a boyfriend who stays over now and then.
house_rules: We are gonna share the flat and the best way is to behave as flat mates.  Preferable relax and positive environment. You are welcome to use the kitchen, fridge and prepare food, to use spices, coffee, tea etc. Be kind to clean after use and put everything where it belongs.  Smoking is not allowed in the house.
host_about:
I live in the North of Amsterdam. I love to enjoy the good things in live, food, music, movies and especially nice moments with my dear friends and family. 
I play a handpan instrument. My favourite transport is a bike (of course for a dutch girl). I traveled for long time in Central and South America and fell in love with Colombia. Beautiful, warm, friendly, spiritual.

transit: From behind central station take city bus number 32 to buikslotermeerplein (The busstop  are "upstairs" behind the central station)  and take off at wervershofstraat . walk straith untill the first street on your right ( after the little churgh) and go in there walk up the road goes up a bid at the end. when you are up the "dijk" you go left and after 20 meters you will see a little blue gate and the enterence of the harbor : "Nauticadam". the boat is behind the blue crane at the end of the wooden boardwalk. There is  free and guarded parking in the harbour. offcourse there is a very good citybus system wich takes you everywhere you want to go .  Or rent our rental bikes for €10,- per day. just let me know in front so i can put them ready for you.  we can also provide a taxi service from the airport to the harbour . just let us know .
access: you have the whole ship for yourself . there is an electronic gate and there is also the harbor chef. dont make noise on the water when you walk over the wooden path to the ship bacause water carries the sound very far. in the ship it is all yours, also the backdeck is a nice terras to sit in the evening or morning sun .
interaction: I willl not see you after the check in day .unless you call me or Jaquelien  you have the whole ship for yourself . it is 100% private ship .
house_rules: leave the boat as you find it . no smoking in the bedrooms . turn of the gas bottle. and the electricity and the heatings system  thermosstaat low ( as it runs on Petrol), everytime you leave the boat.

happily married with two children

summary: Large sunny and comfortable house at an idyllic ancient dike just 10 min from Amsterdam center and 5 min from the countryside. Parking is free! We prefer to rent to families or couples. Discounts may apply for 1-week plus summer stays!
space: The house has four floors with two main living area's, at the garden (lowest) floor a large kitchen and at the dike level (front door) a light and spacious living room.  The dike level also has a large balcony where you can enjoy the evening sun.  The main sleeping flour has 2 large rooms (1 parent master and 1 kids room). The master bed room has a large bed (180x210). The beds in the kids room are normal beds (90x200), but bunk beds. This floor also has a luxurious bathroom with a separate shower, bath and toilet.  The top floor is a spacious open floor with a double bed (160x200). Every floor, except the top, has a toilet, 3 in total. Due to Amsterdam city rules, we are not allowed to host more than 4 persons.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighbourhood is a historical area which goes back to the 16th century. You can find many wooden houses in the street and there are great bars and restaurants close such as Cafe het Sluisje and Hotel de Goudfazant. You can also find the Film museum close (EYE) as well as the NDSM area and the Tolhuistuin (cafe, restaurant and concert hall).  If you like the country side you will find it within 5 minutes biking from our house. In het Twiske you will have a nice lake where you can swim with lots of playgrounds.  All these great spots you can find within 5-10 minutes by bike from our house. There is a 24/7 free ferry taking you the other side of the river in just 5 minutes.
notes: In our neighbourhood you will particularly find families with young kids who want to combine a rustic living on the North side of the IJ river, with lively Amsterdam close just 10 minutes biking. We especially recommend our house for families with kids, their are plenty of toys available.  Please note that we welcome only families, couples and groups of persons who are over 30 years old.
transit: Our house is situated close to the city heart of Amsterdam.  Central Station for example will take approximately 10 minutes either by bike, public transport or by car.  The free ferry continues 24 hours per day! Busses to Central Station depart at 250m from our house every 5 minutes.  Parking in the street is for free.
access: You will have access to the entire house. You can always call us should you have any questions.

summary: Peaceful two bedroom apartment, for up to three guests, situated in Amsterdam’s authentic North.
space: The lodging offers a more relaxed experience than the city’s vibrant core, combining easy admission to Central Station with a rewarding local neighbourhood. Stylishly presented throughout, the residence benefits from plenty of natural light, wooden floors, fresh décor and modern furnishings. The living area offers a chance to unwind after a busy day, providing pleasant wall hangings, a large sofa, flatscreen TV and a dining table. All your favourite snacks and meals can be prepared in the kitchen, which comes equipped with a dishwasher, oven, microwave, hob, fridge and a freezer. The master bedroom is fitted out with a double bed and enables access to a balcony with views across the courtyard. The second bedroom houses a single bed, a bookcase, and a desk and chair. The bathroom completes the apartment with a washbasin, toilet and shower. All in all, the accommodation makes a welcoming holiday home for a small family or a group of friends.

neighborhood_overview: Situated across the IJ water behind Central Station, the apartment blends convenience with a more authentic and relaxed setting. Admission to Amsterdam’s historical core is simple, with regular ferries traversing the river completely free of charge. A brief stroll south towards the water’s banks will guide you past the impressive Eye Film Theatre and Museum. A must for movie lovers, this modern treasure boasts several interesting exhibitions and fantastic views. Plenty of local amenities are close at hand to keep you satisfied throughout your stay, with a scattering of cafes and restaurants providing an alternative to home-cooking. For tasty cuisine, a trendy setting and a fantastic atmosphere, take a brief stroll south to Café Modern or head north to San Remo for delicious pizzas at great value.
transit: There is a ferry every 5 min and it is about a 10-15 min walk to the ferry, that arrives at central station.

name: Spacious house near city centre
summary: Want to enjoy a perfect holiday in a nice house with everything you need? You just found it! Quiet neighbourhood, yet only a 10 minute bike ride to the city centre (free ride with the ferry!).
space: Spacious apartment in the booming Amsterdam North quarter, quiet area, yet just a 10-minute bike ride (including 24/7 free ferry) or 5 minute bus ride away from the Amsterdam city center! Our house is a so-called "maisonette" with two floors and a small attic. The living room is spacious and has a comfortable couch, a bookcase and a TV with over 150 channels. There is free Wi-Fi access. The kitchen includes a fridge, a freezer, a stove, a dishwasher, a microwave, an oven, a toaster, a coffee maker and a kettle. Please feel free to use all our equipments, including the pans to cook yourself a nice meal which you can enjoy at our dinner table. We also have a balcony. Upstairs we have two bedrooms, a bathroom and a separate toilet. One bedroom has a comfortable bed for 2 persons. There is a shower and a washer/dryer which are at your disposal. Towels and clean sheets are provided.

neighborhood_overview: Our neighborhood is unique because it is quiet, close to green areas, yet very close to the city centre. Amsterdam North is a booming quarter with restaurant/party area "NDSM-werf" and Film Museum "The EYE" nearby (5 minute bike ride). Also a 5 minute bike ride away is the free 24/7 ferry service which takes you to the city centre in only 2 minutes. What more: - Lot of nice and cosy dining areas - Idyllic houses on the Buiksloterdijk at a 3 minute walking distance - Small super market around the corner, and larger super markets at walking distance - Brand new public swimming pool behind the house!  - Nice big park nearby (Noorderpark) - On Wednesday, Friday and Saturday the "Van der Pek"-market is open, with nice clothes, wines, Dutch and international food. - There is a large famous Dutch mill at walking distance - Free parking in front of the house.
notes: We will have information about all nice things that you could do in Amsterdam ready for you on the table. You could rent a bike to experience the ultimate Amsterdam feeling!
transit: Bus 34 and 35 are a 1 minute walk away (stop: Sneeuwbalstraat) and will take you to and from the city centre in 5 minutes. The free 24/7 ferry service is a 5 minute bike ride away. You can rent a bike around Amsterdam Central Station or at the ferry (it's cheap!).
access: You will have the entire house to yourself.
interaction: You can always reach us by phone or email if you have any questions.  If we are on a holiday we will have our friend standby.
house_rules: Kindly respect our neighbours (no parties). No smoking inside, only on the balcony. Please close all windows, curtains and the front door with the key when leaving the house.
host_about: Hi all, thank you for viewing my listing. I would love for you to stay at my house and experience the ultimate Amsterdam feeling. I work as a patent administrator at a law firm. I am learning to speak Spanish in my free time.

neighborhood_overview: The house is situated in residential area in the more calm Northern part of Amsterdam. The cosy shopping area Purmerplein is on walking distance. Within 15 minutes you are in the middle of the city centre. But North itself has also many nice hotspots, like Nieuwendammerdijk, Eye filmmuseum, NDSM area. So for great restaurants and culture you are at the right spot in this part of the city.
notes: We have a lovely pair of cats and they need to be fed on a daily basis to keep them happy. Very, very happy.
transit: Getting to the apartment is easiest done by Bus (from Central Station take bus 32 to 'Buikslotermeerplein' and hop off at 'Purmerplein') or by cab, which will cost you around 20 euros. The easiest way to travel in Amsterdam is taking the bike. There's a bike rental shop in walking distance at the campside Vliegenbos.

neighborhood_overview: A former shipyard located on the banks of the River IJ in Amsterdam Noord, the NDSM Wharf has blossomed into an enormous cultural hotspot in recent years.  Evolving culture With grounds exceeding the size of ten football pitches, the NDSM Wharf hosts multi-disciplinary festivals, performances, exhibitions, dance parties and a wide range of other events – from massive to tiny. It is also home to a vibrant community of artists, craftspeople and theatre producers, while an expanding variety of bars and restaurants have embraced this unique waterfront area. The area itself is served by free public transport ferries.

neighborhood_overview: The neigbourhood is friendly and save. And the dyke with its old houses is really beautiful. With a bike you can easy investigate this special North part of the Amsterdam city, with a lot of new trendy hotspots as Eye museum, film theater and restaurant, TolhuisTuin with nice food and live music, NDSM area with festivals and great restaurants.
notes: A nice breakfast is included in the stay!  We do have 3 lovely cats. They will not be at the third floor where the guests have their room.
transit: Close to the house on a couple of minutes walking distance we have a busstop: called 'halte Merelstraat'. Bus 32 and 33 can be taken for a 10 minutes ride to or from Amsterdam Central station. From the station you can walk into the city or take trams. From Schiphol airport you take the train to Amsterdam Central station (15 minutes) en then take bus 32 or 33 to 'halte Merelstraat'. On the right hand you find the beginning of our street the Nieuwendammerdijk.  It is free parking at the dyke. And we have a private parking spot in front of our house.
access: The guests have access to kitchen where breakfast is served, the most upper floor where their sleeping room is situated and the garden.
interaction: During the day, most of the time the guests will be on their own in the house. But we are always available to help with questions and suggestions.
house_rules: No animals are admitted. And the house is a non smoking area. You are allowed to smoke on the balcony or in the garden.
host_about: Hallo we are Rob and Jolanda and we live in the Netherlands with our children. We like to travel and see new places. Rob works for a national telecom company and Jolanda just started her own company after working many years in marketing management jobs. In our free time we go to the movies and have diner in one of the nice restaurants in Amsterdam. Another time consuming hobby we both have is running. We now train for the Amsterdam Marathon October 2014.

space: This apartment is very light and is situated at the waterfront in the nothern part of Amsterdam. FREE PARKING AROUND THE CORNER! The free ferry will bring you to central station in only 5 minutes.  From my balcony you can see the Y-lake, and you see and hear the boats passing by. It's very spectaculair when big cruiseship depart and arrive. Lay down in the hammock and you will feel very relaxed.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Noord is a very exciting and upcoming neighbourhood. You have  very nice restaurants here like Hotel De Goudfazant en Il Pecorino. Walk just 10 minutes and visit Eye, the filmmuseum with a spectaculair terrace. Here you can watch old and new movies. It's very interesting architectural site. You can also eat and enjoy  concerts at the Tolhuistuin, an old garden. Also nice is Pllek, a restaurant with a beach in front of it. The citycentre is very close. With a bike you're there in only 15 minutes.
notes: I have a sofa bed in my living room.
transit: On just 7 minutes walking distance you will find the free ferry to Amsterdam central station. You also have busses. I prefer bikeriding.  This is the best way to see Amsterdam. You can park for free in the area, walking distance 5 minutes.
interaction: I lived in Amsterdam for most of my life, so I know some really nice places. The last 5 years I worked as a reporter in this city and therefore I know a lot about Amsterdam. I would really love to share my knowledge with you! I will leave some nice suggestions on the table!
house_rules: Please take good care of my house. I would like you to take off your shoes because of my wooden floor.  Clean it when you leave. Water my plants. No smoking! No pets!  Thanx!
host_about: Hello! I am Marlies, a journalist and writer from Amsterdam. I live in the Nothern part of Amsterdam. It's a very exciting and fun place to live, because there is so much going on in this area and I really like the water and the boats. I like to explore the city and visit theaters, movies and other cultural cites. I also like to cook. So feel free to use some of my cookebooks. Please install yourself at the balcony in my hammock and you will get very relaxed.

summary: Set in the unique picturesque garden village Disteldorp (with monumental status), this house offers you a luxury home feeling in a sociable neighborhood.  Five minute cycling (you may use our bikes) or ten minute walk to the free 24-7 ferry to C.S.
space: The First Floor offers an open private, serene open sleeping / bathing area including big two-person bed, romantic separation curtain, option for a suspended cradle, bath, rain shower, and a  children bunk bed. There is a small workstation, washing machine, dresser and a suspended cradle.  The Ground Floor has a well-equipped open kitchen, dining table and seating area including TV and Wifi, a bed for age 0-4, and direct access to a garden, which is designed as an extension of the living area.  The house is ideal for a couple or people with  (small) children. This house has truly been optimized by its owners who are both architects.

The North of Amsterdam has a growing number of interesting cultural hotspots such as NDSM, EYE film museum/cinema, Tolhuistuin, Adam Tower, Noorderpark, as well as a number of good restaurants we can advice you.
transit: From the airport: take the train to Central Station (C.S.) or take a taxi.  From C.S.: take bus line 34 or 35 to bus stop 'Mosplein' and walk 5 minutes OR take the ferry to 'Buiksloterweg', and walk ten minutes.  By car: free parking in the street.
access: The house and garden including two adult bicycles (plus child-seats option) and two small children bicycles. The sandpit with toys, and the toy collection inside (for small children) can also be used.
interaction: You don't have to share the house with us. It will be yours for the period of your stay.
house_rules: The entire interior has been renovated with love and some elements are delicate. We expect guests to appreciate this and follow the house instructions to keep it beautiful. No dogs. No smoking inside.

I live together with my girlfriend Amber and our two sons Kai and Sammy.

name: Only 5 minutes to CS , stunning view
summary: New, comfortable ground floor apartment in this popular area along the river and on walking distance of the historic center. Light living room w. terrace, private bedroom w. double bed, shared bathroom, gym, sauna, Wi-Fi and parking.
space: The house is located within minutes from the lively center of Amsterdam and Central Station, in the sunny North side. It is situated next to the Eye Film Museum and the A'dam Tower and 5 walking minutes from the ferry. Peaceful in the night and very close to the old center. 'De Europa" (2011) is a white marble building on the North side of  the IJ river. The apartment (102m2) is light with large windows, spacious rooms and a open kitchen. It has solid parquet flooring throughout the apartment. The building is heated and cooled in an innovative and sustainable way by  soil storage. There is a floor heating and cooling in all the spaces of the apartment.

neighborhood_overview: The area is a new and upcoming part of Amsterdam that is rapidy changing. It is very close to the historic center of the city but due to it's great views and architecture it has it own kosmopolitan feel and it will give you a nice stroll when you come and go. We still get excited with our own neighborhood!  If you don't feel like cooking or simply want to have a night out you also can find this within walking distance. The EYE Film museum, which is the large futuristic building next door, has a beautiful restaurant with a view over the IJ (river) and city. Ofcourse you can also go there for a drink, see a movie at the cinema or an exhibition. The Tolhuistuin and cafe De Pont, two other restaurants nearby, also serve food, and are great spots, if the weather is good, to sit for a drink on their terraces and watch the sunset. In summer you can visit the 'hidden' Tolhuistuin, which is the real garden behind the restaurant, where you can can have drinks or snacks or take a yoga class. Het
notes: - Heating by floorheater, takes at least 4 hours to adjust but is comfortably tuned. - Wi-fi available, information in the guest manual - All kitchentools can be used, also herbs and oil. - Indoor parking space is limited, please ask about availability. - Towels and bedding is available.   - In addition: hairblower, soap, shampoo, haircaps.
transit: From Schiphol Airport you preferably take a 20 minute train to Amsterdam CS. From there you find the ferry 'Buiksloterweg' at 'IJzijde'.  The ferry is a 5 minute walk away from the apartment and brings you to Central Station or Buiksloterweg for FREE in 2 minutes. It goes 24/7 and leaves every 4 minutes during the day (every 10 minutes at night). For a real 'Amsterdam' experience you rent a bike though in Central Station. Always be careful, stay to the right on a biking track and please respond to ringing. Our apologies in advance, we Amsterdam folks can be pretty impatient as cyclists. :-) In case you are not such a dare devil, use our public transportation system. The metro and trams will take you anywhere. Tickets (chipcards) are available at the Touristoffice in front of Central Station.
access: The living room, your private bedroom (20m2), the shared bathroom, kitchen and leisure area are there for your convenience. The second bedroom is where my husband and I stay.  We have no children or pets. There is a indoor parking present and if necessairy availability can be discussed. In the living room there is a tv set. Wifi is available, the login and password are in the guest manual in your room.  We have a nice and clean kitchen with all the basic equipment you need and you can feel free to use it as you like. Also is there a washing machine and a tumble dryer if you need it. The bedroom has a comfortable bed (mattress size 160x200cm / 63"x78") and a closet for your clothes. There is a boom box to play your music. We will leave an international adapter to charge your phones so you don't need to worry about that. Also is there a coffeemachine and a tv. The bathroom has a large bath, separate shower, toilet, and two sinks with a large mirror. Towels of different sizes are availabl
interaction: We will welcome you, hand over the key and tell you everything you need to know. There is a manual for guests available that might come handy. We wil give you privacy during your stay but feel free to ask your questions. If I am not present at the apartment, don't hesitate to call us (tel. +(PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN)).
house_rules: * You probably will find that this is a beautiful and peaceful residential building. To keep it like that and to make your stay a good experience for everybody we allow no pets, smoking, drugs, strangers or parties in the house. * Our area is very safe. This is a ground floor apartment though, so take into account  the following: please close and lock windows and doors when leaving. When you want to sleep with windows open, use the special locks. Please leave no items on the terrace when leaving, including the pillows.  * Our keys are very pricy. In case you lose the key of the house, the blue drop or the keycard of the garage we have to charge you 75 euro each. After your stay please hand over the keys personally or leave them in the mailbox. Thank you
host_about:
My name is Nisha and I am living in Amsterdam, The Netherlands. I work as a Project Manager at Mindwize Group, helping charities to run their fundraising campaigns. I am married and my fab husband is originally from Kosovo and now based for a year in Amsterdam. He just started a new job at HP.

We enjoy life! Next to work we spend most of our time together, practicing hot yoga, riding our bikes, get together with friends for drinks, enjoy city life, spend time with our family and travel as much as we can!

Whenever we travel we always use Airbnb. We love to have an authentic local experience and usually stay off the beaten track. We are friendly and positive people, sensitive towards other's needs and respectful to house rules. We love making new friends and are open-minded people. We are also pretty independent and love our privacy too, :)

As hosts we are thrilled to have guests from countries all over the world. We want to make them feel welcome and comfortable and that they belong here. We are available for our guests' questions and a chat and also give them their rest and privacy after a full day of sight seeing. We've made a guest manual with where to find the tourist infomation and a list with suggestions we personally like and recommend in Amsterdam. 

If you have any questions, please reach out and contact me. Thanks for your interest in my profile! Hopefully we meet some time soon!

name: Faralda Crane Hotel: Free Spirit
summary: Rise high above the city bustle in a monumental harbour crane. Enjoy a phenomenal view over Amsterdam from your luxurious design suite or from the hot tub on the top deck of the crane.
space: Enjoy an amazing view over Amsterdam and the river IJ from a luxurious design suite in a monumental harbour crane. When the wind blows, the crane turns, and the view changes! Take the elevator to 35  meters height and enter The Free Spirit Suite.  A contemporary room concept based on the language of the harbour and industry. Sober materials and soft colours pleasing the eye, however with a very high level of comfort. To make the experience even more perfect, you can relax in a hot tub on the top deck of the crane, overlooking Amsterdam.

transit: From the airport you can take a train to central station (15 minutes). There you exit on the North side, and take the ferry that's to the utmost left of the train station to NDSM-wharf (also 15 minutes). During the crossing you will already see the Faralda Crane, located 600 metres from the ferry stop NDSM, where you get off.  You can park your own car on site for just €7,80 per day (reservation is not needed) or travel in style with a VIP limo from the rental service  close by, that we can arrange for you.

interaction: You will have total privacy, but you can always phone me for anything you need. Please give me a call beforehand, so I can hand you the key cards upon arrival. After your stay you can leave the key cards in the mailbox.
house_rules: Suites are for adults only. Non-smoking.  No pets.

name: apt. full of light, space & comfort
space: Bed & Breakfast Riet is a modern, spacious,comfy apartment with it's own entrance. The apartment exists of one big space and a separate bathroom with toilet. neighborhood_overview: As you maybe know, Amsterdam North is an upcoming district with new restaurants opening up and international companies moving in. From our house you can easily go to the centre of Amsterdam (5 minutes by car, 8 minutes by bike), you can easily go to the country side (to hire a boat or to cycle and see a lot of typical Dutch villages and a lot of nature (5 minutes by bike and you are in the middle of the nature). For example the Waterland tour will take you almost exclusively by scenic paths across a nature reserve. Through centuries old picturesque villages, past countless brooks and waterways and straight through green pastures. And of course there is also a lot to do in the Amsterdam Noord district:   Creative & active Amsterdam Noord is an inspiring and vibrant part of Amsterdam with unique architecture. Until the 1980’s a large part of Amsterdam Noord was used as a shipyard. Currently you will find many creative agencies and cultural entrepreneurs on these premises. The NDSM Wharf
transit: From the central train station of Amsterdam there are several ferries which go day and night to the north of Amsterdam and back. During the day they go every five minutes. By night they go every 10 minutes. Alle the ferries are for free. By car there is of course a tunnel. The connection by bus is also very easy. There are several buses to the centre. From our house to the nearest ferry (buiksloterweg) it is only eight minutes by bike. You can take the bike on the ferry.

host_about:
Hi! My name is Karin, and I am owner and sailor of this wonderful traditional  sailing ship called Averechts. My husband Tom is skipper. Together we happily sail and manage the ship, always meeting and welcoming new people, make them happy. In wintertime, from November 1 till May 1, we are available in Amsterdam as a group accomodation, and of course we will try to make a little trip with the ship around the Amsterdam-Lake.  That we do for free  if the ciurcumstance allow it. We have a central heating system, so in wintertime it is nice and warm aboard!   In summer time, we sail nice sailing tours, starting from a villiage up in the north of Holland, and we sail along IJsselmeer and to the islands in the Waddensea
When our guests want to sail luxuous, I will make them breakfast, lunch, dinners, and so on. We love to make sure our guests are comfortable. 
We  enjoy our  work a lot. It is hard work, but it is our own, and it makes us  feel very satisfied and proud when people are so happy on our ship! Welcome aboard!

name: Comfortable Family home
summary: If you would like to enjoy the business of the city and the calmness of a family home you have come to the right place. Our home, which accomodates 5, is located in a quiet area with the centre of Amsterdam a 15 minutes bike ride away. Welcome!
space: The house is an old working class house, but is big enough for our family (and yours) to comfortably live in. With a nice spacious living room, three bedrooms, a small bathroom and a garden you have the perfect base to wander around the city or even go into the countryside. Both spring and summer make for great seasons to stay here, and the Christmas lighting on the houses in the Winter are a match for the best decorators in the world ;-)

neighborhood_overview: The house is situated in residential area in the more calm Northern part of Amsterdam. The cosy shopping area Purmerplein is on walking distance. Within 15 minutes you are in the middle of the city centre. But North itself has also many nice hotspots, like Nieuwendammerdijk, Eye filmmuseum, NDSM area. So for great restaurants and culture you are at the right spot in this part of the city.
notes: We have a lovely cat who is a real peoples animal that loves to be around. When you stay in our home all we ask of you is to feed him so he will stay happy and the peoples cat he always has been.  Be aware that the bathroom has no door but curtain!
transit: Getting to the house is easiest done by Bus (from Central Station take bus 32 to 'Buikslotermeerplein' and hop off at 'Purmerplein') or by cab, which will cost you around 20 euros.  The easiest way to travel in Amsterdam is taking the bike. There's a bike rental shop in walking distance of the apartment at campsite Vliegenbos.

name: Large waterfront house on a dyke!
summary: Large house (200m2) on a typical Dutch dyke. Family oriented with large garden (180m2). In a beautiful and quiet area, only 15 mins from Central Station. Swimming pool nearby. Lots of games (table tennis, darts). Ideal as a basis to enjoy Amsterdam.
space: Our house was built and the nineties and has completely been redecorated last year. It is modern and spacious with high ceilings. Well suited for families. Small children need to take care as there are stairs.
description: Large house (200m2) on a typical Dutch dyke. Family oriented with large garden (180m2). In a beautiful and quiet area, only 15 mins from Central Station. Swimming pool nearby. Lots of games (table tennis, darts). Ideal as a basis to enjoy Amsterdam. There will be a personal host to check you in. We are standing ready for questions or queries during your stay. From Schiphol, a taxi costs 60 to the house.  If you rent a car, it is free parking in front of the house. Take the train to Central Station, then bus 35 which departs above the station. (CS IJzijde). Hop off 10 minutes later at stop "Sneeuwbalstraat". It is a 10 minute walk from there to the house.  Or bus 32 (CS IJzijde) hop off at Merelstraat, it is a 5 minute walk from there.
neighborhood_overview: Buiksloot is an old village that once bordered the sea. Our house is built on the sea dyke. The village has now been enclosed by the city of Amsterdam. It is a very green area with a windmill and a petting zoo nearby.
notes: The house is ideas for a family, two couples or business travellers.
transit: From Schiphol, a taxi costs 60 to the house.  If you rent a car, it is free parking in front of the house. Take the train to Central Station, then bus 35 which departs above the station. (CS IJzijde). Hop off 10 minutes later at stop "Sneeuwbalstraat". It is a 10 minute walk from there to the house.  Or bus 32 (CS IJzijde) hop off at Merelstraat, it is a 5 minute walk from there.

space: On the picturesque ancient 17th century Buiksloterdijk in Amsterdam North is our spacious apartment of 80m2 (860 sq.ft.).  It is an oasis of peace and yet only 10 minutes by bike from Amsterdam center or 6 minutes by bus, 3 stops to Amsterdam Central Station, the middle of town. In fact you are much closer to the city center than most other places in Amsterdam.  The Buiksloterdijk used to be the place where the Dutch East India Company captains retired. The houses where called 'the captains heaven'. The water of the IJ-river that runs trhough Amsterdam used to come right to the house. Now it is a polder.  It is the feeling of being close to the buzzing scene of Amsterdam and still feel like your in the countryside. That is why this location is one of the most sought after locations of Amsterdam coming second after the canal district in surveys.  The view is beautiful. Overlooking the North Holland Canal. space: Since June 2013, together with our dog Otto, we inhabit this quiet and luminous space in Amsterdam Noord. This apartment is a living dream for who ever is interested in art, culture, and urban environments.  As an artist and an urban geographer, we enjoy to share our space with other inspiring professionals. Our collection of contemporary literature is an up-to date overview of the best publications, available for our guests, to enjoy a quiet stay, get inspired or calm down after a long day in the crowded streets of the canal area. The apartment has a sunny terrace with a small choice of edible plants and a BBQ. Enjoying the breakfast sun and the evening light on the terrace is one of our favorite summer recreations. The location of the apartment is suitable for whoever wants to enjoy the calm of a neighborhood in transformation while being near Central Station.

neighborhood_overview: The city of Amsterdam is situated along the shores of the river IJ. The part on the southern shore offers the globally known facilities that attract millions of tourists each day; while the northern part is where tourists rarely go. After WW2 the ‘Noord’ neighborhood was built to house shipyard workers. Today, this neighborhood is witnessing a massive redevelopment process, which includes the allocations of international cultural hotspots  such as the EYE Film Museum, and more authentic local examples, such as the Tolhuistuin Summer Garden, the characteristic Open Coop, the first 3D Printed Canal House and 2 of the best restaurants of the city: Il Pecorino (if you like real and amazing italian food) and Cafè Moderne (if you want to be surprised by a weekly menu of dutch wonders). Although the city center offers a lot of traditional experiences, Amsterdam Noord is the next big thing of the city.
notes: We are available to answer any question, just ask.
transit: The easiest way to arrive here by public transit is by taking the ferry service from Central Station, which is free of charge.
access: Guests will have access to our whole apartment. Including kitchen stoves with roast and normal oven, dishwasher and a wide and comfortable and luminous bar, for cooking a big dinner at home.
interaction: We are a busy working couple with not much time for our guests. We prefer to rent the whole apartment during our travels abroad. It is however also possible for 2 persons to stay while we are in the house. We have a dog that loves the company of people. And we also have a good knowledge about local amenities, cultural events, and bars.   If you are looking for info about tourist attractions, we can help you, but we are more focused on local events and happenings.
