neighborhood_overview: The apartment lies just across the water from central station, in the lovely area of Amsterdam North. A free ferry travels day and night and takes you across the water in just 3 minutes. The NY Times recently called this one of the hippest neighborhoods in the world. A lot of young creative people moved here during the past years, which gave rise to many cultural hot spots, bars and restaurants. This results in a very vibrant and open atmosphere, without the hecticness of the city center. Staying here gives you the possibility to explore this new and less touristic side of Amsterdam, while being only a few minutes away from the rest of the city. Make sure to check out: - the EYE film museum (3 mins by bike), with it's incredible architecture - De Ceuvel (3 mins by bike): front runners in sustainable urban development, with one of the nicest terraces in Amsterdam - The NSDM werf (8 mins by bike): former harbor area, which was transformed into a creative hot spot, with lots of nice bars
transit: There is a bus stop just across the street, however I recommend to take the ferry and walk or cycle your way through Amsterdam.  For people traveling by car: there are free parking spaces (one of the few left in Amsterdam) just across the street.
access: You will have access to all areas on the ground floor, except for my roommates room. Next to that you have access to a washing machine, which is located in the hallway on the second floor.
interaction: I won't be in Amsterdam during your stay, but I will leave you a list with some of my personal highlights in the neighborhood. If you have any other questions, you can always call me on my cellphone, or ask my room mate.
house_rules: Please don't smoke inside or be loud at night. Other than that, enjoy it like it's your own apartment.
host_about: Hi, my name is Jelger. I am a 25 years old masters student. Next to that I make music and organize art and music events in Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview: For decades the district of Noord, or North, was an undesirable place. But in recent years the district improved so much, that Noord is now an attractive alternative for the city centre. The last few years Amsterdam North evolved from blue-collar industrial area to a red-hot art neighborhood. The coolest area of the city! Quiet and vibrant at the same time!  Just around the corner of the apartment you’ll find - a supermarket with lot’s of fresh, home made, take away food  - beautiful restaurants & cafe’s overlooking the water - a variety of take away food - a great yogaschool - bouldergym In the area within 15 minute ride on your bicycle, you'll find - a concert hall for popmusic & cultural centre - cinema art house - even more beautiful restaurants & cafe’s overlooking the water - giant, (monthly) indoor flea market  - historical Dutch wooden houses, a mill and the traditional 'polder' - meadow landscape
transit: The area is separated from the rest of Amsterdam by the river IJ, but the (free) ferry ride takes only a few minutes. Our apartment is located less then a ten minute walk to the ferry.  There's a busstop a few minutes by foot. The bus runs 24 hr/day. During the day it leaves every ten minutes to Central Station. From there all highlight's of Amsterdam are reached easily. Amsterdam Noord is the only place in Amsterdam where you can park your car for free.
interaction: Of course we provide you all the essential information about our neighborhood, so you have no problem finding your way around.  We're standby if you have any questions or problems during your stay.
house_rules: We expect our guests to have a good time and respect the following rules -  don't smoke inside; -  not play music after 10 pm; -  no pets; -  we love it if you take your shoes off inside;
host_about: Ik hou van reizen, kamperen, de natuur in gaan en op het strand zijn, maar net zo goed hou ik van lekker lummelen thuis en mooie dingen ondernemen in mijn eigen buurt, want overal ligt het avontuur voor het oprapen, zolang je het wilt zien! Ik ben enthousiast, positief en vriendelijk. Rustig en netjes.

neighborhood_overview: De Nieuwendammerdijk is one of Amsterdam's most beautiful streets, with its "village feel" but close proximity to the city centre it really is the "best of both worlds". Pub with terrace at walking distance, countryside and forest close by, as well as trendy restaurants, the ferry to the city centre, hotspot NDSM, Eye filmmuseum.
notes: The house is mainly made of wood; with few straight lines to be found. Beautifully askew; typical for Amsterdam!
transit: Two comfortable bicycles provided with the apartment.  Five minute walk to the bus stop. Free parking!

The owners provide laundry service for a small fee but there is also a laundromat close by. An interior door connects the apartment to the rest of the house, this door can be locked on the apartment side. The hospitable owners are always happy to provide extra services where needed.
interaction: Welcome drinks and introductions at arrival. Always available for questions and help where needed.
house_rules: We expect our guests to behave like good neighbours, treat the property and its inventory with respect and refill any food items before departure. Smoking is only allowed outside on the terrace.  We appreciate social interaction with our guests when both parties wish it.
host_about: Mijn huis is belangrijk voor me; ik hou van kleuren, antiek, curiosa, tuinieren en van gezond en biologische eten. Ons huis is groot en staat altijd open voor onze kinderen, vrienden en mensen die een tijdje onderdak nodig hebben.

neighborhood_overview: Situated north of the IJ River, the apartment encourages you to explore authentic Dutch life unspoilt by the tourist crowds. Safe and peaceful, the surrounding area is home to two beautiful natural highlights adored by the local community, the Florapark and the Vliegenbos. The latter has existed for over 100 years as a charming city forest, highly recommended for a leisurely stroll or picnic. Several cafes, restaurants and stores can be found within easy reach and the impressive EYE Film Theatre and Museum ánd Adam Tower is accessible by bike in less than ten minutes. Discovering Amsterdam’s historic core, home to such famous highlights as Dam Square, the Red Light District and the Canal Belt, is simple. The nearby bus link allows access to Central Station in just twelve minutes, although a brief bike ride to the water’s edge provides an alternative method, with a series of ferries departing across the IJ free of charge on a regular basis.
notes: There are two sweet cats in the house. Hilda, the neighbour is taking care for them if necessary. The other neighbour, Marieke, is taking care of the chickens.
transit: You can easily get to the house by bus from Central Station, or by bike with the 24/7 free ferries. Both around fifteen minutes. Bike rental just around the corner.
access: You have full and private access to the house during your stay.
interaction: For the rental of my house I asked Jolanda and Rob from Home2host to take care of everything, from the booking, the welcome at the house, the cleaning of my house after your stay. They will also handle all communication with you.
house_rules: Please respect the house and the neighbourhood. No smoking inside, no loud music, parties or drugs. Let us know your estimated time of arrival ánd departure as soon as possible.  We charge €20 for late check ins after 9.00 PM.
host_about: Hello I am Chris. I live in the north part of Amsterdam. I am excited about renting my dear house to people who want to explore the great city of Amsterdam and enjoy living at a calm authentic dyke.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is in the North of Amsterdam, recently proclaimed one of the most upcoming and exciting neighborhoods in Europe by the New York Times. Here a good article in the Guardian with lots of tips! (URL HIDDEN) The neighbourhood is relaxed, green and very close to the IJ river, with a beautiful view over the city. The neighborhood is residential, but lively and urban with grocery shops and many different inhabitants reflecting the city's charm. There's a little playground in front of the house, making it perfect for kids. There are some amazing restaurants around, ranging from cheap ones nearby, to higher prized but extremely good restaurants in industrial area's around. More and more alternative spaces and communities are opening up in the Noord. The cinema and film museum EYE is very near. For bars, clubs and clothing shops it's still better to cross the water and go into the center, which is also not far.
notes: We prefer families staying in our apartment. This is not a party apartment.
transit: The best way to get from the airport into the city is by train. It takes you to Central Station in 15min and is cheap. You get to our apartment by taking a ferry directly behind the Central Station, which takes you across the water (for free!) in 5 min, offering a beautiful view. From there it's a 5 min walk to our place. The ferry nearest to our place goes until midnight, after that you can take another ferry, which crosses regularly 24/7. From that ferry it's just a 10 min walk to our place.  Central Station is the central point for all public transport in Amsterdam, which will make it easy for you to move around the city from there. You can also easily walk into the centre from the station, or bike of course! Our place is very accessible by car and there's lots of (free) parking space around. We advise you not to take the car into the city centre. It's full and parking is expensive there.
access: We offer you our apartment as we like to enjoy it ourselves and hope you will feel at home! You will have access to all our utilities, Wifi and parking in the neighborhood. Our apartment is on the second floor, so you have to walk up two flights of quite steep stairs.
interaction: We rent out our apartment when we are away ourselves, so generally we don't get to see much of our guests. We do like to communicate well before and after your stay and give you lots of tips. We are always available by phone if something goes wrong. We have good contact with our neighbors. Friends and family are living down the road, so there's always someone around to give a helping hand when necessary. We will love to give you tips and routes to special places. It's for instance very easy to bike to some beautiful Dutch villages, windmills and fields just North of Amsterdam, but also to rough industrial areas where creatives are slowly settling.
house_rules: We only take families or groups of friends over 27 as our guests, if you don't fall within this category (even if we trust you are great and respectful people) we cannot accept you, because of agreements with our neighbors. Most important for us is that you respect the neighbors, both inside the apartment as out in front. The couple living directly under us have an infant and a newborn baby, the other neighbor is elderly and quite ill. They are the ones experiencing our guests and we don't want to cause them any distress. To assure this we agreed on some rules with our neighbors, this means: - No parties - No music after 22.00 - No more than 6 people in the house - Please walk quietly up and down the stairs - We do not allow pets in our apartment due to allergies, sorry! - Smoking is absolutely not allowed inside the house, but you can smoke on the balcony.  - Please don't throw your cigarette butts in our neighbors' garden, but put them in the ashtray. - No loud chatter on the balcony
host_about: We are Anna -visual artist and filmmaker- and Marnix -freelance composer and teacher. We are in our early thirties, and enjoy to travel for work and pleasure. We love our neighborhood, city and apartment, so we are happy to share it with you when we are not there ourselves!

name: The Little House in the garden
summary: You can book your own  wooden Little House in the charming garden of Nancy & Hans Wiltink, called 'Garden at Sea' (Tuin aan Zee). An oasis in the city, next to an old lock in the canal. It's built as a place to relax, no cooking facilities.
space: Long ago (once upon a time) the water between the city of Amsterdam and this garden was a salty sea. Huge tall-ships passed the lock, coming back from the Indies, loaded with spices and other goods. The area later developped as an industrial area, with shipyards and related industries. Nowerdays the North part of Amsterdam - Amsterdam across the sea so to speak - is rediscovered, and is seen as one of the most trendy neighbourhoods of the world. nancy works as a storyteller, Hans is consultant for sustainable projects.

neighborhood_overview: Recently discovered by people from all over the world: after Londons Southbank, The North part of Amsterdam is now booming. Funny café's and restaurants are opening everywhere, it's hard to give an overview, since so much is happening right now. The Amsterdam Film museum, trendy Paradiso concert Hall, festivals: it's all happening over here, the sunny side of the water.
notes: In your little house and in the garden: - Traditional dutch cupboardbed (sleeps 2) - Small loft with 2 beds - Sitting area - Woodstove inside, open fireplace outside with BBQ opportunity - Free coffee, tea, dutch breakfast biscuits with homemade jam & traditionale Duivenkater bread with butter - No cooking facilities or oven other than a small microwave - Free wifi - Free parkingspace (nocampers or mini-vans) - Private terrace - Lots of books to trade, read & games to play - Nancy's top 10: the ten nicest restaurants, walks, teraces, trips, shops etc. - A natural swimmingpool Extra: - Jam and honey from the garden. - We can fill the fridge with (real) breakfast or local beer & bites - Nancy can take you on a walking or biking storytour, ask for price & route    Breakfast next door (starting 9.00a.m.) 3-5 min walk - Open Coop mo-fr. - A-lab: Coffee Virus mo-fr - Café de Pont mo-su Or take the ferry to Centraal Station, many breakfast opportunities starting at 6.00
transit: A free ferry runs 24 h to the central station. This is a 5 min. walk from our home, and the ferry takes 3 min. It runs every 6 minutes. You can even go 'ferry hopping' to discover the area: more ferry's leave from behind the central station, all free. All buses, trains and metro's leave from central station, the main hub. Trains to the airport Schiphol are convenient and safe, not more than 15 minutes. Bikes for rent nearby. The most ideal and local means of transportation.
access: Your own 'Little House' is in the garden, you have your own sitting space and share the garden with us. There is a fresh water swimming  pond (no chlorides), chickens roam around and an orchard with pear trees, plums and cherries.
interaction: We live in our own house. Interaction is an option, you can just pick up the key and we respect your privacy. Nancy organises storytelling tours that you can book as an extra. Any time we are at home we love to give you tips about what to do or where to go.
house_rules: - No pets and no smoking - Clean up if you make a mess, pay damage. - The natural swimming pool is not fenced off. Children that can't swim should never be left alone outside the house.

name: Comfortable and Bright Sailing Ship
summary: Looking for a group accommodation in Amsterdam? Nothing is more fun than sleeping on a ship. The Maxima is different than usual, has round shapes, shiny showers, clean lines and coloured doors. The ship is located at Amsterdam-IJburg.
space: De Ruimte The Maxima is a traditional sailing ship from 1900, but a little different than other traditional ships in Holland. With a modern interior, round shapes, lots of colours and pleasant atmosphere you feel at home right away. The living space consists of a dayroom with kitchen where you can cook, relax, be together and celebrate your holidays. There are two showers, two toilets and six cabins for two persons, and one cabin for four. There are only single beds. In total there is space for 18 people. In the summer months, the Maxima sails on the Wadden Sea as a charter ship. It is also possible to book a day-sailing-trip when you sleep on the ship in Amsterdam. For information and bookings, we refer you through to our booking agency: Captain Quality. Or you can just send us an Airbnb message for more info!

On the pictures you can see on what a beautiful and idyllic the Maxima is anchored. Because this is a private site, parking your car is free when you stay at the Maxima! The NDSM area emerged the last five years as one of the hippest and most creative neighborhoods in Amsterdam. In the summertime there are festivals organised every weekend, and in the winter there are all creative and cultural events in the huge warehouses. Two minutes walk from the boat you will find Café Noorderlicht, an organic restaurant that already had sustainability and bio-products before it became a trend. In the evenings they often have bands. Tip: go when night falls a local beer on the terrace overlooking the water and the Amsterdam skyline. name: Zonnig huis in Amsterdam Noord
summary: My house is located in wonderfull Amsterdam Noord, 10 minutes from Central Station and the city center. In a quit neighborhood next to a park, swimming pool and a couple of grocery stores are just around the corner.
space: My house has a big downstairs living area with open kitchen en a nice glass facade facing the garden. With good weather, the doors facing the garden can be opened and breakfast in the garden is really relaxing. A lot of light and sun is presented all day. A mix of modern and vintage decorative elements, wood and an modern fire place will give you a warm and comfy feeling. The house has 2 toilets, one downstairs and one in the small but functional bathroom. Upstairs are 2 bedrooms, the one facing the garden has a big mezzanine bed. The one facing the street has a bureau and the washing machine and dry cleaner are located in this room.
description: My house is located in wonderfull Amsterdam Noord, 10 minutes from Central Station and the city center. In a quit neighborhood next to a park, swimming pool and a couple of grocery stores are just around the corner.
neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam Noord is a little village in the city. To reach it, you have take the public transport boat from central station. A lot is going on here and recently it was elected to be one of the top three hippest places in the world to live. It's 10 minutes away from the city center and 10 minutes away from the 'polders' , the dutch countryside. Nearby my house you can find a small grocery, a bio shop, a nightshop, 3 super markets and on wednesday-friday and saturday there's a big open market in walking distance, selling local products. Bars and restaurants are well presented, you will find a map at my place and the location where to find these. A brand new swimming pool is just around the corner and it's a beautiful starting point to explore the city or the Dutch country side by bike.
notes: I have a bird in my house, it's a small harmless yellow singing canary in the living room. Wakes up when the sun rises and starts to sing, this can be a little bit early if you want to sleep longer. There's an easy solution to keep her quiet, a blanket can be put over the cage in the evening and you can take it away again when you wake up. I just ask not to leave the blanket too long covering the bird, and not to play with the bird, cause she's easily stressed. Food is available for refill the containers if necessary. Keep an eye on the water container and please from time to time, fill it up. Most of the times it will have enough food and water for 3 days.
transit: Busstop (bus 34-35) is just around the corner  and brings you in 10 minutes to central station or back. A quick 15 minutes walk brings you to the 'Pont', a free public transport ferry that crosses the water to central station and back, every 10 minutes, 24/24h. If with the car, there's free parking in my street and its save to park here. Bikes can be rented in Noord.
access: You are welcome to use the garden, the living space, the kitchen, the bedrooms and the bathroom. The attic is private.
interaction: You can reach me by mail, phone or (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) and I will make the best of it to respond as fast as possible. Friends and family live nearby and can be contacted if needed.  If I am not there, they will provide the keys of the house and show you around.
house_rules: I love my house, it's a great place to live in. I hope you will have the same feeling when staying here. It's a calm neighborhood and I have friendly neighbors. I would like to keep it that way. No smoking is allowed in the house. No drugs are allowed in the house. Beers/wine/spirits are present in my house, it's not for the guests. It's part of the decoration and for personal use. Feel free to use sugar-coffee-honey-tea-chili sauces- spices that you can find in the kitchen. Soap, garbage bags, tabs for the dishwasher and landry machines can be used. And like everywhere, try not to break anything and be respectfull. Garden door and front door have to be locked when leaving the house, and the windows facing the street have curtains to be closed at night. Don't put valuable items in front of the windows when leaving the house.All areas can be used accept the attic, this is a private area! Water the plants and feed the bird :-), thanks!
host_about:
Hi, my name is Joachim, Belgian, I'm a Chef in Amsterdam!

I like good food, nice beers, photography and traveling.

Lived 7 years in Paris, love the frenchies, la baguette, les croissants, la France  the culture of eating!

Moved to Amsterdam a couple of years ago and bought me a house here. 

I like watching a good movie, or go to concerts, festivals, visiting brocante and antique shops , the 80's, riding my motorbike and taking pictures!

I'm social, and a calm person, care about others and believe that good communication can avoid a lot of problems.

neighborhood_overview: The house overlooks the beautiful Noorderpark in a quiet neighborhood. The new eco-friendly swimming pool (indoor and outdoor pools) lies in the street. In the neighborhood there are several playgrounds, shops and restaurants. Especially some more alternative pots, wherefore there is no space in the center of Amsterdam, are just around the corner; as de Ceuvel, Pllek, Tolhuistuin or Noorderlicht. Places where you can enjoy good food (also vegan and veg), nice people, nice music, and above all the space and ease! By bike or public transport you are in 10 minutes in the red light district or the Jordaan. The ferry to get to the center goes on a regular schedule and sail at night. In other words; the best of both worlds! Near Center for the real Amsterdam experience, but great to come home in the quiet and fashionable north between locals!
notes: The house is rented with Lizy the cat! Like to rent out to cat lovers. Lizy is a friendly cat who likes cuddling and chatting with you. In consultation Lizy could possibly stay somewhere else. My preference goes to guest that stay more than one night. Two night minimum.
transit: Free parking in front of the house, so suitable to come by car (and then use it no longer in Amsterdam !!!). To reach the house with public transport, the central station is 3 busstops away. Or take the ferry and bike / walk for few minutes. At the house I have two real Amsterdam bicycles to use. If these bikes are to robust for your taste, than bicycles can be rented from the ferry to Central Station. With the bike it is 7 minutes to the ferry, which goes to the other side in 3 minutes.  2 minutes walk there is a bus (34 & 36) to central station which is at CS in 10 minutes, from where there is all kinds of public transportation.
access: My whole house is accessible except for the locked closets and the garden shed.
interaction: My name is Irene and I am your hostess. We will meet on arrival and departure. But for questions and tips I am always available and nearby. My preference goes to guest that stay more than one night. Two night minimum.
house_rules: It is a quiet and friendly neighborhood. Parties, drug use, orgies or loud music are not permitted. Inside the house no smoking or dope.
host_about:
Ik ben een vrouw van in de dertig die woont en werkt in Amsterdam. Ik heb veel gereisd en weet hoe heerlijk het is om op reis te zijn en me niet tussen alle toeristen te bevinden. Om die reden biedt ik graag mijn huis aan zodat Amsterdam beleefd kan worden zoals ik het beleef, als een zeer relaxte en vriendelijke wereldstad waar ruimte is voor iedereen!
Zelf ben ik heel sociaal en hou van gezelligheid. Ik ben dan ook goed in staat om leuke tips te geven zodat de ervaring in Amsterdam nog leuker wordt!

The keys will be in a lockbox waiting for you.
house_rules: * laugh a lot & be happy * 3 goldfish live here, so please feed them & they will love you * please no candles  * lock studio door at all times, don't answer door if someone rings or knocks, they are probably looking for a hair cut * no smoking inside, please go outside for that * turn off lights, heater and all electronics when you aren't using them please * leave your trash & recycling. I will take care of it
host_about:
I live my life with a goal to Liberate People to fully express themselves.   I Have a Professional Attitude & i'm very committed to Dreaming up New Things & Doing them.. meaning i am a Visionary & a Doer. 
I am very Artistic expressing my art through Costume Design, Hairstyling, Makeup & Performing career wise . i am also a Yogi & have an  Adventurous disposition. 
i'm very interested in Community, travel & play. 
i love to ride my Bike**
My Art Studio/Hair salon is in an up & coming area of Amsterdam Noord. we have a cafe on the bottom floor that offers the most delicious  coffee my neighbor hand roasts. Sometimes you can smell him roasting down the hall. there are gourmet restaurants just a few minutes walk away and a grocery store right around the corner. it's very easy to get to Amsterdam center either by bus or bike within about 15 min. and if you ride bike or walk the other direction, you find old little villages that are so charming. we also have a free ferry outside the building that brings you over to Amsterdam Oost where there's even more to explor. I rent out my studio when i'm out of town as a unique experience. It is 2 levels with a view of the city to the left, the little forest to the right and a little village, windmills and overview of Amsterdam Noord straight ahead.  It's situated in a cluster of buildings all filled with entrepeneurs. it's a unique chance to stay in an area not often accessible to people.  It is my Art studio, but there is a shower and toilet, kitchenette, internet, TV and i have a couple bicycles you can also rent. This is not a place for parties, but if you would like a nice special spacious spot to stay while you're visiting Amsterdam,. shoot me a message 1- 4 people

name: 17 Century Canal Villa Free Parking
space: Stay in the ambience of Holland's 17th century Golden Age. Just around the corner from a working windmill, this beautifully preserved home was built by a Dutch East Indies captain to house his family while he was at sea. It is centrally located, a mere 7 minute bike ride to the heart of the city. Parking is free!  The home has canal views, is quiet, quaint and authentic, boasting all the amenities of the 21st century. Your comfortable bedroom has WiFi, a private marble bathroom one flight up, a 2nd 1/2 bathroom and a sunny patio. There is a kitchenette with a Microwave/Oven, coffeemaker, electric kettle, toaster and fridge. Coffee, tea, fruit, milk and muesli available. Hosts (MD and linguist) are well traveled and friendly. A brand new public swimming pool with open access terras is located across the street. Facing your home is a large public park offering open air performances in the summer. The cafe in the park is open all-year-round. Bike routes abound. Golf lovers have facilities

notes: Peace and quiet and easy access to the hustle and bustle of downtown Amsterdam. Nice little cafe on the corner breakfast, coffee,cake and simple meals.
transit: Parking is free, safe and right outside the door. Airport connections are a simple 20" train ride and a short bus trip from downtown Amsterdam. Public bus transport to Amsterdam city center: a five-minute stroll from your front door. Fresh food grocery shopping is a mere 3" walk.
access: Museums: Van Gogh and Rembrandt at your service; canal boat rides, windmills, tulip fields, theater, restaurants, cafes, bike paths, festivals, swimming, golf, fitness. Amsterdam has something for everyone!  Live like a 17th century aristocrat at Amsterdam Canal Villa.
interaction: Interaction with guests: as much or as little as you like!
house_rules: No smoking please. We appreciate the quiet of our neighborhood and hope you will too.
host_about: I own and run a language school. Am interested in all things beautiful: theater and the arts. I love to swim and to travel, both of which I have done extensively. I was born in NJ and have been living in Amsterdam for most of my adult life.

There is a chinees take-away next door. there is a good thay restaurant 100meters away. there is a snackbar / sandwich shop 50 m. and next to the snackbar is a coffeeshop for all typical Amsterdam smokeries.  There is a liqour store at the corner next to the snackbar. the bakery is crossing the street from the liquor store. there you will also find a pizzaria take-away and a good surinam restaurant. more to the right from the bakery there is a turkisch supermarket for all vegetables, meat, cheeses, olives and all good stuff. to the right of the turisch supermarket  you will find the daily market ( on wednesday friday , saturday) and the dutch supermarket the Albert Heijn.   behind the market you have the street Hagendoornweg wher
notes: Including:  -bedlinnen. -two parking places -free pool biljard. -beer tap.  - wifi. hi fi stereo with mini jack .  dvd's /  cable T.V. . -kitchen with oil vinagar peper salt herbs all cooking stuff.  but:  -bring your own towels for the shower. ( people using everyday a new towel forces me to not include towels anymore sorry . if needed we can rent a towel for €2,- per towel )  - possible to rent bikes. reserve them up-front. let me know before you come so i can heve them ready at your arrival. There are 6 double beds. ( double beds only) there are upstairs two private bedrooms with each a double bed ( there is one bedroom with an extra sleeping sofa. but you only use that one if you are with 11 or 12 peopel) . then downstairs in the big warehouse space are two entresols with each two double beds . and there is a double bed sofa in the living space in the corner. so downstairs are no private rooms only upstairs two private bedrooms.
transit: from behind the central station you can take the city bus nr 34 or 35  which will bring you in two stops to the  busstop Mosplein at the kamperfolieweg. there you can get out and crosses the street a litlle bit further where there is a crossover with stoplights.   you go in that street: "Ribesstraat"  and cross the next street where you see the beginning of the Papaverweg where is on your right hand the Mercedes oldtimers garage.  after 30 meters you see the Kropaarstraat going to the left  along the water (water on your left hand ) . where you want to go the number 10 . on the corner.
access: you have the whole building for your self. there is 100% privacy . I am not there . only you and your friends . there will be no other guests.  you have the whole building only for you and your group.
interaction: You will not even see me . only at chec- in and check-out time. and when you call me on my mobile. or your hostess Esther 0031- 6 12796715
house_rules: you can do anything to feel at home . just respect my warehouse because i made everything myself and did it with a lot of love . everything is handmade and created from my own mind.  just respect everythin.  I also like to have a good time but don't shoud on the street and if you play loud music . then close the doors so you keep the noise inside and not on the street. Don't spoil this for the people wanting to come here after you. smoking is allowed, only not in the bedrooms and not in the beds. only smoke in the front of the building at the pool table area . . watch out there are smoke alarms .  when you smoke allways open a window or main door . remeber it is allowed in Amsterdam so it doesn;t matter you can smoke outside as well.   have fun but respect my Warehouse.

neighborhood_overview: You have the impression of living in a village, with all necessary shops nearby. This northern part of Amsterdam brings you the perfect blend of tranquility and the vibe of the city . It’s only a 5 minute bike ride to meadows or a 20 min bike ride to the centre of Amsterdam (including a refreshing ferry ride to the central station).  Our house is located at the very charming and characteristic Nieuwendammerdijk and close to the A10 motorway (no noise!). The property has a small front and back garden and is situated at a quiet street . Lovely to come home to after a day in the city.  A beautiful start to explore the city is the EYE movie centre, which is located near the ferry and gives you a wonderful view at the IJ river and Amsterdam.  In the opposite direction you can take a bike to the ancient villages Durgerdam, Holysloot, and Ransdorp, while Broek in waterland, Marken and Volendam are close by car.
notes: We prefer a family and someone to give our funny cat her daily food.
transit: From Schiphol Airport it takes 30 to 45 minutes with public transport (train, bus).  Bus 32 takes you from the central station in about 12 minutes to our house (from the busstop another 3 minutes walk to our house).
access: Guests can enter the house on two different floors. There are 3 floors at your disposal. The top floor is for private things.
interaction: We won't be there during your stay.
house_rules: We don't like when people smoke in our house. It's ok to use the garden or in front of our house.

neighborhood_overview: Our appartment is situated in Noord,a quiet but upcoming part of town very close to the busy city centre. Nearby there are some good restaurants: Stork, Cafe Modern, de Goudfazant, Noorderlicht, Pllek. All off these spots are famous for their industrial looks. If you prefer to cook for yourselves: there's a supermarket 2 blocks away.  At a walking distance you find the new cinema and filmmuseum the EYE. In summer, there are concerts in the Tolhuistuin and the M-Lab theatre is literally round the corner.  When you want to see typical Dutch landscapes you can rent a bike and discover little villages like  Durgerdam Zunderdorp, Monnikendam, Ilpendam, Volendam, Broek in Waterland. In the city center you find all things that make Amsterdam famous: the museums, the canals, red-light district, market-places etc. etc
notes: Smoking is only permitted on our balcony.
transit: There's a free ferry connection from 6.00 to 24.00 hours  - between the City Centre, Central Station, and our neighborhood IJplein. From there on it's a 5 minute walk along the IJ promenade to our apartment. (There are night busses and taxi's too),   From Schiphol Airport there's a direct train every 15 minutes to Central Station There's free parking in the surroundings.
access: Our 58m2 meter  apartment with balcony is all yours! If you leave the house to discover the city: you take a five minute walk along the river, then the free ferry will take you to the old city in 5-20 minutes. When you stay at home: enjoy the beautiful view from our apartment: the clouds, the sunset, the ships passing by and the view at new and old Amsterdam.
interaction: -We are always willing to help you out when needed. We will be around only on request and respect your privacy. - Meanwhile you can always phone us, or mail us with your questions. - On the apartment you can find much information about the city with her museums, restaurants, outgoing places etc. - you see also a map off the city.  -we speak Dutch, English and German and a little bit French
house_rules: - Respect the apartment as if it is yours, - No smoking in the hole building, no drugs, no parties, - no pets, - Be nice to our neighbors , don't make too much noice and be quit after 10 PM - not more then 2 persons are aloud to stay in our apartment, - please leave the apartment and kitchen clean, - make sure you have turned off the heating, electric appliances and the gas before you leave, - clear away the waste to the little square behind the building, there are bins for paper and glass . You can also find in the bedroom,a plastic card which you need to trow rubbish into a container.
host_about:
We are Margreet and Toon Vis. This year we celebrated the fact that we are happily married for 44 years. Because our 3 kids moved to Amsterdam with our grandchildren, we decided to leave the south of Holland, where we normally live, for at least one week a month . That's why we ended up buying our Amsterdam appartment. 

We are looking forward to share our stunning views over the IJ river with our guests and are willing to give you all the information you need to enjoy our up and coming neighbourhood as much as we do.

Hope to meet as many off my guests here from all over the world!!!

neighborhood_overview: This is a trendy upcoming neighborhood with the new film institute Eye (museum, restaurant, and cinema with an excellent choice of classic and new movies), the new music venue Paradiso Tolhuistuin, with a waterfront beach-like terrace. There are several new trendy restaurants, (book)shops and other creative initiatives. It is the area where the hipsters go these days, because it is very central, yet green and spacious - near the waterfront, but also close to rural Amsterdam, 'het Waterland'.  Our boat is on a canal which leads to the IJ-river and the former NDSM shipyard, the hip cultural hotspot of Amsterdam.
transit: The ferry, just a few minutes from our boat, will take you in aprox 1,5 min (all night, no costs) straight to Amsterdam Central Station on the south bank of the IJ-river. Moreover, just around the corner is a bus stop that will take you in 10 minutes to Central Station.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is located in a peaceful green neighbourhood on the banks of the Ij in Amsterdam Noord - dubbed the most up-and-coming part of the city. In front of the house, a park is being planned, but 50 metres down the street is a park running along the water: perfect for a picnic, people-watching or gazing at the water. The EYE film museum is practically on our doorstep and prominent in our view (it's the white space-ship looking building in the photos). Further towards the ferry is the 'Tolhuistuin', which is an art space, concert hall cafe and restaurant all rolled into one. By early 2016, the A'dam tower should be opening, boasting a revolving restaurant at the top. The NDSM wharf is close by, with its industrial charm, creative industry and plenty of good cafes and restaurants. Closer to home is a market 3 times a week, shops and cafes, and a number of playgrounds.
notes: A private parking place for your car is also possible. Please ask for the possibilities.
transit: Public transport is very easy:  The ferry across the IJ in Amsterdam-Noord and back is a very famous connection. Every day many people travel through this GVB ferry connection to Amsterdam-Noord and visa versa. You can make free use of the GVB ferries.  And transport is 24*7 available for you. The Ferries are located behind the central station by the IJ. It's only 1 minute by Ferry to cross the IJ.  And you can walk (2 minutes) to the apartment from there it's behind the famous Eye building.
access: You have acces to all rooms of the apartment. Including the kitchen, Bathroom and Balcony.  Bedrooms Facilities: A- Two 2-person bedroom in a private room. This is a Box Spring and possible to separate them if needed. And extra services HD television with 24 hour sports channels or movies.  Bedlinen and towels are provided for free during your stay. You also receive two sets of keys of the apartment.
house_rules: If you agree with the house rules you are welcome to my apartment. Parties are not allowed in the apartment. You will stay in the best (top A location) apartment building and area of Amsterdam. And the concierge of the apartment building want to keep it this way.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. More and more hotspots are popping up! Visit urban beaches like Café de Ceuvel and Pllek! Both perfect spots to relax and enjoy the warm weather on the waterfront. Other nice places overlooking the IJ-lake are film museum EYE (enjoy the sunset on their beautiful terrace!), seafood restaurant Stork and THT restaurant. One of our favourite areas in Amsterdam North is the NDSM Wharf. Known as one of the best festival locations of Amsterdam. North is also the place to be for vintage and thrift shopping. You can’t miss the monthly flea market in the IJ-hallen, a true second hand heaven.
notes: Guests we look for: - Respectful of neighbours (keep level of noise down) - Non-smokers (or smokers that smoke outside) - Above 30 when in a group - Any age if staying as a couple At time of departure: make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done, the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean. All keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee. Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment.
access: You will access to the entire apartment. Make yourself at home!
interaction: I will meet you at the apartment, handle the keys and show you around. After that feel free to contact me on Airbnb if you need any assistance or tips! I am more then happy to help you!

neighborhood_overview: Despite its status as "off the tourist track", Amsterdam North is actually quite central and accessible - free ferries depart from behind Central Station four or more times per hour and stop at several points north of the IJ; the approximate travel time takes around five minutes. Once up north, visitors should note that the streets are more spread out and the public transit more sparse than in the Center, but there's also considerably less traffic - all of which makes it the ideal terrain to explore by bike. Bikes can be rented near Central Station and taken on the ferry.

The wide open kitchen is fully equipped and is in direct contact with the living room. The master bedroom, main bathroom (with big bath) and walk-in-closet are situated on the ground floor. neighborhood_overview: The house is situated in the bustling and lively area of Amsterdam Noord. A great neighbourhood, which is getting increasingly popular amongst residents and tourists. It houses some of Amsterdam's great museums (e.g. the EYE Film Museum), but also great contemporary art centers (e.g. Tolhuistuin, NDSM) and many of our city's finest restaurants (e.g. Hotel Goudfazant, Cafe Modern, Stork). Rough around the edges sometimes, Noord also features some of Amsterdam's most beautiful streets. Truly one of the great gems of Amsterdam!

With the historic city of Amsterdam only 10 min bike-ride away and the forest literally in our backyard, we truly have found the best-of-both worlds here in Noord. A great great place to live, for both us and the kids!

summary: A National Monument only 10 min away from Dam Square and Central Station. Bikes included!  Renovated in 2013. Luxury appliances. Nespresso, Private Parking. Rain shower. Great bed. Sun-filled garden. Welcome gift basket.
space: A unique national monument, in a former village thats has been enclosed by the city and protected as national heritage by the state. Even our Amsterdam friends feel like a tourist when they are here! The house has been architecturally re-designed just last year.  We worked on it for a full year, restoring original elements while creating a light filled modern space. We have a high-end kitchen with a kitchen island, a SMEG oven, Nespresso Machine, silent dishwasher and many other appliances. The house also features a luxury bathroom with heated floor tiles, a walk-in rain shower and an extra shower head (working simultaneously), dimmed lighting etc. Downstairs we have an open floor plan, creating space and light with a view of the old church and the chestnut tree out  front and open nature view out back. The L shape allows for separate seating and dining areas. The big garden doors allow you to bring the outside in and the 4 skylights really connect the house with it's lovely surroundin

neighborhood_overview: Enjoy everything the city has to offer, yet feel like you're staying on the country side.. Enjoy the hustle and bustle of the city center one day and take a bike ride towards the traditional villages of Holland such as Monikkendam the next.  We are located at 'Meerpad' which means lake path.  The small lake is enjoyed by kids for swimming in summer and skating in winter. On the other side we have the Vliegenbos (a city forest) perfect for your morning jog!  Around the corner you find the Nieuwendammerdijk, Famous Dutch Heritage with a Golden Age Captain's houses, a cute harbor and a lovely cafe called 't Sluisje.  We will provide you with a detailed map so you can find the nearest supermarkets, bakeries etc.  Our neighborhood is very popular for walking and biking tours. (Get used to people passing the house and pointing excitedly ;-)) We will provide you with detailed directions.
notes: We offer you a unique experience. There are no other areas within the city that offer you this type of living.
transit: There are multiple bus connections close by, taking you to Central Station within 10 minutes. From there you can walk anywhere within the city center, or take a tram to any other neighborhood, such as the Museum Square. You can also take one of our bikes and use the ferry that leaves every 5 minutes, connecting you with the city center. We will provide you with all the information you need to make the most out of your stay.
access: Please feel free to use your house as it is your home. We have put so much love and effort in this place and would love to share this with guests from all over the world.
interaction: We have just moved to this house, for reviews on me as a host, please check out my other listings.
house_rules: Our house is made from wood. So please be very mindful of gas, fire etc. We have put a lot of time, love (and money) in this house. So we are looking for guests who will use your house as a quiet and comfortable abode while visiting the Amsterdam or other parts of the Netherlands.
host_about:
I love unexpected smiles, I love not wanting to finish a book, I love that special moment when you take the first bite of something really delicious and your face gets all crazy, I love getting lost in foreign cities while pretending I live there, I love hearing stories from cab drivers, cashiers and concierges because they make your anonymous day so personal, I love it when you admit something silly and then the other person starts to laugh and admits to the same thing and you feel so normal and connected, I love taking naps after lunch, I love giving out energy and ignite something or someone, I love understanding new bits and pieces about myself and the world, I love dressing up on a dull tuesday morning, I love meditating and yoga, I love uncool second hand stores with all their junk and gems, I love to create new projects, ideas and plays, I love to hang around the house with friends and so much more.

My husband Jurre and I love renting out our home because it provides us with a reason to travel :)  We have truly enjoyed seeing our home through foreign eyes, appreciating it anew when we are back in the city.

Oh and some stats too of course:  32 years old, freelance actress. I studied Acting in NYC and I also have a  Master's in Communication from the University of Amsterdam. I also completed a Yoga Teacher Training in Rishikesh India but that’s just for fun ;-)

There's lots of windows throughout the house so light everywhere. The house is 110m2 and has 2 floors. Inna & I live on the lower floor where we have our bedroom, living room, kitchen and bathroom. There are 2 AirBnB bedrooms upstairs that share a bathroom. Each room has a small kitchen with fridge, water cooker and microwave.  Please note that even though, the stove appears in the pictures, it is unconnected for safety reasons, so guests cannot use it. However, the small kitchen corner is convenient to make any other small quick meals. There's free parking close by and we love this neighborhood! We look forward to meeting you here.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is very peaceful and near the city center. It is very easy to get to the house from the Central Station. It is 2-3 minutes ferry ride that goes every 3 minutes during the day and every 12 minutes during the late hours (after 21:00). Once you cross the IJ canal, it is 10 minutes walk to the house. The ferry goes 24/7. I enjoy the ferry rides to the center and back it's nice to go over the water and with great view and boats passing by Amsterdam.  There are 3 supermarkets close to the house, and one of them offers great cheap deals for breakfast, lunch and dinner. This part of Amsterdam also offers great dinning experiences and fun things to do such as NDSM shipyard, local flea market, EYE film museum and much more. On arrival I'm happy to tell you everything Amsterdam has to offer! transit: The easiest way to get to the house from the airport is to take a train. It is 15 minutes ride and it costs 4.20,-. I always advice our guests to rent bicycles for the city to have the most convenient way to discover the city at your own pace. It is around 12,- per day (inc. insurance) and you can lock the bicycles outside of the house.

Amsterdam Noord has become one of the trendiest neighborhoods of Amsterdam if not THE trendiest. That is because of the festivals, the giant flee market, all the new restaurants, the beautiful and interesting film museum and all the artists who have their studios here. The most agreeable thing of our neighborhood is the calmness and the green with all the flowers!  Two ferryboats will bring you for free in 5 minutes to Central Station if you want to visit the city Centre with its world famous musea, its canals, its beautiful neighborhoods and shopping centers. neighborhood_overview: Noord is extremely close to Amsterdam Central Station, and thereby totally convenient for anywhere you may want to go in Amsterdam, the Netherlands, Europe. It's so fun to ride the free ferry for 5 minutes and arrive at the station! Amsterdam Noord itself is a happening neighborhood: the Brooklyn of Amsterdam, where many Amsterdammers, tourists, and others come for music festivals and concerts at Tolhuistuin and Cafe Noorderlicht, to name just a couple of the venues, to see films and visit the museum exhibitions in the beautiful Eye Film Institute, to visit markets and cafes, and to have the best views of Amsterdam across the river! Hop over to old Amsterdam for the classic historical setting, and come home to the cutting edge and artsy, modern Noord!
notes: There is a cat who lives here. She mostly keeps to herself. Please make sure she has water and his cat food once every day or every other day, and please don't feed her other food.

host_about:
Hi! My name is Nikky Ligthart. 
I am 27 years old and I live with my boyfriend Mike in our apartment in Amsterdam. I work for a big theatre in Amsterdam, so I love to go to plays. I have a lot of friends whom I often go to restaurants/bars with, to eat or drink something.  I play football two times a week. 

I live for 10 years in Amsterdam now, from which 6 years in Amsterdam Noord, the upcoming part of Amsterdam. There is a lot to do in Amsterdam Noord but if you want to go to the city center, it's just a 10 minutes walk to Central Station. The ferryboat goes every 5 minutes so thats an experience by itself! If you rent a bike you can see a lot of Amsterdam. The typical Amsterdam buildings, canals, streets, the many people by bike, museums, the Dutch people and more!

Hotspots in Amsterdam Noord:
-Pllek
-De Ceuvel
-Tolhuistuin
-Eye Museum

Good restaurants in Amsterdam Noord:
-Pllek 
-Loetje aan het IJ
-Smaaqt
-De goudfazant
-Stork

Al hotspots above are within 5 a 10 minutes by bicycle from our apartment! 

Amsterdam is a busy/load city, so our apartment is the excellent choice if you want to be in the city center within 10 minutes, but also want some peace. There is not a lot noise in the street, you can park your car for free in the front of the apartment and you're in a real Amsterdam neighborhood. 

The apartment is 90 m2 and has two levels. First level has a nice living room, a kitchen with a little balcony were you can eat something. 
Upstairs you'll find the master bedroom with kingsize bed and a nice bathroom with a bath.

If you have any questions you can always email me! 

I hope to meet you and that you have a pleasant stay in Amsterdam!

Greetz Nikky

neighborhood_overview: Noord Amsterdam North has an industrial feel and became one of the coolest neighbourhoods over the last years. More and more hotspots are popping up! Visit urban beaches like Café de Ceuvel and Pllek! Both perfect spots to relax and enjoy the warm weather on the waterfront. Other nice places overlooking the IJ-lake are film museum EYE (enjoy the sunset on their beautiful terrace!), seafood restaurant Stork and THT restaurant. One of our favourite areas in Amsterdam North is the NDSM Wharf. Known as one of the best festival locations of Amsterdam. North is also the place to be for vintage and thrift shopping. You can’t miss the monthly flea market in the IJ-hallen, a true second hand heaven.
access: You will access to the entire apartment. Make yourself at home!

house_rules: Treat the apartment as if it were your own and keep in mind that you have neighbours. The apartment is a regular home not an after hours club, so no parties, no drugs, no loud music/TV, etc. Police will fine when complaints are made after 23:00 (11pm) or before 07:00 (7am). At time of departure: make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done, the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean. Smoking of any kind is not allowed, this may also result in a triggering of the fire alarm. All keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee. Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment. If host is not informed of defects, host cannot be held liable for resulting damage to personal items.

neighborhood_overview: Our house is located in the upcoming Amsterdam North. Very child friendly neighborhood with lots of playgrounds. Perfect for families! It's a calm area, yet very close by the buzz of the city center. It's a 10 minute walk to the free ferry which brings you in only 3 min to Amsterdam Central Train Station.
transit: Free car parking in front of the house. At the backside from Central Station you take the free ferry called "Buiksloterweg" which takes you in 3 min. to the North side. The ferry goes during the day every 6 minutes and from 21:00 to 07:00 every 12 min.  When you arrive at the North side with the ferry it is a 10 min. walk to our house. By bus (euro 2.90 p/p): At the North side you can take the bus 38 direction -Elzenhagen Noord- and get out at -Hagedoornplein-. The bus ride takes 5 min.
access: During your stay we will be on holiday.  The whole house of 150 square meters will be yours.
interaction: In case you have any questions or problems during your stay, you can always contact Daniel's mother and Kim's sister. They live very close by. Of course you can also contact us directly by mail/phone. We will be in the South of France We have 2 sweet lady cats. They will be in the house. Daniel's mother and Kim's sister can come to the house to take care of them during your stay. This takes about 10 min per day and can be done at a time you prefer... They only need some dry food to eat  and water to drink:). but it's also possible that you take care of them. Just please let us know us what you prefer :).
house_rules: Smoking only allowed on the terrace or in the kitchen No music or loud talking in the evening/night on the terrace. We trust you to take care of the house if it where yours.  Please always lock the front door.
host_about: Hi, nice to meet you fellow travellers. We are Daniel (38) and Kim (37), and together with our wonderful 2 sons (4 and 7) and 2 cats we live since 7 years on the North side of Amsterdam.  We love travelling, interior design, art, fashion, flee markets and up- and recycling . We work in the fashion industry. We love to live here with our kids as the city center is very close but we can also enjoy the nature in a  lovely forest which is a 5 minute walk from our house. The beach is only a 30 min. train ride from Central station. Our passion is to make you feel at home! Hope to welcome you soon!

The dining room has room for ten people (baby chair also available), just like the living room with tv. That last part of the houseboat lies totally under the water level, and you can stare all day (or wave, if you like) at all the sailing boats passing by. neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North boasts the best of contrasting worlds: vast green expanses and charming little villages plus some of the city's most cutting-edge architecture, exciting festivals, artist studios and stylish waterside hangouts with beautiful terraces. In recent years North has become a creative hub, with artists’ cooperatives and youth brands such as MTV, IDTV and Red Bull attracted by the converted factory buildings and hangars. A smorgasbord of new restaurants, bars and shops have followed suit, many sitting pretty on the sunny side of the IJ-facing waterfront.
transit: To get to the city center of Amsterdam, there are several possibilities. * It is a six minute walk to the bus stop (bus 32) and then a ten minute drive to Central Station. * You can rent bicycles upon your arrival (at Central Station, for example) and bike ten minutes to the free ferry between Amsterdam-Noord and the city centre. * You can go by car, it is a ten minute drive to the centre. Here you can park free. * And if you like you can even walk there, it's about thirty minutes before you reach the free ferry to the city centre. This ferry continuous all night. Other shopping centre and several supermarkets are close by, as well as parks, small playgrounds, hiking and biking trails and of course your private swimming pool: the river our boat lies in.
interaction: When you visit our place, it will be all yours and therefore we won't be anywhere near unless you need us. Of course we will answer all the questions you might have on forehand. During your stay you can always contact us and we will provide our help as soon as possible.
house_rules: *No bachelor- or other parties on this houseboat * If you care for a sigaret, please don't do it inside or at our piere in front of the boat. * Our neighbors like their quiet time after ten pm and we kindly ask you to make (loud) conversations or phone calls inside the house rather than on the terraces. *Same as first note: please know that our house is no partyboat. Enjoy your stay, and care about our personal belongings and the peace of our neighbours!

neighborhood_overview: Away from the crowded, touristy streets, but at only 10 minutes from the city centre you find this nice, safe and quiet neighbourhood. A good night sleep is guaranteed!  Amsterdam North is a very booming area with exclusive restaurants, bars like Eye, Pllek, Noorderlicht, Café De Ceuvel and many more.  Around the corner is a park and many nice play yards for children. Around the corner there are a few little stores to buy groceries (Sneeuwbalstraat & Azaleastraat) and a bio store at Kamerfoeliestraat.  Also there are a few restaurants. The two Thai places at Kamperfoeliestraat have delicious food. Two blocks from the house there is bakery Isken to buy delicious bread and pasteries.  By bike, car or public transport you can go to the bigger shopping areas in North like Buikslotermeerplein and Banne shopping mall.  Also there is a local market on every wednesday, friday and saturday at Mosplein (10 minutes walking distance). At 3 minutes walking distance you'll find a newly built swimmin
transit: Free parking in front of the house.  Every 5 to 10 minutes there goes a public bus to the city centre which takes 10 minutes. You can take bus 34 & Bus 35 from bus stop Sneeuwbalstraat at Kamperfoelieweg. At 10 minutes biking distance you can take the free ferry, from where it is 2 minutes to the Central Station. (Ferry Buiksloterweg)  From the airport you take any train to Amsterdam Central Station and than bus 34 or 35 to bus stop Sneeuwbalstraat. (30 minutes travel in total)
access: You'll have the complete house (53m2) for yourself, including: private entrance on the first floor,  living room, bathroom/toilet and open kitchen on the second floor, bedroom and washroom (washing machine) on the third floor.
interaction: If there is anything you need feel free to ask me!
house_rules: Please treat the apartment with respect, like you would treat your own place.  No smoking inside. Please leave your shoes in the hallway downstairs. No animals. Always lock the door when you leave the house. For the rest just enjoy the house: mi casa es tu casa
host_about:
My name is Floortje and I'm 38 years old. I'm very happy with my boyfriend and our 2 year old son. We love to travel the world and meet all different kind of people and other cultures. We like to travel very primitive, with a back pack and also more luxureous.  
I feel that Airbnb is a nice way to experience the local way of life. That's one of the reasons why I want to offer my house to other travelers in the world. 
I hope you feel at home just as much as we do.... Enjoy Amsterdam to the max!

neighborhood_overview: According to the New York Times, Amsterdam-Noord (Amsterdam-North),  is one of the most hip and happening neighbourhoods in the world. Located  in between the bustling city centre and the rural Waterland, Amsterdam-Noord is the 'best of both worlds' spot for you to start exploring the Dutch capital and its surroundings. Most Amsterdammers use the free ferry to go to 'Noord'. This complimentary boat ride operates 24/7 and brings you from the jetty at the back of Central Station to the sunny side of the river IJ. On the northern banks you will find the spectacular designed EYE building (accommodating a cinematography museum, restaurant and cinema), the stage and restaurant Tolhuistuin and the soon to be opened ADAM tower... Our house is situated at 2km from these hotspots in the green and quiet Bloemenbuurt (flower district), a popular residential area with low-rise, terraced streets, named after flower bearing plants and herbs. The Bloemenbuurt dates back to the mid 1920s, created to ho
transit: By car: easy accessible from ring road A10, free unlimited parking in the street. By foot/bike/ferry: The complimentary ferry to Amsterdam Centraal Station is only 2 kilometers away. Within a 25 minute walk or a 10 minute bike ride, you will reach this free ferry - Buiksloterwegveer - which operates 24/7 . Departures during day time every 6 minutes at night every 12 minutes. By bus/public transport: Bus stop Sneeuwbalstraat is located at 400 meters, with a super frequent  bus service - Line 34 and 35 - from/to Centraal Station (in 10 minutes) during day time.  The night service Line 763 runs every 30 minutes in the weekend and once every 60 minutes on weekdays.
access: Ground floor: spacious and light living room and kitchen (including stove/ electric oven, microwave and dishwasher), toilet and hallway with stairs giving access to the first floor. The two bedrooms (including two double beds/a single mattrass is available) are situated on the first floor as well as the basic bathroom with shower.
interaction: Living in Amsterdam and working in the local tourism industry for over 15 years, I know most attractions, museums and tours by experience. Hospitality is my middle name, and therefore I am looking forward to provide you with all the information, tips and tricks you need for a comfortable and unforgettable stay in Amsterdam. When I am not in town (since you will be living in my place) nearby living friends and/or neighbours will be stand by in case of undesirable events or emergencies.
house_rules: We expect our guests to behave quietly and respect our property and neighbours. This means: - no pets - no smoking indoors (feel free to smoke in the garden) - no parties/no loud music - it is not allowed to invite people over
host_about:
Hi, my name is Kris!

In the late seventies I was born on the Frisian island Ameland. After growing up in Harlingen and studying tourism in Groningen, I moved over to the one place that stole my heart: Amsterdam.

Since 2011 I live together with my beautiful and creative girlfriend Cynthia in the cosy and beloved family home that you are about to rent. Cynthia and I both love to travel (mainly backpacking, scuba diving/snorkelling) and instead of asking our neighbours to water the plants while we're away, we recently decided to join the Airbnb network.

Where Cynthia loves to draw and paint, I personally never get tired from cycling, skating, walking, running or kayaking through the city and its surroundings. We are both big fans of the Amsterdam cultural activities and nightlife. Together with our friends we often check in at the local bars, restaurants, clubs, museums, theatres, concerts, festivals and techno parties. 

Cynthia and I place people above material things, nevertheless our house is decorated with quite a lot of books, drawings, memories, photo's and  souvenirs from our adventures and travels. Most stuff meaningless to others, but priceless to us.

We are looking forward to welcome relaxed and responsible guests in our residence. So feel free to request, and we will get back to you as soon as possible...

Dan ben je van harte welkom!!  We want your stay to be a happy one.
host_about:
Hello,

We as a family live in Amsterdam with a lot of fun, pleasure and gratitude. We want to welcome you to this beautiful an open minded place.

Besides work and hobbies: inspiration, vocation, work, career and self-confidence, we as a family like it very much to open our doors to guests from around the world, to exercise our languages ​​and exchange tips.

In our spare time we enjoy running and walking outside and watching good movies curled up together on the sofa and enjoy each others company. We love reading before going to bed, on a sunday-afternoon or in bed. 

We love the sound of Chopin but also westernized indian music from Deva Premal. We enjoy eating out, organic food, recipe's from the oven, warm quiches, pies but also fish, lots of fish and vegetables.

We love to travel and want to see so many countries and places: an elephant trek in India, a jungle tour and diving in Thailand, on a camel through the Sahara and in a jeep from South to North Africa, but we also enjoy sightseeing and shopping in San Fransico, Florence, Naples and Venice. There is so much to see and discover ..

In Amsterdam, our doors are open for you.

Judith & family

Hallo,

Wij als gezin wonen in Amsterdam met veel plezier en dankbaarheid. Wij heten je van harte welkom om deze prachtige een open minded plek te zien en ervaren.

Naast werk en hobby's: inspiratie, roeping, werk, carrière en zelfvertrouwen, genieten we als een gezin van het openstellen van onze deuren open voor gasten uit de hele wereld, om onze talen te oefenen en tips uit te wisselen.

In onze vrije tijd genieten we van hardlopen en wandelen en kijken we opgerold op de bank naar goede films genietend van elkaars gezelschap. We houden van lezen en voorlezen voor het slapen gaan, of lezen op een zondag-middag als de kinderen lekker in de kamer spelen.

We houden van het geluid van Chopin, maar ook verwesterde Indiase muziek zoals die van Deva Premal. We houden van yoga, stilte, meditatie. We genieten van uit eten gaan, biologisch voedsel, recept komt uit de oven, warme quiches, taarten, maar ook vis, veel vis en groenten. Maar het meest genieten we van grappen en de humor tussen ons.

Wij houden van reizen en willen nog heel veel landen en plaatsen zien en ervaren: een olifant trektocht in India, een jungle tour en duiken in Thailand, op een kameel door de Sahara en in een jeep van Zuid naar Noord-Afrika, maar we ook genieten van bezienswaardigheden en winkelen in San Fransico, Florence, Napels en Venetië. Er is zoveel te zien en te ontdekken ..

In Amsterdam staan onze deuren voor je open.

Judith & gezin

host_about:
Ervaren bemanning

Aan boord van de “Catharina van Mijdrecht” bent u in de handen van een vakkundige en ervaren bemanning. Met hun jarenlange ervaring weten zij elke zeiltocht tot een onvergetelijke ervaring te maken. Jos Rodewijk is de schipper die jullie veilig over de woelige baren voert. Danny Honig is de gastvrouw en zorgt er voor dat het jullie op culinair gebied aan niets ontbreekt. Bij gelegenheid wordt het team uitgebreid met ervaren freelancers, bijvoorbeeld voor uw trainingen.

Passie voor water
U bent in handen van een ervaren bemanningGeboren en getogen in het Zuid-Hollands plassengebied leerde ik als snel omgaan met het water. Op mijn twaalfde zeilde ik al zelfstandig. Toen ik later van deze passie voor water mijn beroep kon maken greep ik die kans met beide handen aan.
Op mijn schip draait het om de beleving van mijn gasten. Of ze nu een paar uurtjes of meerdere dagen aan boord zijn, mijn streven is om ze een belevenis mee te geven waar ze het nog lang over zullen hebben. Jong of oud, gepassioneerd zeiler of passieve genieter, iedereen voelt zich thuis op de Catharina van Mijdrecht.
Jos Rodewijk, schipper.

Passie voor lekker eten
Ervaren bemanningAls telg uit een bekend soepmakersgeslacht zat de passie voor  koken al in de genen. Met ouders die bovendien op de Holland-Amerika Lijn voeren combineer ik nu beide werelden door de catering te verzorgen aan boord van de Catharina van Mijdrecht. Het is altijd een weer een uitdaging om onder de soms lastige omstandigheden aan boord toch een lekkere maaltijd op tafel te zetten. Met veel creativiteit en passie probeer ik regelmatig nieuwe gerechten uit. Ik ben pas tevreden als mijn gasten het zijn.
Daniëlle (Danny) Honig, catering.

neighborhood_overview: In the hip & trendy northern part of Amsterdam, you have the best of both worlds! On the one hand, you can be in the city center in 5 minutes by bus or 15 minutes bike ride including the ferry. On the other hand, within a 10 minute bike ride, you can be biking or hiking in the beautiful Dutch countryside. The northern part of Amsterdam is currently the most upcoming, dynamic and exciting part of the city. New cafés and restaurants, galleries, art projects, innovative architecture, and the likes. The new EYE film theater and cafe/restaurant is one of the most impressive places and view points in the city, the new THT cultural center and restaurant, etc. are all around the corner. The good thing is that our neighbourhood is also residential and calm. Many families live here. We live opposite a park and around the corner of a fairytale forest. As said, we are also nearby the countryside. The pitoresque little harbour of the Nieuwerdammerdijk, including cute old Dutch café 't Sluisje, is a
notes: We also have a lovely cottage in our garden that we rent out to guests. As they have a private entrance at the back of the cottage and it is on the other side of the house, you will therefore hardly notice them. We never really do! They do have access to our garden.
transit: There are plenty of options to get around with public transport. The train from the airport brings you to the Central train station in 15 minutes. From there two buses 32 and 33 leave every 5 minutes to take you within 5 minutes directly to our place.
access: You will have access to all our facilities including  flat screen TV, all-inn kitchen, washing machine, dryer, wireless internet, etc. etc.
interaction: Depending on you, we can provide information about the city and all connectivity, etc.

name: Sunfilled Room in 3 Story House
summary: Our beautiful, four-bedroom house filled with light is in Amsterdam-North. Just two minutes from the ferry boat that takes you across to Central Station for free, the location is ideal. Tranquil and green, yet extremely close to the centre of town.
space: What's unique about our place is the fact that we are so close to all the great things Amsterdam has to offer, and we also happen to be on one of the most peaceful streets in town. We're surrounded by beautiful trees and our balcony is ideal for relaxing on a warm, sunny day. We don't smoke inside the house, but smoking is absolutely allowed on the balcony. We have two toilets, one on the first floor, and one on the second floor. The house can fit a lot of people. We have four bedrooms, one of which will be taken by our roommate. Two rooms will be available to guests: the Sky Palace, which is the beautiful big attic room with a double bed in the loft and possibility for another double bed under the loft, and the Sunfilled Room on our second floor, which also gets incredible light all day and has a beautiful view of the trees on our green street, and has a very comfortable double bed. We even have a sleeping couch in the living room which pulls out to a lovely double bed (and you'll hav

neighborhood_overview: Our house is located in the north of Amsterdam, which is quickly becoming one of the most interesting neighbourhoods in town. Just minutes away are the Eye Film Museum, great cafés and restaurants by the water, an organic food market every Friday, parks and a beautiful forest, and the NDSM-warf (10 minutes by bike, or take the ferry boat from Central Station to NDSM) where you'll find Europe's biggest monthly flea market De Ijhallen, restaurants, cafés, and festivals in the summer.
notes: We have two bunnies that are very friendly and easy-going. They mostly live on the balcony. Our roommate will take care of them, but of course you can play with them as much as you like!
transit: The ferry boat that goes from Central Station to Ijplein is ideal, since from there it's just a couple of minutes walk to our house. The boat runs from 6.20 am till midnight. The Buiksloterweg ferry, which is only a little bit farther from our house (about a ten minute walk) goes all night, so it's always easy to get home. Here are the boat timetables: (URL HIDDEN) From Central Station you can get all the buses and trams and metros you need to get around town easily, and it also serves as a perfect location to start wandering from!
access: We have an amazing kitchen with a kitchen island/bar stool area that we love to use as our dinner table because it's right next to the balcony and gets lots of light. Feel free to play our piano as much as you want (just don't play too much at night as the neighbours need their sleep!) The bathroom has an amazing shower and bathtub, there are tons of towels and a washer and dryer for you to use. You'll share these spaces with our roommate, but since he'll be in and out, you'll have a lot of space.
interaction: We're a group of four friends living together. This summer, three of us will be travelling so that leaves one of us in the house. He will be here to welcome you, give you the keys to the house, show you around, and answer any questions you have. He will be working a lot so will mostly be around in the evenings. Just make yourself at home and enjoy the house and the city.
house_rules: Make yourself as comfortable as possible, enjoy our beautiful house and neighbourhood! Just try to be mindful of the neighbours. Generally noise isn't a problem here, but please mind the obvious things like blasting music at night.

host_about:
Hello! 

I'm Marleen, 37 years. I live with my husband and three children at the age of 2, 4 and 6 years in Amsterdam. Kasper (my husband) and I both work and therefore we love to go on trips ourselves when we have the time. Hiking, skiing and relaxing in a different environment. 

Last year we have traveled around Europe for three months. That was the first time we rented out our house. That time we used an agent. Now we rent our home directly which makes it more fun since you have direct contact with the tenants. Now we learn about why they wnat to visit Amsterdam and are happy to help them with tips for good restaurants, fun activities in and around the city. 

Our house is wonderfully light, spacious and fully equipped. Also an ideal place for children to play and a garden where you can enjoy a good glass of wine in the sun after a day of sight seeing Amsterdam. 

Hope to see you, 

Greets 
Marleen

neighborhood_overview: If you don’t want to cook, or simply want to have a night out you can find this within walking distance. The EYE Film museum has a beautiful restaurant with a view over the IJ river and city, of course you can also go there for a drink and see a movie at the cinema. The Tolhuistuin and cafe De Pont also serves food and during summertime you can enjoy concerts & festivals at the Tolhuistuin. There is a local street market, 'van de Pekmarkt', every Wednesday, Friday & Saturday, it’s a 10 minute walk and has many little shops as well.

host_about:

At home in Amsterdam we love cooking and spending time with friends and family at the diner table. After traveling it is great to come at home, look out over the water and bike through the city!
