description: Our beautiful, four-bedroom house filled with light is in Amsterdam-North. Just two minutes from the ferry boat that takes you across to Central Station for free, the location is ideal. Tranquil and green, yet extremely close to the centre of town. What's unique about our place is the fact that we are so close to all the great things Amsterdam has to offer, and we also happen to be on one of the most peaceful streets in town. We're surrounded by beautiful trees and our balcony is ideal for relaxing on a warm, sunny day. We don't smoke inside the house, but smoking is absolutely allowed on the balcony. We have two toilets, one on the first floor, and one on the second floor. The house can fit a lot of people. We have four bedrooms, one of which will be taken by our roommate. Two rooms will be available to guests: the Sky Palace, which is the beautiful big attic room with its own sink, a double bed in the loft and possibility for another double bed under the loft, and the Sunfilled Room
neighborhood_overview: Our house is located in the north of Amsterdam, which is quickly becoming one of the most interesting neighbourhoods in town. Just minutes away are the Eye Film Museum, great cafés and restaurants by the water, an organic food market every Friday, parks and a beautiful forest, and the NDSM-warf (10 minutes by bike, or take the ferry boat from Central Station to NDSM) where you'll find Europe's biggest monthly flea market De Ijhallen, restaurants, cafés, and festivals in the summer.
notes: We have two bunnies that are very friendly and easy-going. They mostly live on the balcony. Our roommate will take care of them, but of course you can play with them as much as you like!
transit: The ferry boat that goes from Central Station to Ijplein is ideal, since from there it's just a couple of minutes walk to our house. The boat runs from 6.20 am till midnight. The Buiksloterweg ferry, which is only a little bit farther from our house (about a ten minute walk) goes all night, so it's always easy to get home. Here are the boat timetables: (URL HIDDEN) From Central Station you can get all the buses and trams and metros you need to get around town easily, and it also serves as a perfect location to start wandering from!
access: We have an amazing kitchen with a kitchen island/bar stool area that we love to use as our dinner table because it's right next to the balcony and gets lots of light. Feel free to play our piano as much as you want (just don't play too much at night as the neighbours need their sleep!) The bathroom has an amazing shower and bathtub, there are tons of towels and a washer and dryer for you to use. You'll share these spaces with our roommate, but since he'll be in and out, you'll have a lot of space.
interaction: We're a group of four friends living together. This summer, three of us will be travelling so that leaves one of us in the house. He will be here to welcome you, give you the keys to the house, show you around, and answer any questions you have. He will be working a lot so will mostly be around in the evenings. Just make yourself at home and enjoy the house and the city.
house_rules: Make yourself as comfortable as possible, enjoy our beautiful house and neighbourhood! Just try to be mindful of the neighbours. Generally noise isn't a problem here, but please mind the obvious things like blasting music at night.

name: Romantic Dutch house on old dike!
summary: Our wooden historical monument (+garden), built in 1748, is located just above Amsterdam center, in a very attractive, safe and friendly area called Nieuwendam.  Parking is FREE and bus or bike rides take only 20 minutes to town. Min. stay 3 nights.
space: You stay in the "downthedike" part of an authentic historical (rijks)monument, with all modern facilities one needs: wonderful Auping boxspring beds, (2x200/90cm), a massagechair to relax on, your own bathroom, a MAC to use. Enjoy the garden or watch life pass by on the frontbench. The kitchen is shared with us , but we will mainly use another one, upstairs, were we live.

neighborhood_overview: The up-and-coming north of Amsterdam is one of the favorite spots to go and explore. There’s so much going on, and the neighborhood is becoming increasingly popular with locals and tourists alike. Near to our house you will find good restaurants like "the Goudfazant" or "Stork", a bit further cultural hotspots like "The Ceuvel" and "Pllek". Watch a movie in EYE and have a drink on their terras overlooking the water and town. When you have enough time, DO visit ( By bus, car or bike)  typical Dutch villages in Waterland like Durgerdam, Ransdorp, Broek in Waterland, Monnickendam, Marken ( traditional costumes still worn) etc.
notes: 5 minutes walk on the dyke will bring you to one of Amsterdam's nicest and oldest cafe's on the waterfront: het Sluysje. Have a drink ( or homemade soup/salad or Dutch tapas called "bitterballen"), and meet the locals inside or on the terras. In the summer weekends there is a boat connecting Nieuwendam to the C.S. or other parts of town across the water.
transit: 5 minutes walk from the house is a busstop ( line 32). The bus will bring you to the Central station in 20 minutes.  In front of our house or in the rear, you can park your car for free. When you come by plane, you can take a train to Amsterdam C.S. ( 10 minutes) and from there, walk up to the rear side and 1 floor up to the buses, you take nr 32 direction Buikslotermeerplein. Get off, either before or after the Purmerplein and walk towards the Dike ( to your right)
access: The (red) door at the side of the house, will be your entrance (not too high, so watch your head!) To get your fresh bread in the morning at the bakery just behind the house on a (round) 'square' ( the Purmerplein, with restaurants, postoffice, pharmacy and shops) you can leave and come back via the gardendoor as well.
interaction: We speak Dutch, English, German, French and are learning Spanish.  We We travelled a lot ourselves, so we know the importance of "feeling at home while on the road". That's why we want you to feel free to use our music-instalation, kitchen utensils, books, massage-chair, keyboard and PC...  We may be outdoors now and then but when we are home we love to help you to make the most out of your stay.
house_rules: We provide (self-service) coffee/thea, cereal, jus and milk, beschuit (dutch round toasted bread) met hagelslag, cheese, eggs and fruits for breakfast. Fresh bread can be purchased on the Purmerplein, right behind the house. You can also do some cooking in the kitchen if you like . Smoking is no problem in the garden or on the bench in front of the house.
host_about: We are Toon&Anneke, used to run a catering business for 25 years, now enjoying more time off, making trips with our camper, citytrips, enjoying opera, ballet, theater, musea, festivals and concerts in and around town. There is so much going on in Amsterdam nowadays. Also Amsterdam north( above the IJ) is booming with new and very special cafe's, restaurants, cultural events etc)

name: Sunny apt close to Central Station
summary: Sunny and private apartment in a calm area only minutes away from Amsterdams Central Station. Close to Damsquare, the red light district, Jordaan & 9 streets, while still being able to enjoy all the benefits of a quite neighborhood.
space: Take the free three minute 'IJpleinveer' ferry from Central Station and walk ca. 8 more minutes to the apartment. (At night, or very early in the morning, use the 24/7 'Buiksloterwegveer' ferry in which case the walk is five minutes longer.)  Amsterdam is a very walkable city and the red light district, Jordaan area, nine streets, dam square etc. are all within walking distance. I recommend renting a bike if you want to experience Amsterdam like a local: it's fun, convenient and you'll get a decent workout while you're at it.  If you want to stay a little longer.. there's a large supermarket closeby. While you're here: feel free to watch some of the DVDs or read a book if you see something you like.

Enjoy the view from the free ferry to and from Central Station, get your groceries at 'Foodmarkt', a hip supermarket that combines grocery shopping with live cooking, watch a movie at 'Eye' the filmmuseum and cinema with a spectacular view over Central Station, enjoy authentic Italian pizza with a great view over the river IJ at 'Il Pecorino', all within walking distance from the apartment.
house_rules: Please respect the neighbours and don't make too much noise in the evening. This is a no smoking apartment. No cats allowed due to allergies of the home owner. Let's discuss it if you'd like to bring a dog with you.
host_about:
Hi, I'm Jurrie, I live and work in Amsterdam and theatre & traveling are my main passions. I try to see as much of the world as I can, and often prefer to hop from one place to the next after a couple of days. 
I enjoy exploring new places, getting lost in foreign cities and am a sucker for David Mitchell stories, fancy rooftop bars & everything remotely connected to both ice cream & chocolate. I plan to live in a penthouse with a rather amazing view one day, but for now it's a cute one bedroom apartment pretty close to Amsterdams Central Station, and you can rent it if you want to spend some time in this amazing city. :)

I like the combination of a very peaceful and quiet neighborhood while the city is ver
neighborhood_overview: I like the combination of a very peaceful and quiet neighborhood while the city is very nearby. I also enjoy the ferryrides to the center and back very much. Looking over the water, it's just a nice five-minute break in the day. And although the center has obviously more to offer then this neighborhood it's fascinating to see this part of the city change rapidly: it's getting more attractive every day. With the Eye filmmuseum, the Tolhuistuin and next year the A'dam Tower there are are some main atttractions just around the corner. At the same time with a 15-minute ride by bike in the other direction you are in the nature and you can jump in the Markermeer and swim outdoors...if the weather is nice which can be a problem now and then :-)
notes: I have been living in Amsterdam for more then ten years now and i like this city a lot. If you are interested in other parts of the city then the well known areas then knock on my door! I might have some suggestions.
transit: It's hard to miss the apartment. From the central station the ferry 'IJ-plein' brings you directly in the street of the apartment. Another five minutes walking and you will find the hammock waiting for you.
access: You get your own pair of keys and the apartment is yours!
interaction: I live in the apartment one floor lower and i like to help, think along or advise about the possibilities  Amsterdam has to offer so feel free to knock on my door.
house_rules: It's a non-smoking apartment. Smoking outside of the window is ok. The view is nice. Just being respectful for the apartment and the neighbours (I am one of them :-))

neighborhood_overview: In the Northern part of Amsterdam, you have the best of both worlds! On the one hand, you can be within 5 minutes busride (or a 12  minute bike ride and a 3-minute boatride) in the city centre. On the other hand, within a 10 minute bikeride, you can be biking or hiking in the beautiful Dutch countryside.    The Northern part of Amsterdam is currently the most upcoming, dynamic and exciting part of the city. It is being discovered by artists and most of the innovations are happening here. There is a great offer of new restaurants and entertainment.   The good thing is that our neighbourhood is also residential and calm. Many families live here. We live opposite a parc and around the corner of a fairytale forest. As said, we are also nearby the countryside.  Finally there is free parking! This is very special, compared to other parts in the city.

Amsterdam Noord has many green parks, open water and canals, little harbors, houseboats and 17th century dike houses. Although it looks like a small picturesque village it is close to the central station, only 10 minutes bike ride or 10 minutes drive to the centre of the city with the lovely canals and museums. name: Houseboat near centre of Amsterdam!
summary: Welcome to our beautiful houseboat in the middle of nature but near the city centre at the same time. Here you can jump out of a window for a cold dip in the river and cycle to the hottest spots in Amsterdam!
space: We offer you a brand new water villa with the romance of passed days and the conveniences and comforts that come with solid ground. Your entrance is the front door on your right at the end of our pier. You'll step into the dining kitchen, of course with all the necessary equipment like a refrigerator, an electric stove and a microwave. A bay window from floor to ceiling leads to your private, floating terrace, for those moments when you prefer the tranquility of the water above a green garden. There is a fully equipped bathroom on the first floor too, with a rain shower, a hand shower, a toilet and a sink. Then you take the stairs down and you'll find the bedroom with a double bed totally below water level. And if requested at your booking, there will be an extra mattress for a child or friend of yours.

neighborhood_overview: Amsterdam North boasts the best of contrasting worlds: vast green expanses and charming little villages plus some of the city's most cutting-edge architecture, exciting festivals, artist studios and stylish waterside hangouts with beautiful terraces. In recent years North has become a creative hub, with artists’ cooperatives and youth brands such as MTV, IDTV and Red Bull attracted by the converted factory buildings and hangars. A smorgasbord of new restaurants, bars and shops have followed suit, many sitting pretty on the sunny side of the IJ-facing waterfront.
transit: To get to the city center of Amsterdam, there are several possibilities. * It is a six minute walk to the bus stop (bus 32) and then a ten minute drive to Central Station. * You can rent bicycles upon your arrival (at Central Station, for example) and bike ten minutes to the free ferry between Amsterdam-Noord and the city centre. * You can go by car, it is a ten minute drive to the centre. Here you can park free. * And if you like you can even walk there, it's about thirty minutes before you reach the free ferry to the city centre. This ferry continuous all night. Other shopping centre and several supermarkets are close by, as well as parks, small playgrounds, hiking and biking trails and of course your private swimming pool: the river our boat lies in.
interaction: When you visit our place, it will be all yours and therefore we won't be anywhere near unless you need us. Of course you can always contact during your stay and we will answer your questions if possible.
house_rules: * If you care for a sigaret, please go outside.  * Our neighbors like their quiet time after eleven pm and we kindly ask you to make (loud) phone calls inside the house rather than on the terraces. * One last note: please know that our house is no partyboat. You are our quest and we ask you to act like one. Enjoy your stay, and care about our personal belongings too.
host_about: 27 jaar en journalist, woonachtig in Amsterdam-Noord. Sportief, reislustig. Samen met Domin heb ik een jonge dochter.

space: Come and stay in our beautiful house in Amsterdam Noord! The house lets in lots of light and there's plenty of space to relax after you have spent your time in the city. There are 2 AirBnB bedrooms upstairs that share a bathroom. Each room has a small kitchen with fridge, water cooker and microwave.  Please note that even though, the stove appears in the pictures, it is unconnected for safety reasons, so guests cannot use it. neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is very peaceful and near the city center. It is very easy to get to the house from the Central Station. It is 2-3 minutes ferry ride that goes every 3 minutes during the day and every 12 minutes during the late hours (after 21:00). Once you cross the IJ canal, it is 10 minutes walk to the house. The ferry goes 24/7. I enjoy the ferry rides to the center and back it's nice to go over the water and with great view and boats passing by Amsterdam.  There are 3 supermarkets close to the house, and one of them offers great cheap deals for breakfast, lunch and dinner. This part of Amsterdam also offers great dinning experiences and fun things to do such as NDSM shipyard, local flea market, EYE film museum and much more. On arrival I'm happy to tell you everything Amsterdam has to offer! name: Spacious & Bright 1918house 200m2
summary: Enjoy Amsterdam at its best! Stay in a classical spacious 1918-dikehouse in a pituresque street of Amsterdam (protected cultural area!) and discover this great city!
space: Our 3-storey-house, located in a protected historical area of Amsterdam, is build in 1918. We've completely renovated it but kept the beautiful classical features, e.g. stained glass, Art Deco-sinks in all bedrooms, etc. So you will enjoy the typical classic 19th century architecture, yet enjoying all the luxuries of a modern home. The house is a typical dikehouse: opening to the garden there's the spacious modern kitchen, a luxurous bathroom with jacuzzi and walk-in-shower, and separate toilet. On the dike-level/first floor there's the livingroom, with en-suite the study. The livingroom - with pianocorner -features large windows opening to the adjacent greenery.  Also on this level there's the 2nd toilet. 2nd floor: you will find 3 bedrooms, which can accomodate up to 6 people (3 x 2). Bedroom 1: 1 kingsize bed, bedroom 2: 1 double bed (140x200), bedroom 3: 2x single beds (90x200). Shower and 3rd toilet are also on this level. And last but not least there's the rooftop-balcony where y

notes: We have one important condition: you can only rent the house if you are willing to feed our cats. They don't need a lot of care, only some fresh water and food every day. Most of the time they're out in the garden, they just sleep inside the house at night. The cats are very sweet and used to children.
transit: Public transport within 150m. Public bus to Central Station takes 10 minutes.

interaction: There's a cleaning service every week. Our housekeeper will make sure the house is clean.

name: Faralda Crane Hotel:  Secret Suite
summary: Rise high above the city bustle in a monumental harbour crane. Enjoy a phenomenal view over Amsterdam from your luxurious design suite or from the hot tub on the top deck of the crane.
space: Enjoy an amazing view over Amsterdam and the river IJ from a luxurious design suite in a monumental harbour crane. When the wind blows, the crane turns, and the view changes! Take the elevator to 40 meters height and enter the classic oriental Secret Suite. Saturated colours become more vibrant and shapes slightly more abstract, but still lush and super comfortable. To make the experience even more perfect, you can relax in a hot tub on the top deck of the crane, overlooking Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview: Faralda Crane Hotel is situated at an old shipyard, but with  different restaurants in walking distance. For instance a high end French restaurant and a funky beach club. Amsterdam Central Station and the city center are just across the river, 15 minutes by  (free) ferry.
transit: From the airport you can take a train to central station (15 minutes). There you exit on the North side, and take the ferry that's to the utmost left of the train station to NDSM-wharf (also 15 minutes). During the crossing you will already see the Faralda Crane, located 600 metres from the ferry stop NDSM, where you get off.  You can park your own car on site for just €7,80 per day (reservation is not needed) or travel in style with a VIP limo from the rental service  close by, that we can arrange for you.

neighborhood_overview: The northern part of Amsterdam is currently the most lively, dynamic and exciting part of the city. New cafes and restaurants, galleries, art projects, innovative architecture. Near-by The EYE film theater and cafe/restaurant is one of the most impressive places and view points in the city, the new THT cultural center and restaurant, etc. are all around the corner.
transit: THE BEST WAY TO GET TO MY PLACE From Schiphol Airport to Central Station by train: - Once you have cleared customs and still in the airport, follow the signs to the train station, which is located underground of a big hall with high ceiling. Don’t forget to buy the train tickets prior to your departure (the machines are yellow and next to the escalators – ask for help if you need any assistance);  - From this hall, go down the escalators to the railway station, but first find out on the boards above the escalators which train will take you to Central Station (Amsterdam Central or Amsterdam CS). The trip will take about 15 minutes if you take the fast train. From Amsterdam Central Station you take the bus 32 or 33 (363 night bus). When you leave Central Station you walk to the bus stop CS IJzijde and then take a bus to my place. The final bus stop when you have to get off is located 2 minutes away from the house and is called Rode Kruisstraat.  You can also use a free ferry between Amst

interaction: The keys will be delivered to you upon arrival and collected upon departure. Feel free to ask me for any tips about Amsterdam :)
house_rules: Your holiday - your time. No one else will be present during your stay. Smoking is allowed but only outside. Please turn off all lights, heating and power when you leave the house. Please, be kind to the neighbours (no parties please!) Animals are not allowed.
host_about:
I am a freelancer who works and enjoys life in Amsterdam. I think this city is a perfect place to stroll around and 'get lost' in, but since I know the neighborhood well, I'd be more than happy to give some nice inside tips of great restaurants, bars and shops.

I love to create and make beautiful & good things happen. I love to eat good food with a nice glass of wine (at home or out), especially with good friends. I like traveling and have been to many places but yet many more to explore!

I look forward to meet you! You are very welcome in my house and wish you will feel at home!

neighborhood_overview: Ideal place for those who love the city, the outdoors and atmosphere. Its just the best of both worlds! It is beautifully situated right at a lovely park with a tennis court, a yoga centre and right at a small harbor. Amsterdam Noord has many green parks, open water and canals, little harbors, houseboats and 17th century dike houses. Although it looks like a small picturesque village it is close to the central station, only 10 minutes bike ride or 10 minutes drive to the centre of the city with the lovely canals and museums. It is a thirty minute drive from the beaches.  At he banks at the North side of the IJ (ten minutes ride) you will find one of the most hipster neighbourhoods in the world.  Previously disused warehouses host creative start-ups, festivals, restaurants and, once a month, mega flea market.

The villa is spacious and light, with all the comfort you need. The surroundings of the house are quiet and peaceful, that is of great comfort after a day in the busy town of Amsterdam. Easy and quick access to the city centre by public transportation.
space: The houseboat has 3 floors, downstairs is the spacious and luxury bedroom with one big double box spring bed, and a beautiful bathroom with rain shower and bath. On the ground floor you will find the fully equipped kitchen with oven, fridge and water cooker. Outside you can enjoy the swim terrace in summer. On the top floor you have access to the light and comfortable living room with pantry, including fridge, water cooker and Nespresso coffee machine, and an outside terrace with table and couch.

neighborhood_overview: IJburg is a modern architectural area with beautiful designed water villa's. The area has all the facilities you need, including supermarkets, nice restaurants and bars and a great beach club called Blijburg. There is also a nice harbor with terraces, where you can enjoy the boats coming in and out of the big lake.
transit: You have easy access to public transport with tram 26 that stops 2 minutes walk from the villa [ it runs every 4 minutes ] The tram will bring you to the inner city in 15 minutes. If you arrive at Schiphol Airport it is 20 minutes by train to Central Station, from there you take tram 26 to IJburg and stop at Steigereiland. The best deal is to by a 1, 2 or 3 day Amsterdam Travel Ticket, unlimited travel across Amsterdam and including an airport return train ticket. You can get it at Schiphol at NS Tickets & Service, AKO bookshops or Holland Tourist Information.
interaction: Ik zal er zijn om je te ontvangen de dag van incheck en bij het uitchecken. Ik kan je tips geven over de leuke plekken van Amsterdam. Als er tijdens je verblijf vragen zijn, kan je me altijd bereiken en als het nodig is, ben ik in 40 minuten in de villa.
house_rules: - Het is niet toegestaan binnen te roken, het gebruik van drugs of te veel alcohol is overal verboden. Geen kaarsen binnen of buiten. Respecteer de privacy van de buren en maak geen lawaai. Laat geen lichten of verwarming aan als je de villa verlaat. - Most important, relax and enjoy your stay!

neighborhood_overview: At the apartment an extensive brochure will be available with information about the apartment, surroundings and tourist options.  Next to the apartment is a small neighborhood store, a five minute walk will get you to the mall with an Albert Heijn supermarket, butcher and pharmacy. In the summer you can swim in the area, its within walking distance of a children's beach located at the Diemerpark and within 10 minutes lies the biggest city beach of Amsterdam called Blijburg.  On the island are some good restaurants where M'Chi is an absolute must to visit!
notes: We aspire to be excellent hosts and our reviews are our proof of this. Feel free to ask any questions you might have and we will be happy to inform you! We are looking forward meeting you! Harold and Tamara
transit: The apartment is perfectly situated for public transport as the tramstop is right in front of the building. The nr. 26 tram will bring you to Amsterdam Central Station (mid-center) in ten minutes and has a high frequency of travel and high quality of service. Previous guests have mentioned the very easy connection to the inner city in their reviews so be sure to get the best of both worlds.. easy access to the touristic sites while having a big modern apartment to leisure in after a long day in the busy center! Travelling from Schiphol Airport is just as easy. You best take the trainservice to Amsterdam Central Station, a high frequency and quality connection. After about 20-25 minutes you arrive at Amsterdam CS. At the square in front of the station the VVV-tourist office is situated which can assist you with the planning of your visit. access: You can make free use of all facilities in the apartment. No smoking in the apartment please. Next to the front door is a hallway leading to the stairwell where you have free space to smoke.
interaction: We will meet you at the apartment when you check-in. After a small tour around the place to explain about e.g. the use of the appliances we will handover you two sets of keys to the apartment.  We are not in the apartment during your stay but are always available by e-mail, telephone or sms/(SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) for any questions or problems you might encounter.. you are our guests!
house_rules: Enjoy the apartment.. have a wonderful stay! We will provide clean towels, you are free to use the washing machine, dryer etc. free of charge. Please note that due to our apartment being located in a residential complex we have set houserules to prevent disturbance to other owners in our building. We are orientated towards families as our area is very childfriendly and offers a nice more relaxed atmosphere than the busy inner center. As we like to keep the good understanding with our neighbours we do not allow stag parties and groups that are made up of just people under 23 years old. Just treat our place as you would be staying in the home of a good friend! We are looking forward meeting you! Harold and Tamara
host_about: Easy going, enjoying life.. family-man with a beautiful wife. 5 year old son and newborn twin boy and girl!

neighborhood_overview: Do you prefer a quiet and green neighbourhood? Then IJburg is the place to be: the first residents established here only several years ago. This new district near Diemerpark consists of a number of artificial islands: Steigereiland, Haveneiland West and East and the Rieteilanden. In the summer you can completely relax at the Theo van Gogh in the Park. One hotspot to check out in IJburg at least once is the urban beach Blijburg. besides sunbathing and eating delicious food, you can enjoy several events. With tramline 16 you are within 10 minutes at central station!
notes: Guests we look for: - Respectful of neighbours (keep level of noise down) - Non-smokers (or smokers that smoke outside) - Above 30 when in a group - Any age if staying as a couple At time of departure: make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done, the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean. All keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee. Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment.

name: light spacious apartment on IJburg
summary: Light spacious two storey apartment in a small charming apartment complex with a beautiful garden. The apartment has two comfortable bedrooms with double beds. The area is quiet and safe. The connection to the centre is very easy and fast by tram.
space: Light sunny apartment on IJburg. IJburg consists of several artificial islands and is known for its modern architecture. The apartment is located in a cozy apartment complex "Vrijburcht" and is located on the second and third floor. On the second floor there are two bedrooms with in each bedroom a double bed. On the third floor is a spacious living room with an open kitchen. Next to the kitchen is a sunny balcony. The property has a courtyard where children can play safely and there is a café restaurant with a terrace on the water. In good weather you can swim in the water. The connection to the center is excellent. Tram number 26 is a 3-minute walk away and runs every 4 to 10 minutes.  Within fifteen minutes you are at Central Station.  One tram stop away is a shopping center. IJburg has several restaurants.

name: Floating house
summary: A floating house, clear water to dive into after an intense visit to the city centre. Our 3 story house with 3 bedrooms offer a sea of tranquility & relaxation. A BBQ on the roof, or a swim from the terrace, this is were holidays begin.
space: Best of both worlds. Our spacious house will give a great holiday, both at home as in Amsterdam. Within an arm lengths of the heart of the city, it offers a superb place for relaxing and sightseeing.

It's a great openness that surrounds the house. Bright skies, calming waters & boats everywhere. Groceries/supermarkets at 500m, tram-station just down the road (10 min. to Amsterdam  Central Station) and a park at 500m You have a private & secluded underground parking. host_about:
My name is Derk, and together with my wife Florentine and our two kids we live in our floating house, 10 minutes by tram from the heart of Amsterdam.
Apart from enjoying our jobs as innovation consultant and producer of photoshoots, our whole family loves the water! In summer we go surfing, swimming, paddling, wake boarding or snorkeling. And in winter we hope to go skiing and skating, when there's ice. Year round we like to travel, surf, sail and kiteboard.

neighborhood_overview: The location is excellent to explore the city of Amsterdam (just 14 minutes by frequent street tram to the center (till late in the evening) and many other points of interest in Holland. Although it is close to the center, it offers a pleasant stay in a quiet, save and beautifull suburb, called IJburg.  You will find shops, supermarkets (open 7 days a week), nice restaurants (Italian, Greek, Chinese, Dutch pancakes etc) and cafés and a harbour, all within 10 minutes by foot. Nearby is a beautiful park suitable for running, bootcamps, skating, cycling and hiking. In the park is a small beach with save and good swimming facility for small children. You can do many activities in the immediate surrounding such as: ‘supping’, kite surfing, visit the old castle 'Muiderslot' and little isle ‘Pampus' (departure by ferry at the Harbour of IJburg). Also you find several play grounds for the children. At the other side of IJburg, you find a populair, funky beach at the IJmeer called ‘Blijburg’ wi
notes: IJburg is a dynamic suburb in development, on the artificial island there are several buildingprojects. One is located at the otherside of our canal (30 meters) where beautifull watervilla’s are being built.  You can make use of all our bikes, including 2 racing bikes (adults), 3 bikes for children, 1 adult bike and our ‘’bakfiets’’: a typical dutch family bike for little children (and all your grocery). It will take about 30 minutes to bike to the old city centre of Amsterdam.
transit: Walk 4 minutes to tram stop with direct connection (tram 26) to Amsterdam Central Station in 14 minutes.  Within several minutes you reach the A10 by car (free parking in your private garage).
access: The entire house except for 1 room at the 2nd floor which is used as storage. Off course I appreciate it if you keep it nice and tidy.  No smoking inside and no pets allowed. The house is not noisy, but the neighbors appreciate it if you are quiet during the early morning hours. The neighbors are great people, that you will have little trouble with, during your stay.
host_about: I am Erika and I am happy to offer our kidsproof family house to you and your family! I live here with my husband and 3 children: 2 boys in the age of 8 and 10 and our daughter of 7. Feel yourself at home in our convenient family house, surrounded by water, architecture, restaurants, shops, loads of Duplo, LEGO, Barbie-dolls, skates, steps and free bikes including a typical dutch 'bakfiets'! My husband and I work in marketing & media and like to sport, travel and enjoy nature, music and good food & wine. Welcome in Amsterdam!

name: Urban Villa @IJmeer close to centre
summary: Very large (300m2) free standing villa, with the south facing garden on the IJmeer lake with direct access to swimming water from private jetty.
space: Very large (300m2) free standing villa, with the south facing garden on the IJmeer lake with direct access to swimming water from private jetty. The house was built by leading sustainable architect Paul de Ruiter for a larger family with separate guest quarters for grand parents or a second couple. Ideal for two families holidaying together. All this at only 12 minutes by tram from Amsterdam Central Station. The house is very light and airy with floor to ceiling windows, full height sliding windows and hard wood flooring throughout. Thus guests are in direct contact with the nature outside and can fully appreciate the views of the IJmeer, Diemerpark and Diemer beach across the water. The ground floor is a loft style living, combining the living room and kitchen. Large sliding doors open to the 40m2 elevated wooden deck seamlessly extending the living room and kitchen. The entire deck is shaded with automatic sun screens. A large table with attached benches offers seating for up to 12 p
description: Very large (300m2) free standing villa, with the south facing garden on the IJmeer lake with direct access to swimming water from private jetty.
neighborhood_overview: IJburg a suburb of Amsterdam built in 2004 on a man made island in the IJmeer, part of the largest lake of the Netherlands. The southern part is very green and quiet, with mostly families with kids living here. With over 30 shops, more than 10 restaurants a few bars and two beaches everything you need is close by. Touristic highlights are easily reached by tram (30 minutes door-to-door) or by bike (30-45 minutes).
notes: A cargo bike (bakfiets) is available to do your shopping at IJburg and to go for a nice ride to the beach with the kids.  PS4, Wii, XBOX, guest account on iMac BBQ Trampoline in garden Ultra high speed internet connection (fiber), fixed and Wired Rasberries, strawberries and apples from the garden (in season)
transit: In 5 minutes you'll walk to the tram stop for Tram 26, this takes you in 12 minutes to Amsterdam CS. Amsterdam CS has round the clock train connections to Schiphol. There are three parking spots on our own terrain.
access: The front door is accesible from the front deck. The office door will be closed during your stay.
interaction: There is a contact person available at all times during your stay.
house_rules: General house rules apply to the apartment: - No loud music, noise or other nuisance in the apartment - No smoking in the apartment or in the common entrance - No drugs - No house parties, no persons permitted in the house except for the people who have booked (after midnight) - For the loss of keys, we charge 20% of the security deposit - CLEANING: We will take care of cleaning so no need to vacuum or mop the floor but please make sure that the dishes are done and the garbage has been put out on the street on the last pick up day (see information book in house) or dumped in a trash container outside) -If you need to check in to the apartment between 21:00 (9PM) and midnight, this is possible, but there is an additional fee of €25, after midnight that will be €50. Thank you for understanding.
host_about: I am the managing partner to a leading boutique consulting network. I am a dad of 3, runner and love fine food and drink.

neighborhood_overview: The youngest, upscale and upcoming part of Amsterdam Our home is located in the centre of IJburg with the beach, harbor, park, shopping centre and several playgrounds in few minutes walking distance. Getting to the hart of Amsterdam is a piece of cake, it's a 15min ride by public transport to the Central Station, The Dam and Royal Palace. Each area of Amsterdam has its own character and charm, and its own unique variety of shops, restaurants, cafes, museums and attractions.
notes: No smoking No drugs No shoes inside No pets In the spirit of our home-happyness we kindly request you to take your shoes off once you enter our home, to leave your pets somewhere else safe&sound and to smoke outside. If you wish to party and experiment, downtown would be the place to do that. Amsterdam has more than enough coffeeshops so please don't bring your stuf to the apartment. This is a residential area, meaning you've got neighbors. During the day kids are playing on the streets and in the gardens and making noise after 22.00h is not appreciated.
transit: Amsterdam is a world-class international transport hub and there are countless ways of getting into the city. Amsterdam boasts an impressive public transport network including metros, buses, trams, ferries and trains to help you get around the capital. Amsterdam is easy to navigate by car, but  when it comes to parking, due to the compact layout of the city and the limited number of (affordable) parking spaces, public transport can help you make the most of your trip.
access: We provide our guests access to all inside & outside spaces of our home including the access to our gym located across the street.
interaction: During your stay we will be more than happy to help out, whenever needed. So please do reach out to us.
house_rules: Inspired by AirBNB community sharing their beautiful homes, we decided to share ours with you. We hope you will treat our home with care, enjoy the time you spend here and come back to visit us again. Like mentioned before, our home is perfect for couples, friends and families.
host_about: Hi there, my name is Edvina and I am a traveler. Although I really enjoy calming and mind reviving trips to the nature, it's actually locals in urban areas that get me most inspired and energized. My home on the island of IJburg, the youngest neighborhood of Amsterdam, is the perfect quiet and peaceful base to explore the vibrant hart of the city whenever in need of inspiration. As I'm a quality oriented person, on my trips I prefer to taste a bit of local spirit rather than work my way down a sightseeing to-do list. Through AirBNB I gladly grasp the opportunity to invite you to explore the city as a local and become a 'Amsterdammer' for a weekend of a week.

space: You will feel right at home here: The 95m2 apartment has a modern, open kitchen and a very light and large living with a stunning view across the water. There's a bathroom with shower and bath, a large balcony, a secure underground parking, and even a jetty to keep a boat. There are two bedrooms, but only the master bedroom is available. The house is very comfortable, modern, spacious and quiet. It's a great holiday home from which to explore Amsterdam and the beautiful countryside around it. It's also the perfect place to get inspired and fully focus on a project.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is situated on Steigereiland. A small, newly built island just outside the city. Before you go into Amsterdam, make sure to have a look here. It is a very special area, praised for its unique architecture, such as the modern floating houses which are scattered around the apartment. Water is all around you, as are boats, islands, birds, authentic small towns, and so on. In the summer you can swim right in front of the house. No tourists, just the occasional friendly resident. A 5 min. walk takes you to the next island, where you will find shops, bars, restaurants, etc. (Blijburg city beach, M-Chi's, Pinxos, etc.) Or stroll to the Diemerpark, the prefect place to walk, run, bike, skate, or relax.
transit: You might think it's a long way out of the city, but tram 26 drives you into the very heart of Amsterdam in less that 10 minutes. It comes by every couple of minutes, so you don't have to worry to miss it. At night, there's a night-bus going every hour. A taxi from the centre costs between 20-25 euro. By bike, it takes around 25 minutes to the centre. The highway is very nearby, so it's easy to get in and out of the city by car. Schiphol airport is just a 20 minute drive.
access: You have access to every part of the house except he smallest bedroom. If you let us know in advance, you can make use of the secure parking space under the building.
interaction: We will make sure you arrive in a clean apartment, all ready to go. You will receive all the necessary information to use every feature of the house and feel right at home. If there's anything you need, we will be ready to help you, or will make sure that someone nearby can help you out.
house_rules: We expect guests to treat the apartment and everything in and around it respectfully. It is our private home which we love dearly, please treat it accordingly. It is not at all a noisy apartment, yet make sure you don't disturb the neighbors. If anything breaks, please replace or notify so we can arrange replacement ourselves. No smoking, except on the balcony.

neighborhood_overview: Do you prefer a quiet and green neighbourhood? Then IJburg is the place to be: the first residents established here only several years ago. This new district near Diemerpark consists of a number of artificial islands: Steigereiland, Haveneiland West and East and the Rieteilanden. In the summer you can completely relax at the Theo van Gogh in the Park. One hotspot to check out in IJburg at least once is the urban beach Blijburg. besides sunbathing and eating delicious food, you can enjoy several events. With tramline 16 you are within 10 minutes at central station!
notes: Guests we look for: - Respectful of neighbours (keep level of noise down) - Non-smokers (or smokers that smoke outside) - Above 30 when in a group - Any age if staying as a couple At time of departure: make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done, the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean. name: Contemporary house in Amsterdam
summary: This is contemporary design the way it was meant to be, but build with children in mind in the IJburg area, 10 minutes from Amsterdam, Europe's most exciting capital! Country side meets Energy.
space: This is contemporary design the way it was meant to be, but build with children in mind in the IJburg area, 10 minutes from Amsterdam City Centre The area is surrounded by water so you'll feel in the country side but just a tram or bike ride away from Europe's most exciting capital. Proud to say our house, designed by Rowin Petersma, was nominated in 2010 for the renowned Dutch BNA Architecture Award. Our house is very spacious (260m2), light and very comfortable. name: NICE APARTMENT WITH PANORAMA VIEW
space: THE APARTMENT This wonderfully spacious and light apartment has a lot of windows on every side with a spectacular view of the IJssel lake and the city line. On the North side of the building you will have a nice view on a village called Durgerdam. From the living room there is access to a large balcony (north west) with a lake view where you can enjoy the sunset in summer. The kitchen overlooks the Ijssel lake. The total space available within the apartment is 93 square meters. The apartment contains a living room with an open fully equipped kitchen, bathroom with a shower and a toilet. There are also 2 bedrooms of which one room will be available for Airbnb customers. When you're with 4 people, 2 of them can sleep in the livingroom on an inflatable bed. Space enough. There are towels, pillows and bed sheets which are available during your stay. This apartment is perfect for people who like the crowded life of Amsterdam, but at the same time like to have a quiet place to stay.  Televis

host_about:
Hi, we are Michiel & Jane of bnbmanager. 

Bnbmanager is a team of professional hosts established by travelers just like you. We believe in sharing homes. Wherever you are, it is delightful to explore and discover an unknown city from an authentic home. 

On behalf of home owners we advertise their properties through our airbnb profile and support them by offering you a pleasant stay. 

When you book your holiday with bnbmanager, you can be confident of a memorable stay and an experience through the eyes of a local. We are more than happy to share our knowledge, give you the best insider tips and recommendations about Amsterdam.

If you have any questions, holiday wishes or simply want to have a chat, then feel free to contact us any time. We always reply within an hour!

We look forward to being your host! :)

name: Houseboat "Castafiore"
summary: Note: The Castafiore has moved. The Castafiore is a former cargo ship from 1896. She was 10 years ago converted into a luxury motor barge. Aboard you will find o.a. Central Heating, a fully equipped kitchen, TV, stereo, washing machine and dryer.
space: The Castafiore is a former cargo ship from 1896. She was 10 years ago converted into a luxury motor barge. Aboard you will find o.a. Central Heating, a fully equipped kitchen, TV, stereo, washing machine and dryer. Almost like a house.  If you come with six people (only in the summer season), the barge is complemented by a cabin speedboat. In the cabin you can sleep with two people . You will be living in a private luxury space of appr. 80m2. It can easily hold 4 people in 2 double beds. One of the bedrooms has still parts of the original carpeting from 1896. For the rest the interior is modernized with central heating, air-conditioning, a fully equipped kitchen etcetera. Public transport is nearby and takes throughout the city as well as the rest of the Netherlands. There is not much use for a car down town. But if you travel by car consider free parking at our house. 45 minutes to the boat from there by public transport, or a 30 minutes watertaxi (€ 50 one way)

neighborhood_overview: You are on the edge of Amsterdam about 10 km from the center. While in Amsterdam , it seems like a natural . Good for walking, running , biking , fishing, swimming , (kite ) surfing, birding etc.
notes: We have 4 bikes for rent, a nice way to quickly explore the city. (7.50 per day if you order in advance) If you sail , you can rent the dinghy for € 50.00 per session of about five hours. In those five hours, you can sail around the entire city. You see Amsterdam from the water and are not a tourist nomore . Although we do not serve breakfast , you always find plenty of nice ingredients in the fridge for your first breakfast.
transit: If you do not bike or use the dinghy entering the city, you can either use public transport or a combination of public transport / car , public transport / cycling , public transport / walking. With good weather, you can also buy a speedboat ticket to Amsterdam for € 50.00 (max 6 persons , one way) If you want to use a taxi , we recommend taking an uber account.
access: The boat is all yours, except for the engine room. It also has a terras on deck.
interaction: We will see each other at your check in. We'll be there for questions to be answered.
house_rules: No nuisance for neighbors, no noise on deck or on the jetty. Smoking only outside on deck.

neighborhood_overview: IJburg is known for its diversity and creativity and is an architectural mecca for anyone with a love for architecture, design and creativity. Its a unique experience to stay on this  special man made island in the IJmeer and from there to visit Amsterdam city centre.  In 10 minutes walking distance you reach the nicest and most famous city beach Blijburg, with a restaurant, live bands, a campfire and a fireplace. Open all year! IJburg has its own harbor surrounded by trendy restaurants, bars and a Saturday market with local products.  If you bring your dog, you can stroll into the Diemerpark and visit the 19th centrury fort, converted into a restaurant. You can do your shopping in a nearby small shopping center with, inter alia, two supermarkets, bakery, butcher, fish shop and a fastfood restaurant. We’re both self employed and our house is our home ánd our office. We’re socially engaged and play an active part in all kinds of stuff going on in our community. We just love meeting people and helping out where we can. 
We usually get up earlier to walk our dog in the park or to dive into our busy daily work routines. When I’m not working I love going into town with friends, or meeting up with my grown up children who live in the city centre. I also enjoying redecorating our house – a lovely pastime that for me, is a piece of work that’s permanetly ‘in progress’! 

We’re keen users of AirBnB facilities ourselves and now that our children have moved out, its time for us to repay the hospitality others have shown us in the past. We set our standards by looking at what we expect ourselves. We enjoy helping you feel at home and adding a personal touch to your visit, but only when a little bit of help is asked for. We like to give you as much room as possible to discover Amsterdam and its surroundings in your own pace and at your own discretion.

We believe in a sustainable economy and enjoy meeting people through acts of sharing what we have with others.

We believe in a sustainable economy and enjoy meeting people through acts of sharing what we have others. Our house is like a wayside inn. We enjoy making people (EMAIL HIDDEN)e stay with us, enjoy what our house, what our island and what our city have to offer!

With a young population of 20,000, this child-friendly city quarter is known for its diversity and creativity. It’s a small mecca for anyone with a love for architecture and city development. Visit the marina surrounded by trendy restaurants, bars and a Saturday market with local products. In 10 minutes walking distance you can sit yourself down at the recently upgraded city beach Blijburg, with it’s restaurant, live music, campfire and fireplace. Open all year incidentally.  Or stroll through the Diemerpark and visit the 19th century fort Puur, recently converted into a modern restaurant (dogs allowed). You can do your shopping at the nearby shopping centre, with two supermarkets, a bakery, butcher’s shop, fishmongers, pharmacy and local restaurants. We even have our own community store, selling products made by local artisans.  If you like sports, you jog (a run around the island and park is about 10 km
notes: We’ll be sharing the bathing facilities in the mornings, but because we’re early risers, there are usually no ‘traffic jams’ for the bathroom or at the kitchen table. For a small additional fee we can pick you up at the station or airport, if our time allows.
transit: Amsterdam’s bustling city centre is easily accessible by tram – it runs every 6-10 minutes, from early morning to just after midnight. The night bus runs from 1:00 pm throughout the night. During the week once an hour, on weekends once every half hour. A two-day tourist ticket for the tram, metro and (night) busses costs around € 12.00.  Alternatively you can go for a tour by bike. The beautiful bike ride from our home to the centre of Amsterdam takes about 35 minutes. Bikes are available for rent in the town centre. The rates are about € 8.00 for a day and € 15.00 for 24 hours.
access: You’ll have access to the entire house during your stay, except for our basement and our private office on the 2nd floor.
interaction: It’s important that you feel at home in our house. We always meet our guests and show them around the house personally. We love to help you along if you want to know more about our island or on what’s going on in town. Please let us offer you a coffee or a glass of wine on arrival.  During your stay you’ll have your own key so that you can come and go as you like. We spend most of our time working in our offices, leaving the rest of the house to you.
house_rules: No smoking in the house. Our neighbours have young children, please respect their lives. Dogs are welcome!
host_about:
My husband Paul and I have been living on IJburg since 2008. Paul’s a management consultant and I work as a coach for ‘patchwork families’. We’re both self employed and our house is our home ánd our office. We’re socially engaged and play an active part in all kinds of stuff going on in our community. We just love meeting people and helping out where we can. 
We usually get up earlier to walk our dog in the park or to dive into our busy daily work routines. When I’m not working I love going into town with friends, or meeting up with my grown up children who live in the city centre. I also enjoying redecorating our house – a lovely pastime that for me, is a piece of work that’s permanetly ‘in progress’! 

We’re keen users of AirBnB facilities ourselves and now that our children have moved out, its time for us to repay the hospitality others have shown us in the past. We set our standards by looking at what we expect ourselves. We enjoy helping you feel at home and adding a personal touch to your visit, but only when a little bit of help is asked for. We like to give you as much room as possible to discover Amsterdam and its surroundings in your own pace and at your own discretion.

We believe in a sustainable economy and enjoy meeting people through acts of sharing what we have with others.

We believe in a sustainable economy and enjoy meeting people through acts of sharing what we have others. Our house is like a wayside inn. We enjoy making people (EMAIL HIDDEN)e stay with us, enjoy what our house, what our island and what our city have to offer!

The area has all the facilities and amenities you need including supermarkets, some nice restaurants & bars and a great beach with beach club Blijburg. notes: This is a non-smoking apartment.
transit: You have easy access to public transport with a tram stop 1 minute walk from the apartment (it runs every 6-10 minutes). The tram will bring you to the inner city centre, Central Station within 10 minutes. If you like to rent bicycles, it is also possible to take the bike on the tram with you. The night bus runs the whole night from 12.30 to the city centre and back to the apartment (takes a bit longer about 30 minutes).  If you come from Schiphol Airport it is 15/20 minutes by train to Central Station, from there you take Tram 26 (Ijburg written on the front) and stop at tram stop Steigereiland (which takes 12 minutes). This tramstop is at the end of our street and it is a 1 minute walk to the apartment.
interaction: The apartment is completely private with its own entrance, but we do live on the other levels of the house and have our front door in the shared hallway on the ground floor. In the summer you can completely relax at the Theo van Gogh in the Park. One hotspot to check out in IJburg at least once is the urban beach Blijburg. besides sunbathing and eating delicious food, you can enjoy several events. With tramline 16 you are within 10 minutes at central station!

The boat is environmental friendly, as the electricity is self generated with the roof solar panels, while the heating comes from the "pellet heater" an eco-friendly installation which uses pellets, a waste product from the wood processing industry to heat the boat and the warm water.

summary: A comfortable, modern and light appartment with spectaculair views on the IJsselmeer and the isle of Pampus. Only 15 minutes from the city center by tram. A private parking space under the apartment. We are new on Airbnb: will you be our first guest?
space: Do you want to enjoy the beautiful historical city center of Amsterdam, with its canals, pubs and museums, but also have a relaxing stay? IJburg is the place to be.  IJburg has a perfect location: by tram it's only 15 minutes to the city center (30 minutes by bike). But, contrary to the city center, it is nice and quiet, clean and modern. IJburg's location is not only practical, it is also beautiful as it is surrounded by water, natural parks and modern architecture. Also, it has a very nice city beach with restaurants and pubs (called Blijburg).  In the summer, you can have a swim in the lake or go to the harbor to rent a sailing boat, surf gear, wakeboard etcetera. In the winter, if its cold enough, you can go ice skating on the canals of IJburg. Also, nature lovers can go for a run in one of the nice natural parks IJburg is surrounded with. host_about:
Together with Maartje, I live and work in Amsterdam. 

We bought our apartment because we love the sea and the city. This place combines both; we look at the isle of 'Pampus' from our living room, and we can reach the hart of the city (Central Station) in less than 15 minutes. 

In the weekends we go outside and enjoy the nature, but we also enjoy reading and art. We love to sail (regattas) on the dutch lakes or we take our mountain bikes to the forrest. In the wintertime we often go to the Alps to go skiiing.

Especially with kids it is a joy to live here.  There are several play grounds and swimming possibility’s.   For shopping we have a small shopping center nearby with two supermarkets, a drug store, bakery and butcher. There are two health centers with doctors and pharmacy on IJburg.
notes: There is free wifi through the whole house. After your stay in the house it will be cleaned. For this the costs are €50,- and have to be paid on top of the rent.
transit: Within 2 minutes walk from the house there is a tram stop from which a tram to the city leaves every 5 minutes.
access: The guests can use the whole house.
interaction: You can always reach us by mobile phone. Also we have very friendly neighbors who can help you in case you have a question or if some device in the house doesn’t work.
house_rules: Smoking in the house is prohibited.
host_about:
My name is Jacqueline and I am 48 years old. I was born in Wormer (near to the Zaanse Schans with the famous windmills) and I moved to Amsterdam when I studied at the University of Amsterdam (Urban Studies). I’m living in Amsterdam now for almost 30 years and I really love the city. Half a year ago I started my own business in real estate and retail which is challenging and fun! 
My boyfriend's name is Patrick and he was born in Rozenburg, a small town near Rotterdam but but he also loves Amsterdam and lives here now for more then 30 years. He is 45 years old and has been a chef since he was 17 years old. At the moment he is working at The North Sea Jazz Club in Amsterdam but form August 1 he will be a full time teacher. 
We have two lovely daughters (4 and 5 years old) named Thirza and Lara and we are all very happy to live on IJburg. We love our house, the possiblity's of IJburg and the people who live here.

neighborhood_overview: IJburg is famous for it's design and architectural structure. Lots of water (modern canals) and lakes. Newly made islands, as where the Dutch are famous for. The first residents only live here since 2003. The atmosphere is city like and also a little like I remember as expats. A lot of people do know eachother, which I think is special for a big city. There is high speed and very frequent public transport just around the house. In 15 minutes you are in front of the famous Central Station right in the center of Amsterdam.
notes: The beautiful penthouse is situated on Amsterdam IJburg. On the 7th and 8th floor. It has an elevator that brings you right up. The building and the house are perfectly secured. The bed is one big boxspring bed (180x200), on request it comes with one big cover or two single covers.  Only on special request you can bring a child up to 6 years. (+€15,- per day) Please be aware that the MINIMUM stay in July and August is 5 nights.
transit: Parking on the streets at evenings is difficult. But you can hire my private parking on request. Tram 26 stops very nearby (Halte Diemerparklaan) as well as the bus does (lijn 66 GVB). You can rent a (e)bike just around the corner at Auke's. Walking in the beautiful Diemerpark and on very save pavements. The Dutch design their public space around bikes, so try out the Dutch way of transport yourself on save bikelanes.
access: You can use the whole penthouse except for my personal bedroom and the bedroom of my six year old son. You sleep in a double boxspring bedroom with direct access to the roof terrace. On request you can rent the private garage during your stay as well.
interaction: I might be travelling or abroad when you arrive but you can always call me or a good friend who lives on 5 minutes away. We provide every kind of service.  Of course there is a guest handbook with a lot of information about the house and the great city of Amsterdam ;)
house_rules: I respect my neighbours very much and I hope you do as well. Feel free and enjoy your stay, but avoid loud music and high heels, specially after 2100h. (9pm) No extra visitors allowed! The house is solely rented out to couples or single travelling persons older then 28 years of age. One child up to 6 years old (on special request and rate) is possible. He or she sleeps then in my sons bed. Enough toys to play with! ;)
host_about: Hi there, my name is Bob and I'm a happy traveller. Relaxt, easy going. Business man and entrepeneur; work hard, play hard. Father of my beloved son Daan (6), and I very much love to cook and sail. Like the Dutch Wadden Isles very much as well as I love Portugal and the rest of this great world. Happy to welcome you soon in our lovely designer penthouse with private roof terrace and great overview on IJburg Amsterdam, The Netherlands.

space: Houseboat in the most innovative district of Amsterdam.  LaCorteSconta B&B is located in a modern residential area, 12 min. from Amsterdam Central Station by tram (line 26, Steigerieiland stop) where you will reach an area free from the many tourists who crowd the city and full of water and green space.  The B&B is a Floating-Villa on 3 floors moored in the lake IJ. The 3rd floor is where we live with my 2 little children. The large living room (breakfast area) and the under water floor (guests area) complete the location. Each room has a double bed, WiFi, TV or computer and other services.  The bathroom, shower, bath, double hand-wash and toilettes are shared, according to the traditional philosophy of coexistence and respect that belongs to the B&B concept itself. The bathroom cleaning is provided daily.  Breakfast will be personalized according to particular allergies or special requests. Guests can experience the best of this district through the houseboat that will make your stay

neighborhood_overview: A good alternative to the chaos of the city to rediscover the peace with an original houseboat. The floating house is in the neighborhood of Ijburg recently built. Typical Dutch management of the sea combined with care and originality of the building. All united in a residential neighborhood, young and cosmopolitan. Nearby there are possibilities of shops, supermarkets as well as peaceful places where to drink and eat. Dutch quiet a few steps from the vitality of the center.
notes: Accessibility: easy by walk \ by Airports \ from nearby railway stations \ Station by bus \ Cruise Ships. Connections: Close to the center (12 min by tram to Central Station) and easy access to all major attractions of the city (Center \ Museumplein \ Zoo ..) and surrounding areas (Muiden \ Zaanse Schans \ Volendam \ Marken ..). Possibility to rent a bike or organize a tour. Parking: Possibility of public parking at 14 eur \ day or alternatively with the cheapest parking P + R Zeeburg or Private Garage. HouseBoat: It is located in a unique area where nature, sports, architecture, sustainability of the sea and lifestyle come together. The original experience of living in an authentic houseboat of latest generation. Breakfast: Fresh breakfast every morning with flexible hours, possibility of room service or use the take away service. Breakfast can customize according to allergies or vegetarian preferences. Free Services: all free services (some on request): Kitchen, Laundry, Equipment fo
transit: The houseboat is a 12 min from the central station with the tram 26 (stop Steigereiland). Bike use: Excellent starting point for visiting the city center and get lost among the many parks of Amsterdam or in Ijburg. The tram 26 is one of the few city tram that will allow you to enter with the bikes and in 10 minutes to the Central Station and many other destinations through the line of regional trains. We offer a bike rental service for a fee, alternatively there are many options to rent a bike. IJburg Beach The beach is set in a frame vaguely bohemian, where besides sunbathing you can entertain during the evening with music, bonfires and fireworks. Surfcenter IJburg, perfect for water sports enthusiasts who can rent windsurfing equipment or take lessons. One of the great advantages of Strand IJburg is that here you can swim. To get to Strand IJburg (Muiderlaan 1001) you can take tram 26.
access: All guests are provided with the key of their room and the key of the main entrance so as to be always independent. All the room are placed in the under water floor (Guest Area).  The Toilet and bathroom with tub and shower are shared. Both are in the guest area. A spacious living room also used for breakfast is our Common Area.  The use of the kitchen and laundry with arrangements in advance is free.
interaction: The owner will welcome you at your desired check in time and provide you all the necessary information to visit the city!  There is often somebody in the location to help you with information and helpful tips for your travel experience.
house_rules: Please contact me to to indicate your arrival time. Bathroom and toilets are shared with any other guests. Although the bathrooms are cleaned daily, please use it with respect. All rooms are non-smoking. There is the possibility to smoke on the patio or in the living room in according with the other guests and home uses. Animals allowed. In the case of large animals or particularly invasive it may be required at an additional cost. Children under 6 stay free using the same bed. Ability to add a baby cot at no extra charge (only in larger rooms). No extra bed availability.   Common Area open from 8 am until 9 pm Breakfast from 8:00 to 10:00. (Flexible). Check in between 3pm and 4pm. Check-out before 11 am.
host_about:
Welcome to my wonderful houseboat! I live here with my two children Rocco and Dante. You may have understood that I come from Italy! I left my hometown Venice and my "adopted city" Rome, spent 10 years traveling to different continents and finally I chose to move here in Netherlands five years ago, to try to make a change of my life. I have found a wonderful and exciting city that can give back a lot from hard work. In addition to the "cancer" like me who love sea, open spaces bright and clean but at the same time be able to find any stimulus from a dynamic and cosmopolitan city, I found the perfect place to continue my journey!

Benvenuti a tutti nella mia fantastica casa galleggiante! Vivo qui con i miei due bambini Rocco e Dante. Avrete forse capito che vengo dall'Italia! Ho lasciato la mia città natale Venezia e la mia "adottiva" Roma, passato 10 anni a viaggiare per diversi continenti e alla fine ho scelto di trasferirmi qui in Olanda 5 anni fa per cercare di dare una svolta alla  mia vità e ho trovato una città meravigliosa e stimolante che puo restituire molto dal duro lavoro. Inoltre per i "cancro" come me che amano il mare, gli spazi aperti, luminosi e puliti ma allo stesso tempo avere la possibilità di trovare qualunque stimolo da una città cosi dinamica e cosmopolita, ho trovato il luogo perfetto per continuare il mio viaggio!

name: House on the waterfront, Amsterdam
summary: Spacious and light apartment on the waterfront located on IJburg, 10 minutes by tram 26 from  the historic center of Amsterdam. With two bedrooms and a lounge bed.  Sunny terrace on the waterfront. This apartment has a minimum stay of 4 nights.
space: The apartment is situated on the ground floor and has one bedroom with a king size bed, one bedroom with a (double) sofabed and a large lounge bed in the living room. The living room has an large glass front, and a cozy terrace overlooking the water. In summer you can swim just in front of the apartment, where a small jetty provides easy access to the water. The apartment provides the opportunity to experience the dynamics of the big city, while the peaceful surrounding prevents you from getting exhausted. The area is surrounded by contemporary architecture. The Diemerpark, where you can walk, jog or have a pick-nick, is at 1 minute walking distance. There is a theatre and café right on the corner of the apartment building. IJburg shopping center is fifteen minutes walk, or one tramstop away. The tramstop is 3 minutes walk from the apartment.

name: Amsterdam, IJburg modern City House
summary: IMPORTANT NOTE: ONLY FOR RENT AUGUST 5 – AUGUST 27 2016
space: This spacious, modern, light family house is situated at IJburg, à newly developed area in East Amsterdam. IJburg is mainly pouplar with young families and has à vibrant, energetic feeling to it. THE house was built under architecture in 2007, is 240 m². On the groundfloor there is a large living-kitchen with sliding doors to the sheltered garden. The first floor has a grand living room with fire place, a connected spacious playroom for kids. The second floor counts 3 bedrooms, 1 bathroom (with shower and toilet). The third floor is an airy, spacious loft, with reading corner, a master bedroom with double bed and large bathroom (with bathtub and large shower en toillet). The entire place counts 3 toilets, garden has been equiped with Weber BBQ.  Great, green surroundings. Blijburg city Beach is nearby (for swimming, eating, drinking & dancing). The large Diemerpark is just around the corner: fabulous jogging, cycling, skeelering, and swimming in the lake 200 meters from the front door.

IJburg is mainly pouplar with young families and has à vibrant, energetic feeling to it. THE house was built under architecture in 2007, is 240 m². On the groundfloor there is a large living-kitchen with sliding doors to the sheltered garden. The first floor has a grand living room with fire place, a connected spacious playroom for kids. The second floor counts 3 bedrooms, 1 bathroom (with shower and toilet). The third floor is an airy, spacious loft, with reading corner, a master bedroom with double bed and large bathroom (with bathtub and large shower en toillet). The entire place counts 3 toilets, garden has been equiped with Weber BBQ.  Great, green surroundings. Blijburg city Beach is nearby (for swimming, eating, drinking & dancing). The large Diemerpark is just around the corner: fabulous jogging, cycling, skeelering,
interaction: I can be reached per email.

Werkster - door onszelf aangesteld - komt wekelijks voor 50 euro schoonmaken. Deze schoonmaak is verplicht. Geld gaarne voor de schoonmaakster achterlaten in enveloppe op de keukentafel.
host_about: Moeder van 3 kinderen, getrouwd. Eindredacteur van beroep. Wij (mijn man, onze drie kinderen & ik) wonen sinds 2005 met veel plezier op IJburg na 15 jaar in de binnenstad van Amsterdam te hebben gewoond. Mijn man is architect en heeft ons huis zelf ontworpen. IJburg is een moderne wijk, veel huizen zijn gebouwd onder architectuur. De wijk heeft veel water. Je kunt er fantastisch sporten en zwemmen – een van de redenen waarom het er zo ideaal wonen is met kinderen. Maar tegelijkertijd is het op een steenworp afstand van de stad. Op de fiets kun je via de geweldige Nesciobrug de stad in rijden (halfuurtje en je zit in de Jordaan) en met de tram sta je in tien minuten op Centraal Station! Die combibatie maakt IJburg eigenlijk ideaal – ook voor reizigers. Na een hele dag musea afstruinen en door de hectische stad te hebben gelopen kun je op IJburg fijn bijkomen aan de waterrand (we hebben een eigen steiger plus zeilbootje!), in onze tuin of in het nabijgelegen Vrijburcht café. Kinderen kunnen op straat spelen of zwemmen met buurtkinderen. IJburg is kortom ideaal voor gezinnen die ‘best of both worlds’ zoeken.

Hey! How is it going today? Allow me to have a few seconds of your time to tell you a few things about myself. My name is Guilherme de Almeida. I am 28 years young. Personally I like to perceive myself as a global citizen. This is because I’ve been traveling and living in different places ever since I can remember. 

I am a person that is always open to new ideas, experience and people. I am a very curious and ambitious person who is committed to excellence.  I’ve a broad field of interest and my flexibility has allowed me to meet and learn from people from all walks of life.

In my spare time I like to practice sports, explore new grounds, meet interesting people and expand my knowledge on almost any subject. You can always wake me up to talk about your passion. 

As your guest I'll probably be the invisible ghost. Waking up at sunrise and returning only after sunset.  There is so much to experience and so little time. Don’t you think? 

As your host I'll make sure to give you the best hospitality as I possibly can. You having a great experience is  my number one goal. I take pride in assisting you with anything you need. I like to stand for integrity and quality.  Personally I feel  that when you are traveling you should feel just as comfortable as you feel at your own home. Believe me you won’t be sorry to spend time at our place. So, do you feel like having a pleasant time? Get in touch today and make it happen!
