name: Private cottage at waterfront
summary: Get the best of both worlds! Located at the northeastern fringe of the city you are close to the hustle and bustle of the city while at the same time you can enjoy the peace and quiet of the countryside. The cottage is separate of our main house: privacy!
space: The cottage is detached from our family home and has its own acces from the road. Also it has great views!
description: Get the best of both worlds! Located at the northeastern fringe of the city you are close to the hustle and bustle of the city while at the same time you can enjoy the peace and quiet of the countryside. The cottage is separate of our main house: privacy! The cottage is detached from our family home and has its own acces from the road. Also it has great views! WiFi internet. Free parking. The level of contact is entirely up to you. We want to do everything we can to help you be comfortable in the cottage and in Amsterdam at large. Also if you're travelling alone and want some company just knock on the door and feel free to come in and have a chat. And if you don't feel like going out for dinner or cooking for yourself, you can always check what we're having and join us or take a plate to your room (small extra fee). My family and I are keen on meeting new people but we are also very considerate of everyone's privacy. The peace and quiet of the garden and the cottage can be very relaxin
neighborhood_overview: The peace and quiet of the garden and the cottage can be very relaxing. To have this paradise within Amsterdam's ring road is a blessing we enjoy every day! Also, because of being right at the waterfront, the view is very dynamic, with all the professional shipping driving by.
notes: Although the cottage is entirely private, it does sit in our garden. When the weather allows for it you'll have your own terrace and outside sitting area to enjoy the sun, but you are also welcome to use the rest of the garden.   Did I mention our house, garden and cottage sit right on top of a dyke? It's about as Dutch as it gets! Our house was built in 1910 for the lock keepers of the nearby locks that separate the Amsterdam river IJ from the greater IJmeer (part of the former Zuiderzee sea). The house is right by the waterfront at the intersection of the River IJ with one of Holland's major channels, which is why there's a lot to see for nautical fans.
transit: The tram is only a 10 minute walk or a 3 minute bike ride away. It takes you to Centraal Station within 10 minutes. Also you can add bikes to your reservation (€5 per day) to help you get around even more. If you're tired and don't want to ride back home you can even bring your bike into the tram. Also, within 10 minutes by bike you are at the heart of 'Waterland' the charming historic countryside north of Amsterdam, with great bike lanes taking you from one character loaded village to the next. This area is also great for hiking, bird watching and general outdoorsyness.
access: WiFi internet. Free parking.
interaction: The level of contact is entirely up to you. We want to do everything we can to help you be comfortable in the cottage and in Amsterdam at large. Also if you're travelling alone and want some company just knock on the door and feel free to come in and have a chat. And if you don't feel like going out for dinner or cooking for yourself, you can always check what we're having and join us or take a plate to your room (small extra fee). My family and I are keen on meeting new people but we are also very considerate of everyone's privacy.
house_rules: Our family house, garden and cottage are a great place to stay and relax in, however bringing in guests is not allowed. Also we don't want any drugs on the premises. In general we ask our guests to be respectful to the cottage and its quiet and peaceful surroundings. We are a family with two children ages 8 and 9 and our number one priority is providing them with a safe and tranquil home. If your goal is to party hard in your accomodation, look elsewhere. If you are looking for an easygoing, quiet, cosy and romantic hideaway in a bustling city: you have found it!

name: The Bedstay - authentic, cosy and unique retreat
summary: A restored and well-appointed cabin in a peaceful yet bohemian neighbourhood just 10 mins by tram from the city centre. Located on the IJmeer to the east of the city. Parking available
space: If you're looking for a great place to stay in Amsterdam that's a little different, The Bedstay is an ideal choice. Suitable for 2 people, it's a cosy renovated cabin, beautifully restored to a high standard, located in a quiet, artistic area to the east of the City. It's just a few minutes' walk from the tram stop Zuiderzeeweg - so it's ideally situated for a relaxing few days exploring the City. The Bedstay is light, clean and airy, with a super-comfortable bed (bedstee) built into the wall in the traditional Dutch style. There's a shower room with toilet and washbasin, and a small living area with table and two chairs. Tea, coffee and some tasty Dutch snacks are provided. Free Wi-Fi is provided (although it can be a little slow) and there is a plentiful supply of hot water. Very tall guests will need to be careful with the low beam (1.85) in the room but I have padded it with foam at the crucial point!

neighborhood_overview: The Bedstay is situated, within the ring road, on Zeeburg Island. A quiet area in the east of Amsterdam on the IJmeer. The citycentre is easily accessible from here. It is also a good starting point for beautiful walking or cycling routes through the small fishing villages  along the IJsselmeer and the green area Waterland.
notes: The price includes heating, bed linen and towels. Also coffee, tea and a few snacks are provided in the cabin.  Breakfast is not included though available on request.
transit: Tram 26 from Zuiderzeeweg brings you to the Central Station within 10 minutes.  Bikes can be rented in the area.
access: The Bedstay is located in the Theo Niermeijer Sculpture Garden where I have lived for over 20 years (my cabin is next door). It's a quiet, semi-rural setting, created and populated by artists and quite unlike anywhere else in the City. Although there are very few cafes and shops nearby, access to the city is very easy either via tram (Zuiderzeeweg is just a few minutes' walk away) or bike. Parking is available right outside The Bedstay so it's ideal if your arriving by car.
interaction: I am here to welcome the guests to the accommodation and can give advice on things to do in the city and surrounding area.
house_rules: Binnen niet roken
host_about:
Ik ben Engelse en woon al meer dan 20 jaar in Nederland in een van de woonwagens op dit kunstenaars terrein. Ik ben zelf Bouwkundig Ingenieur en heb naast mijn werk, bij diverse architecten bureaus, de vroegere wagen van mijn dochter omgebouwd tot ''The Bedstay'', ik vind het geweldig om mensen een unique ervaring te kunnen geven op deze bijzondere plek. Ik ben regelmatig op de racefiets te vinden in de mooie omgeving maar ga ook graag naar concerten of een van de vele musea in Amsterdam.  
I am English and have been living in the Netherlands for more than 20 years in one of the caravans in this artists garden. I am a building engineer and inbetween working, at various architects offices, I have renovated the wooden cabin which was used by my daughter, and turned it into'' The Bedstay'' I think it's a great place and a unique experience to stay here. I regularly cycle in the surrounding area on the racing bike but also love going to concerts or to one of the many museums in Amsterdam.

neighborhood_overview: Our cornes house is a beautiful bright specious family home (150 sq meters) build in 2010 and situated right at of the canals of IJburg. We have a specious balcony hanging over the water with a beautiful view right at the Theo van Gogh park with several playgrounds for the kids and a Jeu de Boules court. We have 4 bedrooms and 3 of them are located on the same floor.  Lovers of modern architecture and easy access to water sports are particularly well served here. The city beach called Blijburg ((URL HIDDEN) is just around the corner. And 5 minutes walking distance you will find the harbour with nice cafe's, restaurants and bars. We love (Dutch) design, which you'll see back in our home. We have an indoor parking place in a private parking garage, about 20 meters from the house which can be used.
notes: IJburg equals water. It consists of several islands connected by bridges, has a harbor and the city's only real beach. The water reflects in the air and the light is therefore brighter than in the rest of Amsterdam. The wind blows stronger than in the rest of Amsterdam, like a sea breeze. The wind blows away the clouds and the sun seems to shine more often. IJburg feels like a holiday island all year.  The first house at IJburg was build in 2002. By now, the islands have 15.000 dwellers and are still growing. The main islands are Steigereiland (pier island), Rieteiland and Haveneiland (harbor island).  IJburg is already discovered by many tourists who love the combination of modern architecture, water, nature, good restaurants and hip shops. IJburg has much to offer for architecture lovers. Barcelona even got inspired by IJburg when it designed its own enlargement El Prat Nord.  There are lots of playgrounds for the kids and of course Blijburg beach and its beach club. We do have a cat

summary: A sunny garden in the newest area of Amsterdam!! Private parking place, spacious & light house, lots of toys for kids, including a swing! Nearby beach, but also a 15 tram ride from the centre (Amsterdam CS). Sleeps 4 adults (only couples) and 2 kids.

On the other side of the island is a beautiful green park (Diemerpark), in which you can go running or take a nice walk.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood has it's own beach (Blijburg) and till the end of august 2015 next to the beach is an Urban Campsite, check the website for more info and give it a visit. In the harbor, yes we have our own harbor, there is a market every saturday. You can visit paviljoen Puur (beautiful walk) in the weekends (check the website). And have real good coffees at Espressofabriek (IJburglaan). At the beginning of IJburg there's a shopping area, where you can by all you grocery at different supermarkets.

access: In consultation.
interaction: During your stay you can always contact me by sms, (SENSITIVE CONTENTS HIDDEN) or phone. We're around somewhere in the Netherlands (probably with our campervan).  We have neighbors and friends who can help you with a spare key or other things. If you have any questions about the house or about the area, contact me!
house_rules: The property is new in 2015, that means that the house is totally new furnished. Therefore, we expect from our guests that they respectfully handle the house and stuff in it. Don't scratch the ground floor; avoid scroll with hard objects.  Close doors well, also do the pins on the sliding doors in the living, left and right at the bottom, when you check out. So leave the apartment from the front door. Also if you're at home it is safer to lock the gate to the parking lot. And when you use the shed; don't forget to close this too. IJburg feels very safe, but it's still the big city you're living in...
host_about:
About myself:
I love traveling. Have in the past traveled extensively in Asia. Since the arrival of our children we do not travel with a backpack, but we often make a trip with our Volkswagen camper van. In addition, we regularly go to Spain or Italy for a week to feel the sun.
I also like to read a good book in the hammock in our lovely garden. Or I drink coffee or a glass of wine with friends on a terrace in the park or in the playground.
I work as a teacher. The students keep me young and free-thinking.

We live in a lovely neighbourhood on IJburg, close to the city, but also close to a beach, lake and big park. Amsterdam is not only open-minded and laid-back, but also has much to offer on a cultural and artistic area. We would like to give you the chance to discover this lovely city and relax back in our quiet house  & garden.

Welcome to Amsterdam!
Our property is in principle available every weekend, from saturday till Monday. It is also possible to rent the property during school holidays (check the calendar for the exact dates) which I try to keep up-to-date.

Over mezelf:
Ik hou van reizen. Heb in het verleden veel gereisd in Azië. Sinds de komst van onze kinderen reizen we niet meer met een rugzak, maar gaan we er vaak tussenuit met ons Volkswagen camperbusje. Daarnaast gaan we regelmatig een weekje naar Spanje of Italië om de zon te voelen.
Daarnaast lees ik graag een goed boek in de hangmat in onze heerlijke tuin. Of ik drink koffie of een goed glas wijn met vriendinnen op een terras, in het park of in de speeltuin.
Ik werk als docent. De leerlingen houden me jong en vrij denkend.

Wij wonen in een heerlijke, ruime woning op IJburg in Amsterdam. Amsterdam is niet alleen ruimdenkend en laid-back, maar heeft ook veel te bieden op cultureel en kunstzinnig gebied. Wij willen je graag de kans geven om vanuit ons relaxte huis deze heerlijke stad te ontdekken.

Welkom in Amsterdam!
Onze woning is in principe elk weekend beschikbaar, van zaterdag t/m maandag. Daarnaast is het mogelijk om de woning in de Nederlandse schoolvakanties te huren.
Bekijk de kalender, die probeer ik up-to-date te houden.

summary: A cosy home quietly situated in Amsterdam with a stunning view. Perfect for a family with 3 children, or 2 couples. Private parking! Available 22 July-13 August with a minimum stay of 6 nights. Roof terrace, and swimming around the corner!
space: Enter through the hallway into the kitchen living room on the ground floor. All that you need to cook for a large family is provided: pots and pans, oven dishes, a dishwasher, knifes and cutlery, as well as salt and spices. Whatever you need you can use. The table by the window seats five (one high chair for children age 3-12).  There's a small sofa and comfortable chair but no tv downstairs. Also downstairs is the storage area with the washingmachine and dryer. On the first floor are our three daugthers' bedrooms. Two bedrooms with each a high sleeper and the third bedroom is very small with a single bed (all 3 beds are 90x200). The toilet and bathroom are separate. There's a bath, a shower over the bath, and a washbasin. Towels, a hairdryer, and handsoap are provided and if there's a shampoo or one of our soaps you'd like to try you're welcome to.  Throughout the whole house are bookcases with lots of classics (I studied English Literature) so if you need a book during your stay feel

There's a bath, a shower over the bath, and a washbasin. Towels, a hairdryer, and ha
neighborhood_overview: Our house is situated at the quiet end of IJburg. There's hardly any traffic in front of the house and we use the pavement as our front garden. IJburg is a new area with lots of families and nice architecture (we get a lot of city planning students walking around the island). There is a beach at the IJsselmeer side of the island and a small beach in the Diemerpark. There's even a special surf beach with a surfschool. Lots of people sup around these waters. And of course canoeing is another option.
notes: Our house is clean and cosy, but no showroom. We live in our house and enjoy our furniture as do our three rowdy girls, so here and there it might show. We also welcome people to enjoy the house in full so whatever is here you can use. So, books, toys, bikes, sandbox, umbrellas, etc, are all here to use. We just ask that you use it in a loving way, as we try to do.
transit: Tramline 26 takes you right into the heart of the city in about 10 to 15 minutes. By car it's only minutes to get to the eastside or the centre, for instance the zoo, or several daily markets. But beware parking is expensive. By bike it's about a 20 minute ride to the eastside which is a nice area with lots of reastaurants, shops, markets, parks, and museums. To the centre it's about a 30 minute ride. Walking would take about an hour (but it would be a nice walk through a park and along the Amsterdam-Rhine canal before you reach the eastside)
access: The whole house is at your disposal, we won't lock any rooms. Also what's in and around the house is free for use. There's a bike (see photo), children's bikes and toys, lots of books, and a hairdryer.  Free (!) parking at the rear enclosed safe parking area (in the courtyard).
interaction: During rental periods we will be on holiday ourselves but we'll always be available for contact by phone, email, or app. My mother will also be here in Amsterdam (she lives in the city centre) and will be there for key exchange and will also be available for questions. She has lived in Amsterdam all her life, has worked with tourists, speaks English, Portugese, French, and German and knows the good places.
house_rules: We only accept bookings of guests who have ID-verification. Since some of us are very allergic to certain animals and are also asthmatic there can be absolutely no pets. And no smoking or drugs of any kind!  We like to take off our shoes once inside (Amsterdam is not the cleanest city with regards to dogs although our area is fine) but this is up to you.
host_about:
We are a married couple with 3 daughters: Lottie (3), Tess (6), and Ella (9). Chiara has lived in Amsterdam all her life and Itse for most of his adult life. We've been together for 20 years. Before our daughters were born Itse studied sociology and Chiara English Literature. At present Itse works for the city counsil of Amsterdam, and Chiara works at home, looking after the children. 
We always go to the UK on holiday to go walking and fossiling on the beaches of the Jurassic Coast. 
Favorite tv series are MASH, Hill Street Blues, Morse, Great British Bake Off, Masterchef, Downton Abbey, anything British actually...  and many more of course.
Film: The Big Lebowski
We are vegetarians. Chiara loves to bake. Chiara and Ella do yoga. Tess is a little ballerina. Lottie is mainly being naughty. And Itse is a keen surfer and runner.
Chiara likes jazz, Itse not so much. He likes Coldplay, she not so much. We both like The Doors.
Happiness is not a destination but a way of life.

host_about:
Wij zijn Jorrit Stracke en Dirk Minnebo. Samen runnen wij Iambnb. 
Iambnb verhuurt mensen hun appartementen terwijl zij op vakantie zijn. Op die manier zijn er altijd leuke woningen vrij voor mensen die Amsterdam willen ervaren als een local.  

Dirk heeft rechten gestuurd en ik, Jorrit, voor piloot. Echter hebben we beide voor een andere koers gekozen en hebben wij nu ons eigen bedrijf.

Dirk en ik staan relaxt in het leven en houden van hard werken, maar ook van Amsterdam. Inmiddels beheren wij al ongeveer 60 appartementen in en om Amsterdam! We hebben daarom al veel ervaring en doen ons uiterste best die te gebruiken om uw verblijf bij ons zo aangenaam mogelijk te maken.

Onze hobby's zijn voetbal, filmmaken, uitgaan en andere leuke dingen doen. Natuurlijk is Iambnb ook eigenlijk een hobby, omdat wij dit met zoveel plezier doen.  
Wij kijken er naar uit om u te verwelkomen in Amsterdam!

This new district near Diemerpark consists of a number of artificial islands: Steigereiland, Haveneiland West and East and the Rieteilanden. name: Sleep in your own boat in Amsterdam
summary: Old style Dutch boat is docked at our pier attached to our 2-floor apartment on a canal in Amsterdam (IJburg). With 1 double bed, 2 small couches, tv, wifi, fridge and stereo. Shared shower and toilet in main house.
space: To stay on the water in Amsterdam adds a special flavor to your stay in the city of canals.
description: Old style Dutch boat is docked at our pier attached to our 2-floor apartment on a canal in Amsterdam (IJburg). With 1 double bed, 2 small couches, tv, wifi, fridge and stereo. Shared shower and toilet in main house. To stay on the water in Amsterdam adds a special flavor to your stay in the city of canals. Our house is a 2 story apartment in an apartment building. You enter the house at street level and walk through our hall directly to the stairs that take you to -1 water level. At the -1 level is your bathroom and toilet. You share this with our three children. At -1 level you exit our house to enter the pier and walk to the boat. You can always use our main kitchen to prepare a meal. Also you can use our washing machine and dryer. Our family consists of 5 (my husband Marc and me, our 3 Brazilian kids (Leticia 19, Felipe 15 and Lucimari 13), our 2 dogs and 1 cat. But since you are on the boat and we are in the main house, your privacy is assured. Tram #26 stops in front of our house
neighborhood_overview: Sleeping on a canal! This completes your Amsterdam experience.
notes: To stay on a boat is a special experience. Expect cosy surroundings.  Parking: if you come by car, we advice to park your car 5 minutes from our house in a parking garage where you can park your car for EUR5,00 per 24 hours.
transit: Tram #26 stops in front of our house and takes you central station within 15 minutes.
access: Our house is a 2 story apartment in an apartment building. You enter the house at street level and walk through our hall directly to the stairs that take you to -1 water level. You can always use our main kitchen to prepare a meal. Also you can use our washing machine and dryer.
interaction: Our family consists of 5 (my husband Marc and me, our 3 Brazilian kids (Leticia 19, Felipe 15 and Lucimari 13), our 2 dogs and 1 cat. But since you are on the boat and we are in the main house, your privacy is assured.
host_about:
We are a Dutch couple and love to welcome you to our house & boat. We know  how to help you have a great stay. Just before we got married in 1999, we traveled for one whole year (Asia, Australia, New Zealand and South America). We lived in U.S.A., Switzerland and Curacao. In 2005 our lives got enriched with our three Brazilian children (now 19, 15 and 13) and for the next couple of years our basis will be in Amsterdam.

A long time ago ;-) Marc studied Business Administration and I studied economics and we are both entrepeneurs. Over the years I became more and more interested in energy and consciousness and immersed myself in these subjects by studying Reiki, Holistic Massage, Consciousness & Enlightenment. We currently own three companies (telecom, housing valuation services and energy healing).

space: The room has 5 m wide windows with an open view towards the gardens and other houses that were build under architecture.  The Sunsetroom is located on the second floor of our house. Groundfloor and first floor are private, you share the bathroom with the other guest at the second floor, NOT with the owners.  The room contains a doublebed (140x2m), a small tv, a small desk and a loungechair. We provide clean sheets and towels and free use of coffee, tea and wine. If you love architecture IJburg is the place to be. It's the newest neighborhood in Amsterdam with a great tram connection to the old city. From our spacious home in less than 15 minutes to the Grand Central Station & the centre of the city.

neighborhood_overview: IJburg is an architecturally fascinating area in Amsterdam. It is an area which quite literally sprung up out of the water only 10nyears ago. Close to the centre but pleasantly removed from the bustle. This spacious house is located in one of the most child friendly neighborhoods of town with suitable small beaches nearby (Blijburg) and many nice villages to visit ( by car or bike, nice and safe bicycle roads!). There is a zoo close by (Artis), you can make a trip to the island Pampus and across the house is a large park called Diemerpark. On IJburg are several restaurants, shops, a nice little harbour etc.
notes: The house is clean and there will be fresh beddings + towels for you. Also we have kids toys/games. The beds are made when you arrive. We have a cat.
transit: It takes less than 5 minutes walk to get to the nearest tramstop. Tram 26 leaves every 5 minutes during daytime and every 8 minutes in the evening. It only takes 15 minutes to get to the Central Station (located in the city centre) once you’re in the tram. After 1 AM a night bus goes every half hour to- and from Central Station and Leidsesquare/Rembrandtsquare (well-known bars are situated here) to IJburg.  Also bus 66 is available, which goes to the Bijlmer (near to the Amsterdam Arena).
access: You share the bathroom with guests from the other room Sunsetview. The apartment is perfect for families or couples who like to unwind from a hectic day in the city centre.
interaction: At your arrival you will find information about Amsterdam in English, French or Deutsch. Just let us know your wishes/questions and we like to help you! We are always reachable by mobile phone.
house_rules: No drugs, no smoking nor excessive alcohol allowed, no parties  allowed.  Only guests with a positive attitude in life.
host_about:
Ik ben geboren en getogen in Amsterdam en kan je/jullie dus veel tips en adviezen geven over al het moois dat Amsterdam te bieden heeft. 
Ik ben een fervent cultuur-, en muziekliefhebber en weet voor jullie de leuke optredens, festivals en exposities te vinden wanneer je mij laat weten waar je interesse naar uitgaat.

neighborhood_overview: IJburg is a modern architectural area with beautifully designed boats in Amsterdam. The area has all the facilities and amenities you need including supermarkets, some nice restaurants & bars and a great beach with  beach club Blijburg. Here you can also go sailing, windsurfing, kite surfing and paddle boarding. There is also a nice harbour.
notes: If you would like to check in early or to check out late please let me know. Normally I can be very flexible with this. But sometimes (and this is rare) check in / check out times can overlap when leaving guests have a late flight and arriving guests are coming early. In that case check out time is 11 am and check in time 1 pm.
transit: I have a private underground parking space 50 meters from the houseboat which the guests are welcome to use for free. On arrival I will give you the transponder for access to the garage.  You have easy access to public transport with a tram stop 6 minutes walk from the houseboat (it runs every 6-10 minutes). The tram will bring you to the inner city centre like Central Station within 12 minutes. It is approx. a 30 minute cycle to the inner city centre from the houseboat but it is also possible to take the bike on the tram with you. The night runs the whole night from 12.30 to the city centre and back that takes 30 minutes.  If you come from Schiphol Airport it is 15/20 minutes by train to Central Station, from there you take Tram 26 (Ijburg written on the front) and stop at tram stop Steigereiland (which takes 12 minutes).  And it is a 5 minute walk to the houseboat.
access: There is a common front door and in the hallway you have your own private entrance/door to the top floor. The combined private spacious balcony/terrace and top floor of 70 square meters is totally yours. The balcony sliding window doors can be opened up into one large open spacious indoor/outdoor living space where you can relax with the stunning views over the water. Enjoy barbecuing if you like :-). The terrace has a large table with chairs and a hammock to relax in. You can wake up and have a lot of fun swimming in the water around the houseboat in the summer. Or feel welcome to use the free paddle boat to paddle around on the lake between the newly architectural designed houseboats or just for your kids to have fun with.
interaction: I am happy to tell you about about all the nice  places to see and visit and give you some good local tips to help you to have a great experience in Amsterdam. I always try to be available when the guests check in but sometimes this might be not possible, if so I can leave the keys in a keybox for you. And of course if you have some questions, I am available as I am living on the downstairs floor's of the houseboat with my four year old son Ties and my two year old daughter Vera.
house_rules: You are welcome to smoke on the terrace but please do not smoke indoors.
host_about:
I am living with my five years old son Ties and three years old daughter Vera on a very modern houseboat that I designed  in 2010. 
In my spare time I really enjoy working on my old sailing boat, rowing boat and the two canal boats (trying to keep them afloat...:) I also really love windsurfing , so as you can tell by now I really enjoy water and water sports.

Amsterdam is a great city to visit and especially on a houseboat. You will have a great time and I am happy to tell you about the more hidden things to see and to do so you can really enjoy the city!

neighborhood_overview: IJburg is a new area in Amsterdam, built on water (when Dutch people need land, they build it in water!!). It consists of 7 islands, and the apartment is  located on the main island. As it is close to the city centre and very spacious, many young families with kids live here.  Around the corner of the apartment (2 minutes walk) there is a picturesque harbour with nice restaurants and bars where locals enjoy a meal and a beer together (Dok 48, NAP, Cafe Ed). Around the other corner (1 minute walk), there is a very nice coffee bar where you can enjoy great breakfast and coffees, always nice people to have a chat and hear about the neighbourhood! The beach is at 5 minute walk and at the beachclub "Blijburg" you can enjoy drinks and food whilst sitting around the fireplace, watching the sun go down or see the surf dudes do their trics. Supermarket, butcher, bakery and pharmacy  is around the corner for all your groceries. The Diermerpark is a huge parc, very suitable for running or a fresh
notes: If you look for a quiet place surrounded by nature, with nice local bars and restaurants to unwind after visiting Amsterdam for the day, this is the place to be!   If you are looking for partying in the evening, I recommend to look for a place right in the city centre.

Exclusive designshop across the street with a lunchroom and restaurant and a unique view on the waterside. Then there is a second (low profile) restaurant in front of the bridge around the corner.  A shopping center with 2 supermarkets, lunchrooms, bakery, restaurants, etc. just one tramstop away or a short walk over one of the bridges. neighborhood_overview: IJburg is a unique residential neighborhood on the east side of Amsterdam which is built on artificial islands that have been raised from the lake (Ijsselmeer).  Featuring modern architecture that include floating homes, inter-connected canals, a marina, shops, restaurants and bars, popular beach (Blijburg) and a nature reserve (Diemerpark).  Cycle paths connect IJburg to Amsterdam and local attractions such as Muiden and Muiderslot Castle.
notes: There is ample street parking available.  Day pass is €16 per day, free after 7pm, Sundays and public holidays.
transit: Easily accessible by car, only 2 minutes from the A10. Tram (26) is 5 minutes walk from the apartment which takes 15 min to central Amsterdam. Trams come every 5 mins during the day and 10 mins in the evening (until 00:30). There is also a night bus. Install the app '9292' on your phone to plan all travel by public transport.
access: There is a large completely enclosed common garden area with 2 children's play areas, seating and access to the water. You are welcome to use it.

neighborhood_overview: Do you prefer a quiet and green neighbourhood? Then IJburg is the place to be: the first residents established here only several years ago. This new district near Diemerpark consists of a number of artificial islands: Steigereiland, Haveneiland West and East and the Rieteilanden. In the summer you can completely relax at the Theo van Gogh in the Park. One hotspot to check out in IJburg at least once is the urban beach Blijburg. besides sunbathing and eating delicious food, you can enjoy several events. With tramline 16 you are within 10 minutes at central station!
access: You will access to the entire apartment. Make yourself at home!
interaction: I will meet you at the apartment, handle the keys and show you around. After that feel free to contact me on Airbnb if you need any assistance or tips! I am more then happy to help you!
house_rules: Treat the apartment as if it were your own and keep in mind that you have neighbours. The apartment is a regular home not an after hours club, so no parties, no drugs, no loud music/TV, etc. Police will fine when complaints are made after 23:00 (11pm) or before 07:00 (7am). At time of departure: make sure the apartment is tidy, the dishes are done, the garbage is bagged and the oven, hob and fridge/freezer are clean. Smoking of any kind is not allowed, this may also result in a triggering of the fire alarm. All keys must be returned upon departure. Failure to do so will incur a replacement fee. Guests must immediately inform the host of all defects in the apartment and damages that occur in the apartment. If host is not informed of defects, host cannot be held liable for resulting damage to personal items.

neighborhood_overview: IJburg is the modern architectural paradise in Amsterdam. The apartment is located on 'Steigereiland', one of the 5 islands which makes IJburg. The area has all facilities and amenities, supermarkets, restaurants, bars, city beach & beach club Blijburg (with sailing & kite surfing areas) and a cosy harbour with nice restaurants. The tram, leaving in front of the building, brings you in 10 minutes to Central Station.
notes: Complimentary coffee and tea. Towels and bedsheets provided.
transit: From Amsterdam Central Station: Tram 26 stops right in front of the apartment and brings you in 10 minutes to my place / from my place to the city center. There is a private parking at the back of the apartment which I will lead you to upon arrival.  If you're travelling by car there I have private parking available for free! (parking on the street costs € 3,- per hour in all of IJburg)

interaction: Feel free to contact me prior to your arrival with any questions. I will try to make your stay as comfortable as possible.
house_rules: No pets and party's. No smoking inside the apartment, please smoke on the balcony. Treat my place as you would treat the place of a dear friend.

If you have any special requests for your stay or need information on places to go, please do not hesitate to drop me a line. I will try to answer you as best I can to make your stay pleasant and comfortable!

name: Sailing barge Confiance, Amsterdam
summary: The Confiance is a skillfully refitted operational sailing barge. During winter she's moored in Amsterdam-IJburg. A combination of urban qualities with a unique location and breathtaking view. By public transport only 20 min to the A'dam city centre.
space: The “Confiance” is an operational sailingbarge originally built in the early 1900’s. During the winter of 2013 she was skillfully refitted in order to fit the high standard for accommodating guests. During the winter-season the “Confiance” will be moored in IJburg to serve as a picturesque Bed& Breakfast/ group accommodation.  Situated on the southern shores of what used to be called the Dutch Southern sea, IJburg combines it’s many Urban qualities with a unique location and a breathtaking view.  The “Confiance” can facilitate 22 guests divided over; 7 cabins for 2 persons and 2 cabins for 4 persons. The ship has 2 toilets along with 2 showers and a spacious and comfortable day area, furnished with tables and a big squishy lounge sofa. The fully equipped galley has plenty of room and should be able to satisfy all your culinary needs. Trams and Busses go back and forth between IJburg and the center of Amsterdam on a regular basis and travelling should take you no longer than 20 minutes.

name: Cozy Room in Big HouseBoat
summary: Double room with French bed. Perfect for young couples or single guests. This little but cozy Double Room is placed under the water level and offers you a unique experience. Please note that the baby cots are not available in this room.
space: Houseboat in the most innovative district of Amsterdam.  LaCorteSconta B&B is located in a modern residential area, 12 min. from Amsterdam Central Station by tram (line 26, Steigerieiland stop) where you will reach an area free from the many tourists who crowd the city and full of water and green space.  The B&B is a Floating-Villa on 3 floors moored in the lake IJ. The 3rd floor is where we live with my 2 little children. The large living room (breakfast area) and the under water floor (guests area) complete the location. Each room has a double bed, WiFi, TV or computer and other services.  The bathroom, shower, bath, double hand-wash and toilettes are shared, according to the traditional philosophy of coexistence and respect that belongs to the B&B concept itself. The bathroom cleaning is provided daily.  Breakfast will be personalized according to particular allergies or special requests. Guests can experience the best of this district through the houseboat that will make your stay

neighborhood_overview: A good alternative to the chaos of the city to rediscover the peace with an original houseboat. The floating house is in the neighborhood of Ijburg recently built. Typical Dutch management of the sea combined with care and originality of the building. All united in a residential neighborhood, young and cosmopolitan. Nearby there are possibilities of shops, supermarkets as well as peaceful places where to drink and eat. Dutch quiet a few steps from the vitality of the center.
notes: Accessibility: easy by walk \ by Airports \ from nearby railway stations \ Station by bus \ Cruise Ships \ Public transport 24/7 Connections: Close to the center (12 min by tram to Central Station) and easy access to all major attractions of the city (Center \ Museumplein \ Zoo ..) and surrounding areas (Muiden \ Zaanse Schans \ Volendam \ Marken ..). Possibility to rent a bike or organize a tour. Parking: Possibility of public parking at 14 eur \ day or alternatively with the cheapest parking P + R Zeeburg or Private Garage. HouseBoat: It is located in a unique area where nature, sports, architecture, sustainability of the sea and lifestyle come together. The original experience of living in an authentic houseboat of latest generation. Breakfast: Fresh breakfast every morning with flexible hours, possibility of room service or use the take away service. Breakfast can customize according to allergies or vegetarian preferences. Free Services: all free services (some on request): Kitchen
transit: The houseboat is a 12 min from the central station with the tram 26 (stop Steigereiland). Bike use: Excellent starting point for visiting the city center and get lost among the many parks of Amsterdam or in Ijburg. The tram 26 is one of the few city tram that will allow you to enter with the bikes and in 10 minutes to the Central Station and many other destinations through the line of regional trains. We offer a bike rental service for a fee, alternatively there are many options to rent a bike. IJburg Beach The beach is set in a frame vaguely bohemian, where besides sunbathing you can entertain during the evening with music, bonfires and fireworks. Surfcenter IJburg, perfect for water sports enthusiasts who can rent windsurfing equipment or take lessons. One of the great advantages of Strand IJburg is that here you can swim. To get to Strand IJburg (Muiderlaan 1001) you can take tram 26.
access: Double room with French bed. This small Double Room is placed under the water level and offers you a unique experience. The windows on the edge of the water allow guests a very unusual situation accompanied by ducks and swans. Please note that baby cots is not available in this room. All guests are provided with the key of their room and the key of the main entrance so as to be always independent. All the room are placed in the under water floor (Guest Area).  The Toilet and bathroom with tub and shower are shared. Both are in the guest area. A spacious living room also used for breakfast is our Common Area.  The use of the kitchen and laundry with arrangements in advance is free.
interaction: The owner will welcome you at your desired check in time and provide you all the necessary information to visit the city!  There is often somebody in the location to help you with information and helpful tips for your travel experience.
house_rules: Contattami per indicare l'orario di arrivo. Bagno e toilettes sono condivisi con altri eventuali ospiti.  Nonostante i bagni vengano puliti quotidianamente, siete pregati di usarlo con rispetto. Tutte le stanze sono non-fumatori. C'è la possibilità di fumare sia nel patio o nel soggiorno compatibilmente agli altri ospiti e usi della casa.  Animali ammessi. Nel caso di animali di grandi dimensioni o particolarmente invasivi potrebbe essere richiesto un costo aggiuntivo.  I bambini fino a 6 anni soggiornano gratuitamente nei letti presenti. Possibilità di aggiungere una culla senza costi aggiuntivi (solamente nelle stanze più grandi). Non consentiti letti aggiuntivi. Area Comune aperta dalle 8am fino le 9 pm  Colazione dalle 8:00 alle 10:00. (Flessibile). Check-in tra 3pm e 4pm.  Check-out entro le 11 am.
host_about:
Welcome to my wonderful houseboat! I live here with my two children Rocco and Dante. You may have understood that I come from Italy! I left my hometown Venice and my "adopted city" Rome, spent 10 years traveling to different continents and finally I chose to move here in Netherlands five years ago, to try to make a change of my life. I have found a wonderful and exciting city that can give back a lot from hard work. In addition to the "cancer" like me who love sea, open spaces bright and clean but at the same time be able to find any stimulus from a dynamic and cosmopolitan city, I found the perfect place to continue my journey!

Benvenuti a tutti nella mia fantastica casa galleggiante! Vivo qui con i miei due bambini Rocco e Dante. Avrete forse capito che vengo dall'Italia! Ho lasciato la mia città natale Venezia e la mia "adottiva" Roma, passato 10 anni a viaggiare per diversi continenti e alla fine ho scelto di trasferirmi qui in Olanda 5 anni fa per cercare di dare una svolta alla  mia vità e ho trovato una città meravigliosa e stimolante che puo restituire molto dal duro lavoro. Inoltre per i "cancro" come me che amano il mare, gli spazi aperti, luminosi e puliti ma allo stesso tempo avere la possibilità di trovare qualunque stimolo da una città cosi dinamica e cosmopolita, ho trovato il luogo perfetto per continuare il mio viaggio!

name: stunning & spacious family home!
summary: Best way to stay in Amsterdam! Spend some days or more with friends and family in our lovely warm and trendy house! Close to the exciting city centre and perfect to enjoy the beautiful nature and architecture around
space: Our family home is very spacious (200m2), light and comfortable.  Located at a corner so surrounded by windows, a patio and two sunny terraces. Just aside the house we have a small green garden and a communal playground where kids can safely play their outdoor games.  Ground floor:  entrance, study area, 17 meter long corridor, 3 bedrooms. All bedrooms have large single beds: 120*200 or 130*200, even suitable for two (small) people. Two bathrooms with toilet and shower, one with a bath. Washing room with washing machine and dryer. Patio with a fig tree. First floor: Very bright living room (70m2) with open kitchen and a large panoramic window. Fully equipped kitchen with oven, microwave, dish washer, large fridge, espresso machine and everything you need to prepare great meals. And if you like to make some healthy juices, you can use our Slow Juicer or blender for a smoothy. We have a sunny green balcony where you are able to enjoy your drinks or meal during summer days. neighborhood_overview: Our spacious & modern family house is situated at IJburg,  a newly developed area in East Amsterdam.   IJburg offers everything you need, and has a trendy and relaxed atmosphere. If you love modern architecture or like water sports you will find everything here: Swimming, wind/ kitesurfing, kayaking, sailing and ice skating in winter.  In the Diemerpark you are able to cycle, walk, swim or relax. Every corner of the street has a play ground for kids. The area has some nice venues like a cosy harbour with nice restaurants and bars, small cinema with movies on friday and the city beach & famous beachclub Blijburg ((URL HIDDEN) Local stores and super markets are just a 5 minute walk away. So we all live at the sunny side of life on this island! We love Amsterdam ! In a very short distance you are in the busy, exciting city centre where you can visit all the great museum and attractions the city has to offer. Canals, restaurants, shopping and the zoo Artis are all close. And you also may v
notes: Although we are not in the house you will find our two sweet cats to take care of. The cats love to be outside and you only need to feed them and give them some of your attention
transit: How about public transport? Within short walking distance tram nr.26 will bring you to central station in 15 minutes day and evening (until 00:30h), leaving every 6 minutes. You can bring your bike or baby stroller on the tram! After midnight a night bus (nr.359) will bring you back home or take you to the central station. Also bus 66 is available, which goes to the business district Amsterdam Zuid Oost. .  Very cheap parking possibilities available, 8 euro a day, to be accesed 5 minutes by tram. Amsterdam airport (Schiphol) is close by
access: The apartment is perfect for families, small groups (up to 6) and couples who like to unwind from a hectic day in the city centre.  We love to welcome you at our family home and whish you an excellent stay.
interaction: At your arrival you will find  information about Amsterdam in English. Just let us know your wishes/questions and we like to help you! We are always reachable by mobile phone.
house_rules: • A minimum stay of 3 nights is mandatory (in summer 4 nights)  • The listed price per night is based on an occupancy of 4 people •The house is clean and there will be fresh beddings & towels.  Extra beddings or cleaning in between is possible if you stay more than a week (on request / extra charge). If you need any (biological) food or drinks before arrival let us know. Coffee and tea are already here. We charge an additional cleaning fee of 50 euros for cleaning afterwards •Deposit: €200 •It is a non-smoking/ no-drugs place. Smoking is only possible on the balcony or roof terrace.  •The house is located in a residential area, not suitable for loud parties.  •Free WIFI available. •And... leave the house as you found it

neighborhood_overview: We call IJburg our holiday island, because of its beautiful location surrounded by water and natural parks. It offers everything you need, and has a trendy and relaxed atmosphere (in comparison with busy city center).  Traveling to the center is very convenient by tram (15min) or beautiful by bike (30min).   IJburg is ideal for water (sports) enthusiasts and for kids. Swimming, wind/ kitesurfing, kayaking, wake boarding, sailing and ice skating in winter is practiced a lot. Every corner of the street has a play ground for kids. On IJburg you can enjoy boutiques, bars and restaurants, the harbour with nice terraces and famous beachclub Blijburg. Architectural lovers will appreciate contemporary design and nature lovers can go out for beautiful trips (e.g. jogging).
notes: We have prepared a hand-out with suggestions for doing on IJburg. Optional: For your day of arrival we can prepare you a biological dinner, ready to be heated in the oven. For breakfasts we can prepare home made granola with yoghurt, fresh fruits, coffee and thee. We can organize delivery of fresh biological food/ vegetables directly from local farmers (delivered saturday morning), if you send us your grocery list in advance! There are 3 bedrooms: - Masterbedroom with a 180cm * 220cm bed - Girl's room with a 140cm * 200cm bed - Baby room with a 160cm * 200cm bed The baby cot and child's bed can be used on request and can easily be moved to another room. On request we can host an extra person on an airbed/couch.
transit: Within short walking distance tram nr.26 will bring you to central station in 15 minutes day and evening (until 00:30h), leaving every 6 minutes!  You can bring your bike or baby stroller on the tram!  After midnight a night bus (nr.359) will bring you back home or take you to to central station. If you come by car we offer a free parking place in our garage. It will provide you great flexibility to also explore beautiful areas around  Amsterdam.   Schiphol airport is 20minutes (app.€38) to IJburg bij Taxi or easy accessible by tram and train (40min).
access: With 6 people access to all 3 bedrooms, with 4 people to 2 bedrooms. Access to parking garage for free parking of car. Acces to communal court yard with 2 separate play grounds for kids. (Optional) Access to scullery with washing and drying machine.
interaction: Please contact us as much as you need via e-mail  or phone. We like you to feel welcome, at home and give you suggestions if you want. Dinner (for day of arrival) and breakfasts are optional!  We won't be in the house during your presence but are willing to help you with every question you have!
house_rules: No pets, no smoking inside, no big parties and strangers in the house. We expect you to treat our stuff and neighbors  as if they where your own.
host_about:
I am an entrepreneur and own a sustainability and innovation consultancy in construction industry.
I want to help the world transition to a more sustainable future.
I live on IJburg with Aukje (online consultant) our daughter (4 year old) and son (1 year old). 
I love to windsurf in front of my house, running through the parks, playing outside with the kids and enjoying the city with my friends.  
Aukje and I have high standards for hospitality and love to give you a great experience!
